230000925,SOLD,"JC, Heights",42 HUTTON ST,Condominium,540,6452,"$273,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,5,"JC, Heights",07307,03804,00023,,,,,,1,0,1,3,,"$273,000","$269,000",$505.56,$505.56,1/17/2023,5/24/2023,6/27/2023,113,113,,6/27/2023,,,,"$3,448",2022,$216,,Conventional,No,No,No,,,Corner of Sherman,"Sold strictly AS IS.  Spacious 1 bedroom on the 2nd floor of a quiet 9-unit pet-friendly building with washer/dryer in the basement. Hardwood floors, updated kitchen and bathroom, smart layout with an entryway and coat closets. Separate eat-in kitchen and large windows that keep it bright even on the rainy days. Perfect for a 1st time home buyer or investor. Fabulous location in booming Jersey Heights with 2 supermarkets nearby , local parks, coffee shops and gourmet eateries, as well as Central Avenue shopping/dining nearby. Perfect location for busy commuters, near express NYC midtown buses, local buses, Journal Square Path Station, and 2nd Street Light Rail. "
230006745,SOLD,"JC, Heights",50 RESERVOIR AVE,Condominium,494,6452,"$274,900",CONDO-COOP,,1,104,"JC, Heights",07307,05007,00019,,,,,,1,0,1,3,,"$274,900","$274,900",$556.48,$556.48,4/27/2023,5/5/2023,6/16/2023,8,8,,6/16/2023,,,,"$4,066",2022,$308,,Conventional,,,,,,Reservoir Ave and Webster Ave,"This stylishly renovated 1 bed / 1 bath is located on tree lined Reservoir Avenue, in one of Jersey City Heights’ most stately pre-war condominium buildings. Unit 104 features an open floor plan living room / kitchen area, high ceilings, solid oak hardwood flooring, & LED lighting throughout. Large windows flood the space with natural light. The new kitchen has under cabinet LED lighting and high-end appliances including dishwasher, microwave, gas range & refrigerator. The new bathroom’s subway wall tiles and hexagonal porcelain floor tiles are simultaneously contemporary and a nod to the building’s heritage. Comfortably sized bedroom with a large closet. Pre-wired for cable and FIOS. The building features app-enabled video entry & laundry systems. This is one of the best locations in the Heights; hip shops & restaurants, parks, and NYC buses are all in easy reach. Also nearby: Riverview Farmers Market, Reservoir park trails, Pershing Field Athletic Center, Hoboken’s 2nd St Light Rail station, CitiBike, Central Avenue shopping district and more."
