250005305,SOLD,"JC, Heights",50 RESERVOIR AVE,Condominium,500,1713,"$315,000",CONDO-COOP,,4,404,"JC, Heights",07307,5007,19,Heights,,,,,1,0,1,4,,"$315,000","$299,000",$630.00,$630.00,3/20/2025,4/1/2025,5/2/2025,12,12,,5/5/2025,,,,"$4,422",2024,$427,,Cash,,,,,,PROSPECT AND BOOREAM,"Bright and Spacious 1-Bedroom with Stunning NYC Views. Own this recently renovated, bright, and spacious 1-bedroom, 1-bathroom apartment on Reservoir Avenue! Located in a charming pre-war building, this home seamlessly blends modern conveniences with classic architectural details. Enjoy breathtaking views of the New York City skyline from the living room and bedroom, where large windows fill the space with natural light. The open floor plan connects the living room and kitchen, creating a perfect space for relaxing or entertaining. High ceilings enhance the home's airy, open feel, while the spacious bedroom easily accommodates a king-size bed. Ample closet space ensures plenty of storage. Building amenities include an app-enabled video entry system for security and convenience and an on-site laundry room. Situated in one of the most desirable locations in Jersey City Heights, you’ll be just steps from parks, shops, and cafes, with easy access to transportation for a quick commute to NYC. Parking available nearby for an additional fee"
210000135,SOLD,"JC, Heights",140 WEBSTER AVE,Condominium,,1691,"$315,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2R,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,1,0,1,4,,"$315,000","$325,000",,,1/4/2021,3/19/2021,8/25/2021,74,74,,9/12/2021,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Griffith St & Hutton St,"The ultimate urban lifestyle combination of luxury and location is found with these two newly renovated, one bedroom units in the heart of JC Heights. Each space opens up with oversized windows, exposed brick, and wide plank white oak floors throughout. Large open concept kitchens are finished with white custom shaker cabinets with exposed corner shelves, white quartz countertops, contrasting black and white marble-inspired backsplash, matte-black fixtures and stainless steel appliances. Moving through the well-planned flow of the units, modern bathrooms boast a combination of black and grey large slab tile, stylish vanities and brass fittings. The bedroom brings beautiful morning light to start your day off right! Outdoor space is at your fingertips with both Riverview Fisk Park and Pershing Field a short walk away. Enjoy the best of Jersey City Heights and Hoboken, with the eclectic urban scene surrounding, incredible walkability and easy access to NYC."
220004424,SOLD,"JC, Heights",50 RESERVOIR AVE,Condominium,718,6280,"$315,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,306,"JC, Heights",07307,5007,19,,,,,,2,0,1,4,,"$315,000","$320,000",$438.72,$438.72,3/14/2022,4/1/2022,4/22/2022,18,18,,4/25/2022,,,,"$4,440",2021,$449,,Private,No,No,No,,,Baldwin Ave & Lineau Pl,"Between Baldwin Ave & Lineau Pl Welcome to Jersey City Heights, gorgeous pre-war 2Bds 1 Bath Condo. 2 Pets allowed with a max weight of 100 lbs. The building amenities are marble lobby, elevator, laundry room, intercom & security cameras. It's conveniently located near the 2nd St Hoboken Light Rail station and close to all NYC Transportation on a quiet street. Featuring 2022 new appliances, original hardwood floors & original molding. HOA covers Heat & Water. Residents can obtain street parking permit. Not FHA/VA Approved."
260003631,ACTIVE,"JC, Heights",104 HOPKINS AVE,Condominium,846,1754,"$315,000",CONDO-COOP,,G,#1,"JC, Heights",07306,5704,27,,,,,,2,0,2,4,,,"$315,000",$372.34,,3/3/2026,,,37,,,3/3/2026,,,,"$9,411",2025,$368,,,,,,,,Oakland & Central,"Welcome to 104 Hopkins Ave in the highly desired Jersey City Heights, an impeccably renovated 846 square foot garden level residence offering 2 spacious bedrooms and 2 full bathrooms. This beautifully updated home features stainless steel appliances, modern finishes, and a smart layout that maximizes both comfort and functionality, plus the added convenience of an in unit washer and dryer. Enjoy the ease of being just moments from parks, shopping, restaurants, and transportation, making commuting and everyday living effortless. Move in ready and perfectly located, this home delivers style, convenience, and comfort all in one."
220000021,SOLD,"JC, Heights",140 WEBSTER AVE,Condominium,465,1691,"$315,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1G,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,1,0,1,4,,"$315,000","$325,000",$677.42,$677.42,1/2/2022,3/17/2022,6/17/2022,74,74,,6/20/2022,,,,,,$254,,Conventional,,,,,,Hutton St & Griffith St,"Stylish and sophisticated, this newly refinished one bedroom, one bathroom floor-through condo has so much to offer. Settled on a tree-lined street in a sweet spot of Jersey City Heights, the central location is one block to Riverview Fisk Park and Palisades walking paths, plus easy walkablity to 7th Street Light Rail, Central Avenue, Pershing Field Park and more.  Step into the light, bright, open floorplan living area finished with durable designer geometric pattern tile, and an exposed matte black brick fireplace as the centerpiece. L-shaped kitchen is finished with white quartz counters, eye-popping swirled backsplash, matte black faucet, custom shaker cabinets allowing plenty of storage and stainless steel appliances.   Natural light fills the large bedroom with windows and half door with direct access to backyard. Spacious bathroom is finished with contrasting black slab and white subway tile, plus soaker tub and rainhead shower combo. The dedicated laundry room offers brand new Samsung washer and dryer, excellent utility and storage space.  The newly refinished building exterior showcases grey siding, stylish wood paneling, plus new Pella windows. The Heights is one of Jersey City’s most coveted neighborhoods, offering tight-knit community, eclectic artistic vibe, walkability to essential shops, expansive parks, excellent schools and easy accessibility to NYC."
