freshly painted, attractive, ready-to-move-in condo, complete with a newly updated kitchen. Your urban sanctuary awaits!"
240013882,SOLD,"JC, Heights",11 CUNEO PL,Condominium,600,1623,"$330,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,3A,"JC, Heights",07307,05202,00030,Heights,Cuneo Court,,,,1,0,1,4,,"$330,000","$338,000",$550.00,$550.00,7/17/2024,8/9/2024,9/27/2024,23,23,,10/4/2024,,,,"$4,824",2023,$225,2023,Conventional,No,No,,,,Palisade & Ogden Ave,"Welcome to the meticulously kept Cuneo Court residences, nestled on a tranquil treelined street adjacent to the gorgeous green space the Community Garden” at Ogden’s End.   This well laid-out 600 square foot home includes a spacious living room, one nicely sized bedroom & one updated bath.  On the third floor perched above the tree line is this well appointed residence who is illuminated by multiple windows facing every direction which highlights the entire unit.  The recently updated kitchen has an abundance of cabinetry, granite counters, and chic backsplash.  Additional features are hardwood floors throughout, coat closets, storage closets, nice high ceilings, and a door to directly access the outdoor balcony-escape.   All visitors are greeted by a true & well-maintained lobby, also enjoy refreshed common hallways & carpeting, common well-manicured landscaped backyard, and the spotless laundry room.  Neighborhood boasts the Janet Moore Playground, the Ogden's End Community Garden, and a dog park. So many neighborhood amenities within a few blocks includes a larger community sized grocery store, Farmers Market in Riverview Park, eatery hits from Bread & Salt, Corto, Fox & Crow”, Franklin Social, Green Pair”,  Low Fidelity (LoFi to the locals), home-made ice cream at Milk, Sugar, Love”, and Choc-O-Pain bakery,   Close to the Hoboken steps,  NJ Hudson Light Rail, NJ transit buses to NYC located around the corner on Palisade Ave and more! Low HOA Fee is only $212 per month. Building requires buyers to have 20-25% down, call for more information, do not miss out!"
