220000034,SOLD,"JC, Heights",380 BALDWIN AVE,Condominium,800,1598,"$330,000",CONDO-COOP,,2nd,2R,"JC, Heights",07306,,,Heights,,,,,2,0,1,5,,"$330,000","$325,000",$412.50,$412.50,1/2/2022,2/1/2022,3/21/2022,30,30,,3/22/2022,,,,"$3,117",2020,$170,,Conventional,,,,,,Route 139 & Fleet St,"Be the first to live in this beautifully 2 bedroom and 1 bath gut renovated condo unit in the desirable Jersey City Heights area. This impeccably renovated condo features bedrooms on opposite side, brilliant recessed lighting, new hardwood floors, crown molding throughout and ample-spaced bathroom with an elegant glass enclosed shower. The designer open kitchen features a white cabinetry, white backsplash tiles, granite countertop and is equipped with brand new stainless-steel appliances.  The main bedroom comfortably fits a king-sized bed, nightstands, dressers and has a bonus unit next to it which can be used as an office or walk-in closet or a nursery. Unlimited options. 2nd bedroom can easily fit queen size bed and furniture. Shared laundry and yard. Low HOA monthly fee and incredible location with easy access to Journal Square Path, all major highways and life essentials."
250005919,SOLD,"JC, Heights",259 GRIFFITH ST,Condominium,688,1186,"$331,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1,"JC, Heights",07307,0304,00020,,,,,,2,0,1,5,,"$331,000","$339,000",$481.10,$481.10,3/27/2025,6/2/2025,6/26/2025,67,67,,9/28/2025,,,,"$5,631",,$238,,Cash,No,,,,,JFK AND SUMMIT AVE,"Nestled in the vibrant Jersey City Heights, this inviting 2-bedroom, 1-bathroom condominium offers 688 square feet of comfortable living space. The well-appointed kitchen features stainless steel appliances, granite countertops, and generous cabinet storage. Privacy is assured with bedrooms thoughtfully placed at opposite ends of the unit. Additional features include a full bathroom with a relaxing jacuzzi tub, a flexible space that can serve as a dining area or home office, and lofty ceilings that create an open and airy ambiance. Enjoy low HOA fees, along with convenient amenities such as a shared laundry room, a large storage room, and a pet-friendly backyard for entertaining and relaxation. The condo's prime location ensures easy access to transportation, including direct buses to Port Authority and the Journal Square PATH station, making NYC commuting a breeze. Additionally, the high Walk-Score offers an array of diverse dining, grocery, and shopping options along Central Ave. Pictures are Virtually Staged. "
250005609,SOLD,"JC, Heights",543 PALISADE AVE,Condominium,693,1724,"$332,500",CONDO-COOP,,B,5,"JC, Heights",07307,02305,00030,Heights,,,,,1,0,1,4,,"$332,500","$329,000",$479.80,$479.80,3/24/2025,6/2/2025,9/4/2025,70,70,,9/5/2025,,,,,,$241,,FHA,,,,,,South & Bowers,"Discover a remarkable blend of sophistication and comfort in this exquisite 1 bedroom, 1 bathroom offered at 543 Palisade Ave. A highly coveted location known for its proximity to the Light Rail station, Riverview Park, and a plethora of shops and restaurants. Parking is available for an additional fee and being sold with the ADU unit (a studio apartment) above the parking space in the back garage on the left. The ADU can be used as additional living space or it can be rented or used as an air bnb. Step inside this luminous home, featuring a generously sized bedroom and a full bath, where every detail has been carefully crafted to provide a luxurious living experience. Commute effortlessly and access public transportation with ease, as Palisade Ave offers direct bus lines to popular destinations such as NYC Port Authority, Hoboken, and Downtown JC. The nearby Hudson Light Rail Stations provide additional convenience for your travels. When it comes to leisure activities, indulge in the offerings of Pershing Field, just three blocks away, which boasts an indoor pool and an ice skating rink for year-round enjoyment. For outdoor enthusiasts, Riverview Park beckons with its breathtaking views, hosting a vibrant Farmers Market, movie nights, and a plethora of neighborhood events. Take the next step and contact today to schedule a private showing and obtain further details about this exceptional opportunity."
250001146,SOLD,"JC, Heights",193 OGDEN AVE,Condominium,455,1713,"$334,000",CONDO-COOP,,4,4e,"JC, Heights",07307,5101,3,Heights,,,,,1,0,1,3,,"$334,000","$334,000",$734.07,$734.07,1/16/2025,2/4/2025,3/13/2025,19,19,,3/17/2025,,,,"$4,411",2023,$353,,Cash,,,,,,Corner of Ogden Ave and Franklin St,"NYC views and a prime location are highlights of this bright, beautifully renovated top-floor apartment in an elevator building. With unobstructed skyline views from every room, this unit offers a perfect blend of style, comfort, and convenience. The apartment features stainless steel appliances, including a dishwasher, a newly renovated kitchen, fresh paint throughout, and a spacious bathroom with a newly installed waterfall showerhead. High ceilings, 6-foot tall windows in every room, and hardwood floors create a light-filled, modern space. The building includes a washer and dryer on every floor and is pet-friendly. Conveniently located just a 5-minute walk from the 2nd Street Light Rail, near both the Hoboken and Journal Square PATH stations, and with a bus stop just a few steps from the front door, this home is perfect for commuters. It’s also just one block from Riverview Park and within steps of local favorites like Choc-o-Pain, Ichiban, Prato Bakery, and nearby grocery stores."
220003147,SOLD,"JC, Heights",200 CENTRAL AVE,Condominium,572,1702,"$335,000",CONDO-COOP,,4,D4/404,"JC, Heights",07307,4904,0008,Heights,,,,,1,0,1,4,,"$335,000","$325,000",$585.66,$585.66,2/23/2022,3/29/2022,5/17/2022,34,34,,5/17/2022,,,,,,$305,,Conventional,,,,,,Booraem Ave. & Reservoir Ave.,"This adorable recently fully renovated 1 bedroom & 1 bath duplex condo has an abundance of natural light (South-facing).  The attention to detail in the recent renovations are top-notch.  Kitchen dining island, quartz countertops, stainless steel appliances, a fully renovated bathroom (all March 2020), hot water heater (Sept 2018), HVAC (June 2019) and new flooring.  Right across the street from Pershing Field and steps from the restaurants and shops of the sought after neighborhood of Jersey City (Heights).   Bus access to NYC is right on the corner.  If that weren't enough, an assigned parking space is included in the HOA!"
210026010,SOLD,"JC, Heights",52 BEACON AVE,Condominium,732,6199,"$335,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1,"JC, Heights",07306,05906,00006,,,,,,2,0,1,4,,"$335,000","$339,000",$457.65,$457.65,11/21/2021,12/20/2021,1/27/2022,29,29,,1/28/2022,,,,"$4,571",2021,$336,2021,Conventional,,,,,,Oakland & Baldwin,"Welcome home to this 2 bed 1 bath condo with a 400+ sq ft deeded backyard, perfect for entertaining or just relaxation.  Spacious living room, kitchen with stainless steel appliances, quartz countertops, ceramic tile flooring and portable dishwasher. Bedrooms are located on opposite sides of the unit for added privacy. Hardwood floors throughout, stackable washer/dryer and parking for rent in the lot next door. Minutes to various transportation options and in a thriving JC Heights neighborhood, this is the perfect space for commuters. This home is close to the Journal Square Path and is conveniently located near the NJ Turnpike and Holland Tunnel, bus stops, Pershing Field Park, and a variety of shops, supermarkets, restaurants, cafes and so much more."
260005172,ACTIVE,"JC, Heights",100 LEONARD ST,Condominium,700,1605,"$335,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,3L,"JC, Heights",07307,,,,,,,,2,0,1,4,,,"$335,000",$478.57,,3/24/2026,,,16,,,3/24/2026,,,,"$5,550",2023,$362,2025,,,,,,,Hague and Leonard,"Don't miss this light filled and nicely renovated top floor two bedroom unit in booming Jersey City Heights!  This efficient two bedroom has soaring ceiling height and a nice flexible/open layout; the large bay window allows for amazing natural light throughout the day.  The bathroom and kitchen have both been thoughtfully updated, meeting the modern buyer's wishlist.  The kitchen has gas for cooking, generous cabinet space and stone countertops, making this a chefs dream.  The bathroom has a newer medicine cabinet and sleek stainless steel fixtures.  The bedroom will easily accomodate a queen sized bed and has a large walk-in closet.  The HVAC was replaced just over a year ago, giving you peace of mind with your investment.  The building offers shared laundry and private storage space in the basement, offering nice amenities at this price point.  Close to shops, restaurants and the bus into NYC off Kennedy Blvd, this condo checks all the boxes.  Come see why everyone is moving to the Heights!"
220011967,SOLD,"JC, Heights",76 HUTTON ST,Condominium,631,1597,"$339,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,4,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,2,0,1,5,,"$339,000","$349,000",$537.24,$537.24,6/30/2022,8/26/2022,12/5/2022,57,57,,12/5/2022,,,,,,$325,,Conventional,,,,,,Cambridge & Hancock,"Located less than one block from Central Avenue in Jersey City Heights, and walking distance to Riverview Fisk Park with jaw-dropping NYC skyline views and 9th street Lightrail access, this newly renovated two bedroom home offers ultimate location and lifestyle, plus deeded parking included!   Beautiful brick exterior gives way to the fully updated two bedroom, 1.5 bath floorplan with classic style and all the upgrades. Timeless design shines through the split layout home with elements like classic wood casing around windows and neutral color palette. Wide plank hardwood floors, plus neutral slab tile in kitchen allow for both coziness, convenience and cottage feel.   Kitchen features contrasting black quartz counters with white cabinets including accent glass displays, white tile backsplash and stainless appliances. Bathroom hosts neutral tile with mosaic accents, spacious vanity with black porcelain counter plus medicine cabinet mirror for additional storage.  It’s no wonder Jersey City Heights is in such high demand with its vibrant community, eclectic restaurants and shops, excellent schools, spacious parks and easy NYC access."
220018062,SOLD,"JC, Heights",21 HANCOCK AVE,Condominium,700,1683,"$340,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,4,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$340,000","$349,000",$485.71,$485.71,10/10/2022,11/4/2022,1/6/2023,25,25,,1/14/2023,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Franklin and Hutton,"21 Hancock is a newly and tastefully renovated Condo building located in the heart of the most desirable section of Jersey City Heights. This home offers a bright, modern and airy 2 Bedroom, 2 Full Bathroom condo. Attention to craftsmanship is seen from the refined restoration of the exterior to the elegant entryway and brand-new interior of the Condo. The layout gives way to high ceilings, beautiful hardwood floors, and fantastic natural light in the bedrooms. The kitchen includes granite countertops, stainless steel appliances, and ample cabinet space. This perfect picture is finished with in-unit Laundry and Central AC to provide all of the modern conveniences that every homeowner needs. Situated steps away from the bus that can take you to NYC Port Authority in 35 minutes, or to Journal Square Path station in 10 minutes. This home is perfect for NYC commuters looking to live in a peaceful neighborhood."
