230019201,SOLD,"JC, Heights",231 GRIFFITH ST,Condominium,630,1597,"$349,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,F,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,2,0,1,5,,"$349,000","$349,000",$553.97,$553.97,11/14/2023,11/27/2023,12/27/2023,13,13,,12/28/2023,,,,,,$234,,Conventional,,,,,,Milton Ave & Summit Ave,"Freshly refinished two bedroom home offers unbeaten location and excellent opportunity. Step in from the tree-lined street, through the secure entrance, and into the flowing layout finished with wide plank floors and classic finishes.   Fully updated eat-in kitchen showcases traditional white cabinets, contrasting black quartz counters, white tile backsplash and stainless appliances, plus full-size closet for pantry. Bedrooms offer extras like beautiful windows, ceiling fan and walk-in closet, while bathroom is finished with spacious vanity, tile finished to ceiling, and bathtub plus shower.   Located directly across from Leonard Gordon Park in the heart of Jersey City Heights, this home offers walkability to excellent parks and major thoroughfares of Central and Summit Ave. The Heights is known for its vibrant artist’s culture, close-knit community and easy access to NYC, Hoboken and surrounding neighborhoods."
240002124,SOLD,"JC, Heights",179 MANHATTAN AVE,Condominium,761,6,"$350,000",CONDO-COOP,,3rd,C1,"JC, Heights",07307,004301,0011,Heights,,,,,2,0,1,4,,"$350,000","$319,900",$459.92,$459.92,2/4/2024,2/22/2024,4/23/2024,10,10,,4/24/2024,,,,,,$275,,Conventional,,,,,,Beach St & Sherman Pl.,"Located in the heart of Jersey City Heights, this wonderful 2 bedroom 1 bath condo is an opportunity that you won't want to miss! With just under 800 sq ft. of space this unit offers a flawless and well distributed space that enhances the use of every part of the home.  Moreover, the living room boasts with sunlight and a perfect blend of comfort and tranquility where you can just sit back and relax.  Eat in kitchen features tiled floors, good cabinet space and has been kept well, ready for a personal touch.  This delightful home has also hardwood floors throughout the rest of the unit and lots of closet space.  Enjoy the convenience of having the laundry facility in the basement/ ground level.  HOA fees include heat and hot water.  Great for commuters with a bus stop right down the street, easy commute to NYC and other parts of Jersey City.  Close to parks, schools, restaurants and so much more.  A must see, book your appointment today!"
220008739,SOLD,"JC, Heights",101 ZABRISKIE ST,Condominium,724,1691,"$350,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,4,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,2,1,1,5,,"$350,000","$375,000",$483.43,$483.43,5/16/2022,6/10/2022,7/6/2022,25,25,,7/13/2022,,,,,,$319,,Conventional,,,,,,JFK and Summit Ave,"Perfectly positioned in the heart of Jersey City Heights, this completely updated home offers classic design and thoughtful layout to tick all of the urban luxury boxes. Light radiates onto the neutral palette and beautifully stained original hardwood floors of this 2 bedroom and 1.5 bath home, while the split bedroom layout give optimal privacy and flexibility.  Walk into the open floorplan living and kitchen area complete with walnut cabinets, accent exposed shelves, white quartz counters, classic subway tile backsplash, matching stainless sink and appliances plus brushed nickel fixtures.  The front bedroom boasts oversized bay windows and huge side-by-side closets, plus full bath adjacent. Through to the back, owners enjoy convenient in-unit washer and dryer, plus additional half bath and bedroom.  Building exterior received recent upgrades as well with updating siding and fresh trim. Less than 1 block from Leonard Gordon Conservancy Park, this home is also quick walking distance to urban thoroughfares Summit and Central Ave plus beautiful Pershing Field Park and next door Reservoir. Jersey City Heights offers vibrant community, great restaurants and essential shops, excellent schools, and easy NYC access."
