240018794,SOLD,"JC, Heights",96 BOWERS ST,Condominium,0,6614,"$350,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2L,"JC, Heights",07307-2009,02206,00007,Heights,96 Bowers St. Condominium,,,,1,0,1,5,,"$350,000","$339,500",,,9/23/2024,10/1/2024,10/18/2024,8,8,,10/25/2024,,,,"$5,075",2023,$254,,Cash,,,,,,CAMBRIDGE AVE & HANCOCK AVE,"Introducing a brilliant opportunity to live in Jersey City Heights - modern, south-facing 1 bedroom, 1 bathroom condo in a highly coveted location. This historic building underwent a conversion in 2011, resulting in six stylish condos. Step inside this thoughtfully designed residence and flowing functional floor plan, boasting an open-concept living room and kitchen adorned with an alluring 18-count Edison bulb chandelier, stainless steel appliances, granite countertops, and stunning dual-tone cabinetry. This attractive condo delights in numerous remarkable features including: sealed and restored exposed brick accent wall, high ceilings, chic-minimalistic bathroom, modern light fixtures, and gleaming Kempas solid wood flooring. Additional features include central AC/Heat (condenser unit replaced March 2024), an in-unit washer/dryer, overhead cargo compartments above closets, deeded storage room in the basement and a shared backyard."
210001654,SOLD,"JC, Heights",136 NEW YORK AVE,Condominium,733,5528,"$350,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1R,"JC, Heights",07307,04504,00007,Heights,None,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$350,000","$349,900",$477.49,$477.49,1/19/2021,1/24/2021,3/23/2021,5,5,,3/26/2021,,,,"$5,251",2020,$265,,Conventional,No,No,No,,,Ferry st. and Franklin st.,"Welcome home to this beautifully updated 2 BR, 2 Bath condo with a private outdoor terrace in a pet-friendly building in prime Jersey City Heights.  High ceilings and an open-concept kitchen with granite counter tops and stainless-steel appliances and breakfast bar.  This condo features central air, hardwood floors and recessed lighting, and a Jacuzzi. This building has just 5 units.  Also included is a locked private storage unit in the basement. W/D in the building.  Commuting to the city is easy, with the Hoboken 2nd Street Light Rail Station just a quick walk from your door, offering direct connections to the PATH train, WTC and Herald Square. One block away, a bus stop offers direct routes to New York City and the Journal Square PATH station.  The condo is walking distance to Riverview Park, Jersey City's municipal pool, and numerous bars, restaurants, shopping areas, and convenience stores. "
260003918,ACTIVE,"JC, Heights",464 CENTRAL AVE,Condominium,620,1623,"$350,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1A,"JC, Heights",07307,2202,15,,,,,,1,0,1,3,,,"$350,000",$564.52,,3/6/2026,,,34,,,3/6/2026,,,,"$5,413",2025,$302,,,,,,,,South & Congress,"This one bedroom in a historic converted school house is exactly what you've been looking for! This cozy corner unit is private and spacious, with windows facing the building's quiet courtyard. The bedroom has the oversized walk-in closet of your dreams as well as additional overhead storage. The pet-friendly building features a welcoming common courtyard, a washer/dryer room on the same floor as the unit, and all in the heart of Jersey City Heights! Enjoy immediate access to the vibrant neighborhood's shops and restaurants, only one block from Washington Park. Commuting is effortless with a direct bus to the Port Authority Bus Terminal and to the Hoboken Terminal stopping right outside your door. The 9th Street Light Rail Station is also a short trip around the corner-- this is a location you cannot beat. Schedule your private viewing today!"
240009324,SOLD,"JC, Heights",74 PALISADE AVE,Condominium,833,1687,"$350,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1,"JC, Heights",07306,6901,1,,Persing Condo Association,,,,2,0,1,5,,"$350,000","$345,000",$420.17,$420.17,5/16/2024,5/29/2024,7/12/2024,13,13,,7/13/2024,,,,"$4,305",2023,$300,,Conventional,,,,,,Hoboken Ave and Palisade Ave,"Southern, Eastern, and Western exposures pour into a perfectly situated floor plan for your city living with NYC views, captured in the heart of Jersey City's vibrant landscape. Discover the enchanting allure of 74 Palisade Avenue, Unit 1. Upon entering, you are greeted by soaring high ceilings and an inviting open floor plan that seamlessly integrates the living, dining, and kitchen areas, creating the perfect space for both relaxation and entertainment. Natural light floods the newly painted interior, highlighting the rich hardwood floors, exposed brick, and contemporary finishes throughout. The perfect urban kitchen is a home chef's delight, featuring sleek granite countertops, custom cabinetry, a hanging pot rack/holder, and a suite of stainless steel appliances. Whether you are hosting a dinner party or preparing a casual meal, this space is sure to inspire culinary creativity. The tranquility of the primary bedroom awaits you at the end of the day, boasting a spacious layout, ample closet space, and soundproofed windows. An additional bedroom/flex space offers versatility for guests, a home office, or any other configuration, ensuring ample space to suit your lifestyle needs. The well-configured full bathroom is almost fully tiled and adds a window for brightness. A large private storage is located on the ground/basement level of the building. Saunter outside to the shared outdoor oasis, where you can unwind and soak in the sunshine, create your own vegetable or flower garden, or dine al fresco on warm summer evenings. Ideally located and just mere moments away from bustling downtown Jersey City, residents of Pershing Condos enjoy easy access to an array of opportunities at your doorstep; from eclectic dining, bakeries, coffee shops, boutique shopping, several farmers' markets, parks and greenery, arts and entertainment, and a plethora of historic and cultural treasures. Commuting is a breeze with nearby access to major highways and public transportation, including the PATH train and numerous bus lines, offering a seamless journey to Manhattan and beyond. An immaculate and unique opportunity to own a piece of Jersey City's flourishing real estate market. This is a residence that embodies the pinnacle of urban living. Welcome home to a life of radiant and enduring appeal in a city where you can truly 'Make It Yours.'"
