220016137,SOLD,"JC, Heights",76 HUTTON ST,Condominium,631,1597,"$365,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,2,1,1,5,,"$365,000","$375,000",$578.45,$578.45,9/8/2022,10/27/2022,12/19/2022,49,49,,12/19/2022,,,,,,$310,,Conventional,,,,,,Cambridge & Hancock,"Located less than one block from Central Avenue in Jersey City Heights, and walking distance to Riverview Fisk Park with jaw-dropping NYC skyline views and 9th street Lightrail access, this newly renovated two bedroom home offers ultimate location and lifestyle, plus parking included!   Beautiful brick exterior gives way to the fully updated two bedroom, two bath floorplan with classic style and all the upgrades. Timeless design shines through the split layout home with elements like classic wood casing around windows and neutral color palette. Wide plank hardwood floors, plus neutral slab tile in kitchen allow for both coziness, convenience and cottage feel.   Kitchen features contrasting black quartz counters with white cabinets including accent glass displays, white tile backsplash and stainless appliances. Bathroom hosts neutral tile with mosaic accents, spacious vanity with black quartz counter plus medicine cabinet mirror for additional storage.  It’s no wonder Jersey City Heights is in such high demand with its vibrant community, eclectic restaurants and shops, excellent schools, spacious parks and easy NYC access."
250020640,SOLD,"JC, Heights",252A NORTH ST,Condominium,721,1725,"$365,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,#201,"JC, Heights",07307,603,62,,Colunbia Court,,,,2,0,1,4,,"$365,000","$365,000",$506.24,$506.24,10/7/2025,11/13/2025,12/23/2025,37,37,,12/29/2025,,,,"$5,569",2024,$458,,Conventional,No,No,No,,,Corner of North Street,"Your amazing real estate opportunity starts here! This spacious 2-bedroom, 1-bath condo offers 721 sq ft of living space, featuring a newly renovated kitchen and bath, and easy-care flooring throughout. Additionally, this unit comes with an oversized garage deeded to you, plus a shared laundry room with your own washer & dryer included plus extra storage. You'll be ideally located in the desirable Western Slope neighborhood of the Jersey City Heights, offering convenient access to NYC bus transportation, all major highways, and shopping. This opportunity won't last long, so act fast!  "
240006096,SOLD,"JC, Heights",34 PROSPECT ST,Condominium,850,298,"$365,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,4,"JC, Heights",07307,05801,00026,,,,,,2,0,2,6,,"$365,000","$375,000",$429.41,$429.41,4/2/2024,4/29/2024,7/30/2024,27,26,,7/31/2024,,,,"$8,426",2024,$352,,Conventional,,,,,,Reservior & Waverly St,"Beautiful 2br, 2ba in a fantastic JC Heights location close to the 100 steps into Hoboken! Excellent to owner-occupy or keep as an investment. Enjoy the hardwood floors, dishwasher, in-unit washer/dryer, central AC/Heat, terrace, and shared backyard! Easy commute to NYC with a bus stop on the corner to JSQ or Port Authority. Photos of similar unit in the building."
210004450,SOLD,"JC, Heights",22 CHARLES ST,Condominium,1050,6395,"$366,500",CONDO-COOP,,3,3R,"JC, Heights",07307,2804,38,Heights,,,,,2,0,1,6,,"$366,500","$374,900",$349.05,$349.05,2/25/2021,4/27/2021,6/24/2021,61,62,,6/24/2021,,,,"$4,977",2020,$350,,Conventional,No,No,,,,Central Ave and Summit Ave,"Motivated Seller - bring all offers! This home is located in a moderate cencus tract and qualifies for mortgage discounts and programs - perfect for a first time homebuyer!   Bright and airy top-floor condo with loft-style ceilings.  Over 1,050 sq ft of living space with 2 bedrooms, 1 bath, plus loft (office/studio/zoom room - or use your imagination on how to reconfigure this space to have high ceilings in dining area too). Kitchen features SS appliances and gas range, washer/dryer available in the basement with additional storage. Parking available across the street for $250/mo. Shared backyard, perfect for kids, pets or entertaining!  Hallways will be painted and carpets replaced this May!   Conveniently located on a quiet, treelined street. Steps away from the NYC bus, Washington and Riverview-Fisk Parks, as well as the shops and restaurants on Central Ave. CitiBike and Hudson-Bergen Lightrail to Hoboken and Exchange Place PATH.  Don't miss this incredible opportunity to live in a hot neighborhood of Jersey City!"
230008290,SOLD,"JC, Heights",77 SHERMAN PL,Condominium,768,6142,"$367,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07307,03603,00017,,,,,,2,0,1,4,,"$367,000","$365,000",$477.86,$477.86,5/19/2023,6/12/2023,7/24/2023,24,24,,7/25/2023,,,,"$5,451",,$460,,Conventional,,,,,,Summit and Sanford Pl,"Welcome to this gorgeous neighborhood otherwise known as Sherman Place. Tree lined and dotted with beautiful historic homes - Sherman Place is one of Jersey City's most desirable streets. This perfect starter home comes with one dedicated parking space. It offers a functional box layout with no wasted space, beautiful freshly refinished hardwood floors, spacious oversized living room with plenty of room for multiple seating areas including home office or play area! Two spacious bedrooms with ample closet space and bright sunny windows offer plenty of room for a queen bed and even a king sized bed. The bright, modern, kitchen features white cabinetry, stainless steel appliances completely updated in 2017/2018. Freshly painted in a bright creamy hue by Benjamin Moore offset with a few charcoal accents - - simply put, this unit is ready for its new owner. Professionally managed, the maintenance fees include heat and hot water as well as general maintenance and trash removal (no hauling trash to the curb). Sherman Place is situated in between two fabulous parks - Pershing Fields -  which offers 13 acres of recreation including an indoor pool, runners track, baseball, ice skating and more. Leonard park is also short walking distance and offers another 5 acres of open park, gardens and green space. The Main Street Central Ave is two blocks away with dozens and dozens of eateries and shopping. NYC busses stop on Summit Ave, Kennedy Blvd and Central Ave. This is the perfect mix of beauty and convenience in city living. "
220012164,SOLD,"JC, Heights",102 OGDEN AVE,Condominium,665,1598,"$369,000",CONDO-COOP,,4,401,"JC, Heights",07307,05202,23,,Ogden Parkview Condos,,,,1,0,1,3,,"$369,000","$364,000",$554.89,$554.89,7/5/2022,7/11/2022,9/2/2022,6,6,,9/7/2022,,,,"$4,949",2021,$221,,Conventional,,,,,,Cuneo & Ogden,"Why rent when you can own!! This great bright and spacious 1bd/1b condo is located in exclusive Ogden Ave.  Features high ceilings, open floor plan from the living room to the eat-in kitchen, granite countertops, SS appliances, updated bath, central air conditioning, warm light-tone hardwood floors, In Unit Washer/Dryer, and plenty of closet space!  Ogden avenue in Jersey City Heights is the most sought after street, it's filled with local treasures, Ogden's End Community Garden, Ogden's End Dog Park, and Janet Moore Park are all right outside of the door.  Riverview Arts district is home to Coffee Shops, Dining, Bakery, Shopping, Entertainment, and Farmers Market. Easy access to NYC, Hoboken and Jersey City Downtown, NYC bus only minutes away, 11 minute short distance to the 2nd street light rail station. SUPER LOW Maintenance Fee and pet friendly bldg.  This condo is ready for their new owners to make some new memories!"
230007606,SOLD,"JC, Heights",244 WEBSTER AVE,Condominium,805,1597,"$369,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,3L,"JC, Heights",07307,2306,11,Heights,,,,,2,0,1,4,,"$369,000","$369,000",$458.39,$458.39,5/10/2023,5/18/2023,6/23/2023,8,8,,6/27/2023,,,,"$5,532",2022,$250,2023,Conventional,,,,,,Bowers & South,"Why rent when you can own? Perfect 2 bed, 1 bath or 1 bed with den in the heart of Jersey City Heights.  Recently renovated and freshly painted, move right in and enjoy all this beautiful home has to offer.  Soaring ceilings and huge windows flood the home with natural light.  The eat in kitchen features white cabinets and stainless steel appliances and a 2 in 1 washer/dryer. The newly renovated bathroom is a classic with white subway tile, black floor tiles and a rain shower.  Enjoy recently refinished hardwood floors throughout and charming historic details.  The bonus room is perfect for an office or second bedroom. Ample closet space and private storage in the basement provides space for all your belongings.  You'll love hanging with your neighbors in the shared backyard.  Close to all the Heights has to offer including award winning restaurants and schools.  Riverview Park is 2 blocks away and features the best views of NYC, a weekly farmers market and other fun events. Also, enjoy all Washington Park has to offer including tennis courts, basketball courts and other events. Close to transportation, buses to NYC and the Lightrail."
250022193,SOLD,"JC, Heights",465 PALISADE AVE,Condominium,527,6638,"$370,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1R,"JC, Heights",07307,03001,00020,Heights,,,,,1,0,1,5,,"$370,000","$355,000",$702.09,$702.09,10/27/2025,11/14/2025,2/5/2026,18,18,,3/5/2026,,,,"$5,203",2025,$200,2025,Conventional,,,,,,Bowers St and Griffith St,"Welcome to your own sunny sanctuary overlooking Riverview-Fisk Park, offering stunning Manhattan skyline views and a front-row seat to one of Jersey City’s best farmers markets every Sunday from spring through fall.  This bright and spacious one-bedroom home has been beautifully maintained and thoughtfully updated, blending charm and modern convenience. Step inside to discover 9-foot ceilings, a mix of hardwood and porcelain tile floors, and a stylish exposed brick chimney stack that adds character and warmth. The modern kitchen features stainless steel appliances, granite countertops, and a subway-tiled backsplash, while floating shelves throughout the home provide both functionality and flair.  With five closets and additional basement storage, there’s plenty of room to keep everything organized. The building’s smartphone-enabled intercom system ensures you never miss a delivery—even when you’re away.  Commuters will love the convenience of this location—just a half block from the NYC, Hoboken, and Journal Square PATH buses, a short walk to the Congress Street Light Rail, and steps from a Citi Bike dock. Enjoy the best of the Heights with Modcup, Bread & Salt, and Corto right around the corner.  But the true showstopper is the 40-foot fenced-in backyard—a rare find in the Heights. This private retreat comes fully furnished with outdoor tables, Adirondack chairs, a premium Weber Genesis II grill, and bistro lighting throughout. Whether you’re gardening, entertaining, or simply unwinding with a morning coffee or evening cocktail, this outdoor space is the perfect extension of your home.  Don’t miss your chance to own this special piece of the Heights—schedule your private showing today!"
210023648,SOLD,"JC, Heights",256 SHERMAN AVE,Condominium,950,6078,"$370,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,2,0,1,5,,"$370,000","$375,000",$389.47,$389.47,10/14/2021,11/2/2021,12/29/2021,19,19,,12/29/2021,,,,"$4,505",2020,$230,2020,Conventional,,,,,,CONGRESS AND SOUTH,"Welcome to 256 Sherman Avenue residence two.  A charming 2 bedroom situated in one of the nicest areas in JC Heights. This residence features beautiful gleaming hardwood floors, large spacious rooms, master bedroom with walk-in closet, combo w/d & plenty of sunlight from the east and west.  Put your own taste on the kitchen which offers large space along with an area for dining.  Don't forget the common backyard oasis with deck to enjoy late fall nights & outdoor gatherings.  The location is unbeatable, a quick 3 min walk to the 9th St. Lightrail, 2 blocks to Riverview Park, 1 block to Washington Park & all of the highly desirable restaurants, grocery stores, coffee shops along both palisade avenue and central avenue."
230003976,SOLD,"JC, Heights",100 LEONARD ST,Condominium,690,6199,"$370,000",CONDO-COOP,,1st,1R,"JC, Heights",07307,00402,00042,,,,,,2,0,1,5,,"$370,000","$365,000",$536.23,$536.23,3/12/2023,3/24/2023,4/28/2023,12,12,,4/28/2023,,,,"$5,161",2022,$362,,Conventional,,,,,,Kennedy and Nelson,"Beautiful 2 bedroom condo located in Jersey City Heights - with a private yard! This home boasts open concept living, a fully equipped kitchen with stainless steel appliances, granite counter tops, and cherry oak cabinets. The primary bedroom features a bay window that welcomes in lots of natural light, the second bedroom has a large walk-in closet. The bedrooms are on opposite ends, providing separation and privacy. Full bath with tub, ceramic tile, and pedestal sink. Ample closets throughout, stunning hardwood floors, central A/C and heat, and high ceilings. Private storage room and common shared laundry in the basement. This home is situated in a desirable location in Jersey City, known for its great restaurants, shops, and easy access to transportation. It's perfect for those who want to be close to the city but also have a quiet retreat to come home to."
