220008224,SOLD,"JC, Heights",295 NEW YORK AVE,Condominium,687,1603,"$375,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,3,"JC, Heights",07307,02306,00055,,295 New York Avenue,,,,1,0,1,5,,"$375,000","$375,000",$545.85,$545.85,5/9/2022,5/13/2022,7/11/2022,4,4,,9/6/2022,,,,"$3,710",2021,$244,,Conventional,,,,,,South & Bowers,"Beautifully maintained, spacious home on the second floor of a four-unit condo building in Jersey City Heights. The layout is flexible: it can be used as a one or two bedroom.  This home was completely updated in 2016, and features stainless steel appliances, granite countertops, in-unit washer/dryer, hardwood floors, attic storage space and double-paned, energy efficient windows.  Additionally, this home has a private, large secure storage area in the basement.  There is also common storage, and a shared backyard.  The building is pet friendly.  This home is in a terrific location.  It is one block from Riverview Park where you can access multiple buses.   It is also a short walk to the Congress Street Light Rail with connections to the PATH.  Easy access to restaurants, schools, shopping and more!   "
260004273,ACTIVE,"JC, Heights",391 CENTRAL AVE,Condominium,644,1713,"$375,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,5,"JC, Heights",07307,2804,30,Heights,,,,,2,0,1,6,,,"$375,000",$582.30,,3/11/2026,,,29,,,3/11/2026,,$0,0,"$5,525",,$300,,,,,,,,Charles and Thorne streets,"Welcome home to this beautifully renovated 2-bedroom, 1-bathroom apartment at 391 Central Avenue, Unit #3! Situated in the vibrant and convenient Jersey City Heights neighborhood, this residence offers the perfect blend of classic charm and modern upgrades.  Step inside and be greeted by gleaming hardwood floors that flow seamlessly throughout the entire apartment. The stylish kitchen boasts elegant shaker cabinets, providing ample storage and a sophisticated touch. You'll appreciate the convenience of an in-unit washer and dryer, making laundry day a breeze.  The thoughtful design extends to the details, with striking black trim adding a contemporary edge to the space. Beyond the apartment itself, you'll also benefit from extra storage space located in the basement – perfect for stowing away seasonal items and more.  Located on Central Avenue, you'll find yourself surrounded by an array of local shops, restaurants, and cafes. Enjoy easy access to public transportation, making your commute to NYC and other parts of New Jersey a cinch.    Don't miss this opportunity to live in a beautifully appointed apartment in one of Jersey City's most desirable neighborhoods! Schedule your showing today. Parking available nearby for an additional fee."
220017907,SOLD,"JC, Heights",57 ST PAULS AVE,Condominium,974,6199,"$375,000",CONDO-COOP,,"1,2",2,"JC, Heights",07306,06807,00010,Heights,,,,,2,0,2,7,,"$375,000","$365,000",$385.01,$385.01,10/6/2022,11/26/2022,12/20/2022,51,51,,12/20/2022,,,,"$4,553",2020,$417,2021,Conventional,,,,,,Baldwin & Oakland,"This perfectly priced 2 bedroom 2 bathroom plus a den duplex in the heart of Jersey City Heights has it all! First floor features spacious living room and dining room with tons of natural light w/ hardwood floors throughout, large windows, high ceilings, and recessed lighting. Fully equipped kitchen includes brand new stainless steel appliances. Main bedroom has a double closet and full bath with a jacuzzi. Hallway features a linen and coat closet for plenty of storage. Lower level offers a generously sized bedroom with a walk in closet, window bench, and full bathroom equipped with shelving. A den area is perfect for home office or family room. Washer and dryer in common area. Shared backyard. Building is minutes to the Journal Square Path station, and buses to downtown JC and NYC for a commuters dream!"
260001224,ACTIVE,"JC, Heights",3444 JOHN F KENNEDY BLVD,Condominium,750,1601,"$375,000",CONDO-COOP,,4,4F,"JC, Heights",07307,,,,,,,,2,0,1,5,,,"$375,000",$500.00,,1/23/2026,,,76,,,1/23/2026,,,,"$6,017",2024,$349,,,No,No,,,,Bowers & Charles,"Welcome home to this sunlight filled, bright corner unit with high ceilings located in the Heights section of Jersey City. Partial views of Manhattan, views of the meadowlands and views of the JC skyline with three sides of the unit with  windows. Peace of mind in this two bedroom unit with so many updates and upgrades!  13 gorgeous new wood  oversized south  west and north facing windows allows sunlight to flood into every room.  Warm hardwood lead you through to the updated kitchen with custom cabinets  sleek black granite countertops and updated appliances. The living area space in bright and with original stain glass window and a pocket door opening up to the dinning room. Central HVAC system. Private secure storage area in basement along with washer/dryer. Very quiet, must see unit."
