260006126,ACTIVE,"JC, Heights",198 BOWERS ST,Condominium,721,1597,"$379,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,301,"JC, Heights",07307,2704,30,Heights,,,,,1,0,1,5,,,"$379,000",$525.66,,4/7/2026,,,2,,,4/7/2026,,,,"$4,474",,$250,,,,,,,,Summit & Milton,"Bathed in light and brimming with character, this beautifully renovated one bedroom home offers a rare blend of timeless design and modern livability. Perched on a tree-lined street in The Heights just steps from Summit and Central Avenues, each residence feels like a hidden gem—where classic charm meets contemporary comfort.   Step inside to sun-splashed interiors with floor-to-ceiling windows and peek-through openings illuminating classic hardwood floors throughout. The kitchen is finished with natural wood cabinetry, granite counters and a full stainless appliance suite. Boasting elevated touches like pressed tin ceiling tiles and ornate medallions, this unit also includes beautiful built-in living room storage cabinets for extra charm and convenience.  The primary bedroom hosts a graceful archway, crown molding trey ceilings, plus glowing wall sconces for an atmosphere of refined coziness. Generous windows flood the room with light, while the walk-in closet adds enviable storage. The bathroom features a soaking tub and shower combo, medicine cabinet storage, and tile that stretches to the ceiling.   Positioned less than a block from Summit Avenue and moments to Washington Park and the 9th Street Light Rail elevator, these homes are perfect for those seeking character, comfort, and connectivity. Jersey City Heights is known for its artistic community, charming boutique shops and restaurants, excellent parks and schools, and easy accessibility to NYC and surrounding neighborhoods."
