230013149,SOLD,"JC, Heights",464 CENTRAL AVE,Condominium,650,6199,"$385,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,B7,"JC, Heights",07307,02202,00015,Journal Square,,,,,1,1,1,4,,"$385,000","$349,000",$592.31,$592.31,8/7/2023,8/11/2023,8/16/2023,4,4,,8/17/2023,,,,"$5,002",2022,$290,2023,Cash,,,,,,Congress & South,"This Historical schoolhouse built in 1876 is of French neo classical structural brick design, located in the heart of the booming Jersey City Heights, corner of Central and Congress Ave minutes to Light Rail.  Duplex Soho style Loft with boasting 16ft ceilings and an abundance of natural light, open concept living room dining room, with a massive cast iron Corinthian column and spiral staircase, presenting an urban Industrial Architectural feel. A galley kitchen along with a half bath complete the main level. Upper floor with iron railing overlooking the main level, offers a true loft living bedroom with a full bath and dual closets. Hardwood floors throughout, new fixtures in bathrooms. Built to last, with brick structural walls up to 36” thick this multi century building offers an outdoor oasis gated courtyard common area with two 50 year old ornamental cherry trees and a tall hemlock border features a blue slate table and garden, Elevator, on-site laundry facilities for extra convenience and a lower monthly condo fee. Near the beautiful Washington Park with ball fields and large wooded lawns, and restaurants, bars, shops all within a few minutes away making this suited for any lifestyle! Right outside the hustle and bustle of Manhattan, and convenient to the Lincoln and Holland Tunnels (less than 1 mile); close to buses to the Hoboken Path terminal, NY Port Authority and Journal Square Path Station, and the light rail truly making this a commuters’ dream!"
