260004689,ACTIVE,"JC, Heights",149 WEBSTER AVE,Condominium,667,1719,"$389,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,5,"JC, Heights",07307,3804,15,,,,,,2,0,1,4,,,"$389,000",$583.21,,3/17/2026,,,23,,,3/17/2026,,,,"$6,666",2025,$350,,,,,,,,hutton and Griffith,"Welcome to 149 Webster Avenue, Unit 5—a beautifully appointed two-bedroom, one-bath residence offering both comfort and convenience in a prime location. This charming home features an extra-large primary bedroom, second bedroom and full bath with beautiful hardwood floors and central a/c.  The kitchen is equipped with granite countertops and stainless steel appliances, blending style and functionality for everyday living and entertaining. Sunlight fills the space, creating a warm and inviting atmosphere throughout.  Additional designated storage available in the basement as well.  Ideally situated in a vibrant neighborhood, this home offers easy access to local shops, restaurants, parks, and everyday conveniences. Commuters will appreciate the proximity to major transportation options, including nearby bus routes and light rail service, providing a seamless commute to NYC and surrounding areas. A perfect opportunity to enjoy modern living in a highly accessible and desirable location."
220021919,SOLD,"JC, Heights",258 NEW YORK AVE,Condominium,620,1702,"$390,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,6,"JC, Heights",07307,03001,00041,,,,,,2,0,1,4,,"$390,000","$399,000",$629.03,$629.03,12/27/2022,1/13/2023,3/6/2023,17,17,,3/6/2023,,,,"$6,136",,$281,,Conventional,,,,,,Bower and Griffit,"Ideally laid out and bright two bedroom condo located in prime section of Jersey City Heights. This unit features an open floorplan with updated kitchen featuring granite countertops, stainless steel appliances and a breakfast bar. Bedrooms are at opposite ends of the apartment for maximum privacy. You can even enjoy your own deck space off the back. The building features a laundry room in the basement and a shared backyard. Ideally located just a short distance to the 9th St Light Rail Station, and near bus lines to Journal Square and NYC."
240008788,SOLD,"JC, Heights",1012 SUMMIT AVE,Condominium,650,1603,"$390,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,3L,"JC, Heights",07307,02804,00002,,,,,,2,0,1,6,,"$390,000","$399,000",$600.00,$600.00,5/9/2024,6/1/2024,7/10/2024,23,23,,7/11/2024,,,,"$5,146",,$277,,Conventional,,,,,,Charles and Thorne,"1012 Summit Ave is in the heart of the Heights - one block from restaurants and shops on Central Ave, a 10 minute walk to Washington, Riverview, and Pershing Square Park, and a 25 minute commute to Port Authority, NYC. Unit #3L offers 2 large bedrooms on opposite ends of the home & an updated kitchen and bath. The kitchen boasts gleaming stainless steel appliances, a brand new GE Profile microwave, newly painted cabinets with gold hardware, sleek pendant lighting, and additional task lighting with under-mount, motion sensor LEDs.  The updated bathroom offers a new vanity with quartz countertop and an LED-lighted mirror/medicine cabinet - both offering must have storage solutions that are on everyone's wish list.  Head outside through glass French doors, and enjoy an outdoor oasis of your own. This condo's other notable features include: Central A/C, high 10 foot ceilings and gorgeous hardwood floors, laundry in basement, and a dedicated storage room for each unit. Building is also professionally managed. Enjoy the peace and quiet of top floor living, with great indoor and outdoor space, and a great location - all without breaking the bank!"
250005801,SOLD,"JC, Heights",96 BOWERS ST,Condominium,0,6095,"$390,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,3L,"JC, Heights",07307,2206,7,,,,,,1,0,1,4,,"$390,000","$370,000",,,3/26/2025,3/31/2025,5/9/2025,5,5,,5/9/2025,,"$230,100",2023,"$5,170",2023,$266,,Conventional,,,,,,Palisade Ave and Central Ave,"Modern, south-facing, top-floor 1 bedroom, 1 bathroom condo in a highly desirable location. This historic building was converted in 2011 into six stylish railroad-style condos. Step inside this thoughtfully designed residence—the largest in the building—featuring an open-concept living room and kitchen area with new stainless steel appliances, granite countertops, a stone backsplash, and mahogany cabinetry. This charming condo boasts numerous remarkable features, including high ceilings, an office nook, custom shelving and storage in both closets, gleaming hardwood floors, a fully renovated bathroom, and deeded roof rights to the western half of the roof, offering the option to build a roof deck! Additional highlights include central AC/heat, a new in-unit washer and dryer, overhead storage, and a deeded storage room in the basement. Located in the vibrant Heights neighborhood, residents will enjoy an array of trendy coffee shops and restaurants just moments away, including ModCup, Bread & Salt, Corto, Busy Bee Organics, and more. The condo is also near the renovated Riverview-Fisk Park, which features a seasonal farmers market, food trucks, basketball courts, a dog run, and a gazebo with panoramic views of the stunning New York City skyline. Commuting to NYC is a breeze, with a direct bus to Port Authority just a block away and convenient access to the 9th and 2nd Street Light Rail, providing a direct connection to the Hoboken PATH. Additionally, this property benefits from its proximity to the Central and Palisade Avenue redevelopment zones, promising future growth and development in the area."
250014512,SOLD,"JC, Heights",391 CENTRAL AVE,Condominium,644,1713,"$391,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,C,"JC, Heights",07307,2804,30,Heights,,,,,2,0,1,6,,"$391,000","$399,000",$607.14,$607.14,7/16/2025,8/4/2025,10/1/2025,19,19,,10/6/2025,,$0,0,"$5,525",,$300,,Conventional,,,,,,Charles and Thorne streets,"Welcome home to this beautifully renovated 2-bedroom, 1-bathroom apartment at 391 Central Avenue, Unit #3! Situated in the vibrant and convenient Jersey City Heights neighborhood, this residence offers the perfect blend of classic charm and modern upgrades.  Step inside and be greeted by gleaming hardwood floors that flow seamlessly throughout the entire apartment. The stylish kitchen boasts elegant shaker cabinets, providing ample storage and a sophisticated touch. You'll appreciate the convenience of an in-unit washer and dryer, making laundry day a breeze.  The thoughtful design extends to the details, with striking black trim adding a contemporary edge to the space. Beyond the apartment itself, you'll also benefit from extra storage space located in the basement – perfect for stowing away seasonal items and more.  Located on Central Avenue, you'll find yourself surrounded by an array of local shops, restaurants, and cafes. Enjoy easy access to public transportation, making your commute to NYC and other parts of New Jersey a cinch.    Don't miss this opportunity to live in a beautifully appointed apartment in one of Jersey City's most desirable neighborhoods! Schedule your showing today. Parking available nearby for an additional fee."
240010770,SOLD,"JC, Heights",138 LEONARD ST,Condominium,1012,6078,"$391,000",CONDO-COOP,,1R,1R,"JC, Heights",07307,00402,00058,,,,,,3,0,2,7,,"$391,000","$399,999",$386.36,$386.36,6/5/2024,8/2/2024,9/12/2024,58,58,,9/12/2024,,,,"$4,973",2022,$337,2024,Conventional,,,,,,Kennedy & Nelson Avenue,"JC DUPLEX W/ BACKYARD! This unit is fully renovated from top to bottom. This 2-Bed (convertible 3-Bed), 2-Bath gem offers ample room with both a balcony and backyard. The first floor has an open living room, kitchen, and dining room layout with one full bath. Two bedrooms are located on the first floor, providing convenient access, with one of them boasting a private balcony. The lower level can be set up as a potential third bedroom or additional living room/office/playroom area. The second bathroom and laundry hook-up are off this room as well. The unit has natural light throughout and high ceilings, creating a bright and welcoming atmosphere. Ideally located near JFK Blvd, Washington Park, and Summit and Central Ave for shopping. Rental parking nearby. Proximity to transportation, including buses to NYC and the Light Rail, this is a fantastic opportunity for a JC Heights lifestyle. Don't miss out—book your showing today!"
210025705,SOLD,"JC, Heights",1209 SUMMIT AVE,Condominium,,5926,"$393,750",CONDO-COOP,,4,422,"JC, Heights",07307,501,2,Heights,,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$393,750","$400,000",,,11/15/2021,12/1/2021,1/5/2022,16,16,,1/7/2022,,,,"$6,409",,$344,,Conventional,,,,,,JFK BLVD & SUMMIT,"Welcome home to this updated Jersey heights unit in an elevator building. Full bathroom on main floor, two bedrooms & one bathroom upstairs. Recessed lighting on main floor & an abundance of window light throughout showcasing the immaculate condition. One garage parking space, gym, & laundry room are included! Near by the light rail station. New York City bus stop right out front granting NYC access in just minutes."
230017073,SOLD,"JC, Heights",101 ZABRISKIE ST,Condominium,724,1597,"$395,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,6,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$395,000","$399,000",$545.58,$545.58,10/11/2023,10/17/2023,11/27/2023,6,6,,11/27/2023,,,,,,$319,,Conventional,,,,,,JFK and Summit Ave,"Perfectly positioned in the heart of Jersey City Heights, this completely updated home offers classic design and thoughtful layout to tick all of the urban luxury boxes. Light radiates onto the neutral palette and beautifully stained original hardwood floors of this 2 bedroom and 2 bath home, while the split bedroom layout give optimal privacy and flexibility.   Walk into the open floorplan living and kitchen area complete with charcoal-gray cabinets, white quartz counters, classic subway tile backsplash, matching stainless sink and appliances plus nickel fixtures. The front bedroom boasts oversized bay windows and huge side-by-side closets, plus full bath adjacent. Through to the back, owners enjoy convenient in-unit washer and dryer, plus additional bath and bedroom. Building exterior received recent upgrades as well with updating siding and fresh trim.   Less than 1 block from Leonard Gordon Conservancy Park, this home is also quick walking distance to urban thoroughfares Summit and Central Ave plus beautiful Pershing Field Park and next door Reservoir. Jersey City Heights offers vibrant community, great restaurants and essential shops, excellent schools, and easy NYC access."
240007131,SOLD,"JC, Heights",138 LEONARD ST,Condominium,796,1597,"$395,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2L,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,2,0,1,6,,"$395,000","$399,000",$496.23,$496.23,4/17/2024,5/6/2024,6/14/2024,19,19,,6/14/2024,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Nelson & JFK,"Discover a rare gem in Jersey City Heights with this beautifully updated two bedroom home with two private outdoor terraces. French country meets urban luxury with features like wide plank hardwood floors, beautiful bay windows and natural wood accents throughout.  The flowing floor plan offers both a formal living and dining area, with a farmhouse chic kitchen in the heart of it all. Charm emanates with navy cabinetry, butcher block countertops, herringbone tile backsplash, exposed shelves and stainless appliances. Bathed in natural light from the sliding glass doors, owners can easily slip out to the secluded private terrace for a morning cup of coffee or evening respite.   An oversized bay window brings breathtaking light to the front bedroom while the back bedroom offers an additional private back terrace giving ultimate indoor / outdoor living. The bathroom hosts a sizable vanity plus medicine cabinet for plenty of storage, plus a soaker tub shower combo for convenience and flexibility.  Ideally located in the heart of The Heights, owners are walking distance to expansive Washington Park with sports facilities, walking trails and dog run, as well as Summit and Central Ave with essential shopping and vibrant community. A premium neighborhood in Jersey City, The Heights is known for its eclectic vibe, beautiful parks, great schools and easy access to NYC and surrounding neighborhoods."
