210002451,SOLD,"JC, Heights",44 SHERMAN AVE,Condominium,926,1623,"$399,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,3D,"JC, Heights",07307,04502,00002,,44 Sherman,,,,1,1,1,4,,"$399,000","$399,000",$430.89,$430.89,1/28/2021,3/5/2021,4/16/2021,36,36,,4/16/2021,,,,"$4,872",2020,$427,2021,Conventional,No,No,No,,,Franklin and Hutton,"Gorgeous and spacious duplex currently being used as a 1BR, deeded as a 2BR [convert back to 2BR by adding back the wall, see attached floorplan]. Main, entry level spacious LR, DR, Kitchen and 1/2 bath with sliding glass doors to spacious balcony with spectacular views of NYC skyline. 2nd floor currently a huge master bedroom and full bath with tons of closet space. Building features elevator and laundry rooms on floors 1, 2 and 5. Parking spot #14, closest spot to Elevator"
210019552,SOLD,"JC, Heights",41 BEACON AVE,Condominium,600,1419,"$399,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07306,,,,,,,,2,0,2,6,,"$399,000","$399,000",$665.00,$665.00,8/18/2021,8/25/2021,11/19/2021,7,7,,11/22/2021,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Palisade Ave & Baldwin Ave,"Welcome home to this magnificently crafted new construction 2 bd/2 ba condo! This building is located in Jersey City Heights moments from the Journal Square PATH and an anticipated urban city park called the Bergen Arches! The large oversized kitchen contains white shaker cabinets, blue opaque backsplash with gleaming quartz counter tops, stainless steel appliances, and washer/dryer hook ups. The wide plank maple hardwood floors stretch from bedroom to bedroom and throughout the living space. The bathrooms boast sleek, modern finishes, gold accents, and designer vanity. Large windows in all rooms let in a ton of natural light and showcase this home like you wouldn’t believe! Pre-negotiated rental parking nearby completes the picture!"
230014677,SOLD,"JC, Heights",157 NELSON AVE,Condominium,755,1597,"$400,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2L,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$400,000","$425,000",$529.80,$529.80,9/5/2023,12/22/2023,3/5/2024,108,108,,3/5/2024,,,,,,$313,,Conventional,,,,,,Leonard St & North St,"Refresh your lifestyle with this newly refinished two bedroom two bath home in the peaceful neighborhood of Western Slope in Jersey City Heights. With beautiful bay windows, a neutral color palette and flowing floorplan, this home is walking distance to peaceful Washington Park and bustling Summit Avenue for the ideal urban lifestyle balance.  The bright and airy kitchen boasts white shaker cabinetry including a custom wine rack, gleaming quartz counters, tile backsplash and stainless appliances. Natural light drenches the generous bedrooms with oversized windows on either end of the split-plan layout, while classic trim highlights the oversized bay windows in the primary ensuite. Updated bathrooms bring sophistication and practicality with sizable vanities, soaker tub or shower with rainhead fixtures, and polished chrome fittings.  Owners enjoy access to coveted Washington Park with sports facilities, walking trails, landscaped gardens, farmers market, playground and splash pad and more. Jersey City Heights is known for its vibrant community, excellent shops, restaurants and schools and easy NYC and Hoboken access."
220004991,SOLD,"JC, Heights",73 IRVING ST,Condominium,680,1468,"$400,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,201,"JC, Heights",07307,00805,00001,Heights,,,,,1,0,1,3,,"$400,000","$400,000",$588.24,$588.24,3/23/2022,4/22/2022,6/7/2022,30,30,,6/13/2022,,,,$0,,$0,,Conventional,,,,,,Corner of Kennedy Blvd,"Welcome to 73 Irving Street! Be the first to live in the last unit available in this 4-story, new construction boutique building in blossoming Jersey City Heights! This property is situated on a corner lot, allowing for optimal lighting through its numerous floor-to-ceiling windows throughout the unit. You will enter onto beautiful 8” white oak floors into an open layout concept. The kitchen was uniquely designed with custom cabinetry, custom, uniquely ribboned quartz countertops and backsplash and Samsung stainless steel appliances. The unit includes central heating/cooling, washer/dryer, Pella LifeStyle Series windows and cement-fiber structural 3/4 tongue and groove sub flooring for added comfort and durability. 73 Irving Street is conveniently located 1 block from the JFK Blvd/North St bus stop that takes you right into Port Authority NYC, is 2 blocks from Washington Park and is surrounded by retail and food options. A short distance away is Riverview Fisk Park, where you can enjoy a weekend farmers market and a gorgeous Manhattan skyline! Taxes should be independently verified by Jersey City tax assessors office. Developer filing for 5-year tax abatement."
240002012,SOLD,"JC, Heights",120 SHERMAN AVE,Condominium,865,1294,"$400,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2G,"JC, Heights",07307,,,,,,,,1,0,1,4,,"$400,000","$415,000",$462.43,$462.43,2/2/2024,3/13/2024,5/10/2024,40,40,,5/13/2024,,,,"$8,455",,$344,,Conventional,,,,,,Griffith & Bowers,"OPEN HOUSE Saturday 11am-2pm and Sunday 1-3pm! Welcome to this 1 bed, 1 bath condo in the heart of the Riverview Arts District. The open living/dining space boasts soaring ceilings, new hardwood floors, and an updated kitchen with stainless steel appliances and quartz countertops. The full bathroom has been modernized, with the option to convert one closet back into a half bath. The spacious bedroom features a large closet with custom built-ins. Enjoy the building's amenities, including a full-sized gym, elevator, laundry on each floor, parking garage with bike storage, and more. Conveniently located near Riverview Park, bus routes on Palisade Ave, Congress Street Light Rail, and Washington Park. Extra storage $25/month Parking $200/month Gym membership $35/month"
250020987,SOLD,"JC, Heights",258 NEW YORK AVE,Condominium,620,1686,"$400,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,3R/6,"JC, Heights",07307,03001,00041,Heights,,,,,2,0,1,5,,"$400,000","$420,000",$645.16,$645.16,10/10/2025,2/24/2026,4/7/2026,101,101,,4/7/2026,,,,"$6,469",2024,$281,,Conventional,,,,,,Bowers & Griffith St,"Set proudly atop New York Avenue this top floor Jersey City Heights two bedroom one bathroom condominium delights! High ceilings welcome you in and the open flow from room to room invite you to stay. The primary bedroom is flooded with natural light making it the perfect space to relax and unwind after a long day out on the town. The kitchen boasts a gas range, stainless steel appliances, granite countertops, large wood cabinets and a breakfast bar open to the living room for easy entertaining. Pass the bathroom down the hall to the second bedroom complete with ample storage and large french doors allowing the gorgeous eastern light to fill the room. Through the doors you'll find your private deck with quiet east facing views, the perfect spot for a morning coffee as the sun rises over Manhattan. In the basement you have a large locked private storage room and free laundry machines. Packed with promise this space is the perfect starter home situated a block from River View Park, and some of the best restaurants and coffee shops in NJ. NYC transportation steps away completes this incredible property, Don't miss this opportunity to live the high life in the Heights!"
230014513,SOLD,"JC, Heights",76 HUTTON ST,Condominium,630,6199,"$400,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,3,"JC, Heights",07307,03802,00020,,,,,,2,0,1,5,,"$400,000","$385,000",$634.92,$634.92,8/31/2023,9/6/2023,10/20/2023,6,6,,10/23/2023,,,,"$4,247",2022,$307,,FHA,,,,,,Cambridge & Hancock,"Welcome to your piece of paradise in the Heights! This 2 bed, 1 bath with parking less than 1 block from Central Ave and close proximity to Riverview Fisk Park awaits its next buyer! Whether you choose to owner occupy or invest, this cozy unit in an unbeatable location will not disappoint! Only 1 floor up and complete with split style living, with bedrooms on opposite ends of the unit for the ultimate privacy, open kitchen leading into a comfortable sized living room and hardwood floors throughout except in the kitchen where you will enjoy neutral tiling that helps define the space. Additionally, the unit boasts split mini / ductless AC wall units, an elevated luxury. Head down to the basement for Shared laundry and extra storage space along w/the boiler units as to keep your in-unit closets freed up for even more convenient storage needs! Don't miss this one!"
240013531,SOLD,"JC, Heights",118 LEONARD ST,Condominium,890,1623,"$400,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,6,"JC, Heights",07307,00402,00051,,Chelsea Heights Condos,,,,1,1,1,4,,"$400,000","$375,000",$449.44,$449.44,7/12/2024,7/26/2024,8/23/2024,14,14,,8/26/2024,,,,"$5,741",,$325,,Conventional,No,No,No,,,Nelson Ave. & Kennedy Blvd,"Searching for a comfortable home that offers the easy-care, urban lifestyle you’ve always wanted? Enviably set in Jersey City’s The Heights neighborhood, this incredible duplex condo residence might just be what you’re looking for! Previously used as a warehouse, this brick building has been beautifully reimagined into a city haven with high ceilings, detailed millwork, neutral tones, and gleaming oak hardwood flooring. Recessed lighting and brilliant sun streaming through tall windows create a lively atmosphere where a seamlessly flowing layout allows effortless entertaining across the living area. Serve refreshments in the adjacent dining corner, adorned with an elegant chandelier suspended from two-story ceilings. Whip up signature dishes in the bright kitchen with its stainless steel appliances, custom cherry cabinetry with under-trim lighting, chic backsplash, and sleek quartz countertops extending to the two-seater, pendant-lit breakfast bar. A large skylight illuminates the staircase leading to the loft-level bedroom, featuring a work area, dual walk-in closets, and a tastefully updated ensuite with renovated shower/tub combo. A powder room downstairs is available for visitors. Other notables include the new central air and heat system, new hot water tank, a basement storage room, and laundry accessible within the building. Favorably located a short distance from the beating heart of Downtown, enjoy proximity to vibrant Washington Park, the Journal Square PATH station, buses to NYC, and plenty of restaurant options like Leo’s Bakery & Deli, Garcia’s, El Cuco, Coach House, 512 Quantum Sound, and Rumba’s Cafe. Plus, ShopRite of Hoboken and Trader Joe’s are just moments away. Come for a tour before it slips by you! "
240005413,SOLD,"JC, Heights",154 BOWERS ST,Condominium,982,1597,"$400,000",CONDO-COOP,,4,4d,"JC, Heights",07307,02803,00037,Heights,,,,,2,0,1,5,,"$400,000","$400,000",$407.33,$407.33,3/22/2024,5/9/2024,6/21/2024,38,38,,6/22/2024,,,,"$6,182",,$540,,Conventional,,,,,,Central Ave and Summit Ave,"Welcome to your new home in the heart of Jersey City Heights!  Bright and airy 2 bedroom/1 bath condo. This charming corner condo offers a great layout with tons of natural light. Efficiently designed kitchen has wooden cabinetry, granite countertops stainless steel appliances and ceramic tile floor. Kitchen opens to a separate dining room. The living room provides ample space for relaxation and entertainment. Graciously sized main bedroom with windows on two walls. Stylishly appointed tiled bathroom. Gleaming hardwood floors throughout add elegance and warmth.  This home offers an abundance of closet space. Well maintained elevator building, on-site laundry room and parking available. Convenient to NYC transportation, shopping, parks, restaurants and more. Don't miss the opportunity to make this your home! Schedule your personal tour today."
230003837,SOLD,"JC, Heights",63 SHERMAN PL,Condominium,992,6199,"$400,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,BE,"JC, Heights",07307,03603,20,Heights,The Ariston House,,,,2,0,1,6,,"$400,000","$399,000",$403.23,$403.23,3/9/2023,3/17/2023,5/15/2023,8,8,,5/15/2023,,,,"$6,254",2023,$488,,VA,No,No,,,,Summit and Central,"Welcome to The Ariston House. Located in HOT Jersey City Heights on a lovely street surrounded by stunning Victorian homes. This Pre-war, pet friendly building consists of 53 homes and features a beautiful lobby, elevator, and laundry room. Rare Private entrance w/foyer and huge storage room truly make this 2 Bedroom/1bath feel truly unique. One level living with no stairs needed for access. Recently upgraded and move in ready w/lots of natural light. Open floor plan with large living room and eat in kitchen. The main bedroom is large enough to fit a king bed and office/sitting area. Second room can accommodate a queen bed or make a wonderful office. Modern eat in kitchen w/white shaker cabinets , stone grey quartz countertops, SS appliances ,subway tile backsplash and pantry . Freshly painted throughout, refinished hardwood floors and ceiling fans in all rooms. Enjoy the Spa-like bathroom w/ brand new vanity, large soaking tub and modern fixtures. Close proximity to public transportation, citi bikes, shopping , Pershing Field Park and Leonard Gordon Conservatory. The perfect blend of urban convenience with a suburban feel."
250005605,SOLD,"JC, Heights",100 LEONARD ST,Condominium,689,6443,"$400,500",CONDO-COOP,,1,1L,"JC, Heights",07307-3107,402,42,Heights,,,,,2,0,1,4,,"$400,500","$400,000",$581.28,$581.28,3/24/2025,4/11/2025,6/30/2025,18,18,,7/2/2025,,,,"$5,580",2024,$362,mo,Conventional,No,No,No,,,Leonard," Welcome home to this bright, sunlight filled, single level living condo in the heights section of Jersey City. Peace of mind in this two bedroom unit with so many updates and upgrades! A gorgeous new, large bay window (installed in March 2025) allows sunlight to flood into the front bdrm. Warm hardwood floors lead you through to the updated kitchen with tall cherry cabinets, sleek black granite countertops and stainless steel appliances. The bathroom was remodeled in 2021 with handrail, and modern finishes. The living area space in bright and open with a great under the stairs storage area. The 2nd bdrm has oversized doorway, a large walk in closet and access to the backyard porch and patio area which isn't shared with any other unit, a small piece of privacy to call your own! The perfect spot to plant a container garden or just relax outdoors. Also offered with this condo, is a private, secure storage area in the basement along with brand new (free use) washers in the laundry space. New HVAC to be installed in April, new water heater in 10/24, lighting fixtures were updated in 2023. Close proximity to pharmacies,eateries,salons,dry cleaners, banks,dog park and so much more. Great commuter location as well with bus to NYC on the corner and just 15 minutes to midtown."
