230002966,SOLD,"JC, Heights",22 CHARLES ST,Condominium,1050,6078,"$402,500",CONDO-COOP,,3,3L,"JC, Heights",07307,2804,38,Heights,,,,,2,0,1,6,,"$402,500","$425,000",$383.33,$383.33,2/22/2023,4/18/2023,6/21/2023,55,55,,6/21/2023,,,,"$6,546",2022,$325,,Conventional,,,,,,Summit Avenue and Central Avenue,"This stunning condo, located in the highly-coveted JC Heights neighborhood, boasts a complete renovation featuring 2 bedrooms, 1 full bath, and an airy loft space. As soon as you step inside, you'll be struck by the care and attention poured into every detail of the home, including sleek hardwood flooring throughout. The living/dining area offers soaring 14-foot ceilings, providing a spacious and luxurious feel. The recently-renovated kitchen is equipped with top-of-the-line Samsung SS appliances, contemporary cabinetry, timeless quartz countertops, and a stylish 3-seat bar/breakfast counter. The bathroom has been fully redone to incorporate classic and modern style elements, featuring a luxury shower system, marble tile, and double vanity sinks with quartz countertops. Both bedrooms are generously sized and flooded with natural light, offering ample closet space. Plus, the added loft area with 5 ½ foot ceiling provides even more space for you to make your own. Enjoy the convenience of modern Nest thermostats, offering both sophistication and ease. With parks, schools, restaurants, and transportation to NYC just steps away, this location offers everything you need right at your fingertips. Don't miss out on the chance to make this beautiful condo your own!"
210026282,SOLD,"JC, Heights",73 IRVING ST,Condominium,680,1468,"$403,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,301,"JC, Heights",07307,00805,00001,Heights,,,,,1,0,1,3,,"$403,000","$403,000",$592.65,$592.65,11/29/2021,3/2/2022,4/29/2022,93,93,,5/3/2022,,,,$0,,$0,,FHA,,,,,,Corner of Kennedy Blvd,"Welcome to 73 Irving Street! Be the first to live in this 4-story new construction boutique building in blossoming Jersey City Heights! This property is situated on a corner lot, allowing for optimal lighting through its numerous floor-to-ceiling windows. You will enter onto beautiful 8” white oak floors into an open layout concept. The kitchen was uniquely designed with custom cabinetry, custom, uniquely ribboned quartz countertops and backsplash and Samsung stainless steel appliances. The master bedroom is also surrounded by windows and flooded with light. The unit includes central heating/cooling, washer/dryer, Pella LifeStyle Series windows and cement-fiber structural 3/4 tongue and groove sub flooring for added comfort and durability. 73 Irving Street is conveniently located 1 block from the JFK Blvd/North St bus stop that takes you right into Port Authority NYC, is 2 blocks from Washington Park and is surrounded by retail and food options. And a short distance away is Riverview Fisk Park where you can enjoy a weekend farmers market and a gorgeous Manhattan skyline! HOA numbers are approximate and taxes are TBD/should be independently verified by Jersey City tax assessor. Developer filing for 5-year tax abatement beginning of February '22.   "
250011901,SOLD,"JC, Heights",787 SUMMIT AVE,Condominium,811,1597,"$404,000",CONDO-COOP,,4,16(L),"JC, Heights",07307,4801,16,,,,,,2,0,1,4,,"$404,000","$399,000",$498.15,$498.15,6/12/2025,6/17/2025,7/30/2025,5,5,,7/31/2025,,,,"$5,053",,$567,,Conventional,,,,,,Troy,"Step into this stunning 2-bedroom, 1-bath condo, where bright, beautifully renovated living meets the best of Jersey City Heights. With 811 sqft of thoughtfully designed space, this home is filled with natural light pouring in through brand-new windows. The kitchen is a culinary dream, featuring crisp white quartz countertops, high-end cabinetry, and sleek 7 white oak plank floors. Unwind in the serene bathroom, a private spa retreat with marble counters and chic gold accents. The main bedroom is a peaceful haven, while the second bedroom offers versatility as a guest room, home office, or more. Every detail has been carefully crafted, from polished new baseboard covers to a dedicated storage space in the basement. Enjoy breathtaking Manhattan views, scenic strolls around the JC Heights Reservoir, and easy access to shops, restaurants, and NYC via PATH or bus. Plus, take advantage of a first-time homebuyer program with just 5% down and no PMI. Discover the perfect blend of comfort, style, and convenience in this vibrant neighborhood."
210027298,SOLD,"JC, Heights",549 PALISADE AVE,Condominium,1135,1691,"$405,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$405,000","$399,000",$356.83,$356.83,12/17/2021,1/27/2022,3/30/2022,41,41,,4/9/2022,,,,,,$322,,Cash,,,,,,South St & Congress St,"Modern design and mindful finishes heat things up in coveted Jersey City Heights. The white-hot facade of this beautifully refinished Tudor-style stonework building leads to a secure entrance for each of the four 2-bed, 2 full bath homes. Each slightly different floorplan offers a variety of must-haves, each boasting modern design, fresh finishes plus common storage.  Clean lines and simple design echo throughout each unit with gleaming hardwood floors and flowing floorplans. Kitchens shine brightly with sparkling quartz counters, shaker cabinets and stainless Frigidaire appliances, while bathrooms showcase porcelain tile finished to the ceiling plus optimal soaker tubs and showers. Sizable bedrooms with ceiling fans, plus Samsung washer and dryer are standard in each home.  This perfect Palisade location is walking distance to Riverview Fisk and Washington Parks, plus just steps from essential shops, vibrant community, excellent schools and easy NYC, PATH and Light Rail access."
