230009561,SOLD,"JC, Heights",154 OGDEN AVE,Condominium,730,6095,"$407,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2B,"JC, Heights",07307,05103,00009,,Pohlmann Hall,,,,1,0,1,5,,"$407,000","$429,000",$557.53,$557.53,6/9/2023,6/15/2023,9/6/2023,6,6,,9/6/2023,,,,"$5,720",2022,$340,,Cash,,,,,,Franklin & Ferry,"Extraordinary opportunity to own this charming One-bedroom loft-style with parking on a highly coveted block in the Heights! Notable features of this corner unit include panoramic eastern exposure with stunning views of NYC, soaring 17-foot ceilings, oversized windows, and a loft bedroom. The open floor plan encompasses a spacious living room, hardwood flooring, a bonus nook, a full bathroom, and a well-appointed kitchen. Ascend the spiral staircase to unveil a versatile loft area that serves as a full bedroom and provides additional storage space. Pohlmann's Hall, located on Ogden Avenue, holds a prestigious spot on the National Register of Historic Places. Originally constructed in 1874 by a German entrepreneur, it functioned as a social hall, beer garden, and hotel, taking advantage of its breathtaking views of the Hudson River, Manhattan skyline, and even the Statue of Liberty. In the basement, you'll find a room where the beer kegs were once lowered, and a wooden platform at the back of the building was dedicated to dancing. Building amenities include gated parking, a private garden, laundry facility on each floor, additional storage, and bike room. Easy commute to NYC via Light Rail (1 stop connect to Hoboken PATH) and direct buses along Palisade Ave. Close to Palisade and Central Ave redevelopment zones that offer a plethora of chic coffee shops, dining, shopping, and the stunning Riverview Fisk Park with seasonal farmer's market, panoramic NYC views, dog run, day cares, and mini-farm, and basketball courts."
