220001145,SOLD,"JC, Heights",138 LEONARD ST,Condominium,1110,1691,"$412,371",CONDO-COOP,,1,1L,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,3,1,1,6,,"$412,371","$399,000",$371.51,$371.51,1/19/2022,2/18/2022,4/18/2022,30,30,,5/2/2022,,,,,,$250,,Conventional,,,,,,Kennedy & Nelson,"Rare gem shines bright in Jersey City Heights. Newly refinished three bedroom plus bonus room and office offers split level floorplan, two private outdoor spaces plus elegant finishes and elements of history throughout. Light streams in through the double glass sliding doors of the courtyard style balcony and into the flowing floorplan offering distinct living, kitching and dining areas. Centrally located white kitchen gleams with shaker cabinets, quartz counters, tile backsplash and stainless Whirlpool appliances.  Beautiful bay windows adorn the spacious front bedroom, with an additional bedroom plus full bath awaiting in the rear. Head downstairs to bonus room area, third bedroom, office, half bath and additional private balcony for excellent flexibility, function and enjoyment.  Walking distance to expansive Washington Park with sports facilities, walking trails and dog run, as well as Summit and Central Ave with essential shopping and vibrant community, this property offers urban living at it’s finest. Jersey City’s fastest growing neighborhoods, The Heights is known for its eclectic vibe, beautiful parks, great schools and easy access to NYC and surrounding neighborhoods."
230011251,SOLD,"JC, Heights",50 RESERVOIR AVE,Condominium,993,1597,"$415,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,201,"JC, Heights",07307,05007,00019,Heights,,,,,2,0,1,5,,"$415,000","$418,000",$417.93,$417.93,7/6/2023,7/20/2023,8/8/2023,14,14,,8/10/2023,,,,"$6,882",2022,$638,2023,Cash,No,No,,,,Webster Ave & Lienau Pl,"*Unit is now vacant, and has been freshly painted with new lighting installed* Located on the coveted tree lined Reservoir Avenue in Jersey City Heights, in one of the most beautiful pre-war condominium buildings in the area. This spacious corner Two Bedroom residence has windows on 3 sides and is flooded with natural light all day from Southern and Eastern exposures. The dining room with French doors can easily be converted to a third bedroom, den, or home office. This beautiful home retains much of the stunning Old-World details such as hardwood floors, picture rail moldings and plastered ceilings. The windowed galley kitchen has been updated with stainless steel appliances including a dishwasher, microwave, and granite countertops. The stately and imposing building features an extraordinarily elegant marble lobby with original tiled floors, an elevator and laundry room with smart technology machines that notify you when laundry cycle is complete. Perfectly situated one block from NYC bus and hip Palisade Avenue, in a neighborhood full of cafes, coffee shops, art galleries, parks and in close proximity to reservoir,  Riverview Farmers Market, Pershing Field Athletic Center, 2nd St Hoboken LightRail station, Hoboken, Downtown JC, CitiBike, Central Avenue shopping district and more. This fantastic condominium residence is an opportunity not to be missed. Pets welcome."
