240005675,SOLD,"JC, Heights",198 NEW YORK AVE,Condominium,658,1597,"$419,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,3L,"JC, Heights",07307,,,,,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$419,000","$419,000",$636.78,$636.78,3/27/2024,4/4/2024,5/17/2024,8,8,,5/20/2024,,,,"$5,663",,$227,,Miscellaneous,,,,,,Hutton & Griffith,"Settled on a quiet street in Jersey City Heights, this two bed, two bath home is the ideal blend of comfort, classic finishes and convenience. Just one block to Riverview Fisk Park with Manhattan skyline views, and 2nd Street Lightrail Station in Hoboken, both commuting and community are a breeze.  The corner unit brings an opportunity for additional natural light, accentuating the warm tones with high ceilings, bamboo hardwood floors and wood trim and crown molding throughout. The open floorplan brings additional spaciousness, with the eat-in kitchen featuring cherry cabinetry with exposed shelves, granite countertops and stainless steel appliances.  Both bedrooms bring ample square footage and closet space, while bathrooms are finished with natural tiles, bathtub and shower combination, plus vanity with chrome fixtures. Convenience meets luxury with a utility closet housing a stacking washer and dryer, while a storage unit in the basement provides ample space for your belongings.  Jersey City Heights is known for its excellent art scene, beautiful parks, great schools and easy access to NYC and surrounding areas. This move-in ready gem is primed for ideal location and urban living!"
