210002918,SOLD,"JC, Heights",63 SHERMAN PL,Condominium,,1691,"$420,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,A6,"JC, Heights",07307,6306,20,Heights,,,,,2,0,1,5,,"$420,000","$420,000",,,2/4/2021,3/4/2021,5/10/2021,28,28,,5/10/2021,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Summit Ave & Sanford Pl,"Found surrounded by Victorian homes, rows of Poplars and historic charm, The Ariston is a treasure on this sweet street of Jersey City Heights. Combined with ultimate character and modern upgrades, this refinished oversized two bedroom home sweet home offers a bounty of space, urban luxury and opportunity.  This pre war condominium features intricate details like parquet flooring and original crown molding throughout, plus gems like crystal door hardware sprinkled for interest. Renovated kitchen includes earthtone granite countertops, mosaic backsplash, single-handle pull-down faucet, custom cabinetry and stainless appliances including French door refrigerator. Bathroom updates include floor to ceiling tile, pedestal sink, vanity lighting and wall storage all keeping with original old-world charm. Ceiling fans in every room.  Bygone era building with elevator and laundry room is fully maintained. The Ariston is a stone's throw from Pershing Field Park, expansive Reservoir #3 and Leonard Gordon Conservancy,  plus walkable to NJ and NY transit or Citi bike stations. Jersey City Heights is home to the perfect blend of urban and escape, including essential shops, excellent schools, outdoor oases and ever-growing opportunity."
250017856,SOLD,"JC, Heights",391 CENTRAL AVE,Condominium,644,1713,"$420,000",CONDO-COOP,,4,6,"JC, Heights",07307,2804,30,Heights,,,,,3,0,1,7,,"$420,000","$425,000",$652.17,$652.17,9/2/2025,9/16/2025,11/12/2025,14,14,,11/12/2025,,$0,0,"$5,525",,$300,,Conventional,,,,,,Charles and Thorne streets,"Nestled in the vibrant heart of Jersey City Heights, 391 Central Ave #6 presents a charming and modern living space. This inviting residence features two generously sized bedrooms, accompanied by a versatile den that can easily adapt to your lifestyle, whether you need a dedicated home office, a cozy guest room, or a creative studio. Bathed in natural light, the apartment boasts gleaming hardwood floors that create a warm and welcoming ambiance throughout.  The kitchen is a true highlight, designed with both style and functionality in mind. It showcases sleek stainless steel Whirlpool appliances, complemented by elegant shaker cabinets and a classic subway tile backsplash, offering a sophisticated culinary experience. The bathroom provides a touch of contemporary elegance with its glass-enclosed tub, creating a serene space for relaxation. Adding to the convenience of modern living, an in-unit washer and dryer eliminate the hassle of laundry day. Furthermore, additional storage space is included in the basement, providing valuable room for your belongings.  Situated in a prime Jersey City Heights location, this apartment offers easy access to a diverse array of local shops, restaurants, and convenient transportation options. This desirable address provides the perfect blend of comfort, style, and urban convenience, making it an ideal place to call home. Don't miss the opportunity to experience the unique charm of 391 Central Ave #6; schedule a showing today and discover your new Jersey City haven."
210010962,SOLD,"JC, Heights",510 PALISADE AVE,Condominium,900,1603,"$420,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,3R,"JC, Heights",07307,02401,00004,,,,,,3,0,2,6,,"$420,000","$424,900",$466.67,$466.67,5/7/2021,6/18/2021,8/12/2021,42,42,,8/12/2021,,,,"$6,690",20,$387,21,Conventional,,,,,,Bowers and South,"Fabulously appointed 3 bedroom / 2 full bathroom home in the Riverview Arts District of Jersey City Heights.  This truly spectacular home features a fully equipped kitchen with custom cabinetry, stainless steel appliance package and granite countertops. Living/dining room is spacious and bright, features exposed brick, high ceilings and crown molding.  3 true bedrooms - two at opposite ends of the home and one in the middle affording lots of privacy. Both bathrooms are updated, spacious with the primary bathroom featuring a soaking tub. Other highlights include recessed lighting, high ceilings throughout, sunrise and sunset exposure, newly installed hardwood flooring, an abundance of closet storage space, dedicated storage room, free on-site laundry and gorgeous landscaped common yard.  Located adjacent to the newly renovated Riverview-Fisk Park, you'll find convenient access to farmers markets, boutique shops, local restaurants, sweeping views of the Manhattan Skyline and Hudson River, the NJ Transit bus to Port Authority, the 9th and Congress Light-Rail stop and elevator in to Hoboken."
250021341,SOLD,"JC, Heights",102 OGDEN AVE,Condominium,652,5715,"$420,000",CONDO-COOP,,4,402,"JC, Heights",07307,5202,22,Heights,Ogden Parkview Condo,,,,1,0,1,4,,"$420,000","$429,000",$644.17,$644.17,10/15/2025,10/27/2025,12/16/2025,12,12,,12/17/2025,,"$317,800",2024,"$7,140",2023,$239,,Cash,,,,,,Cuneo & Dead End,"Welcome to 102 Ogden Avenue — a bright and comfortable home tucked on one of the most coveted streets in The Heights. The space has great flow, high ceilings and tons of natural light that gives it an open feel from the moment you walk in. The kitchen is warm and functional with solid wood cabinetry, stainless steel appliances, granite counter and a patterned tile floor that adds personality. Enjoy your meals in the built-in dining nook that makes for great use of the space. The living area gets tons of natural light while the bedroom is large enough for a full furniture set up plus a desk or reading spot. You'll also find in-unit laundry, ample closet space and a full bathroom with tub.  Additionally, you’re right across from Riverview-Fisk Park and the dog park and just a short walk to the 9th Street Light Rail elevator and local spots such as The Alps, Low Fidelity, Bread & Salt and everything that makes Hudson County such a lovely place to live."
260003953,ACTIVE,"JC, Heights",102 OGDEN AVE,Condominium,652,1672,"$420,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,302,"JC, Heights",07310,5202,23,Heights,,,,,1,0,1,3,,,"$420,000",$644.17,,3/6/2026,,,34,,,3/6/2026,,"$317,800",2026,"$7,420",2026,$250,2026,,No,No,,,,Ogden And Cuneo,"Welcome home to a bright and sunny one bedroom located on the quiet end of the best street in the Heights. High ceilings hardwood floors and a modern kitchen. The kitchen features solid wood cabinetry, granite countertops and all stainless steel appliances. The spacious bedroom has hardwood floors and a fabulous walk-in closet. Bright and modern luxury bathroom with top of the line fixtures. Relax in your jetted tub! New washer and dryer in home. Central heat and air conditioning. Some of the best dining JC has to offer is within an easy stroll.  Lo-Fi, Bread and Salt, Corto, Bodega and so much more. This home is conveniently located, right next to the award winning Ogden’ End community garden and across from a dog park and kids playground. Spring is coming and the farmers market in Fisk Riverview Park will return soon!  Easy commute to the city and a short walk to the 100 Steps an the 9th Street Light Rail Elevator."
