220009676,SOLD,"JC, Heights",238 OGDEN AVE,Condominium,734,1691,"$430,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,5,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,2,0,1,5,,"$430,000","$425,000",$585.83,$585.83,5/31/2022,6/13/2022,7/15/2022,13,13,,7/15/2022,,,,,,$350,,Conventional,,,,,,Griffith & Franklin,"Perched on coveted Ogden Avenue in the Heights, this freshly renovated two bedroom home offers move-in ready beauty plus walkability to nearby Riverview Fisk Park, light rail train and NYC views / access.  Light floods in through the large windows encased in white molding, illuminating the open floorplan and Maple hardwood floors. Eat-in kitchen bar is finished with sleek black quartz counters and pendant lighting, plus custom white cabinetry, herringbone tile backsplash and stainless steel appliances. Bedrooms include ceiling fans and ample closet space, while the bathroom boasts pedestal sink, gleaming white tile and tub with rain head shower combo.  Timeless brick corner building is situated on a corner lot, offering windows on three sides, and secure entry from the street. Jersey City Heights is known for it’s eclectic shops and restaurants, close-knit community, excellent parks and proximity to nearby Hoboken, Downtown and NYC."
