210015455,SOLD,"JC, Heights",549 PALISADE AVE,Condominium,1,1691,"$440,500",CONDO-COOP,,4,4,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$440,500","$425,000","$440,500.00","$440,500.00",6/25/2021,8/10/2021,10/14/2021,46,46,,10/15/2021,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,South St & Congress St,"Modern design and mindful finishes heat things up in coveted Jersey City Heights. The white-hot facade of this beautifully refinished Tudor-style stonework building leads to a secure entrance for each of the four 2-bed, 2 full bath homes. Each slightly different floorplan offers a variety of must-haves, each boasting modern design, fresh finishes plus common storage.  Clean lines and simple design echo throughout each unit with gleaming hardwood floors and flowing floorplans. Kitchens shine brightly with sparkling quartz counters, shaker cabinets and stainless Frigidaire appliances, while bathrooms showcase porcelain tile finished to the ceiling plus optimal soaker tubs and showers. Sizable bedrooms with ceiling fans, plus Samsung washer and dryer are standard in each home.  The second floor unit radiates sunlight with oversized windows, plus sliding glass doors leading to a large private treetop roofdeck, while the top floor unit elevates with vaulted ceilings, unique lines and master bedroom balcony. The first floor also boasts a beautiful master balcony and the lower unit showcases a thoughtful split floor plan with separate large kitchen and dining.  This perfect Palisade location is walking distance to Riverview Fisk and Washington Parks, plus just steps from essential shops, vibrant community, excellent schools and easy NYC, PATH and Light Rail access."
240011883,SOLD,"JC, Heights",356 PALISADE AVE,Condominium,840,1603,"$442,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1B,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,1,1,1,4,,"$442,000","$449,000",$526.19,$526.19,6/20/2024,7/16/2024,8/22/2024,26,26,,8/23/2024,,,,"$4,532",,$474,,Conventional,,,,,,Franklin and Ferry,"Welcome Home! In today's market where opportunities are scarce this exquisitely renovated 1-bedroom, 1.5-bathroom loft style condo stands out as a rare find. Renovated top to bottom, and spread across two floors, this home features an expansive bedroom suite, 1.5 baths, and a bonus area perfect for a work from homes setup. Brand new wide plank hardwood floors throughout, create an elegant and inviting ambiance. The gourmet kitchen features updated cabinetry with an abundance of storage space, customized back splash and an over sized island that will be sure to satisfy. The spacious living area is bathed in natural light, creating a bright and airy atmosphere that's perfect for both relaxation and entertaining. Head downstairs to your bedroom suite where you are sure to be impressed by the over sized, and customized walk-in closet - a true showstopper - as well as a bonus area perfect for a work-from-home setup. Both bathrooms have been tastefully updated. From sleek fixtures to luxurious finishes, no expense has been spared in creating these stylish and functional spaces. Lastly, and perhaps the most coveted feature of the home is the deeded parking, ensuring that you'll never have to worry about finding a spot after a long day. With NYC transportation right at your door and only a short walk to Hoboken, commuting has never been easier. Outside your doorstep,you'll find yourself in the heart of the Heights surrounded with amenities, including trendy cafes, restaurants, and parks, ensuring that you'll always have something new to explore right in your own neighborhood. Professionally managed building, with low taxes, make this a great opportunity and smart investment."
