240008266,SOLD,"JC, Heights",102 PALISADE AVE,Condominium,1099,1653,"$445,000",CONDO-COOP,,4,4B,"JC, Heights",07306,6901,13,,,,,,2,1,1,6,,"$445,000","$449,000",$404.91,$404.91,5/3/2024,6/26/2024,8/14/2024,54,54,,8/15/2024,,,,"$6,303",2022,$280,2023,Conventional,,No,,,,139 & Fleet St," Walking distance to Journal Square Path and Downtown Jersey City.  Make this top Floor unit with NYC views your new home or investment property.  Sitting just one block into the Heights this location and home has it all.  Features a floor plan that functions as 3 or 2 bedrooms and 1.5 baths enjoy Top of natural light, hardwood floors, Washer/Dryer Hook-up in unit + additional laundry in basement.  The home can be customized and function many different ways creating ultimate flexibility for the owner.  Main features include 3 built-in wall shelving systems, updated bathrooms, high ceilings & ornate light fixtures. The bus to the city is right outside along with a plethora of bars, restaurants and shopping. Call today for more information or to schedule a private showing."
260004440,ACTIVE,"JC, Heights",1 CONGRESS ST,Condominium,950,5069,"$445,000",CONDO-COOP,,2.5,304,"JC, Heights",07307,2404,41,,Kimberly Arms,,,,1,0,1,3,,,"$445,000",$468.42,,3/13/2026,,,27,,,3/13/2026,,,,"$7,742",2026,$383,2026,,No,No,No,,,Ogden Ave and Paterson Plank Rd,"Beautifully renovated 1 Bedroom just steps from the 9th St light rail (via free elevator) & Hoboken! South-facing top-floor unit offers stylish and modern living—just 1.5 flights up in a well maintained boutique building.  The sleek kitchen features stainless steel appliances, quartz countertops, and a custom backsplash, and opens into a spacious living and dining area—ideal for relaxing or working from home. The oversized bedroom comfortably fits a king-sized bed and includes generous closet space. The chic, modern bathroom is outfitted with walk-in shower. Additional highlights include overhead lighting, gleaming hardwood floors throughout, and the convenience of in-building laundry. Enjoy a virtual doorman system (ButterflyMX) and the unbeatable location at the corner of Ogden Ave & Congress St—just moments away from the Hoboken elevator, 9th St Light Rail, and NYC bus stop for easy commuting. Explore everything the neighborhood has to offer, including the Riverview Farmers Market, local eateries, coffee shops, and more! Heat, hot water and gas are included in the HOA. On-site parking avail for $40/mo additional HOA fee. Perfect for first-time homebuyers or investors alike—don’t miss this incredible opportunity! "
230006308,SOLD,"JC, Heights",107 BOWERS ST,Condominium,780,6494,"$446,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2R,"JC, Heights",07307,02901,00006,Heights,,,,,2,0,1,4,,"$446,000","$410,000",$571.79,$571.79,4/20/2023,4/25/2023,6/9/2023,5,5,,6/12/2023,,,,"$5,659",2022,$309,,Conventional,No,No,,,,Cambridge and Central Aves,"Hip, Hot, and Happening in The Heights! This wonderful floor through 2 bedroom condo has been beautifully updated and is in pristine condition.  Open the front door to your large entry foyer and be immediately impressed with gleaming hardwood floors, soaring ceilings, and windows on 3 sides for brilliant light.  The oversized living room is a terrific gathering place to entertain with family and friends, or simply enjoy a quiet evening of Netflix. The windowed eat-in-kitchen features granite countertops, subway tile backsplash, hardwood cabinetry, under counter lighting, and a full suite of stainless steel appliances including 5 burner gas range, d/w, microwave, and french door refrigerator with water/ice.The king-sized primary bedroom is revealed through an historic pocket door, and has an oversized walk-in closet with built-ins.  Your windowed bathroom has been tastefully renovated with glazed ash tile, modern tub/shower/vanity and European toilet.  The equally large second bedroom is thoughtfully placed on the opposite side of the home for both privacy and quiet.  107 Bowers is a well maintained, boutique building, perfectly situated between Central and Palisade Avenues....Corto, Bread and Salt, Choc-o-Pain, Pampita, Dulce de Leche, Modcup coffee, and Riverview Fisk Park are outside your doorstep.  A charming resident's outdoor patio w/ seating, grilling, and dining area is perfect for al fresco evenings.  On-site complimentary washer/dryers, low hoa/taxes, AND a huge dedicated storage area reserved for this unit completes the picture."
260004102,ACTIVE,"JC, Heights",329 PALISADE AVE,Condominium,600,1685,"$449,999",CONDO-COOP,,2,4,"JC, Heights",07307,,,,,,,,2,0,1,4,,,"$449,999",$750.00,,3/9/2026,,,31,,,3/9/2026,,,,"$6,159",2026,$428,,,No,No,No,,,Ferry st & Franklin st,"Welcome to this well-maintained and spacious 2-bedroom, 1-bath corner residence nestled in the vibrant Jersey City Heights neighborhood. With southern and eastern exposures, the home is filled with natural light throughout the day.  Upon entering, you're welcomed by an inviting open-concept layout where the kitchen flows seamlessly into the living area—ideal for both everyday living and entertaining. The kitchen is equipped with sleek appliances including a dishwasher, refrigerator, microwave, and stove, offering both modern style and everyday functionality.  The bathroom features a timeless, stylish design, providing both comfort and contemporary appeal. Additional highlights include beautiful hardwood floors, a neutral color palette, and abundant natural light, all enhancing the home’s classic charm.  Residents enjoy the added convenience of on-site laundry with a washer and dryer located in the building’s basement, eliminating the need for trips to the laundromat.  Ideally located, this home offers easy access to a variety of local restaurants, cafés, shops, and green spaces, including Pershing Field Park and Riverview-Fisk Park.  Commuting is effortless with multiple transportation options nearby, including: • NJ Transit bus stop directly in front of the building with service to Port Authority Bus Terminal • Easy access to Journal Square PATH Station with service to World Trade Center and 34th Street • Nearby 2nd Street Light Rail station connecting to Hoboken, Newport, and Exchange Place  Whether you're an owner-occupant or investor, this property presents an exceptional opportunity in one of Jersey City's most sought-after neighborhoods.  Special Financing Opportunity: Please reach out to our preferred lender Jackie Koven with CrossCountry Mortgage regarding grant programs offering $15,000–$22,000 in assistance and reduced interest rates as low as 5.5%."
260004409,ACTIVE,"JC, Heights",147 NEW YORK AVE,Condominium,700,6199,"$450,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,3L,"JC, Heights",07307,4505,26,Heights,,,,,1,0,1,5,,,"$450,000",$642.86,,3/12/2026,,,28,,,3/12/2026,,,,"$4,031",2023,,TBD,,,,,,,Palisade & Ferry,"Renovation in the works! New Bath, New Kitchen, New Flooring, New Fixtures etc.  All New and Waiting for You! Fully Tiled Bathroom, Custom Kitchen featuring SMEG appliances and built in storage. Beautiful wood floors throughout. Excellent Natural Light. Washer / Dryer In Unit. Plus, a private storage cage on the lower level.   One Bedroom plus Den located on one of the most desirable blocks in the Heights, one block from Palisade Ave. Ultra convenient location offering Restaurants and Shopping, with easy access to NYC, Downtown JC and Hoboken. Transportation options include the LightRail and buses to JSQ and NYC.  *Inquire about Other Units Available."
230005535,SOLD,"JC, Heights",37 BOWERS ST,Condominium,761,1597,"$450,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,2,0,1,5,,"$450,000","$450,000",$591.33,$591.33,4/6/2023,5/18/2023,7/3/2023,42,42,,7/5/2023,,,,,,$161,,Conventional,,,,,,Palisade Ave & New York Ave,"Ultimate urban luxury delights just one block from Riverview Fisk Park in Jersey City Heights. The well-laid out two bed, one bath home is recently renovated and move-in ready. Light floods in through the large bay windows and onto the classic hardwood floors, stylish lighting and neutral color palette.  Kitchen and breakfast area include gray quartz counters with mosaic backsplash, white cabinetry, stainless Frigidaire appliances, and wood tile for added convenience. Spacious rooms offer flexibility with options for additional bedroom, nursery, office or home gym. Bathroom brings stylish black and white retro design with floor to ceiling white subway tile with black grout, geo-tiling on floors, glass shower and matte black fixtures.  Beautifully finished blue exterior brings bright presence to the Riverview Arts District of Jersey City Heights. Nearby Riverview Fisk Park offers elevated NYC views, trails, playgrounds, sports facilities, farmers markets and festivals. Jersey City Heights is known for its eclectic art scene, vibrant community, boutique shops and restaurants, beautiful parks, excellent schools and easy NYC access."
250011705,SOLD,"JC, Heights",50 RESERVOIR AVE,Condominium,993,1713,"$450,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,201,"JC, Heights",07307,5007,19,Heights,,,,,2,0,1,6,,"$450,000","$465,000",$453.17,$453.17,6/10/2025,7/14/2025,8/19/2025,34,34,,8/20/2025,,,,"$7,255",2025,,,Conventional,,,,,,PROSPECT AND BOOREAM,"Bright, Spacious, Charming 2-Bedroom, 1-Bath corner unit condo located in a stately pre-war elevator building on coveted Reservoir Ave. This home blends modern conveniences with classic architectural details. Enjoy lovely south- and east-facing views overlooking the grounds from large windows that fill the space with natural light all day long. This home retains many original details such as gorgeous hardwood floors, picture moldings, plaster ceilings and French doors between the living and dining rooms. The floor plan is laid out to create a comfortable space for entertaining and family time. High ceilings enhance the home's airy, open feel, while the spacious bedrooms easily accommodate a king-size bed. Ample closet space ensures plenty of storage. The windowed galley kitchen boasts modern stainless-steel appliances and granite countertops. Building amenities include an app-enabled video entry system for security and convenience and an on-site laundry room. Situated in one of the most desirable locations in Jersey City Heights, you’ll be just steps from parks, shops, and cafes, with easy access to transportation for a quick commute to NYC."
240007724,SOLD,"JC, Heights",249 NEW YORK AVE,Condominium,700,1597,"$450,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,201,"JC, Heights",07307,2905,22,Heights,,,,,2,0,1,3,,"$450,000","$450,000",$642.86,$642.86,4/25/2024,5/3/2024,6/7/2024,8,8,,6/11/2024,,,,"$5,907",2023,$275,,Conventional,,,,,,Bowers & Griffith,"Located in the convenient and desirable Riverview Arts neighborhood in Jersey City Heights, this two bedroom, one bathroom with bath tub features great natural light, a renovated kitchen, hardwood floors, central air, additional in-building storage, in-building laundry and large shared backyard. Bedrooms have excellent proportions and are located on opposite ends of the home. Live near it all with easy access to NYC transportation, Riverview Park, restaurants and shops."
230012487,SOLD,"JC, Heights",63 SHERMAN PL,Condominium,1043,1568,"$450,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,B6,"JC, Heights",07307,03603,00020,,Ariston House,,,,2,0,1,5,,"$450,000","$469,000",$431.45,$431.45,7/26/2023,9/22/2023,12/1/2023,58,58,,12/4/2023,,,,"$7,149",2022,$527,2022,Conventional,,,,,,Summit Ave. & Sanford Place,"Welcome home to The Ariston at 63 Sherman Place, a treasured tree-lined street in Jersey City Heights surrounded by Victorian homes, and just minutes to Central Ave bakeries, shopping, Pershing Field Park and convenient access into NYC, Hoboken or Downtown Jersey City. This bright & expansive, 2Bed/1Bath southeast Corner unit beautifully blends old world charm with modern upgrades.  This stately pre-war elevator building features intricate craftsmanship and details like parquet hardwood floors, large windows, high ceilings and original crown molding throughout. Enter the home and you are greeted by a gracious entry foyer that's perfect for artwork and clearly separates the large secluded master bedroom and brand new renovated bathroom from the oversized living room, second bedroom/den with french doors and windowed eat-in kitchen with an archway entry, stainless steel gas cooktop/stove, microwave, dishwasher, refrigerator and abundant cabinetry. A bright southeast corner exposure floods in natural light all day long, and a host of sizable walk-in closets offer ample storage for all of your belongings. Building amenities include on-site laundry facility, elevator and are professionally managed. "
260004642,ACTIVE,"JC, Heights",33 GRAHAM ST,Condominium,647,6705,"$450,000",CONDO-COOP,,1&2,3,"JC, Heights",07307,1504,14,Heights,,,,,1,1,1,3,,,"$450,000",$695.52,,3/17/2026,,,23,,,3/17/2026,,,,,,,,,,,,,,Summit & Central Ave,"Welcome to 33 Graham St, Unit 3, a beautifully crafted 1-bedroom, 1-bath offering stylish, low-maintenance living with the quality of brand-new construction. Ideal for first-time buyers, downsizers, or investors, this thoughtfully designed residence features an efficient open layout with a bright living area and a sleek, modern kitchen with ample counter space. The spacious bedroom provides generous closet storage, while the contemporary bathroom is finished with clean, upscale details. In-unit laundry add everyday convenience. Set within a well-established neighborhood with easy access to public transportation, shopping, dining, and parks, this turnkey home is a rare opportunity to own new construction at an accessible price point."
260004113,ACTIVE,"JC, Heights",15 JEFFERSON AVE,Condominium,770,1186,"$450,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2B,"JC, Heights",07306,5902,14,,Dinapoli Condominium,,,,2,0,1,5,,,"$450,000",$584.42,,3/10/2026,,,30,,,3/10/2026,,,,"$7,229",2025,$400,,,,,,,,Palisade and Baldwin Ave,"Welcome home to this bright and modern 2 bed, 1 bath condo offering 770+ sq ft of well designed living space in a prime Jersey City Heights location. This sun filled home features gleaming hardwood floors, large windows, and an open-concept living and dining area perfect for everyday living or entertaining. Step outside to your private ~100 sq ft tiled floor deck, ideal for morning coffee, outdoor dining, or relaxing with fresh air. The modern kitchen is equipped with stainless steel appliances, breakfast bar and ample cabinetry, offering both functionality and sleek design. Both bedrooms are well-sized, while the bathroom features elegant tile work and generous vanity space. Additional highlights include central AC, dishwasher, shared washer/dryer in the basement, private storage, and a charming brick building. Located just off Palisade Ave with a bus stop to Manhattan nearby, and moments from neighborhood favorites like Prato Bakery, Veloce Sandwiches, and the new Abake Café, plus parks, shopping, and restaurants. Citi-bike only one block away on Jefferson/Oakland, this location just cannot get any more convenient! Perfect for commuters and anyone looking to enjoy the best of Jersey City Heights living."
240019540,SOLD,"JC, Heights",42-44 PROSPECT ST,Condominium,813,1597,"$452,000",CONDO-COOP,,4,4A,"JC, Heights",07307,5801,30,,,,,,2,0,2,4,,"$452,000","$415,000",$555.97,$555.97,10/3/2024,10/10/2024,1/7/2025,7,7,,1/7/2025,,,,"$7,681",2024,$264,,Conventional,,,,,,Reservoir and Waverly,"This stunning top-floor, 2-bedroom, 2-bath residence is located in the heart of The Heights, housed within The Juliette—a beautifully restored pre-war brick building, renovated in 2007. The apartment is bathed in natural light, further enhanced by soaring ceilings, oversized windows, and an exposed brick wall. Modern conveniences include stainless steel appliances, an in-unit washer/dryer, central Heath & A/C, and ample storage space. Additionally, the unit includes a private, deeded deck (to be constructed), offering an outdoor escape. Move-in ready, with a low common charge—this home offers both style and comfort. Easy access to NYC Port Authority via NJ Transit bus stop on the corner, JSQ & Hoboken PATH, Lightrail and CitiBike moments away."
220002412,SOLD,"JC, Heights",142 CHARLES ST,Condominium,815,1653,"$454,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,202,"JC, Heights",07307,2603,51,Heights,,,,,1,0,1,4,,"$454,000","$454,000",$557.06,$557.06,2/10/2022,5/23/2022,6/24/2022,102,102,,6/28/2022,,,,,,$356,,Conventional,,,,,,Summit Ave. & JFK Boulevard,"This is a rare and sought-after opportunity to secure your very own slice of history in booming Jersey City Heights. The Packard JC boasts 14 new luxury condominiums that combine the very best in contemporary comfort with original details from this building’s industrial past.  Once the Packard Motor Car Company showroom, this steel and concrete construction, loft-style building is located close to the bustling Central Avenue with restaurants, shopping, cafes and parks nearby.  There is a selection of one and two-bedroom condos on offer that promise a life of elegance. Cooking will be a pleasure in the stylish kitchens with stainless steel appliances, under-mount sinks, breakfast bars and leathered granite countertops with a waterfall edge.  Central AC, Navian on-demand tankless water heaters and an in-unit washer-dryer ensure absolute comfort plus there’s a host of dramatic features including 12 ft ceilings, concrete beams, exposed ductwork and engineered hardwood herringbone flooring. Nearby buses connect you to NYC with easy links to the Journal Square transportation hub. Photos are of a similar staged unit in the building."
230004656,SOLD,"JC, Heights",159 PALISADE AVE,Condominium,950,1686,"$455,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,A,"JC, Heights",07306,05904,00022,Heights,,,,,1,1,1,4,,"$455,000","$460,000",$478.95,$478.95,3/23/2023,5/2/2023,6/1/2023,40,40,,6/1/2023,,,,"$7,306",2022,,,Cash,,,,,,Hopkins & Beacon Ave,"Newly renovated and airy 1 bedroom/ 1.5 bath with office nook in Jersey City Heights. This turn key, open concept, loft style duplex featuring beautiful oak floors throughout, built in furniture, central air/ heat and bright kitchen with new stainless steel appliances. The second floor features 11ft ceilings with skylights, in unit laundry, full bathroom with marble and jacuzzi tub and plenty of storage. Centrally located near downtown Jersey City, Hoboken, JSQ Path, and steps to NYC bus, Citi Bike and rental parking ($130/month).  Low annual taxes: $7306"
220021276,SOLD,"JC, Heights",142 CHARLES ST,Condominium,957,1653,"$459,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,201,"JC, Heights",07307,2603,51,Heights,,,,,1,0,1,4,,"$459,000","$459,000",$479.62,$479.62,12/9/2022,1/4/2023,1/31/2023,26,26,,2/2/2023,,,,,,$412,,Conventional,,,,,,Summit Ave. & JFK Boulevard,"SELLER PAYS $10,000 BUYER CLOSING COSTS FOR CLOSINGS BEFORE FEB 28, 2023!! SPECIAL PROGRAM AVAILABLE - 10% DOWN, NO PMI. This is a rare and sought-after opportunity to secure your very own slice of history in booming Jersey City Heights. The Packard JC boasts 14 new luxury condominiums that combine the very best in contemporary comfort with original details from this building’s industrial past.  Once the Packard Motor Car Company showroom, this steel and concrete construction, loft-style building is located close to the bustling Central Avenue with restaurants, shopping, cafes and parks nearby.  There is a selection of one and two-bedroom condos on offer that promise a life of elegance. Cooking will be a pleasure in the stylish kitchens with stainless steel appliances, under-mount sinks, breakfast bars and leathered granite countertops with a waterfall edge.  Central AC, Navian on-demand tankless water heaters and an in-unit washer-dryer ensure absolute comfort plus there’s a host of dramatic features including 12 ft ceilings, concrete beams, exposed ductwork and engineered hardwood herringbone flooring. Nearby buses connect you to NYC with easy links to the Journal Square transportation hub. Photos are of a similar staged unit in the building."
220010535,SOLD,"JC, Heights",270 HANCOCK AVE,Condominium,850,1526,"$460,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1,"JC, Heights",07307-1927,,,,,,,,2,0,2,4,,"$460,000","$485,000",$541.18,$541.18,6/9/2022,6/29/2022,8/29/2022,20,20,,8/31/2022,,,,,,$200,2021,Conventional,,,,,,Congress & North,Location.... Location.... Welcome to 270 HANCOCK AVE. located 1/2 Block from Washington Park and short walk to Congress St Light-Rail makes this 2 Bedroom 2 Bath Condo the perfect place to call home. The property offers sophisticated modern look with dark oak hardwood floors & many high end finishes. Stainless steel appliances and in Unit full size washer & Dryer gives you modern day convenience. Shared backyard space as well as additional storage offered in basement.
210002778,SOLD,"JC, Heights",47 HANCOCK AVE,Condominium,,1653,"$460,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,102,"JC, Heights",07307,3802,15.01,,The Baxter,,,,2,0,1,4,,"$460,000","$449,000",,,2/2/2021,2/17/2021,3/29/2021,15,15,,3/31/2021,,,,"$5,392",2020,,,Conventional,,,,,,Hutton & Griffith,"Welcome to The Baxter, one of Jersey City’s premier boutique condo buildings. Located in the heart of The Heights, it offers a panoramic view of NYC via open rooftop and walkability to nearby Hoboken. Its exclusive first-floor 2bd/1ba condo features White Oak hardwoods, an L-shaped kitchen with Dacor appliances, quartz countertops and tons of shelf space inside custom soft-close cabinets. This east-facing gem is equipped with an energy-efficient HVAC system, Nest thermostat and web-cam security buzzer. VA approved and pet friendly, this brand-new unit also comes with low HOA fees (water included) plus a flexible closing date. Schedule your private showing today!"
220019107,SOLD,"JC, Heights",46 BLEECKER ST,Condominium,900,1702,"$462,000",CONDO-COOP,,1-2,,"JC, Heights",07307,,,,,,,,2,0,1,6,,"$462,000","$475,000",$513.33,$513.33,10/28/2022,12/15/2022,12/27/2022,48,48,,12/28/2022,,,,"$7,565",,$0,,Cash,,,,,,Summit and Passaic,"Masterfully updated single-family home in The Heights. This is a rare opportunity to own something truly unique: A single family home with the efficiency and affordability of a condo. Low taxes and NO HOA payments make this a very smart affordable option. The 2 bedrooms are nicely situated on the top floor with access to a new roof deck for your enjoyment. The entire house was renovated recently with a central air conditioning system, washer/dryer, bamboo floors, tons of storage and modern kitchen with farmhouse sink and butcher block counters. The renovation also includes an array of energy efficient features for the modern homeowner: windows, insulation, whole-house water filtration and tankless water heater. The roof deck was just added and plans include the option for expanding the deck to the other rooftop. Optional garage parking spot 2 blocks away can be transferred to you for $200/mo. If you haven't already discovered Jersey City Heights, see why it's dubbed the new Williamsburg with a diverse lineup of local attractions, restaurants, venues, cafes, bars, etc. and minutes away from multiple transportation options to Manhattan, Downtown Jersey City, Hoboken and Journal Square."
210004948,SOLD,"JC, Heights",63 SHERMAN PL,Condominium,1148,1526,"$462,500",CONDO-COOP,,5,E7,"JC, Heights",07307-3759,,,,The Ariston,,,,2,0,1,5,,"$462,500","$499,000",$402.87,$402.87,2/16/2021,3/16/2021,5/5/2021,28,14,,5/10/2021,,,,"$5,089",2020,$528,,Conventional,,,,,,Summit & Kennedy,"2 Beds are Better than 1! This absolutely massive 2 bedroom 1 bath beckons you in. As soon as you step foot into 63 Sherman Place, you realize you are not in Kansas any more. The well maintained lobby flaunts its old world charm that new buildings cannot match. Take the newly updated, but historically preserved, elevator up to the Penthouse level. Upon entering the unit, you'll notice the handsomely crafted floors. They guide you into the entrance lounge. Continue on past the eat in kitchen and you'll come to a living room built for lounging, laughing, and loving. walk down the hall and you'll be blown away by just how large both bedrooms are. To quote the movie Step Brothers, there is so much room for activities! Unlike the modern bedrooms that are barely big enough for your bed, both of these impressive rooms have enough space  for King Size Beds, Desks, Dressers, and anything else to make your home life more enjoyable. Make your appointment today to see this gem of the Heights!"
230005518,SOLD,"JC, Heights",142 CHARLES ST,Condominium,807,1653,"$464,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,302,"JC, Heights",07307,2603,51,Heights,,,,,1,0,1,4,,"$464,000","$464,000",$574.97,$574.97,3/31/2023,3/31/2023,3/31/2023,0,0,,4/6/2023,,,,,,$349,,Conventional,,,,,,Summit Ave. & JFK Boulevard,"This is a rare and sought-after opportunity to secure your very own slice of history in booming Jersey City Heights. The Packard JC boasts 14 new luxury condominiums that combine the very best in contemporary comfort with original details from this building’s industrial past.  Once the Packard Motor Car Company showroom, this steel and concrete construction, loft-style building is located close to the bustling Central Avenue with restaurants, shopping, cafes and parks nearby.  There is a selection of one and two-bedroom condos on offer that promise a life of elegance. Cooking will be a pleasure in the stylish kitchens with stainless steel appliances, under-mount sinks, breakfast bars and leathered granite countertops with a waterfall edge.  Central AC, Navian on-demand tankless water heaters and an in-unit washer-dryer ensure absolute comfort plus there’s a host of dramatic features including 12 ft ceilings, concrete beams, exposed ductwork and engineered hardwood herringbone flooring. Nearby buses connect you to NYC with easy links to the Journal Square transportation hub. Photos are of a similar staged unit in the building."
220010783,SOLD,"JC, Heights",78 PATERSON ST,Condominium,804,1597,"$465,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,2,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$465,000","$475,000",$578.36,$578.36,6/13/2022,6/28/2022,8/2/2022,15,15,,8/4/2022,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Pierce Ave & JFK,"Sleek contemporary blends with simplistic earth elements in this gut-renovated condo in Jersey City Heights. The portrait of urban charm, the 2 bed, 2 bath home features white oak floors and bright airy layout, black matte windows and stylish design throughout. Kitchen hosts oversized island finished with waterfall concrete-textured quartz, plus inset sink, glass backsplash and high-end Bosch polished stainless appliances.   Spacious bedrooms host plenty of closet space, while bathrooms pop with white tile set in dark grout, floating custom vanities, and glass showers with hexagon tile and cut-out niche. Designated laundry area hosts full-size Whirlpool washer and dryer for added convenience and upgrade.  78 Paterson is nestled in the heart of The Heights - Jersey City’s fastest growing area - one block from Central Ave with bustling restaurants, shops, excellent schools and vibrant community, and just around the corner from Washington Park with tennis, volleyball, baseball, soccer, playgrounds, splash pad, picnic areas and running paths. Easy access to NYC."
220013130,SOLD,"JC, Heights",349 PALISADE AVE,Condominium,1138,6078,"$465,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,2,0,2,6,,"$465,000","$475,000",$408.61,$408.61,7/19/2022,8/26/2022,9/29/2022,38,38,,9/29/2022,,,,"$7,695",2021,$300,2021,Conventional,,,,,,off palisade,"Welcome home to your recently renovated 3bed (2plusden), 2 bathroom right in the Heart of the Jersey City Heights with direct access to a massive landscaped common backyard (the only unit w direct access). This boutique 4 unit building offers you a first floor residence, featuring an open living room kitchen layout with all GE Stainless Steel Appliances, white Quartz countertops & walk in pantry. Central AC, recessed lighting & Oak Grey flooring throughout. Two main bedrooms (14x10) (11x16 w en-suite bathroom) are at opposite ends of the home with large windows. The third bedroom is ample size(10x7)perfect for a home office or gym. Located on the most desirable block of Palisade Ave, conveniently located steps walking distance to Hoboken 2nd St Light rail station. Bus to NYC Port Authority/Hoboken &; Several Restaurants and shops located on same block, including Choc O’ Pain, Low Fidelity, Pharmacy, nail salon and more. Supremo Supermarket just another block over. Close to Riverview- Fisk Park, known for its Farmers Markets, Jazz Festivals and amazing NYC Views."
