210008225,SOLD,"JC, Heights",124 CHARLES ST,Condominium,,1685,"$465,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1,"JC, Heights",07307,,,,,,,,3,1,2,5,,"$465,000","$479,999",,,4/7/2021,5/20/2021,7/9/2021,43,43,,7/9/2021,,,,,,$175,,Conventional,No,No,,,,Summit ave & Kennedy Blvd,"Welcome to this magnificent 1438 sq. ft. unit ! Brand new duplex with  backyard ! From top to bottom, you have 2 full floors of living space , 3 bedrooms, 2 full & 1 half bathrooms, large living room & Kitchen with shaker cabinets, built in cabinet microwave & quartz island, back yard, and front patio. Modern features include central air & heat, new washer dryer, and tastefully renovated bathrooms. Enjoy the convenience of being located on a quiet street, near Central Ave shops & restaurants, schools, parks and public transportation to NYC."
220010314,SOLD,"JC, Heights",164 OGDEN AVE,Condominium,752,6267,"$465,000",CONDO-COOP,,4,401,"JC, Heights",07307,05103,00008,Heights,OGDEN HEIGHTS,,,,3,0,1,6,,"$465,000","$445,000",$618.35,$618.35,6/7/2022,6/24/2022,8/5/2022,17,17,,8/5/2022,,,,"$4,467",2021,$570,,Conventional,,,,,,Paterson Plank Rd to Mountain to Ogden,"This fantastic unit is the LARGEST in the building. 3 bed, 1 bath on THE MOST DESIRABLE STREET IN THE HEIGHTS. It's the ONLY unit in the Entire Building offering 288 sqft of PRIVATE OUTDOOR SPACE w/ Full City Views! Renovated and Modern, the New kitchen is gorgeous w/ quartz counters, ss appliances and built in coffee bar! Gorgeous parquet HW floors run throughout the first floor living/dining rooms & 2 bedrooms. Each room is finished with crown moldings & the primary bed has double closets with systems! The 2nd Floor features a Bright space w/ HW floors that can be used as a 3rd bedroom (it has a walk-in closet), additional Living Room, den or Home Office with NEW Sliding Doors to enormous, Private Rooftop Deck. Just imagine spending your summer evenings & weekends w/ friends & family entertaining while taking in the amazing NYC views! Bathroom 5 yrs old, NEW building communal Boiler, Roof 2019, Deck 12x24 2019, Windows 2016, NEW building security cameras and video Doorbird coming soon! Convenient, In Unit washer/dryer can easily be swapped out with dishwasher. Laundry and storage offered in basement. Upcoming improvements include New AC sleeve for 2nd fl wall unit. LOW taxes & Fantastic location-1 block to buses to NYC, Hoboken and Journal Square. Walking distance to Light Rail, Supermarket, Riverview Farmer's Market, Parks and some of the best eateries and shopping Jersey City Heights has to offer!"
250011697,SOLD,"JC, Heights",142 CHARLES ST,Condominium,956,1526,"$467,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,301,"JC, Heights",07307,2603,51,Heights,The Packard,,,,1,0,1,4,,"$467,000","$480,000",$488.49,$488.49,6/10/2025,8/2/2025,9/25/2025,53,53,,9/25/2025,,,,"$6,878",2023,$402,,Conventional,,,,,,Corner of Kennedy Blvd. and Charles St.,"Sophisticated Loft Living - The Packard JC 1-Bedroom Loft - Where History Meets Modern Living This is your chance to own a spacious 956 sq ft 1-bedroom, 1-bath condo in the beautifully restored Packard JC, a former Packard Motor Car Company showroom reimagined into a boutique collection of luxury homes.  Located in the heart of Jersey City Heights, this stunning residence offers a blend of industrial character and contemporary comfort. Soaring 12-foot ceilings, exposed concrete beams, and herringbone-engineered hardwood floors set the tone, while central A/C, a Navien tankless water heater, and in-unit washer/dryer provide modern convenience.  An elegant kitchen features stainless steel appliances, a waterfall-edge leathered granite countertop, under-mount sink, and a breakfast bar—perfect for everyday living or entertaining.  Nestled right on Kennedy Blvd., enjoy easy access to buses and the Journal Square PATH, making commuting to NYC is a breeze."
240008431,SOLD,"JC, Heights",684 SUMMIT AVE,Condominium,950,1713,"$467,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,4,"JC, Heights",07306,05603,00067,,,,,,2,0,2,4,,"$467,000","$499,000",$491.58,$491.58,5/6/2024,5/22/2024,7/12/2024,16,16,,7/17/2024,,,,"$6,617",,$188,,Conventional,,,,,,Hopkins Ave & Beacon Ave,"Exquisitely renovated and conveniently located, welcome home to this beautifully lit 2-bed, 2-bath, 950 square foot condo hardwood floors throughout. Your new custom chef’s kitchen boasts quartz countertops, shaker cabinetry, stainless steel Samsung appliances, built in wine fridge and large island with breakfast bar. Complete with 2 spacious bedrooms, modern, renovated bathrooms, and outdoor terrace. The primary bathroom hosts a walk in shower with rain shower head and double vanity. New plumbing and electrical systems, central AC, Nest thermostats, Ring Doorbell, soundproofing are features not to be missed. Easy access to the Holland Tunnel and major highways and a short 10-minute walk to Journal Square PATH Station. Explore nearby parks, dining and entertainment options in Downtown Jersey City and Journal Square."
240012453,SOLD,"JC, Heights",3267 JOHN F KENNEDY BLVD,Condominium,935,5678,"$470,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1,"JC, Heights",07306,,,Journal Square,,,,,3,0,2,6,,"$470,000","$499,000",$502.67,$502.67,6/27/2024,11/13/2024,1/24/2025,139,139,,1/26/2025,,,,"$8,916",2023,$300,Month,Conventional,No,No,,,,Carlton Ave and Beach St,"Welcome to this beautifully 3-bed, 1-bath, 935 square foot condo nestled in the heart of Jersey City Heights with high ceilings and hardwood floors throughout. This home features a newly renovated kitchen and bathroom. The roof was replaced last year, the furnace is 8 years old and the water heater 4 years old. Ideally located close to Journal Square this home offers great commutes to NYC. A must see, book your appointment today!"
260004243,ACTIVE,"JC, Heights",116 OGDEN AVE,Condominium,642,6078,"$470,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,GB,"JC, Heights",07307,5202,18,Heights,,,,,1,0,1,4,,,"$470,000",$732.09,,3/13/2026,,,27,,,3/11/2026,,"$337,400",2024,"$7,581",2023,$300,,,No,No,,,,Booraem Ave & Ravine Ave,"Welcome to Jersey City Heights in the desirable Ogden’s End neighborhood! This ground-level 1-bedroom, 1-bathroom condo offers the perfect combination of comfort, character, and convenience, complete with a private outdoor patio showcasing beautiful Manhattan views. The home features Brazilian Cherry hardwood floors, exposed brick, crown molding, and custom maple kitchen cabinetry, complemented by quartz countertops and stainless-steel appliances. Additional highlights include central A/C and heat, an in-unit washer and dryer, Located directly across from a playground and the Ogden’s End Community Garden, this home sits in a quiet, friendly neighborhood while still being close to everything. Enjoy easy access to grocery stores, restaurants, parks, and NYC/NJ transportation. The bus stop is around the corner, and the 2nd st to the Hoboken Light Rail is within walking distance, making commuting effortless. The HOA covers water/sewer, trash removal, janitorial services, and common area electricity. Seller is relocating.  Kitchen is newly renovated and redesigned (within last 2 years) Bathroom is newly renovated and designed (since Jan '25) Replaced within last 3 years: HVAC system, washer/dryer unit, hot water heater, and painted the walls Other improvements made (outside): wood flooring on outside patio, French doors leading to outside, plastic added to above deck to limit rain exposure, wooden bar top Other improvements made (inside): Additional storage space added — full closet plus additional cabinets."
