250007083,SOLD,"JC, Heights",172 NEW YORK AVE,Condominium,850,1713,"$480,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1L,"JC, Heights",07307,3901,7,,,,,,2,0,1,6,,"$480,000","$475,000",$564.71,$564.71,4/10/2025,5/15/2025,10/20/2025,35,35,,10/27/2025,,,,"$12,309",2021,$290,,Conventional,,,,,,Franklin St and Hutton St,"Discover luxurious living in this stunningly renovated two-bedroom, one-bathroom apartment at 172 New York Ave in the vibrant Jersey City Heights neighborhood! Step inside and be greeted by an open and airy layout, enhanced by beautiful hardwood floors and sleek recessed lighting throughout.  This meticulously updated home offers a truly comfortable and convenient lifestyle. Enjoy the ease of in-unit living with a brand-new full-size washer and dryer right at your fingertips. Ample closet space ensures all your belongings have a place, while wall unit central air provides personalized climate control. A fantastic bonus: custom-built-in speakers perfect for setting the mood or entertaining guests.    The modern kitchen is a chef's delight, featuring brand-new, high-end appliances including an LG refrigerator, a Frigidaire gas stove, and a Beko dishwasher. Whether you love to cook or simply enjoy gathering, this kitchen is sure to impress.    But the real showstopper? Your very own PRIVATE BACKYARD!!!! This rare gem in urban Jersey City Heights offers a tranquil escape for relaxation, gardening, or outdoor entertaining – a true extension of your living space.  Beyond the apartment's exceptional features, the location is unbeatable. Enjoy unparalleled convenience with easy access to public transportation. Just a short block away lies Palisade Ave, offering direct bus lines to NYC Port Authority, Hoboken, and Downtown Jersey City. Commuting is a breeze with the Hudson Light Rail Stations just minutes away.  Embrace the vibrant neighborhood with nearby amenities like Pershing Field's indoor pool and ice-skating rink for year-round recreation. Explore the scenic beauty and neighborhood events at Riverview Park, boasting stunning views of the city skyline.    Don't miss this incredible opportunity to live in a newly renovated apartment with a private backyard in a prime Jersey City Heights location. Schedule your showing today! Parking available nearby for an additional fee"
230011762,SOLD,"JC, Heights",56 GRACE ST,Condominium,900,5713,"$480,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2R,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$480,000","$470,000",$533.33,$533.33,7/13/2023,9/21/2023,1/4/2024,70,70,,1/4/2024,,,,"$6,210",2022,$250,,Conventional,,,,,,Central and Summit,"This newly painted second-floor condo is completely up to date - with stainless steel appliances including a brand new dishwasher, hardwood floors, granite countertops, central air/heat, brand new washer/dryer in the unit, refrigerator with filtered water and a dishwasher. The apartment boasts upgraded technology, including a Nest thermostat and August smart lock. Both bedrooms are spacious with large closets and windows. The master bedroom includes a full bath and large floor plan. The guest bedroom/office has a view overlooking the downstairs neighbor’s garden. Second bathroom is fully equipped with a walk-in spa shower. Jersey City Heights is culturally rich with lots of restaurants and parks in walking distance on both Central and Summit avenues and is walkable to Hoboken. For commuters: there is a direct NYC bus stop on the corner of Grace and Central that runs regularly (1 minute walk) or a 10-15 minute walk to the Congress Street light rail (to Hoboken path or downtown Jersey City). There are four units in the building that are supported by a small and well run HOA for $250 per month. Each set of our neighbors are great company are respectful building partners. You are provided your own storage unit in basement."
