240016122,SOLD,"JC, Heights",510 PALISADE AVE,Condominium,900,1653,"$485,000",CONDO-COOP,,4,402,"JC, Heights",07307,2401,4,,,,,,3,0,2,6,,"$485,000","$469,000",$538.89,$538.89,8/15/2024,9/13/2024,10/25/2024,29,29,,11/6/2024,,,,"$9,207",2023,$419,,Cash,,,,,,South and Bowers,"Rave, radiant and rejuvenating in Riverview Park! Nestled on the trendy Palisade Avenue, this updated 3BR/2B home is the only one that offers a THIRD bedroom and a SECOND bath in the under 500k price range for one of Jersey City's most coveted neighborhoods – Riverview Arts District. Step into a bright and sunny top floor apartment adorned with 12 windows (!) on three sides providing NYC winter views. Unit 402 is located on the detached side of the building and enjoys rare side windows bringing plenty of light to the middle of the apartment too. The spacious layout (feels like a 1000sf) features two large bedrooms on opposite sides for privacy and quiet (both bedrooms with en-suite/adjacent baths), and a nursery/home office. The windowed eat-in kitchen features elegant quartz countertops, a large dining alcove, a 5-burner gas range, a dishwasher, and a convenient breakfast bar. With high ceilings and plenty of closet space, including a secure private 5x6 storage room downstairs, this home effortlessly blends style and functionality. A secluded common back yard and a free (!) common laundry complete the picture. Surrounded by hip restaurants, cafes, and the lush Riverview Park with picnic areas and breathtaking NYC skyline vistas, every day in this neighborhood feels like a retreat and 510 Palisade is at the center of it all. Whether you're sipping a cappuccino at Modcup, chilling with your neighbors at Alp’s or Fox and Crow, picking fresh strawberries at the Farmer’s Market, pumping iron at the new Firehouse fitness club, treating yourself to yummy rigatoni at Corto or a slice from haven at Bread and Salt —this location truly defines a hot and happening community and a commuter's dream. Welcome to your new Jersey City address!"
