260001183,ACTIVE,"JC, Heights",221 COLUMBIA AVE,Condominium,848,6078,"$495,000",CONDO-COOP,,1-2,3 (ADU),"JC, Heights",07307,603,61,Heights,,,,,1,1,1,4,,,"$495,000",$583.73,,1/22/2026,,,77,,,1/22/2026,,,,,,,,,,,,,,Leonard & North,"A rare opportunity to own a fully detached, new construction carriage house-style condo with 1 bedroom and 1.5 bathrooms across 848 thoughtfully designed square feet. This unique duplex residence combines privacy, style, and flexible living in a sleek, modern package. Enjoy your own private entrance and spacious open-concept main level, featuring 10-foot ceilings, 5-inch wide real hardwood floors, and abundant natural light from oversized Andersen windows. The kitchen is outfitted with Samsung stainless steel appliances, custom white shaker cabinetry, and quartz countertops, with a convenient half bath located on the main floor. Upstairs, the spacious primary suite includes a large walk-in closet and a full bathroom with striking floor-to-ceiling tilework. Additional highlights include an in-unit washer and dryer, energy-efficient mini-split systems for heating and cooling, and a 10-year builder’s warranty for peace of mind. Whether you're looking for a private home office setup, a guest suite, or a smart investment opportunity, this detached condo offers outstanding flexibility with premium finishes throughout. "
210021403,SOLD,"JC, Heights",118 COLUMBIA AVE,Condominium,1200,6174,"$495,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1,"JC, Heights",07307,02005,00022,Heights,,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$495,000","$499,000",$412.50,$412.50,9/13/2021,11/1/2021,12/17/2021,49,49,,12/23/2021,,,,,,$250,,VA,,,,,,Thorne and Bleeker,"This Beautiful 2 bed 2 bath condo brings modern sophistication to urban living!  Approx. 1,200 sqft of living space with incredible design. Enjoy tons of sunlight through the enormous windows, sip some lemonade on the front balcony or hang out in your large backyard oasis! (Complete with Fluffy Grass)  The kitchen boasts major cool factor with a black stainless Samsung appliance package complimented by the beautiful, subdued color scheme.  Easy NYC commute, close to many restaurants, and nestled in the Western Slope section of Jersey City Heights. Please note, the parking access is no longer associated with this unit. Please do not open the garage access door as it is being turned into a large storage closet. Parking available for $200.00/month on the block."
230018176,SOLD,"JC, Heights",247 CAMBRIDGE AVE,Condominium,812,6036,"$495,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07307,1601,36,,,,,,2,0,2,7,,"$495,000","$499,000",$609.61,$609.61,10/28/2023,1/3/2024,2/12/2024,67,67,,2/13/2024,,,,"$9,631",,$233,,Conventional,,,,,,Between Congress St & North St,"Welcome to The Heights, where modern luxury and comfort await you! Explore this recently updated 2-Bedroom, 2-bathroom gem that offers 812 SQFT of stylish living in the heart of The Heights. Step into the modern kitchen with beautiful glass tile accents and high-quality European-style faucets. The sleek porcelain tile floors add a touch of class, and the top-notch stainless steel LG appliances make cooking a breeze. The bathrooms are elegant with floor-to-ceiling tiles and fancy cabinets. Outside, you have your very own 112-square-foot private terrace for fun and relaxation. This place is practical with private storage, a washer and dryer, and central air. Steps from many NJ Transit Bus station and Washington Park which has baseball, tennis, basketball, valley ball courts, dog run and etc. Don't miss out on this chance to experience the best of modern living. Contact us today for a personal tour!"
250014479,SOLD,"JC, Heights",43 THORNE ST,Condominium,0,1713,"$499,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1R,"JC, Heights",07307,2804,10,Heights,,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$499,000","$499,000",,,7/16/2025,8/1/2025,10/1/2025,16,16,,10/3/2025,,,,"$8,869",2023,$270,,Conventional,,,,,,Summit Ave & Central Ave,"   Welcome to this vibrant 2-bedroom, 2 bath condo, nestled in the heart of Jersey City Heights. The exterior captivates with its striking contrast of bright white siding, elegant bay windows, and sleek black trim. Step inside to a black marbled lobby that ensures a secure welcome. This contemporary condo comes with a shared backyard and an inviting lounge area. The heart of this home is its designer kitchen, featuring matte black custom cabinets with stylish open shelving, a wine rack, and brass fixtures, all set against a backdrop of waterfall marbled quartz counters and backsplash. The primary bedroom is equipped with an en-suite featuring floor-to-ceiling oversized porcelain tile, matte black fixtures, and a glass-enclosed shower. Living in The Heights means easy access to path, light rail, restaurants and parks! 1 block from the bus to port authority or a 10 min ride to journal square . Come check out 43 Thorne! Parking available nearby for an additional fee"
250011999,SOLD,"JC, Heights",21 HANCOCK AVE,Condominium,1613,1597,"$499,000",CONDO-COOP,,B/1,1,"JC, Heights",07307,4405,29,,,,,,2,1,2,6,,"$499,000","$499,000",$309.36,$309.36,6/12/2025,8/8/2025,10/24/2025,57,57,,10/29/2025,,,,"$8,892",2024,$493,,Conventional,,,,,,Hutton St and Franklin St,"Modern design immersed in a historic brick building, offering a 2-level condo, centrally located to NYC transportation, restaurants, shops, and scenic parks. With over 1600 sqft, this home has endless possibilities. Easily transforms into a 3-bedroom with the existing den. Attention to craftsmanship is seen from the refined restoration of the exterior and elegant entryway. The brand-new interior within this pre-war building allows for extra high ceilings, accompanied by hardwood floors and an open kitchen featuring quartz countertops, stainless steel appliances, and modern soft-close cabinetry. All necessities are met with in-unit Washer & Dryer and Central AC. 21 Hancock Ave is in a vibrant neighborhood of Jersey City Heights with abundant shops and restaurants on Central Ave (just a block away), several parks nearby, an easy commute proximity for getting into NYC, and abundant street parking throughout."
210027422,SOLD,"JC, Heights",116 BOORAEM AVE,Condominium,1,1691,"$499,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$499,000","$499,000","$499,000.00","$499,000.00",12/21/2021,1/11/2022,3/23/2022,21,21,,3/23/2022,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Abbett St & Central Ave,"Explore the perfect mix of urban sophistication and modern spaciousness with this newly refinished two bed, two bath luxury home located in a sweet spot of Jersey City Heights. Bright and airy, light floods in through the windows lined with matte black trim and white molding, and onto the wide plank white oak floors throughout.  Step into the open floorplan highlighted by the waterfall marbled quartz eat-in peninsula island with built-in exposed black shelving. Kitchen continues with white tile backsplash, gold trim, sleek white custom cabinets with black casing and impeccably chosen pendant lighting. Finishing touches include the separate bar area including wine fridge and built-in bottle display, ideal for entertaining or your everyday beverage station.   The primary bedroom features striking deep blue wall paneling, plus walk-in closet and bright light streaming from the big bay window. Design-lovers bathrooms each showcase carefully curated wall-to-wall and top to bottom tile plus shower / soaker tub combo with matte black fixtures and toiletries niche. All units include a centrally located dedicated washer / dryer closet for convenience.  This newly refinished building offers excellent curb appeal, beautifully finished communal stairwell with exposed banister and stylish accents, plus can’t-be-beat location. Steps to either Pershing Field Park and Reservoir, or bustling Central Avenue, this home offers walkability to essential shops, excellent outdoor space and easy NYC access."
