260003045,SOLD,"JC, Heights",433 CENTRAL AVE,Condominium,827,6638,"$500,000",CONDO-COOP,,2nd,2A,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,The James,,,,2,0,1,5,,"$500,000","$499,000",$604.59,$604.59,2/20/2026,3/13/2026,4/6/2026,21,21,,4/6/2026,,,,,,$320,,Conventional,,,,,,Bleeker & South St,"The James, a bespoke collection of direct elevator-to-home condominiums just 20 minutes from Manhattan, presents Residence 2A - a refined one-bedroom plus den home, with the den flexing comfortably into a second bedroom. This residence includes private, keyless elevator entry, a Juliet balcony off the living room, and access to a shared rooftop terrace offering sweeping NYC skyline views. Located in one of Jersey City’s fastest-growing neighborhoods, you’re moments from cafés, major shops, and transportation. Crafted by Hampton Hill and designer walkTHIShouse, The James blends modern elegance with timeless detail through oversized windows, wide-plank white oak floors, and an open, airy plan. The kitchen features quartz countertops and premium stainless steel appliances, while spa-inspired baths are finished with porcelain tile and matte-black fixtures. Building amenities include Swiftlane smart access with video intercom, a package room, bike storage, and the signature rooftop with panoramic skyline vistas. The building is also backed by a 10-year builder warranty. *Please reach out to our preferred lender at CrossCountry Mortgage for grant options ranging from $15,000–$22,000 and interest rates starting around 5.875%.*"
210010871,SOLD,"JC, Heights",71 NORTH ST,Condominium,1127,5743,"$500,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,302,"JC, Heights",07307,1602,1.01,,,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$500,000","$499,000",$443.66,$443.66,5/6/2021,5/12/2021,6/21/2021,6,6,,6/22/2021,,,,"$6,500",2021,$380,,Conventional,No,No,,,,Cambridge Ave & Hancock Ave,"NEWLY UPDATED kitchen/bathrooms in this 2 bed 2 bath gem with a terrance overlooking Washington Park! PARKING SPOT INCLUDED in garage on ground level of building! BRIGHT & open floorpan. Updated bright kitchen with NEW luxe cabinets, granite countertops and all NEW MODERN fixtures. Condo is newly painted and nestled in the heart of the shopping/artist district. Beautiful HARDWOOD floors throughout. BOTH bathrooms have new sleek matching fixtures and NEW cabinets. Kitchen, bathrooms AND hallway have new modern light fixtures! ALL door knobs throughout are new/modern with a matching new front door lock WITH keypad!  Everything in condos has a cohesive sleek and updated modern style! HOA Fee includes building cleaning, mait&repairs/snow removal. 5 yr young elevator mid rise building. Washer/Dryer in common area."
230006647,SOLD,"JC, Heights",510 PALISADE AVE,Condominium,900,6199,"$504,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2R,"JC, Heights",07307,,,,,,,,3,0,2,6,,"$504,000","$499,900",$560.00,$560.00,4/26/2023,4/28/2023,5/12/2023,2,2,,5/12/2023,,,,"$9,053",22,$400,23,Cash,,,,,,Bowers and South,"Spacious, bright, and recently renovated 3 bedroom / 2 full bathroom home in the Riverview Arts District of Jersey City Heights. This truly spectacular home features a fully renovated kitchen with custom cabinetry, stainless steel appliance package and quartz countertops. Living/dining room is large and bright, features recessed lighting, high ceilings and crown molding. 3 bedrooms - two at opposite ends of the home and one in the middle perfect for a home office, nursery, or home gym. Both bathrooms are updated with the primary bathroom featuring a soaking tub. Other highlights include high ceilings throughout, sunrise and sunset exposure, hardwood flooring, an abundance of closet storage space, dedicated storage room, free on-site laundry and gorgeous landscaped common yard. Located adjacent to the newly renovated Riverview-Fisk Park, you'll find convenient access to farmers markets, boutique shops, local restaurants, sweeping views of the Manhattan Skyline and Hudson River, the NJ Transit bus to Port Authority, the 9th and Congress Light-Rail stop and elevator into Hoboken."
210001157,SOLD,"JC, Heights",325 PALISADE AVE,Condominium,924,1702,"$505,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1E,"JC, Heights",07307,05003,00001,,,,,,2,0,1,4,,"$505,000","$525,000",$546.54,$546.54,1/13/2021,1/26/2021,3/22/2021,13,13,,3/22/2021,,,,"$3,919",2020,$473,2021,Conventional,,,,,,Ferry and Ravine,"Beautiful 2 bedroom loft w/ 14ft ceilings at Trolley House Lofts, located near the Hoboken border. This is a sleek apartment w/ polished concrete floors, central air, Nest thermostat, custom closets and an open modern kitchen. Located in a concrete elevator building w/ laundry on every floor, separate bike storage, virtual doorman, remote entry and security cameras throughout. The unit includes 1 garage parking space and extra storage bins. Located on the convenient Palisade Ave with a supermarket just a block away, NYC buses at every block, just a block from Riverview Park w/ NYC skyline view & a farmer's market on Sundays, and just a short stroll to the Hoboken 2nd St Light Rail. Tax abatement in place until 2032!!"
210023080,SOLD,"JC, Heights",502 PALISADE AVE,Condominium,742,6199,"$505,000",CONDO-COOP,,2nd,202,"JC, Heights",07307,08304,00027,Heights,PALISADE SQUARE,,,,1,0,1,4,,"$505,000","$545,000",$680.59,$680.59,10/6/2021,11/10/2021,12/16/2021,35,35,,12/16/2021,,,,"$5,132",21,$188,,Conventional,,,,,,Corner of Holland Street and Palisade Ave,"Designed with the true “urbanite” in mind and meticulous attention to detail, this brand new steel and concrete construction is located directly across from River View Park on a charming cobblestone street. Extra large 1 Br 742 sqft with deeded terrace 72 sqft. This six story mid-rise, elevator building offers 24 high-end luxury residential condo homes. Featuring 9.5 ceilings, 7.5 windows, wide plank Oak hardwood flooring throughout, Kitchen Aid SS appliances, Quartz countertops, high-end kitchen cabinets with under cabinet lighting. Bathrooms feature - Porcelanosa tiles, heated floors in master bath, double vanities, quartz countertops and Moen 90 Degree bath fixtures. Washer/Dryer in unit. Direct NYC bus transportation. There are 3 years left on a 5 Year Tax Abatement. Great Opportunity to own a 1 Br with the best address in the Heights. est 2019"
220002367,SOLD,"JC, Heights",270 HANCOCK AVE,Condominium,910,1717,"$507,000",CONDO-COOP,,3rd,5,"JC, Heights",07307,01603,00045,Heights,,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$507,000","$475,000",$557.14,$557.14,2/10/2022,2/24/2022,7/14/2022,13,13,,7/16/2022,,,,"$3,000",2021,$215,,Conventional,No,No,,,,North St & Congress St,"Contemporary design and high-end sophistication, this is beautiful brick exterior building, renovated and contemporary remodeled, new everything!  In the heart of Jersey City Heights. High ceilings & high-end finishes in this 2-bedrooms, 2-bathrooms. unit elevates luxury lifestyle. Finished with  dark oak hardwood floors features. Excite with White/gray modern custom cabinetry, finished with White quartz counters, stainless steel appliance,  washer and dryer. Freshly designed bathrooms feature black/white marble gray porcelain tile, glass shower with niche and rain head faucet, floating  White vanity and contrasting matte fixtures. Settled into a tree-lined street just off Central Avenue with essential shops and award-winning  restaurants, this home is located on building from Pershing Field Park, has a basketball court, volleyball courts, tennis courts at the park!! plus walkable access to NJ and NY transit or Citi bike stations. excellent schools. Close proximity to the Congress Street light rail station, major highways, PATH stations, and ferry to Manhattan. Other units are available in the building still under remodeling, come by, seeing is believing! "
230010024,SOLD,"JC, Heights",269 OGDEN AVE,Condominium,810,1597,"$510,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,2,0,1,5,,"$510,000","$525,000",$629.63,$629.63,6/16/2023,7/21/2023,2/1/2024,35,35,,2/1/2024,,,,,,$318,,Conventional,,,,,,Griffith & Franklin St,"Modern and move-in ready, this newly renovated ground floor two-bedroom with private backyard is perfectly positioned on desirable Ogden Avenue in the Heights. Modern design brings artistry and spaciousness with wide plank oak floors, clean lines and open floorplan.   Kitchen commands presence with sleek custom cabinetry, gleaming quartz counters and backsplash, and stainless appliances. Split floorplan offers bedrooms on either end of the living space, while elegant bathroom brings creamy porcelain tile & soaker tub. Bedrooms offer wide doorways while extra large windows allow lots of natural light. Large backyard is finished with pavers, landscaping and lawn for ideal outdoor living.   Beautiful brick building offers secure entrance on a tree-lined street less than one block to nearby Riverview Fisk Park with breathtaking NYC views or 9th Street Lightrail Station for Hoboken and NYC access. Jersey City Heights is known for its artisan shops and restaurants, close-knit community, excellent parks and schools."
240005310,SOLD,"JC, Heights",44 SHERMAN AVE,Condominium,1081,1713,"$510,000",CONDO-COOP,,4,4G,"JC, Heights",07307-2264,04502,00002,,,,,,2,0,1,6,,"$510,000","$499,000",$471.79,$471.79,3/21/2024,4/9/2024,5/29/2024,19,19,,5/29/2024,,,,"$7,499",2023,$721,,Conventional,,,,,,Webster & Hancock,"Light and bright spacious corner unit featuring hardwood floors throughout, newly renovated bathroom, updated kitchen, generous sized living area, plenty of storage, and an oversized terrace.  On-site laundry room and exercise room with brand new equipment. Excellent location near JC Heights business district, the area’s best shopping, gourmet eateries, 2 large supermarkets, and nearby public transportation.  Parking available in the building for an additional fee."
250009993,SOLD,"JC, Heights",78 PATERSON ST,Condominium,804,1597,"$510,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1,"JC, Heights",07307,,,,,,,,2,0,2,4,,"$510,000","$525,000",$634.33,$634.33,5/19/2025,7/23/2025,9/22/2025,65,66,,9/22/2025,,,,"$8,800",2025,$284,,Conventional,,,,,,Pierce Avenue & JFK Blvd,"  Seeking a perfect blend of modern aesthetics and urban sophistication? Then look no further! This two-bedroom, two-bath condo, nestled in the heart of the Jersey City Heights, offers unparalleled convenience. Just a stone's throw away from transportation and all the shopping hubs, it's a recent gut renovation that truly impresses. Step into the spacious living area, featuring high ceilings and a wide kitchen island equipped with top-notch Bosch appliances and in-unit laundry, ensuring a hassle-free day-to-day life. Quartz waterfall countertops and a trendy glass backsplash add a touch of elegance to the kitchen. The bathrooms are equally impressive, boasting floating dual vanities and a standing shower, as well as a bathtub. They exude a modern and luxurious ambiance. The location is simply ideal. This quiet tree-lined street is close to shopping, restaurants, and transportation, making it easy to commute to NYC, downtown Jersey City, Hoboken, and all other areas. And with numerous parks nearby, you can enjoy the outdoors whenever you like. The Jersey City Heights neighborhood is known for its eclectic and diverse character, and this condo is no exception. It's a perfect blend of modern living and urban charm, making it an ideal place to call home. All square footage is approximate."
