240003662,SOLD,"JC, Heights",701 SUMMIT AVE,Condominium,841,1419,"$512,500",CONDO-COOP,,1,1,"JC, Heights",07306,5501,22,Heights,,,,,2,0,1,7,,"$512,500","$525,000",$609.39,$609.39,2/27/2024,3/12/2024,4/18/2024,11,11,,4/22/2024,,,,,,$281,,Conventional,No,No,,,,Beacon & Laidlaw,"Welcome home to this beautifully gut renovated unit within walking distance to the JSQ Path Plaza.  The unit stretches close to 1,000 sq ft and contains 2 beds and 1 baths.  The modern kitchen with white cabinets is complemented by black stainless steel appliances and grey granite counters.  Huge windows on the front of the building let in a ton of natural light.  The bathroom offers a sleek floating vanity with a shower/tub combo.  To top it off there is a large private backyard, the perfect place to entertain! Additionally, there is storage space in the basement."
210007511,SOLD,"JC, Heights",223 HANCOCK AVE,Condominium,857,1739,"$515,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,3,"JC, Heights",07307,02203,00023,,,,,,2,0,2,7,,"$515,000","$514,995",$600.93,$600.93,3/31/2021,4/19/2021,6/25/2021,19,19,,7/1/2021,,,,"$7,406",20,$145,20,Conventional,,,,,,Congress and South,"Very low carrying costs make this ideal for personal ownership or an investment! Centrally located within the heart of Jersey City Heights, welcome to 223 Hancock Avenue.  Enjoy the benefit of top floor living with modern finishes and incredible vaulted ceilings.  Built by the sought after developer M2M, this two bedroom two full bath home features quartz counter tops, custom high gloss cabinets, wide-plan oak flooring, GE profile stainless steel appliances, bathrooms fit for spa-like retreats, Nest controlled central A/C, washer and dryer in unit, as well as private storage in the building.  If that was not enough, walk outside to your private balcony overlooking the rest of The Heights.  Just blocks away from the 9th Street Light Rail Station, restaurants, coffee shops and both Washington & Riverview Parks, schedule your private showing now to secure your new place to call home."
220011607,SOLD,"JC, Heights",968 SUMMIT AVE,Condominium,1054,1713,"$515,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,3,"JC, Heights",07307,02801,00004,,,,,,3,0,2,6,,"$515,000","$475,000",$488.61,$488.61,6/24/2022,7/15/2022,8/19/2022,21,21,,8/22/2022,,,,"$7,200",,$142,,Conventional,,,,,,Griffith St & Lincoln St,"Welcome to this newly renovated 3 bed/ 2 bath unit in a Queen Anne Style brick building in the Heights! This top floor unit with NYC views has 12 foot high ceilings and 6 skylights creating a bright and lofty feel to this home. An open concept living & dining area allows for entertaining in style with a fully equipped kitchen featuring an island, stainless steel appliances and quartz countertops. This unit also has a washer and dryer and has multi-zone ductless heating and cooling. Plus, a shared backyard is perfect for summertime gatherings! Located in the heart of Jersey City Heights nearby to restaurants, stores, parks, banks and much more. Easy commuting to Port Authority and downtown World Trade Center."
240015521,SOLD,"JC, Heights",270 HANCOCK AVE,Condominium,902,6199,"$515,000",CONDO-COOP,,2nd,4,"JC, Heights",07307,01603,00045,,,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$515,000","$499,000",$570.95,$570.95,8/8/2024,8/21/2024,10/4/2024,13,13,,10/10/2024,,,,"$9,030",2023,$255,,Conventional,,,,,,North St. & Congress St.,"Introducing this stunning 2 bedroom, 2 bathroom condo in the heart of Jersey City Heights! This beautifully renovated condo features a charming brick exterior, hardwood floors, high ceilings, and ample natural light. Nestled on a tree-lined street, this home offers a fresh design with modern bathrooms and kitchen. Enjoy the convenience of being near essential shopping, restaurants, and parks. Don't miss out on this gem in Jersey City Heights!"
260004478,ACTIVE,"JC, Heights",510 PALISADE AVE,Condominium,900,1623,"$515,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,3R,"JC, Heights",07307,2401,4,,,,,,3,0,2,5,,,"$515,000",$572.22,,3/13/2026,,,27,,,3/13/2026,,,,"$9,702",,$581,,,,,,,,Bowers & South,"You won't believe this space! 3 bedrooms and 2 bathrooms right on Palisade ave! Enter into your open concept living area featuring recessed lighting, room for a dining set and gorgeous exposed brick all saturated with natural light from your west facing windows! Turn right from the living room into a bedroom complete with an ensuite full bathroom-- a luxury you can't usually find in a location like this! The kitchen is efficiently built out with excellent storage space, sleek finishes, stainless steel appliances and an expansive breakfast bar. This space then leads through the two additional bedrooms, and additional full bathroom. Each bedroom in the unit features a ceiling fan and great storage options with both a closet and overhead storage space! You have a dedicated storage space in the basement of the building as well, in addition to a washer/dryer room. All this is located on Palisade Avenue, home to the very best restaurants, shops and bakeries that Jersey City has to offer, a short distance to the Congress / 9th Street Lightrail and elevator to Hoboken, as well as right next door to Riverview Fisk Park, with skyline views you have to see to believe."
240002359,SOLD,"JC, Heights",34 GRACE ST,Condominium,875,6078,"$515,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,3,"JC, Heights",07307,00504,00035,Heights,,,,,2,1,2,5,,"$515,000","$515,000",$588.57,$588.57,2/7/2024,2/13/2024,5/3/2024,6,6,,5/15/2024,,,,,,,250,Conventional,,,,,,Summit Ave. & Central Ave.,"First time homebuyers eligible for up to 22k in assisted down payment/closing costs through preferred lender. Introducing a brand-new, boutique-style 2-bedroom, 2.5-bathroom condo with a private rooftop oasis showcasing spectacular views of the NYC Skyline & Washington Park. It's perfectly situated in the prime Jersey City Heights neighborhood. This exceptional Grace Residence boasts high-end appliances and finishes, an in-unit washer and dryer, soaring 14-foot ceilings, and distinctive bay-style Pella Architect Series windows that bathe the home in natural light. Notable features include custom-built closets, sleek quartz countertops in the kitchens, real red oak European-style stairs, and innovative three-way plumbing fixtures in the bathrooms, offering both a waterfall and regular shower simultaneously.  The design is further accentuated by cove lighting throughout the bathrooms, upgraded tile finishes, floor-to-ceiling tiling, and real shower glass doors. Remarkably, extreme soundproofing has been applied to prevent noise transmission between floors, ensuring a peaceful living environment. Conveniently located next to Washington Park and nestled between Central and Summit Avenue, this condo is within walking distance of major bus lines and the light rail train for direct transportation into NYC."
230001624,SOLD,"JC, Heights",16 TROY ST,Condominium,855,298,"$515,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,201,"JC, Heights",07307,04702,00030,Heights,,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$515,000","$499,000",$602.34,$602.34,1/30/2023,3/13/2023,5/4/2023,42,42,,5/3/2023,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Montrose & Summit Ave,"Welcome to JC Heights newest Condo building 16 Troy St! This one of a kind building is set back from the street giving you the ultimate private feel.  Each unique 2 bed 2 bath units comes perfectly equipped with Frigidaire Gallery appliances, high end finishes, hardwood floors, sonos sound system built in and parking! Vented-out kitchen /vented-out laundry appliances, quartz counters, top of the line materials, built for modern living. Short distance to coveted Pershing Field Park, Central and Palisade Ave restaurant rows. Easy for a commuter with a bus stop to New York or JSQ path station.  Schedule your appointment today!"
250019185,SOLD,"JC, Heights",360 PALISADE AVE,Condominium,1000,6095,"$515,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$515,000","$525,000",$515.00,$515.00,9/17/2025,10/27/2025,12/19/2025,40,40,,1/5/2026,,,,"$10,850",2024,$333,,Conventional,,,,,,Between Franklin and Ferry Street,"Discover this stylish 2-bed, 2-bath condo at 360 Palisade Ave, set within a fully renovated 2020 building. Thoughtfully designed for modern living, it features a bright open layout with oversized windows, flowing seamlessly into a sleek kitchen with stainless steel appliances and abundant storage—perfect for both entertaining and daily life.  The serene primary suite offers a marble-accented ensuite bath, while the versatile second bedroom is ideal for guests or a home office. Enjoy your own private ground-level courtyard—a rare retreat for relaxing, dining, or morning coffee. Additional highlights include central air, in-unit laundry, and a secure video intercom.  Situated just minutes from local shops, restaurants, parks, and NYC transit, this home offers more space, better value, and a vibrant community—making it a smart alternative to Manhattan living. Welcome to the best of Jersey City Heights."
