250000697,SOLD,"JC, Heights",37 THORNE ST,Condominium,845,1713,"$526,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,3L,"JC, Heights",07307,2804,13,,,,,,2,0,2,6,,"$526,000","$525,000",$622.49,$622.49,1/10/2025,1/30/2025,3/10/2025,20,20,,3/12/2025,,,,$0,,$290,,Conventional,,,,,,Summit Ave and Central Ave,"Discover the perfect blend of sophistication and comfort in this stunning 2-bedroom, 2-bathroom residence in the heart of Jersey City Heights. Thoughtfully designed with meticulous attention to detail, this home offers everything you need to live in style. Step into an open and airy living space bathed in natural light, showcasing rich hardwood floors throughout. The chef-inspired kitchen is a true centerpiece, featuring sleek stainless steel appliances, a paneled dishwasher for seamless integration, elegant copper accents in the custom cabinetry, and a striking waterfall countertop that exudes modern elegance. Relax and unwind in the luxurious bathrooms, one with a glass-enclosed shower and the other with a soothing tub, both designed to provide a spa-like retreat. Each detail has been carefully curated to elevate your living experience. Ideally located, 37 Thorne offers convenience, comfort, and timeless style. This boutique 6-unit condo offers a massive storage space right on site. Don’t miss the chance to call Unit 3L home – schedule your private showing today!"
220005318,SOLD,"JC, Heights",56 GRACE ST,Condominium,1098,1603,"$527,500",CONDO-COOP,,1,1L,"JC, Heights",07307,504,46,Heights,,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$527,500","$535,000",$480.42,$480.42,3/29/2022,5/20/2022,6/30/2022,52,52,,7/5/2022,,,,"$6,000",2021,$250,,Conventional,,,,,,Central & Summit,"Welcome to 56 Grace Street, a newly renovated 2 bedroom home located one short block from Washington Park in Jersey City Heights. The home features stainless steel appliances, bedrooms on opposite ends of the home and 2 full bathrooms and laundry in unit. In addition, there is a bonus room downstairs with a staircase inside the home. This bonus room offers room for storage, work from home, or a potential third bedroom. To round out this unique opportunity, there is a sizable backyard perfect for outdoor entertaining, grilling and just relaxing in your private oasis. Close to parks, transportation to NYC and local shops and restaurants, this home is not to be missed! Open House Saturday, May 7, 2022 1pm-3pm."
230007299,SOLD,"JC, Heights",35 MANHATTAN AVE,Condominium,883,5906,"$530,000",CONDO-COOP,, 2,3,"JC, Heights",07307,04402,00013,Heights,,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$530,000","$539,000",$600.23,$600.23,5/5/2023,5/15/2023,6/28/2023,10,10,,6/29/2023,,,,,,,213,Conventional,,,,,,Ferry St. & Franklin St.,"There was no detail spared within these luxury units considering the 10 ft ceilings, outdoor space, high end appliances, vibrant LED lighting, and Pella windows throughout. This building was completely and meticulously gut renovated and upgraded with new plumbing and electric systems, a central sprinkler system, and fire protection. Your home will be equipped with central air, managed by Nest thermostats, a pair of pre-wired speakers in each room, high-end RING intercoms, operated from your phone, and in-unit washer/dryers! Offering custom-made chef's kitchens with designer quartz countertops, Bosch stoves, high-end Bosch appliances, and wide plank oak hardwood floorings makes this unit irresistible! The developer spared no cost on noise reduction and used sounds channels, sound clips, foam insulation, Rockwool, and SounFX sheetrock to keep your noise in and their noise out. Details aside being located in this Jersey City Heights neighborhood leaves you less than 100 feet from the Central Ave Shopping district and nearest bus stops to the PATH and NYC. Long term parking for $200/month is available. There are an abundance of surrounding eateries including Pier 13, The Hutton Bar & Grill, Rumba’s Cafe, and two of the highest-rated locations, Dulce de Leche Bakery and Pampita Butcher Shop! Another gem reveals itself in the Jersey City Heights!"
250007844,SOLD,"JC, Heights",11 CUNEO PL,Condominium,850,6494,"$530,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1D,"JC, Heights",07307,,,,,,,,2,0,1,4,,"$530,000","$525,000",$623.53,$623.53,4/23/2025,5/2/2025,6/5/2025,9,9,,6/5/2025,,,,"$5,734",2024,$278,,Cash,,,,,,Ogden Ave and Palisade Ave,"Welcome to Cuneo Court, a boutique building with low monthly fees and a shared landscaped yard nestled on a picturesque tree-lined street on one of Jersey City Heights' most desirable blocks. This newly renovated and beautifully styled 2-bedroom, 1-bath condo offers 850 sq ft. of thoughtfully designed living space on the elevated first floor—blending sleek, modern finishes with everyday functionality. Step into this chic and modern home with north and south-facing windows, gorgeous newly refinished hardwood floors, recessed lighting, new water heater and three HVAC heating/cooling units for year-round comfort.The sleek newly installed kitchen is a dream for cooking and entertaining, featuring brand-new smart wifi appliances, fridge with water/ice dispenser, convection oven with air fry function, low noise dishwasher, Kohler faucet, an abundance of custom cabinetry, and elegant quartz countertops. The renovated spa-like bathroom is your private retreat, complete with ambient radiant heat flooring and a thermostatic valve shower system for ultimate comfort and style. Enjoy the landscaped common backyard with BBQ grill and onsite laundry room. Location is everything—and this home delivers. You're just steps from the NYC bus, Janet Moore Playground and Ogden’s End Community Garden. Also an easy walk to the 2nd St Hoboken stairs and light rail station, Citibike, Riverview Park, farmers market, supermarket and trendy new restaurants including Prato Bakery, Low Fidelity, The Franklin, Choc O Pain, Corto, The Alps, and coming soon Àbák?Books + Cafe. This condo checks all the boxes for those looking for a tastefully newly renovated home with easy access to NYC transport and perfectly located in the thriving Heights neighborhood. Low monthly fee! 15%+ down payment preferred."
