260005604,ACTIVE,"JC, Heights",70 BOWERS ST,Condominium,1100,1526,"$539,000",CONDO-COOP,,1st,1,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,3,0,1,6,,,"$539,000",$490.00,,3/31/2026,,,9,,,3/31/2026,,,,"$10,000",Est.,$300,,,,,,,,Palisade and Central,"Welcome to Your New Favorite Place (You Just Don’t Know It Yet)  Hey there, future homeowner/hero/urban legend. Feast your eyes on this freshly remodeled 3-bed, 1-bath gem in the Heights of Jersey City — because your current place just isn’t cutting it, is it?  Perfectly sandwiched between Central Avenue and Palisade Ave (like a location panini), you get the best of both worlds: shopping sprees in one direction, scenic park strolls in the other. Boom — nature and retail therapy. Balance.  Inside? You’ve got the goods: gas stove (because food tastes better with flames), microwave (because let’s be honest, you’re gonna reheat a lot of pizza), central air (bye sweat), and yes — an in-unit washer/dryer. That’s right. Laundry. Without the awkward are you almost done with this dryer vibes.  Want more? This home includes the option to purchase an amazing back yard, ready made for stay at home adventures. Are we grillin' tonight? Or chillin' tonight?   Bottom line: this place is great. Call, text, send a carrier pigeon — just make your appointment today."
220021051,SOLD,"JC, Heights",256 NEW YORK AVE,Condominium,1380,6199,"$539,900",CONDO-COOP,,G,1,"JC, Heights",07307,03001,00040,,,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$539,900","$539,900",$391.23,$391.23,12/5/2022,12/16/2022,1/30/2023,11,11,,1/31/2023,,,,"$9,853",22,$175,22,Conventional,,,,,,Bowers and Griffith,"PRIVATE LANDSCAPED YARD! Stunning 2 bedroom / 2 bathroom 1,380s/f condo with direct access PRIVATE YARD situated in the Heart of Jersey City Heights. Entering the home, you will find endless luxury and sophistication. The gourmet kitchen features custom cabinetry, granite countertops, deep sink and top-of-the-line stainless steel appliance package. Open living / dining room is spacious and bright, features custom recessed lighting, crown molding, high ceilings and fireplace. Private yard is complete with planters, grass, custom patio and lots of privacy. Over-size primary bedroom features lots of natural light, an abundance of closet storage, and an en-suite bathroom with massive glass shower, dual vanity and jetted tub. Second bedroom has high ceilings and generous closet storage. Second bathroom features gorgeous tiling throughout, over-sized vanity and shower with soaking tub. Additional highlights include central A/C, washer/dryer in unit (large laundry room), wide plank flooring throughout and so much more. Located on New York Ave, you will find convenient access to shopping, dining, Fisk Park, farmer's markets, coffee shops, the Palisades Cliff, the NJ Transit bus to Port Authority and the NJ Transit Light Rail."
230000320,SOLD,"JC, Heights",483 PALISADE AVE,Condominium,1095,1597,"$540,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1A,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$540,000","$550,000",$493.15,$493.15,1/6/2023,2/9/2023,4/12/2023,34,34,,4/12/2023,,,,,,$291,,Conventional,,,,,,Griffith & Bowers,"Perfect and parkside, location meets luxury with direct park access and excellent walkability, plus high-end finishes and extra square footage.   Loads of natural light flood the classic design and beautiful hardwood floors with details like window casings and tray ceilings. Open floorplan offers abundant space for living, kitchen and full dining area. Kitchen showcases quartz counters, tile backsplash, custom cherry cabinets and stainless appliances.   Primary ensuite offers double-glass doors leading out to the private terrace. Bathrooms offer neutral tones, plus soaker tub or shower and vanity for additional storage. Ample closet space and separate utility room offer added convenience and value.  Beautiful brick building is newly finished with great curb appeal and even better location Enjoy walkability to 9th Street LightRail, PATH train, vibrant neighborhood and Riverview Fisk Park as your permanent playground."
250005090,SOLD,"JC, Heights",71 NORTH ST,Condominium,871,1597,"$540,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,204,"JC, Heights",07307,1602,1.01,,Parkview Manor,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$540,000","$525,000",$619.98,$619.98,3/18/2025,3/24/2025,4/23/2025,6,6,,4/23/2025,,"$362,700",2023,"$8,150",2023,$475,,Cash,,,,,,Hancock & Cambridge,"This spacious and thoughtfully designed Two Bedroom Condominium residence is ideally situated directly on Washington Park in the sought-after Jersey City Heights neighborhood. Featuring two full bathrooms, a large 225 sqft. private terrace and bright natural light, this beautiful home feels open and airy. The generously proportioned living and dining space is open to the kitchen which is complete with wood cabinetry, granite countertops and stainless-steel appliances. Both bedrooms are spacious, and the primary bedroom boasts an en-suite bathroom. Further, the residence is equipped with Central AC and heat, abundant storage space and hardwood floors. Perfectly situated surrounded by beloved local shops, cafes and restaurants, near the 9th Street elevator which provides easy access to Hoboken and LightRail station connecting to PATH and ferry, and across the street from Washington Park with two dog parks, tennis courts, baseball/softball fields, volleyball and basketball courts, 3.8 miles of trails and a children's playground with a water park, this gorgeous home is not to be missed.   "
230006248,SOLD,"JC, Heights",684 SUMMIT AVE,Condominium,915,1653,"$540,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,5,"JC, Heights",07306,5603,67,,,,,,2,0,2,4,,"$540,000","$549,000",$590.16,$590.16,4/19/2023,6/30/2023,8/23/2023,72,72,,8/24/2023,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,beacon and hopkins,"Welcome to Summit Lodge, a meticulously curated condominium building in the Jersey City heights. With its classically ornamental brick facade exterior, 684 Summit Avenue imparts a completely reimagined contemporary design on the interior to create harmonious, lavish, condominiums. Every square-inch of the property has been intricately designed with the end-user in mind. This upper level unit with 12 foot ceiling will consist of roughly 940 sqft of living space and a 1000sf private roof deck with gorgeous NYC skyline views! It boasts 2 bedrooms and 2 baths, custom chef’s kitchen, including designer quartz countertops, Porcelanosa tile and fixtures, Nest thermostats, central air, a Ring Doorbell Intercom, vibrant LED lighting throughout the entire space, and more! Additionally, all units have been upgraded with new plumbing, a new electrical system, and fire protection as well as top of the line sound proofing. The developer spared no costs to soundproof all the units in this building. This includes using open cell foam insulation, QuietWalk floor underlayment, and QuietRock ceiling panels between the floors to dampen the sound. Additionally, using sound clips and sound channels enabled to provide an unmatched level of peace and privacy. Topping this off, the property is located one block away from Highway 139, where you can access many northbound major highways such as Route 3 and Route 1&9 or maybe head southbound towards Pulaski Skyway or Route 440. The building is also only 6 minutes away from the Holland Tunnel via driving, and 13 minutes walking distance to the Journal Square PATH station, making travel to and from Manhattan incredibly easy. Other perks include a plethora of options for restaurants and entertainment for all ages, being that this property is located so close to both Downtown Jersey City and the Journal Square section of Jersey City while having the residential neighborhood feeling of the Jersey City Heights. This property’s location will cater to your every need. Schedule a viewing today!"
240017208,SOLD,"JC, Heights",236 BOWERS ST,Condominium,1183,1597,"$540,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,3,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,3,0,1,6,,"$540,000","$525,000",$456.47,$456.47,9/3/2024,9/10/2024,10/18/2024,7,7,,10/21/2024,,,,"$8,977",,$300,,Conventional,,,,,,Milton & JFK,"Experience classic charm with modern amenities in this bright and beautiful 3 bedroom, 1 bathroom home in desirable Jersey City Heights. Natural light floods through the oversized bay window to the open concept living, kitchen and dining room. Carefully restored historic details echo throughout like original hardwood floors and ceiling medallions now stylishly highlighted with curated fixtures and ceiling fans.  Perfect for entertainment or everyday use, the kitchen is equipped with white shaker cabinets, matte black pulls and fixtures, black granite counters, and a travertine tile backsplash. Stainless steel appliances complete the contemporary look. Bedrooms offer excellent square-footage and sizeable closets, in addition to the separate storage room for ultimate organization. The bathroom is finished with floor-to-ceiling travertine tile with ornate trim, and vanity and medicine cabinet, plus the window allows for natural light into this serene sanctuary. Owners enjoy a designated laundry room offering ideal convenience and utility.  Located in the heart of the Heights, this home offers quick access to vibrant shops, restaurants, and cafés on Summit Avenue and JFK Boulevard. The newly revitalized Leonard Gordon Park and Washington Park are just a short walk away, providing green spaces and recreation with sports facilities, walking paths, playgrounds, splash pad, dog run and more. Jersey City Heights is known for its excellent community and schools, plus easy access to NYC and nearby neighborhoods."
230009570,SOLD,"JC, Heights",701 SUMMIT AVE,Condominium,1000,1419,"$540,000",CONDO-COOP,,3&4,3,"JC, Heights",07306,5501,22,Heights,,,,,2,1,1,6,,"$540,000","$574,900",$540.00,$540.00,6/9/2023,6/23/2023,10/19/2023,14,14,,10/23/2023,,,,,,,,Conventional,No,No,Yes,,,Beacon & Laidlaw,"Welcome home to this beautifully gut renovated unit within walking distance to the JSQ Path Plaza.  The unit stretches close to 1,000 sq ft and contains 2 beds and 1.5 baths.  The modern kitchen with white cabinets is complemented by black stainless steel appliances and grey granite counters.  Huge windows on the front of the building let in a ton of natural light and offer views of lower Manhattan.  The bathroom offers a sleek floating vanity with a shower/tub combo.  To top it off there is a large private roof deck with views of the Empire State Building and Freedom Tower, as well as Journal Square.  The roof also has gas and water lines in addition to a TV hookup for the perfect entertainment space!"
210013274,SOLD,"JC, Heights",253 HANCOCK AVE,Condominium,925,1581,"$540,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07307,1602,20,,,,,,2,0,2,6,,"$540,000","$548,000",$583.78,$583.78,6/2/2021,6/15/2021,9/3/2021,13,13,,9/3/2021,,,,"$6,000",2020,$200,2020,Conventional,,,,,,Congress St & North St,"Say hello to your next Jersey City Heights Newly Renovated Condominium located in a commuter dream location just minutes away from Manhattan! This recently gutted 900+ sq ft 2nd floor unit occupies 2 bedrooms and 2 full baths featuring modern fixtures with contemporary high-end finishes! As you enter this unit, you will be welcomed with a spacious foyer greeting you with its built-in mud room area, as you go upstairs you will find a grand living room with ample natural lighting seeping through its large windows & high ceiling leading to its dining area. It’s beautifully designed modern kitchen is equipped with stainless steel appliances, quartz counters and slab quartz backsplash. This charming gem also provides you with a Master Bedroom En-Suite with a walk-out French door balcony with intricately designed custom trim molding, 1 additional bedroom with a built-in closet for ample storage, and 1 full bathroom. Both bathrooms feature a marble-tiled shower highlighting modern black matte fixtures! This impeccable condominium also includes amazing features like an in-unit laundry including stackable washer & dryer, central heating / cooling, gleaming hardwood floors, and has incomparable location! Residing here will have you just blocks away from parks, cafes, shops, and restaurants along with public transportation like NJ transit, the light rail, and the NY/NJ PATH, getting you into Manhattan in just minutes. This condominium is the epitome of urban luxury living! Schedule a private tour today to see your dream condominium!"
