220002745,SOLD,"JC, Heights",139 LAKE ST,Condominium,1047,1603,"$549,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,2,"JC, Heights",07306,04603,00001,,,,,,3,0,2,5,,"$549,000","$549,000",$524.36,$524.36,2/16/2022,3/4/2022,4/18/2022,16,16,,4/18/2022,,,,"$7,057",21,$213,,Conventional,,,,,,JFK Blvd & Liberty St,"Welcome to this gorgeous corner three-bedroom two-bath on quiet Lake St in The Heights. This open concept condo home was just gut renovated in 2018! The bright living room features 6 oversized windows with granite sills that let in so much natural light. The large kitchen is fitted with granite countertops, all stainless steel appliances, and a movable breakfast bar island for additional storage, seating, and flexibility of space. From there you'll find two equal-sized bedrooms that can accommodate up to a queen-sized bed. The primary suite features a very large layout, double closets, and an ensuite spa-style bathroom. All of this as well as in-unit washer and dryer, LED recessed lighting, crown molding, shared front patio, video doorbell system, and parking available for one car. Close to PATH, all major transportation, restaurants, and shops. "
210011251,SOLD,"JC, Heights",185 WEBSTER AVE,Condominium,1125,1702,"$549,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,1a,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,2,1,1,5,,"$549,000","$549,000",$488.00,$488.00,5/11/2021,7/1/2021,8/23/2021,45,45,,8/24/2021,,,,"$7,225",,$505,,Conventional,,,,,,Griffith and Bowers,"Bright and Spacious 2 Bedroom - 1.5 bathroom home with Parking on desirable tree lined street in Jersey City Heights. This east facing home features 11.5' ceilings and over-sized windows that flood the home with natural light. The gourmet kitchen offers granite counters, stainless steel appliances including a chef inspired refrigerator. Hardwood floors throughout, central a/c, in unit washer/dryer and ample storage space. Both bedrooms are well equipped and can serve a variety of purposes including being used as a home office, a guest room, or for a growing family. Additional storage available in pull down attic. This professionally managed elevator building includes 1 dedicated parking space and a stunning common roof deck with NYC that must be seen to believe. This home is steps to NYC transportation, farmers markets, restaurants and the newly re-opened Riverview-Fisk Park "
220009686,SOLD,"JC, Heights",207 OGDEN AVE,Condominium,890,1597,"$549,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,3L,"JC, Heights",07307,03903,00071,Heights,,,,,2,0,2,4,,"$549,000","$549,000",$616.85,$616.85,5/31/2022,6/7/2022,8/8/2022,7,7,,8/8/2022,,,,"$7,522",2021,$414,,Conventional,,,,,,Franklin & Griffith,"Situated on one of the most desirable streets in all of Jersey City Heights, this move-in ready top floor residence features 890 sq ft of living space including 2 Bedrooms and 2 Bathrooms. This beautiful home boasts 12’ ceilings, original crown moldings, tons of natural light, hardwood floors, recessed & cove lighting (Lutron smart lights), Central AC, in-unit washer and dryer and an abundance of storage. The updated kitchen features plentiful cabinetry, under cabinet lighting, quartz countertops and stainless steel appliances. The living room features a custom built-in media console, two large closets with overhead storage and a dining area. The large sun-filled primary bedroom has a closet with built-ins, overhead storage and an en-suite bathroom with walk-in shower. The bright second bedroom is located on the opposite side of the home with the second bathroom with bathtub in the hallway. Additionally, there is a private in-building 10’ x 10’ storage unit, as well as a quiet shared backyard with a new vinyl fence and grills perfect for entertaining. A shared roof deck is in its planning stages. Ideally located just moments to 2nd Street Light Rail station and buses, Riverview Park’s panoramic NYC views with farmer’s market, schools, and some of the city's most beloved cafes, restaurants & bars."
220006419,SOLD,"JC, Heights",325 PALISADE AVE,Condominium,924,1608,"$549,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1E,"JC, Heights",07307,05003,00001,,,,,,2,0,1,5,,"$549,000","$549,900",$594.16,$594.16,4/13/2022,4/19/2022,6/22/2022,6,6,,7/11/2022,,,,"$6,509",21,$489,,Conventional,,,,,,FERRY & RAVINE,"Welcome to this remarkable 2 bedroom unit in the historic Trolley House Lofts. With soaring 14' ceilings, an open concept kitchen, and polished concrete floors, this loft is designed for entertaining! The unit also comes equipped with central air, a Nest thermostat, custom closets and an assigned garage parking spot with additional storage space! This concrete elevator building conveniently has a laundry room on each floor, separate bike storage, a virtual doorman, remote entry, and security cameras throughout. Situated on the desirable Palisade Avenue, you'll be steps away from everything Jersey City Heights has to offer. Just cross the street to pick up some tasty Choc O Pain pastries and delicious Low Fidelity pizza to enjoy a picnic overlooking the NYC skyline at Riverview Park just down the street. Or if you're in the mood to stay in and cook, pop into the supermarket that's just a block away! And the convenience doesn't end there - easily commute to Manhattan with NYC buses at every block or take a quick stroll to hop on the Hoboken 2nd St Light Rail!"
