240001363,SOLD,"JC, Heights",138 LEONARD ST,Condominium,1012,1597,"$550,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,3R,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,2,0,2,6,,"$550,000","$550,000",$543.48,$543.48,1/23/2024,2/2/2024,3/28/2024,10,10,,3/29/2024,,,,"$5,133",,$325,,Conventional,,,,,,Nelson & JFK,"Discover a rare gem in Jersey City Heights with this oversized 2 bedroom home with 2-story layout and private outdoor space. This newly refinished loft-like residence offers soaring ceilings showcasing modern elegance and thoughtful restoration.  Step inside to the open floorplan large enough for formal dining and living area. Character emanates with exposed brick, Spanish wood door, beautiful bay window and wide plank wood flooring throughout. Bright white kitchen hosts white quartz counters, custom cabinets and all new stainless appliances. Downstairs features the first ensuite complete with access to private outdoor, and bathrooms finished with neutral tones and floor to ceiling tile.  Light streams through the skylit stairwell as you head up to the second floor including additional ensuite with sliding glass door access to an oversized private deck. Finally, climb another level to access the roofdeck with breathtaking cityscape news. Brand new stackable LG washer and dryer are located in the main floor for added convenience.  Ideally located in the heart of The Heights, owners are walking distance to expansive Washington Park with sports facilities, walking trails and dog run, as well as Summit and Central Ave with essential shopping and vibrant community. A premium neighborhood in Jersey City, The Heights is known for its eclectic vibe, beautiful parks, great schools and easy access to NYC and surrounding neighborhoods."
250000566,SOLD,"JC, Heights",138 LEONARD ST,Condominium,976,1597,"$550,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,3L,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,2,0,2,6,,"$550,000","$549,000",$563.52,$563.52,1/9/2025,1/27/2025,2/27/2025,18,18,,2/27/2025,,,,,,$325,,Conventional,,,,,,Nelson & JFK,"Discover a rare gem in Jersey City Heights with this oversized 2 bedroom home with 2-story layout and two private terraces plus rooftop. This newly refinished loft-style residence offers soaring ceilings showcasing modern elegance and high-end finishes.  Step inside to the open floorplan large enough for formal dining and living area. Character emanates with exposed brick, beautiful bay window and wide plank wood flooring. The bright white kitchen hosts white quartz counters, tile backsplash, sleek cabinetry and stainless appliances. Located directly off the kitchen, sliding glass lead to a private balcony ideal for a daily cup of coffee or evening break. A brand new GE Profile washer and dryer single machine is located on the main floor for added convenience.  Light streams through the skylit stairwell as you head up to the second floor which includes an additional ensuite. Bathrooms are finished with floor to ceiling tile in the shower or bathtub, spacious vanities and smart mirrors. While the downstairs ensuite offers access to a separate private terrace, the upstairs equivalent lends itself to the spacious private rooftop with panoramic city skyline views.  Ideally located in the heart of The Heights, owners are walking distance to expansive Washington Park with sports facilities, walking trails and dog run, as well as Summit and Central Ave with essential shopping and vibrant community. A premium neighborhood in Jersey City, The Heights is known for its eclectic vibe, beautiful parks, great schools and easy access to NYC and surrounding neighborhoods.  "
220018665,SOLD,"JC, Heights",54 SHERMAN AVE,Condominium,1249,1603,"$550,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,3,"JC, Heights",07307,04502,004-C03,,,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$550,000","$595,000",$440.35,$440.35,10/20/2022,9/7/2022,12/8/2022,0,0,,12/8/2022,,,,"$8,421",,$325,,Conventional,,,,,,Hutton & Franklin,"Sunny and spacious top floor 2 bed/ 2 bath unit in the heart of the Riverview Arts section of Jersey City Heights *with parking*. This dazzling condo was gut renovated in 2018 and boasts high ceilings, hardwood floors throughout, stainless steel appliances, quartz countertops, central air, and in-unit laundry. The primary bedroom features a walk-in closet and oversized bath. Juliet balconies in the front *and* back create a serene living space in the middle of a bustling neighborhood. Situated between Riverview and Manhattan Parks with easy access to Palisade and Central Avenue bus routes and mere blocks from the 2nd Street Light Rail Station in Hoboken. *Sellers are relocating for work* Video walkthrough here: https://vimeo.com/763974746 Welcome home!"
220007273,SOLD,"JC, Heights",108 MANHATTAN AVE,Condominium,1405,6199,"$550,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,,"JC, Heights",07307,00061,03701,,,,,,3,0,2,9,,"$550,000","$499,000",$391.46,$391.46,4/26/2022,5/5/2022,7/5/2022,9,9,,7/6/2022,,,,"$4,757",,,,Conventional,,,,,,Central Ave & Summit Ave,"This is the home you've been searching for in a great location! This incredibly bright, beautifully maintained 4 BEDROOM condo with a lovely view of Pershing Field Park. Amazing floor plan with incredibly spacious living space and equally impressive true formal dining room. This condo feels much larger than the sq ftge with high ceilings, great layout and gorgeous hardwood floors and pristine original details. Perfect space for entertaining or a growing family, with the generous living/ dining area offering plenty of room to stretch out. Beautiful, formal, long entryway can house your jackets, strollers, scooters & more. 4 true good sized bedrooms gives you the flexibility of accommodating all your new lifestyle needs of living / office / guest rooms. Washer & dryer and a great amount of storage in basement. Enjoy all that Pershing Field Park has to offer with 13.5 acres of outdoor space, swimming pool, ice rink, basketball courts, playground, baseball field, tennis court, track and adjacent to historic Jersey City Reservoir No. 3 where nature abounds. Steps to the vibrant Central Ave shopping district with supermarket, restaurants, cool coffee shops, fun bars, schools, shopping and more. Catch the bus on the corner to NYC and Path. Don't miss out!"
250022764,SOLD,"JC, Heights",281 CENTRAL AVE,Condominium,855,1419,"$550,000",CONDO-COOP,,4,4A,"JC, Heights",07307,3702,29,Heights,,,,,2,0,2,4,,"$550,000","$565,000",$643.27,$643.27,11/5/2025,1/27/2026,2/27/2026,83,83,,3/5/2026,,,,"$7,430",2024,$365,,Conventional,,,,,,Hutton Street & Sherman Pl,"Welcome home to The Beckford — a boutique luxury residence perfectly positioned in the heart of the Central Avenue District of The Heights.  Step off your private elevator directly into this stunning two-bedroom, two-bath condo, where expansive floor-to-ceiling windows frame breathtaking New York City skyline views. Sunlight fills every corner of this sophisticated, high-end home, blending modern comfort with timeless design.  Enjoy premium upgrades throughout, including California Closets, Wi-Fi–controlled heating and cooling, remote-controlled window treatments, and wide-plank white oak hardwood flooring.  The chef’s kitchen is a true centerpiece, featuring custom cabinetry, a mosaic penny tile backsplash, and top-of-the-line Dacor appliances. Both bathrooms are elegantly finished with patterned floor tiles, rainfall glass shower, and floating vanities, creating a spa-like retreat at home.  Residents of The Beckford enjoy exclusive amenities, including a spacious shared roof deck with panoramic NYC views, a shared garden, secured entrance, modern elevator, and bike storage.  Located in the vibrant Heights community, this home is surrounded by award-winning restaurants, trendy cafés, and local boutiques, including favorites like Corto, Renato’s, Box Cafe, Bread & Salt, Lo-Fi, and The Alps. Enjoy a short stroll to the Riverview Farmers Market, Pershing Field Park, and the historic Reservoir, with easy access to NYC and public parking just one block away.  Thoughtfully designed for modern living, this home pairs comfort and style with the welcoming charm of Jersey City Heights.  Special financing options avaiable with preferred Lender.  "
210002384,SOLD,"JC, Heights",974 SUMMIT AVE,Condominium,1090,1691,"$550,000",CONDO-COOP,,4,401,"JC, Heights",07037,2801,5.01,Heights,,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$550,000","$599,999",$504.59,$504.59,1/28/2021,1/28/2021,2/1/2021,0,0,,2/1/2021,,,,,,$412,,Cash,,,,,,Griffith & Licoln,"Welcome to THE SUMMIT in the heart of Jersey City Heights; New Construction, Boutique Condo building with open floor plans & amazing amenities, including:  a shared over-sized roof deck with stunning, 360 panoramic views, elevator, Peloton exercise bike room, bicycle storage. Deeded parking also available. Unit 412 is a modern open layout home with 2 large bedrooms, 2 full bathrooms and ample storage on both level. Elegantly built with modern, high-end finishes, quartz counter tops, hardwood floors, high end GE Cafe appliances (including smart tech induction vented range with Wi-Fi cooking access). Additional smart home features include Yale smart digital locks, Nest thermostat, Verizon FiOS ready,  tankless water heater, Central AC, full size washer/vented dryer. This impressive brick building at the corner of Summit Ave and Lincoln Street is ideally located in Jersey City Heights, near Central Avenue’s Restaurant row, NYC transit and steps away from all of JC Heights parks. Available for Immediate Occupancy and is eligible for 5 year tax abatement!"
220000387,SOLD,"JC, Heights",83 WAVERLY ST,Condominium,0,5745,"$550,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,A,"JC, Heights",07306,04901,00027,,,,,,1,0,1,4,,"$550,000","$525,000",,,1/7/2022,2/8/2022,7/8/2022,32,32,,7/11/2022,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Oakland and Central,"Get in early on this Eco friendly/environmentally sustainable new construction on a quiet street in the booming Heights section of Jersey City. Just blocks whatever you need - from the plethora of diverse activities at Pershing Field Park, shopping, groceries, farmer’s market, schools, day care, old and new eateries from cafes & pubs to 5 star restaurants. A real community feel with modern amenities!! Let’s start with the heart of a home – the chef designed dream kitchen w/ marbled stone countertops, SS Energy Star appliances w/ exhaust fan vented outside for improved air quality, herringbone subway tile backsplash. Although incredibly convenient for walking, biking or public transportation, throw in/provided indoor parking with electric vehicle charging station, bicycle & stroller storage. Stuck inside or need some fresh air head out to your private outdoor space. Help your wallet and the environment with high efficiency insulation on the interior of all exterior walls and the roof, triple pane windows, high efficiency multi-zone heating & cooling system with programmable thermostats, high efficiency LED lighting, EnergyStar rated white roof and a vegetated “green’ roof, water conserving dual flush toilets and a rain water harvesting and recycling system used for flushing toilets. A little more peace & quiet provided by sound attenuating insulation on interior wall partitions while you work from home, read or just relax in your Kohler deep soaking tub. Security conscious, need at home deliveries, let a baby or dog sitter in without giving them a key, no problem – you control access to your place remotely with smart access entry system to the building and residences. Low or non-toxic building materials were used for construction and approximately 90% of all construction waste diverted from a landfill & recycled. Proximity to Journal Square, Hoboken and Downtown Jersey City. 83 Waverly has it all: location, community, diverse activities, quiet nights with family and friends or a night on the town, stop in and check it out for yourself! Estimated completion date is 01/31/2022. Photos are Virtually Staged, finishes are subject to change. 1, 2 and 3 Bedroom Units Available!"
210006541,SOLD,"JC, Heights",103 FERRY ST,Condominium,900,1419,"$550,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2L,"JC, Heights",07307,04401,00016,Heights,Le Navire,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$550,000","$559,000",$611.11,$611.11,3/18/2021,4/19/2021,6/14/2021,32,32,,6/23/2021,,,,,,$203,,Conventional,,,,,,Central Ave & Abbett St,"Le Navire on Ferry St is a luxurious listing that you don’t want to miss! There was no detail spared within these units considering the 12 ft ceilings, a large private roof deck with direct NYC views, the wide plank oak hardwood floors, dynamic LED lighting, and Pella windows run throughout the entire home. This building was completely and meticulously gut renovated and upgraded with new plumbing and electric systems, a central sprinkler system, and fire protection. Your home will be equipped with central air, managed by Nest thermostats, a pair of pre-wired speakers in each room, high-end RING intercoms, operated from your phone, and in-unit washer/dryers. The developer spared no cost on noise reduction and used sounds channels and sound clips, foam insulation, Rockwool, and SounFX sheetrock. The seller can install and L-shaped island upon buyer's request for free or $1000 credit. Additionally there is 450sqft storage space above the master bedroom! Details aside, the location is another bonus that adds to the unlimited amenities here at Le Navire. Being located in this Jersey City Heights neighborhood leaves you less than 100 feet from the Central Ave Shopping district and nearest bus stops to the PATH and NYC. Act fast if you would like to secure a parking space; parking will be available for the first two buyers! If you decide to leave your home, Stop and Shop is only a few blocks away and there are an abundance of surrounding eateries including Pier 13, The Hutton Bar & Grill, Rumba’s Cafe, and two of the highest-rated locations, Dulce de Leche Bakery and Pampita Butcher Shop, all conveniently located. The selections are endless when you reside at Le Navire on Ferry St!"
