220018829,SOLD,"JC, Heights",65 CHARLES ST,Condominium,936,1568,"$560,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,2,0,2,6,,"$560,000","$599,000",$598.29,$598.29,10/21/2022,11/1/2022,1/20/2023,11,11,,1/21/2023,,,,,,,,Conventional,No,No,Yes,,,Summit & Milton,"Welcome to 65 Charles, a tastefully done gut-renovation project located in The Heights neighborhood of Jersey City. Unit 2 is a 936 SQFT 2-bedroom, 2-bathroom with a private terrace and parking included! 9' ceilings and 5 Oak Hardwood floors lead you to a custom kitchen with a Quartz eat-in countertop and double doors letting in natural light from your private outdoor space. Modern bathrooms with master en-suite, laundry in-unit and a great location make this unit a must see!"
240002486,SOLD,"JC, Heights",684 SUMMIT AVE,Condominium,915,1713,"$560,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,6,"JC, Heights",07306,05603,00067,,,,,,2,0,2,4,,"$560,000","$549,000",$612.02,$612.02,2/9/2024,3/4/2024,4/5/2024,24,24,,4/11/2024,,,,"$6,663",,$203,,Conventional,,,,,,Hopkins Ave & Beacon Ave,"Exquisitely renovated and conveniently located, welcome home to this beautifully lit 2-bed, 2-bath, 915 square foot condo with high ceilings and hardwood floors throughout. Your new custom chef’s kitchen boasts quartz countertops, shaker cabinetry, additional row of upper cabinets, stainless steel Samsung appliances, built-in wine fridge and large island with breakfast bar. Complete with 2 spacious bedrooms, modern, renovated bathrooms, and private rooftop showcasing views of New York City. New plumbing and electrical systems, central AC, Nest thermostats, Ring Doorbell, soundproofing are features not to be missed. Easy access to the Holland Tunnel and major highways and a short 10-minute walk to Journal Square PATH Station. Explore nearby parks, dining and entertainment options in Downtown Jersey City and Journal Square."
250008983,SOLD,"JC, Heights",95 WEBSTER AVE,Condominium,963,1686,"$560,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,3F,"JC, Heights",07307,04501,00019,Heights,,,,,2,0,1,5,,"$560,000","$575,000",$581.52,$581.52,5/6/2025,5/28/2025,7/9/2025,22,22,,7/9/2025,,,,"$10,113",,,504,Conventional,,,,,,Franklin & Palisade,"Welcome to this beautifully updated 2-bedroom, 1-bathroom condo in the heart of Jersey City Heights! This stunning home features an open-concept layout with hardwood floors throughout, a cozy fireplace, and tons of natural light pouring in from large windows. The fully updated kitchen is a chef’s dream, complete with modern appliances, sleek countertops, and ample storage. The primary bedroom boasts a walk-in closet, while both bedrooms are generously sized for comfortable living. Enjoy the convenience of in-unit washer and dryer, central heating and air conditioning, and two dedicated parking spots. Located in a prime location, this condo offers easy access to shopping, dining, coffee shops, and transportation, making it perfect for commuters and city lovers alike. Don’t miss this opportunity to own a stylish and convenient home in one of Jersey City Heights’ most sought-after neighborhoods!"
210000793,SOLD,"JC, Heights",974 SUMMIT AVE,Condominium,,1691,"$561,000",CONDO-COOP,,4,409,"JC, Heights",07037,2801,5.01,,,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$561,000","$560,000",,,1/9/2021,1/29/2021,3/25/2021,20,20,,3/26/2021,,,,,,$412,,Conventional,,,,,,Griffith & Licoln,"Welcome to THE SUMMIT in the heart of Jersey City Heights; New Construction, Boutique Condo building with open floor plans & amazing amenities, including:  a shared over-sized roof deck with stunning, 360 panoramic views, elevator, Peloton exercise bike room, bicycle storage. Deeded parking also available. Unit 409 is a modern open layout home with 2 large bedrooms, 2 full bathrooms and ample storage on both level. Elegantly built with modern, high-end finishes, quartz counter tops, hardwood floors, high end GE Cafe appliances (including smart tech induction vented range with Wi-Fi cooking access). Additional smart home features include Yale smart digital locks, Nest thermostat, Verizon FiOS ready,  tankless water heater, Central AC, full size washer/vented dryer. This impressive brick building at the corner of Summit Ave and Lincoln Street is ideally located in Jersey City Heights, near Central Avenue’s Restaurant row, NYC transit and steps away from all of JC Heights parks. Available for Immediate Occupancy and is eligible for 5 year tax abatement!"
240003354,SOLD,"JC, Heights",139 SHERMAN PL,Condominium,1080,1713,"$563,900",CONDO-COOP,,2,204,"JC, Heights",07307,03503,00001,,Sherman Place,,,,2,0,2,6,,"$563,900","$563,900",$522.13,$522.13,2/22/2024,3/5/2024,4/22/2024,12,12,,4/23/2024,,,,$0,,$431,,Conventional,,,,,,Kennedy and Sanford,"Presenting an exquisite condominium nestled in the heart of Jersey City Heights. This splendid residence boasts two generously proportioned bedrooms and two elegant bathrooms, providing a perfect blend of comfort and luxury. Just over 1000 square feet, the condo offers a well-thought-out layout that maximizes both space and functionality. Upon entering, you are greeted by a sophisticated and modern interior design that sets the tone for the entire unit. The open-concept living area seamlessly transitions from the inviting living room to the well-appointed kitchen, creating a harmonious space for relaxation and entertainment. The kitchen features top-of-the-line appliances, sleek cabinetry, and ample countertop space, catering to the needs of culinary enthusiasts and hosts alike. The two spacious bedrooms are designed to offer tranquility and privacy. The primary bedroom comes complete with an en-suite bathroom, providing a serene retreat after a long day. The second bedroom, equally spacious, offers versatility for use as a guest room, home office, or personal sanctuary. Both bathrooms are adorned with contemporary finishes and fixtures, evoking a spa-like ambiance. Natural light floods the living spaces through large windows, creating an airy and inviting atmosphere. The condo also features thoughtfully integrated storage solutions, ensuring a clutter-free living environment. Commuting to Manhattan and other parts of Jersey City is a breeze, thanks to the well-connected transportation options in the vicinity. This building truly caters to a sophisticated urban lifestyle. A unique opportunity to own a slice of modern elegance and urban convenience. A must-see!  "
240019598,SOLD,"JC, Heights",281 CENTRAL AVE,Condominium,800,1549,"$565,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,3B,"JC, Heights",07307,3702,29,Heights,The Beckford,,,,2,0,2,4,,"$565,000","$565,000",$706.25,$706.25,10/3/2024,11/22/2024,1/10/2025,50,50,,1/13/2025,,,,"$7,325",2023,$328,2024,Conventional,No,No,,,,Hutton & Sherman,"Welcome to The Beckford, nestled in the heart of the Central Avenue District of The Heights. This stylish and tech-forward building has what you need to immerse yourself in what The Heights and Jersey City are about and becoming. Three years young, this professionally managed grouping of sleek urban luxury condos is where you want to be. Take the elevator directly to your two-bedroom, two-bath, high-end sanctuary with modern upgrades and access the shared rooftop deck which boasts sweeping NYC and Heights views and has thoughtfully laid out seating. At the building level,  amenities include the large shared roof deck and garden, secured elevator and bike storage room. Each unit is awash in light provided by the floor to ceiling windows and finished with wide-plank, white oak hardwood flooring throughout. Kitchens feature ‘black ice’ quartz waterfall countertops and sleek custom cabinetry, mosaic penny tile backsplash, & Dacor appliances. Well appointed bathrooms shine with pattern floor tile, glass showers, and floating vanities with matte black finishes. Finally, well thought out floor plans offer elevated sound privacy and flow and ease of access to all building amenities. Find yourself located on the main thoroughfare of The Heights, adjacent to the vibrant artist community, essential shops, and one award-winning restaurant after another, while also just blocks to Pershing Field Park and The Reservoir, as well as easy NYC access. "
230009040,SOLD,"JC, Heights",258 SHERMAN AVE,Condominium,812,1597,"$565,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,2,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$565,000","$585,000",$695.81,$695.81,6/1/2023,6/2/2023,8/16/2023,1,1,,8/16/2023,,,,,,$244,,Conventional,,,,,,South St & Congress,"Light, bright and modern, this newly finished two bedroom home is one block to either Washington or Riverview Fisk Park in Jersey City Heights. Elegant design shines with loads of light illuminating hardwood floors and stylish contrasting matte back doors throughout.    Eat-in kitchen gleams with white quartz counters, exposed shelves, custom cabinets, tile backsplash and stainless appliances. Bedrooms boast ample closet space, while bathrooms host finishes like traditional penny tile shower floors, large vanities and polished chrome fixtures. Home features dedicated laundry area for added convenience.   Ideally located in the heart of The Heights, this home is perfectly positioned walking distance to major thoroughfares, great parks, and easy NYC access. Jersey City Heights is known for its excellent community and parks, great schools, eclectic shops and restaurants, and proximity to surrounding urban areas."
230000695,SOLD,"JC, Heights",295 TERRACE AVE,Condominium,1453,1597,"$565,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,2A,"JC, Heights",07306,,,,,,,,3,1,2,7,,"$565,000","$549,000",$388.85,$388.85,1/12/2023,1/23/2023,3/14/2023,11,11,,3/14/2023,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,North St & Leonard St,"Buying a home has never been smarter with this high tech, high-end, new construction home in The Heights. Power is at your fingertips with full control home automation systems in the 3 bedroom, 2 bath, penthouse with private roof deck & a bonus ground-floor home office with powder room.   Control your home with Alexa voice activation, mobile phone, or the 8-inch touch screen giving access to lighting, window shades, security, temperature, or professional audio system with zones in each room! Super smart appliances include dishwasher, washer and dryer, microwave and 36in refrigerator that gives recipes, shopping lists, content review and more.   Modern design matches the interior theme with clean lines, bright tones and thoughtful floorplan. Living room shines with floor to ceiling windows, plus marble fireplace with built-in floating fireplace. Incredible craftsmanship is showcased through stylish accents like light oak herringbone floors, ceiling molding, and carefully curated pendant lighting.   Marbled quartz waterfall counters with eat-in peninsula island and modern white and wood custom cabinetry finish the open floorplan kitchen. Bathrooms boast elements like floor to ceiling tile or matte black wall with matching wide pedestal wash basin. Midnight blue wainscotting bathes the primary ensuite, highlighting the oversized closet and private terrace.   Upstairs layout allows for spacious private roofdeck above, plus incredible separate ground level living area, ideal for additional office, guests or flex space.  Settled on a tree-lined street in a quiet corner of Jersey City Heights, these homes offer walkability to Central Avenue, Washington Park and easy NYC access.  TECH FEATURES Full control home automation system with Alexa voice activation Control your home at your finger tips with smart phone or built-in 8 inch screen the security cameras, video, doorbell, locks, temperature, lighting and all other switches  Full professional audio system with separate zones for each room Fully automated window shades Smart appliances  Microwave Dishwasher Washer & dryer 36 refrigerator with 21.5 inch touch screen providing recipes, grocery shopping, content review and more Smart mirrors in bathrooms"
260001958,SOLD,"JC, Heights",41 BEACON AVE,Condominium,788,1419,"$565,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1,"JC, Heights",07306,,,,,,,,2,0,2,6,,"$565,000","$585,000",$717.01,$717.01,2/4/2026,1/30/2026,2/27/2026,0,0,,2/27/2026,,,,"$8,876",2024,$200,,Conventional,,,,,,Palisades & Baldwin,"Luxury 2-Bedroom/2- Bathroom Condo with Private Backyard in Jersey City Heights. Welcome to this beautifully crafted new construction 2-bedroom, 2-bath luxury condominium located in the heart of Jersey City Heights — just moments from the Journal Square PATH, offering a quick and easy commute to Manhattan. Step into an inviting open-concept living space featuring white shaker cabinetry, a blue glass backsplash, quartz countertops, stainless steel appliances, and wide plank hardwood floors. Large sun-filled windows bathe the home in natural light, creating a warm and airy atmosphere throughout.  The two full bathrooms are designed with modern finishes, sleek vanities, and gold accents, giving each space a boutique spa-like feel. The highlight of this home is your private deeded backyard — a rare find in the Heights — perfect for relaxing, entertaining, gardening, or hosting outdoor gatherings. Enjoy the best of urban living with a peaceful residential feel, minutes from the PATH, local parks, restaurants, and coffee shops. Whether you’re commuting to NYC or working from home, this condo offers the ideal balance of comfort, style, and convenience. Live where style meets convenience in the heart of the Heights!    "
240000937,SOLD,"JC, Heights",21 HANCOCK AVE,Condominium,1613,1597,"$565,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,2,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,2,1,2,7,,"$565,000","$549,000",$350.28,$350.28,1/16/2024,3/21/2024,6/6/2024,65,65,,6/6/2024,,,,"$11,010",2024,$493,2024,Conventional,,,,,,Franklin & Hutton,"21 Hancock is a newly and tastefully restored historic brick building that offers a bright, modern and airy home located in the heart of the most desirable section of Jersey City Heights. With a Private Backyard and over 1600sqft of living space, this home has endless possibilities. Easily transforms into a 3-bedroom through the existing den. Attention to craftsmanship is seen from the refined restoration of the exterior, to the elegant entryway, and brand-new interior of this pre-war building. The layout gives way to high ceilings, beautiful hardwood floors, and fantastic natural light in the bedrooms. The kitchen includes granite countertops, stainless steel appliances, and ample cabinet space. This perfect picture is finished with in-unit Laundry and Central AC to provide all of the modern conveniences that every homeowner needs. Situated steps away from the bus that can take you to NYC Port Authority in 35 minutes, or to Journal Square Path station in 10 minutes. This home is perfect for NYC commuters looking to live in a peaceful neighborhood."
230000317,SOLD,"JC, Heights",360 PALISADE AVE,Condominium,1000,1597,"$565,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1A,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$565,000","$565,000",$565.00,$565.00,1/6/2023,3/3/2023,4/13/2023,56,56,,4/13/2023,,,,,,$397,,Conventional,,,,,,Ferry St & Franklin St,"Built in 2020, this ground-up new construction two bedroom and two bath home offers spacious interior, thoughtful upgrades, a private landscaped back garden & rental parking nearby! Stylish modern exterior gives way to classic design within, featuring light wood tile floors, neutral color palette and ceiling fans. Eat-in kitchen offers peninsula island with gleaming white quartz counters, tile backsplash, custom cherry cabinets and stainless appliances.   Large bedrooms offer plentiful closet space, while the back bedroom hosts double glass sliding doors to the private backyard area. Bathrooms offer floor to ceiling tile, soaker tub and shower with sizable vanity and updated design. Home features dedicated laundry area for convenience.   Modern facade gives great curb apparel on this tree-lined street of one of The Heights most coveted streets. Home offers walkability to Riverview Fisk Park Jersey City is known for its vibrant community and close proximity to excellent schools, expansive parks and easy NYC access."
230020034,SOLD,"JC, Heights",108 OGDEN AVE,Condominium,1385,1605,"$565,000",CONDO-COOP,,1 & G,101,"JC, Heights",07307,5202,22,Heights,,,,,2,0,2,7,,"$565,000","$499,000",$407.94,$407.94,12/1/2023,12/7/2023,2/14/2024,6,6,,2/16/2024,,,,"$8,579",,$476,,Conventional,,,,,,Dead End and Cuneo St.,"Rare opportunity for Eastern exposure on the Southend of Ogden Ave. Duplex unit is move in ready OR ready for your upgrades. Take in skyline views from the deck off the living/dining area. Open kitchen nice for entertaining. 2 levels offers lots of privacy. Currently set up as a 2 + office / den area with separate entrance. Lots of storage and closet space. HVAC, new hot water tank. Dog park, playground, and community garden surround the building. Easy commute down to Hoboken, DWTN JC, NYC. The Heights offers many great restaurants, shopping, parks and entertainment. This is an estate sale so current owners have very little knowledge of the unit. Buyers must do their own due diligence."
230001817,SOLD,"JC, Heights",236 PALISADE AVE,Condominium,1160,1653,"$565,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07306,6001,15,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,6,,"$565,000","$599,000",$487.07,$487.07,2/1/2023,3/7/2023,5/5/2023,34,34,,5/12/2023,,,,,,$252,,Conventional,,,,,,Prospect St. & Waverly St.,"Welcome home to this spacious 1,160 sq.ft. duplex condo with stunning views of Hoboken and NYC. With three bedrooms and two bathrooms, this brand new, fully renovated condo offers plenty of space to satisfy all your lifestyle needs.  The kitchen is stylish and spacious, with ample cabinetry, stainless steel appliances, and Calcutta quartz countertops. It flows seamlessly into the open-plan living/dining area, filled with natural light. You'll also find three bedrooms, one of which is an expansive primary bedroom with en-suite bathroom. There is also a second bathroom to service the other two bedrooms. Other key features of the home include central heat/AC, hardwood floors throughout & in-unit washer dryer.  Located on prime Palisade Avenue, this building is a few blocks away from Pershing Field Park & 2nd Street Light Rail, not to mention the multitude of local shops, restaurants, cafes, parks and all the conveniences of a vibrant neighborhood. All this while still having easy access to the city via public transit or car. Parking is available nearby at an additional cost."
250004410,SOLD,"JC, Heights",37 THORNE ST,Condominium,845,1713,"$565,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,3R,"JC, Heights",07307,2804,13,,,,,,2,0,2,6,,"$565,000","$565,000",$668.64,$668.64,3/8/2025,3/9/2025,5/7/2025,1,1,,5/8/2025,,,,$0,,$290,,Conventional,,,,,,Summit Ave and Central Ave,"Discover the perfect blend of sophistication and comfort in this stunning 2-bedroom, 2-bathroom residence in the heart of Jersey City Heights. Thoughtfully designed with meticulous attention to detail, this home offers everything you need to live in style. Step into an open and airy living space bathed in natural light, showcasing rich hardwood floors throughout. The chef-inspired kitchen is a true centerpiece, featuring sleek stainless steel appliances, a paneled dishwasher for seamless integration, elegant copper accents in the custom cabinetry, and a striking waterfall countertop that exudes modern elegance. Relax and unwind in the luxurious bathrooms, one with a glass-enclosed shower and the other with a soothing tub, both designed to provide a spa-like retreat. Each detail has been carefully curated to elevate your living experience. Ideally located, 37 Thorne offers convenience, comfort, and timeless style. This boutique 6-unit condo offers a massive storage space right on site. Don’t miss the chance to call Unit 3L home – schedule your private showing today! Parking available nearby for an additional fee."
230005481,SOLD,"JC, Heights",65 CHARLES ST,Condominium,936,6354,"$568,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07307,15,2704,Heights,65 Charles St.,,,,2,0,2,4,,"$568,000","$579,900",$606.84,$606.84,4/6/2023,4/20/2023,6/12/2023,14,15,,6/12/2023,,,,"$9,074",2022,$274,0,Cash,No,No,,,,JFK Blvd. & Summit Ave.,"*Completely Renovated** The Heights of Jersey City premieres this 2nd Fl. 2 Bed 2 Bath Turn-Key Condo with Master Suite, sure to impress! Beautifully redesigned inside & out with modern upgrades all through, completely move-in-ready & waiting for you! This stunning home offers a spacious open layout with new luxury flooring, recessed lighting & custom-made shades in every window+ a fresh palette that is easy to customize. Gorgeous Eat-in-Kitchen offers SS Appliances, luxe Quartz Counters and Backsplash, Center Island, & Premium Cabinetry. Down the hall, the Upgraded main bath w/Skylight + 2 generous Bedrooms, inc the Master Suite! MBR boasts its own Modernized ensuite bath with stall shower. 100 Sq. Ft. Private Terrace, In unit Laundry, Mini Ductless Splits for A/C & Heat, 1 Deeded parking space Included, the list goes on! Don't wait, this one won't last long! Come & See Today!!  **Showings to Begin on Thursday, 4/6/23**"
210016151,SOLD,"JC, Heights",54 SHERMAN AVE,Condominium,1175,1713,"$569,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07307,04502,00004,,,,,,2,0,2,4,,"$569,000","$569,000",$484.26,$484.26,7/6/2021,7/26/2021,9/24/2021,20,20,,9/28/2021,,,,"$8,050",,$325,,Conventional,,,,,,Franklin & Hutton,"Welcome home to this bright and spacious 2BD/2BA home on sought-after Sherman Avenue in the Heights. Gut renovated in 2018, this gorgeous home features a rather large kitchen with beautiful Quartz countertops, modern shaker cabinets, subway glass tile backsplash and top of the line stainless steel appliances. The bedrooms are set apart with total privacy in each room. The master bedroom is complete with an ensuite with double vanity, a generous-sized walk-in closet and a juliet balcony. This home also boasts hardwood floors, central air, in unit washer/dryer and high ceilings! All this plus you have your designated parking spot on the premises. Conveniently located two blocks from Palisade Avenue — just steps from buses to NYC, right next to popular restaurants/coffee shops such as Green Pear Cafe, The Franklin, Ichiban Sushi, Choco Pain and The Froth, you could not ask for a better location. You can also walk down to the Light Rail in Hoboken within minutes or the lovely Riverview Fisk Park that hosts farmers markets and events all year round!"
250021587,SOLD,"JC, Heights",433 CENTRAL AVE,Condominium,857,6638,"$570,000",CONDO-COOP,,2nd,2B,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,The James,,,,2,0,1,5,,"$570,000","$575,000",$665.11,$665.11,10/17/2025,12/12/2025,12/18/2025,56,56,,2/4/2026,,,,,,$336,,Conventional,,,,,,Bleeker & South St,"*Limited-time offer: 1 year free HOA, 1 year free parking, and a 2/1 rate buydown with rates as low as 3.5%. Terms and eligibility apply—please inquire for details.* The James, a bespoke collection of direct elevator-to-home condominiums just 20 minutes from Manhattan, presents Residence 3A - a refined two-bed condominium with private, keyless elevator entry, oversized windows off the living room, and access to a shared rooftop terrace showcasing sweeping NYC skyline views. Set in one of Jersey City’s fastest-growing markets, you’re close to major shops, cafés, and transportation. Crafted by Hampton Hill and designer walkTHIShouse, the residence balances modern elegance with timeless detail: oversized windows, wide-plank white oak floors, and an open, airy plan. The kitchen features quartz countertops and premium stainless appliances; spa-inspired baths are finished in porcelain tile with matte-black fixtures. Building comforts include Swiftlane smart access with video intercom, a package room, bike storage, and the signature rooftop with panoramic skyline vistas.*Please reach out to our preferred lender Jackie koven at cross co mortgage for grant options from 15-22 k and interest rates at 5.875.*"
