 modern elegance and urban convenience. A must-see!"
210026905,SOLD,"JC, Heights",83 ZABRISKIE ST,Condominium,800,1691,"$575,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,6,,"$575,000","$575,000",$718.75,$718.75,12/9/2021,11/1/2021,6/7/2022,0,0,,6/7/2022,,,,,,,,Miscellaneous,,,,,,JFK and Summit Ave,"Garden-level grandeur delights with this beautifully refinished two bedroom plus office with backyard. The modern grey brick building is situated in the sweet spot of Jersey City Heights, walking distance to parks, shops and community.  Walk into wide-plank floors below and classic crown molding above. Eat-in kitchen with space-saving peninsula boasts dark custom cabinetry complimented by black quartz counters and tile backsplash. Light flows into bright front office with oversized windows, or head down the hall to the primary bedroom with sliding glass door access to the backyard. Stylish bathrooms bring sophistication with black porcelain counters, dark wood vanity, slab tile to the ceiling and glass showers.  One block from bustling Central Avenue or peaceful Pershing Field and Leonard Gordon Parks, this location brings the best of both worlds for urban living. Jersey City Heights offers eclectic essential shops, vibrant community, excellent schools and easy NYC access."
240017903,SOLD,"JC, Heights",234 WEBSTER AVE,Condominium,1300,6078,"$575,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2L,"JC, Heights",07307,,,,,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$575,000","$575,000",$442.31,$442.31,9/10/2024,11/26/2024,1/17/2025,26,25,,1/23/2025,,,,,,$225,,Conventional,,,,,,"Central Ave, to Bowers St, to Webster Ave","***ONLY 2 UNITS LEFT! SELLER OFFERING 1 YEAR OF PARKING CREDIT!*** Recently constructed condo with a boutique-style ambiance and private rooftop! Situated in the coveted Jersey City Heights neighborhood, 234 Webster offers top-notch appliances and finishes including washer/dryer in unit and stainless steel appliances. With impressive 14-foot ceilings and black custom architect windows, the home is flooded with natural light. Thoughtful design is evident, with custom-built Chanel-inspired closets, elegant quartz one-piece backsplash with countertops in the kitchens, and real oak wood European-style stairs. The bathrooms feature innovative three-way plumbing fixtures, and upgraded hardware. Cove lighting adds a touch of sophistication, complemented by upgraded tile finishes, floor-to-ceiling tiling, and a clean coat of high-end frameless shower glass doors. Experience tranquility with exceptional soundproofing, minimizing noise transmission between floors. The prime location is nestled between Palisade Ave and Central Avenue. Enjoy your neighbors of Corto, Riverview Wine and Spirits, The Franklin, Bread & Salt (Top Pizzeria in Jersey City), Low Fi Bar, and Dulce De Leche Bakery. Close to great attractions such as Jersey City Mural, Hudson River Waterfront Walkway, Trader Joes (10 minutes), and shopping along Central Avenue. The Jersey City Heights neighborhood is very close to the Holland Tunnel, Home Depot, and Newport Center Mall, providing easy access to major bus lines and the Congress St light rail and 2nd St light rail, offering a convenient and direct route to NYC."
220014382,SOLD,"JC, Heights",269 OGDEN AVE,Condominium,988,1597,"$575,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,3,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$575,000","$575,000",$581.98,$581.98,8/8/2022,9/23/2022,11/17/2022,46,46,,11/18/2022,,,,,,$318,,Conventional,,,,,,Griffith & Franklin St,"Modern and move-in ready, this newly renovated two-bedroom home is perfectly positioned on  desirable Ogden Avenue in the Heights. Floor to ceiling windows and sleek design bring artistry and spaciousness with wide plank oak floors, clean lines and open floorplan.  Extra large windows and extra-wide doorways bring a true feeling of manhattan loft living to the space. Kitchen commands presence with sleek custom cabinetry, gleaming quartz counters and backsplash, and stainless appliances. Split floorplan offers bedrooms on either end of the living space, while elegant bathrooms bring creamy porcelain tile, glass shower or soaker tub and double vanity in the ensuite.   Beautiful brick building offers secure entrance on a tree-lined street less than one block to nearby Riverview Fisk Park with breathtaking NYC views or 9th Street Lightrail Station for Hoboken and NYC access. Jersey City Heights is known for its artisan shops and restaurants, close-knit community, excellent parks and schools. "
220006024,SOLD,"JC, Heights",236 BOWERS ST,Condominium,1182,1686,"$575,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07307,2604,35,Heights,,,,,3,0,1,6,,"$575,000","$575,000",$486.46,$486.46,4/7/2022,4/12/2022,5/23/2022,5,5,,5/24/2022,,,,"$6,407",2021,$300,2021,Conventional,,,,,,Milton Ave & Kennedy Blvd,"A stunning condo in the middle of the Heights District in Jersey City which has 3 great sized bedrooms, 1 bathroom. Minutes from public transportation, cafes and shops. The condo boasts an updated kitchen, with modern white cabinets and quartz counters, modern lighting throughout and state of the art Samsung appliances. It comes with a dedicated storage unit, and laundry access in the basement."
240009673,SOLD,"JC, Heights",234 WEBSTER AVE,Condominium,1459,1754,"$575,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2R,"JC, Heights",07307,02306,00005,,,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$575,000","$599,000",$394.11,$394.11,5/21/2024,8/6/2024,10/11/2024,77,77,,10/12/2024,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Bower & South St,"Explore this recently constructed condo with a boutique-style ambiance at 234 Webster Ave, Unit 2R. Boasting two (2) bedrooms, two (2) bathrooms, and a large 530+ square foot private rooftop oasis with breathtaking views of the NYC skyline and Riverview-Fisk Park. Situated in the coveted Jersey City Heights neighborhood, the Webster Residence offers top-notch appliances and finishes, including brand-new stainless steel appliances, central air and heat, and a brand-new washer and dryer in the unit.  Enjoy the spaciousness with impressive 14-foot ceilings and modern black custom windows that flood the home with natural light. Thoughtful design is evident, with custom-built Chanel-inspired closets, elegant quartz one-piece backsplash with countertops in the kitchen, and real oak wood European-style stairs. The bathrooms feature innovative fixtures, upgraded hardware, and an amazing shower experience. Upgraded tile finishes, floor-to-ceiling tiling, and a clean coat of high-end frameless shower glass doors.  Experience tranquility with exceptional soundproofing, minimizing noise transmission between floors. The prime location is nestled between Palisade Ave and Central Avenue, within walking distance to Corto, Riverview Wine and Spirits, The Franklin, Bread & Salt (top pizzeria in Jersey City), Lo-Fi Bar, and Dulce De Leche Bakery. Close to great locations such as Jersey City Mural, Hudson River Waterfront Walkway, Trader Joe's (10 minutes), and shopping along Central Avenue. The Jersey City Heights neighborhood is very close to the Holland Tunnel, Home Depot, and Newport Center Mall, providing easy access to major bus lines and the Congress St light rail and 2nd St light rail, offering a convenient and direct route to NYC. Total Area: 1459.90 sqft (including rooftop, staircase, and entire floor).  Park & Bus stop: Riverview Fisk Park - 2 short blocks via Bowers St  Restaurants nearby: Corto The Franklin Fox & Crow Angry Archie’s  The Hutton Low Fidelity Niches de Colombia  Many many more  Grocery Store: Supremo Food Market    "
210015451,SOLD,"JC, Heights",549 PALISADE AVE,Condominium,1,1691,"$575,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,3,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$575,000","$549,000","$575,000.00","$575,000.00",6/25/2021,7/26/2021,10/6/2021,31,31,,10/7/2021,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,South St & Congress,"Modern design and mindful finishes heat things up in coveted Jersey City Heights. The white-hot facade of this beautifully refinished Tudor-style stonework building leads to a secure entrance for each of the four 2-bed, 2 full bath homes. Each slightly different floorplan offers a variety of must-haves, each boasting modern design, fresh finishes plus common storage.  Clean lines and simple design echo throughout each unit with gleaming hardwood floors and flowing floorplans. Kitchens shine brightly with sparkling quartz counters, shaker cabinets and stainless Frigidaire appliances, while bathrooms showcase porcelain tile finished to the ceiling plus optimal soaker tubs and showers. Sizable bedrooms with ceiling fans, plus Samsung washer and dryer are standard in each home.  The second floor unit radiates sunlight with oversized windows, plus sliding glass doors leading to a large private treetop roofdeck, while the top floor unit elevates with vaulted ceilings, unique lines and master bedroom balcony. The first floor also boasts a beautiful master balcony and the lower unit showcases a thoughtful split floor plan with separate large kitchen and dining.  This perfect Palisade location is walking distance to Riverview Fisk and Washington Parks, plus just steps from essential shops, vibrant community, excellent schools and easy NYC, PATH and Light Rail access."
260000089,SOLD,"JC, Heights",192 CAMBRIDGE AVE,Condominium,1080,1597,"$575,000",CONDO-COOP,,1/2,5,"JC, Heights",07307,2203,2.01,Heights,,,,,2,1,2,4,,"$575,000","$565,000",$532.41,$532.41,1/7/2026,1/15/2026,3/11/2026,8,8,,3/12/2026,,,,$0,,,,Conventional,No,No,No,,,Congress Street & South Street,"Private duplex home with private entrance!  Five new-construction condominium homes redefine modern living in Jersey City Heights. Each home showcases a refined aesthetic and carefully curated details. Chef-inspired kitchens feature expansive Taj Mahal quartz islands, premium LG stainless appliances with gas range, a Frigidaire wine cooler, and Sharp built-in microwave. Primary baths offer a spa-like escape with porcelain and ceramic tiles, frameless glass showers, brushed gold hardware, Kohler fixtures, and natural teak vanities, while secondary baths boast sleek subway tiles, matte black channels, Moen fixtures, and LED mirrors. Wide-plank French oak flooring, soaring ceilings, custom lighting, and built-in electric fireplaces bring warmth and style throughout, creating homes that balance modern sophistication with everyday comfort.  192 Cambridge sits in prime location only one block to Washington Park and a few short blocks to The Arts District surrounding Riverview Park.  Enjoy neighborhood cafés, Central Avenue shops, and vibrant restaurants, with the Congress Street Light Rail a short walk away, you’ll enjoy effortless access to Hoboken and Manhattan while keeping the Heights’ neighborhood charm at your doorstep."
250021035,SOLD,"JC, Heights",69 FRANKLIN ST,Condominium,1000,1549,"$575,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,2,0,2,6,,"$575,000","$579,000",$575.00,$575.00,10/10/2025,12/10/2025,1/27/2026,61,61,,1/31/2026,,,,,,$458,,Conventional,No,No,,,,Webster & New York,"Amazing opportunity to live in a freshly painted, bright & airy 2 bed/2 bath apartment in an ideal Heights location. Updated, European kitchen w/ stainless steel appliances & prep island. 10+ ft ceilings, tons of storage & natural light, exposed brick, & recently refinished hardwood floors. Free Laundry & Storage Cage in Building. Large alcove could house a daybed or office. Outdoor space for relaxing, two gas fireplaces & large Walk-In Closet. Easy walk to public transportation, restaurants, bars, & other urban amenities. Vacant & Ready To Move In! Make an appointment today."
