260003721,ACTIVE,"JC, Heights",16 TROY ST,Condominium,868,6078,"$578,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,201,"JC, Heights",07307,4702,30.01,,,,,,2,0,2,5,,,"$578,000",$665.90,,3/4/2026,,,36,,,3/4/2026,,,,"$10,262",,$258,,,,,,,,Montrose and Summit,"Located in the heart of the vibrant Jersey City Heights neighborhood, this impeccably designed 868 -sf condo built in 2023 offers a sophisticated blend of modern luxury and urban convenience. The open-concept living space is defined by gleaming hardwood floors and recessed lighting, anchored by a chef's kitchen that features a full suite of stainless steel appliancesincluding a French door refrigerator, gas stove, dishwasher, and built-in microwavealongside a dedicated wine refrigerator. The kitchen flows seamlessly into the main living area, where built-in Bluetooth Sonos speakers and a video intercom system provide a high-tech lifestyle. The spacious primary suite serves as a stylish retreat, highlighted by a signature brick wall feature, a double closet, and an ensuite with floor-to-ceiling marble pattern tile, a double vanity, and a sleek stand-up shower. Beyond the interior comforts of central HVAC and a 2nd full bath, this home offers the rare urban luxury of garaged parking for one car plus guest parking. The location is stellar being less than a block from the beautiful 13 acre Pershing Field Park offering an incredible array of year-round amenities, including an ice skating rink, tennis and basketball courts, a running track, and a playground. The property remains a commuter's dream, with the Journal Square PATH station just a less than a mile away as well as nearby bus routes and the Pulaski Skyway ensure you are perfectly positioned for work and play. Set back from the street via a long 100-ft private driveway, this home offers a rare sense of quiet and privacy with extra added security in the city while still being incredibly convenient. Located on a peaceful side street rather than a busy thoroughfare, the property is thoughtfully equipped with exterior and interior security cameras for extra peace of mind. You'll enjoy a calm residential feel just a few blocks from the main strip on the other side of the park, with easy access to shopping, dining, and local activities. Plus, it's only 1.5 miles to the Hoboken PATH, and convenient commuting access to NYC, giving you the best of both tranquility and city convenience."
220008503,SOLD,"JC, Heights",142 CHARLES ST,Condominium,1021,1653,"$579,000",CONDO-COOP,,4,403,"JC, Heights",07307,2603,51,Heights,The Packard,,,,2,0,3,6,,"$579,000","$579,000",$567.09,$567.09,5/12/2022,6/4/2022,6/29/2022,23,23,,6/30/2022,,,,,,$440,,Conventional,,,,,,John F Kennedy & Summit Blvd,"This is a rare and sought-after opportunity to secure your very own slice of history in booming Jersey City Heights. The Packard JC boasts 14 new luxury condominiums that combine the very best in contemporary comfort with original details from this building’s industrial past. The Penthouse units all feature 2 beds, 2 baths and most units offer sweeping views of Manhattan, Journal Square & beyond Jersey City. Cooking will be a pleasure in the stylish kitchens with stainless steel appliances, under-mount sinks, breakfast bars and leathered granite countertops with a waterfall edge. Central AC, Navian on-demand tankless water heaters and an in-unit washer-dryer ensure absolute comfort plus there’s a host of dramatic features including 12 ft ceilings, concrete beams, exposed ductwork and engineered hardwood herringbone flooring.   Once the Packard Motor Car Company showroom, this steel and concrete construction, loft-style building is located close to the bustling Central Avenue with restaurants, shopping, cafes and parks nearby. Nearby buses connect you to NYC with easy links to the Journal Square transportation hub.  Photos are of a similar staged unit in the building."
