230006238,SOLD,"JC, Heights",684 SUMMIT AVE,Condominium,1653,1653,"$585,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1,"JC, Heights",07306,5603,67,,,,,,3,1,2,7,,"$585,000","$599,000",$353.90,$353.90,4/19/2023,6/14/2023,7/12/2023,56,56,,7/14/2023,,,,,,,,Cash,,,,,,beacon and hopkins,"Welcome to Summit Lodge, a meticulously curated condominium building in the Jersey City heights. With its classically ornamental brick facade exterior, 684 Summit Avenue imparts a completely reimagined contemporary design on the interior to create harmonious, lavish, condominiums. Every square-inch of the property has been intricately designed with the end-user in mind. The lower-level duplex units each will consist of roughly 1600 sqft of living space, spanning across 2 solid oak hardwood floors and boasting 3 bedrooms and 3 baths leading to a private backyard space. This unit will come with a custom chef’s kitchen, including designer quartz countertops, Porcelanosa tile and fixtures, Nest thermostats, central air, a Ring Doorbell Intercom, vibrant LED lighting throughout the entire space, and more! The ground level of this unit will also possess a separate entrance and a kitchenette, creating a private and functional space for extended family or guests. Additionally, all units have been upgraded with new plumbing, a new electrical system, and fire protection as well as top of the line sound proofing. The developer spared no costs to sound proof all the units in this building. This includes using open cell foam insulation, QuietWalk floor underlayment, and QuietRock ceiling panels between the floors to dampen the sound. Additionally, using sound clips and sound channels enabled to provide an unmatched level of peace and privacy. Topping this off, the property is located one block away from Highway 139, where you can access many northbound major highways such as Route 3 and Route 1&9 or maybe head southbound towards Pulaski Skyway or Route 440. The building is also only 6 minutes away from the Holland Tunnel via driving, and 13 minutes walking distance to the Journal Square PATH station, making travel to and from Manhattan incredibly easy. Other perks include a plethora of options for restaurants and entertainment for all ages, being that this property is located so close to both Downtown Jersey City and the Journal Square section of Jersey City while having the residential neighborhood feeling of the Jersey City Heights. This property’s location will cater to your every need. Schedule a viewing today!"
230006119,SOLD,"JC, Heights",579 PALISADE AVE,Condominium,987,6078,"$585,000",CONDO-COOP,,102,1W,"JC, Heights",07307,2304,22,Heights,,,,,2,1,1,5,,"$585,000","$550,000",$592.71,$592.71,4/17/2023,4/25/2023,5/18/2023,8,8,,5/20/2023,,,,"$8,555",,,,Cash,,,,,,Congress and South,"If you are looking for that place you can recreate into your own, right in the heart of Jersey City Heights, look no further. This bright and spacious first floor 2 bedroom, 1.5 bath condo has hardwood floors throughout, nice sized bedrooms, ample sized closets, washer/dryer in the unit, updated and upscale bathroom with a heated towel rack too. Central air, forced hot air, recessed lighting, and your very own private terrace which truly feels like the sweet escape that you may be looking for. The shared rooftop access with panoramic New York City views is an extra bonus especially for the summer months ahead to watch the sunset. There is a dedicated storage space in the basement, updated door security system for residents, and all in welcoming community. Centrally located near bodegas, schools, Riverview Park, trains, buses, and of course, New York City."
210025268,SOLD,"JC, Heights",179 LINCOLN ST,Condominium,1365,298,"$585,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07307,02504,00019,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,7,,"$585,000","$599,000",$428.57,$428.57,11/8/2021,12/7/2021,1/18/2022,29,29,,1/21/2022,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Kennedy Blvd & Milton Ave,"Craftsmanship and attention to detail is what you will find with this freshly refinished 2-unit building primely located in Jersey City Heights. Unit 2 is a spacious 3 bedroom 2 bathroom with terrace. Interior boasts 10' ceilings with clean and modern finishes. Kitchens will impress with clean white custom cabinets with matte black hardware, white quartz counters and backsplash. High end appliances and a wine fridge finish off this perfect kitchen.  The Bathrooms, wow with large showers, modern finishes and a spa-like feel. Windows give impeccable natural light. Nestled on a quiet dead end street in the Western Slope of the Heights, you have easy access to the highway and transportation to the city.  Come see for yourself.   "
260006151,ACTIVE,"JC, Heights",207 OGDEN AVE,Condominium,900,6638,"$585,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1L,"JC, Heights",07307,,,,,,,,2,0,2,6,,,"$585,000",$650.00,,4/7/2026,,,2,,,4/7/2026,,,,"$10,570",2026,$325,2026,,,,,,,Franklin & Griffith,"Well-appointed 2-bedroom, 2-bath condo located on Ogden Avenue, one of Jersey City Heights’ premier tree-lined streets. This home features two generously sized bedrooms, including a primary suite with a private ensuite bath.  The kitchen is equipped with granite countertops and stainless steel appliances, while hardwood flooring, central air and heat, and updated windows enhance comfort throughout. Additional highlights include in-unit laundry, abundant closet space, a private 6’ x 9’ storage unit, and access to a newly paved shared backyard.  Enjoy unbeatable convenience with the Sunday farmer’s market at Fisk Park just down the block, along with nearby shopping, dining, and direct bus access. The 2nd Street Light Rail is within walking distance, offering an easy commute to the PATH and NYC. "
210005526,SOLD,"JC, Heights",86 NELSON AVE,Condominium,1175,5292,"$585,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07307,704,52,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,7,,"$585,000","$585,000",$497.87,$497.87,3/8/2021,3/15/2021,4/16/2021,7,7,,4/29/2021,,,,"$7,360",,,,Conventional,No,No,,,,North & Irving St,"Welcome to The Western Slope, a highly desirable neighborhood of JC Heights. This bright & airy 3BR/2BTH condo, built in 2019, features 1175 sf of modern living w/ exclusive private access to apprx 450 sf roof deck.  The sleek, luxurious design runs thruout the entire unit w/ 3 1/4 oak plank flooring, large porcelain tiles in kitchen & baths, waterfall quartz island, Andersen windows, GE Profile appliances, & Moen fixtures. Custom built closets & crown molding, full sized washer/dryer, central Air/Heat & central vacuum system.  The home is outfitted w/ Smart Home features - smart wiring, alarm wiring, virtual doorbell & two 7 monitors capable of controlling lights, video & more.  Split design places two bedrms in rear for privacy & one off L/R with French doors, perfect for an office, den family or guest room.  Master suite inclds walk-in closet, full bath & balcony w/ views of NYC skyline. The open concept living rm/kitchen inclds lots of natural light from large bay window (waterfall island can easily be removed, if desired). The luxury continues outdoors w/ access to private roof deck w/ stunning 360-degree view of NYC skyline & JC, composite decking, gas line for grilling, water spigot for possible rooftop garden, electric + storage room!  Centrally located to NYC transportation, 15 mins to NYC, steps from Washington Park & Leonard Gordan Park.  Plenty of street parking.  4 yrs tax abatement."
230000318,SOLD,"JC, Heights",360 PALISADE AVE,Condominium,1000,1597,"$587,500",CONDO-COOP,,4,4A,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,2,1,2,5,,"$587,500","$599,000",$587.50,$587.50,1/6/2023,2/10/2023,3/17/2023,35,35,,3/17/2023,,,,,,$401,,Conventional,,,,,,Ferry St & Franklin St,"Built in 2020, this ground-up new construction two bedroom and two and a half bath home offers spacious interior, thoughtful upgrades & rental parking nearby! Stylish modern exterior gives way to classic design within, featuring light wood tile floors, neutral color palette and ceiling fans. Eat-in kitchen offers peninsula island with gleaming white quartz counters, tile backsplash, custom cherry cabinets and stainless appliances.   Large bedrooms offer plentiful closet space, while the back bedroom hosts double glass sliding doors to the private balcony. Bathrooms offer floor to ceiling tile, soaker tub and shower with sizable vanity and updated design. Home features dedicated laundry area for convenience.   Modern facade gives great curb apparel on this tree-lined street of one of The Heights most coveted streets. Home offers walkability to Riverview Fisk Park Jersey City is known for its vibrant community and close proximity to excellent schools, expansive parks and easy NYC access."
210008156,SOLD,"JC, Heights",150 WEBSTER AVE,Condominium,1679,1186,"$589,000",CONDO-COOP,,1&2,1,"JC, Heights",07307,03805,00030,,,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$589,000","$595,000",$350.80,$350.80,4/6/2021,4/25/2021,6/8/2021,19,18,,6/9/2021,,,,"$7,796",,$150,,Conventional,,,,,,Hutton & Griffith,"Bright and beautiful, this fantastic duplex features a PRIVATE deeded backyard with a paver patio to extend your home enjoyment to the great outdoors! This well appointed 2 bed, 2 bath home features a spacious kitchen with granite countertops, stainless appliances and custom lighting. An open living/dining area makes for comfortable living and great entertaining. Wide plank cherry hardwood flooring throughout, central A/C, recessed lighting, exposed brick, wainscoting, custom designer bathrooms and a massive PRIVATE full-basement perfect for storage make this unit best in class. Parking is made easy with two rental spots available directly across the street. Easy access to NYC and transportation via buses, train and light rail!"
