240004150,SOLD,"JC, Heights",203 HOPKINS AVE,Condominium,1003,1713,"$590,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07306,05503,00001,Heights,,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$590,000","$595,000",$588.24,$588.24,3/5/2024,3/25/2024,5/3/2024,20,20,,5/10/2024,,,,$0,,$321,,Conventional,,,,,,corner of Bevan St & Hopkins Ave,"Welcome to this newly renovated 1,000 SQFT 2 bedroom / 2 bath condo, in the booming sector of The Heights, minutes from Holland Tunnel, Downtown JC and major routes like Rt. 280, NJ Turnpike, and much more! This 2nd level home features modern style finishes, a large open concept living space, great sized bedrooms, and baths, as well as 1-car parking. Step inside and soak in the beautiful light hardwood floors, and luminous array of recessed lighting, not to mention the end of end display of windows allowing the natural light to seep through. A tucked away full size stacked front loaders create that ease of convenience of having the laundry on the same floor. A modern and chic style kitchen awaits with a full set of state-of-the-art appliances, and gleaming white cabinetry with featured gold hardware. An oversized island makes it the perfect space for hosting family and friends! Two great sized bedrooms and two baths featuring a tub and shower with floating dual vanities complete this space, making for the perfect cozy place to come home to after a long day. This fabulous condo is a must see. "
220000184,SOLD,"JC, Heights",201 ZABRISKIE ST,Condominium,1785,1713,"$590,000",CONDO-COOP,,1st,1,"JC, Heights",07307,03303,00015,Heights,,,,,3,1,2,6,,"$590,000","$599,000",$330.53,$330.53,1/4/2022,1/21/2022,3/21/2022,17,17,,3/21/2022,,,,,TBD,$315,2021,Conventional,,,,,,Terrace & Western Ave,"Step inside your brand new gut-renovated from the studs out 3 bedroom, 2 ½ bath condo duplex located in the thriving district of Jersey City Heights! Boastingjust under 1800 sq ft of livable space, plus over 800 sq ft private back yard and dedicated off street parking spot in front. Located near Manhattan Ave, Leonard Gordon Park, and Tonnelle Avenue, this beautiful home has much to offer! Enter into the glamorous kitchen complete with gourmet black stainless steel appliances, custom two-toned cabinets, “Calacatta Bello” Quartz countertops and backsplash, and a large sized island with a waterfall countertop. Black Matte style hardware and light fixtures give this beautiful kitchen a modern flare! On the main floor you also have a great sized dining/living open concept space with a half bath located right off the living space perfect for entertaining guests. The open concept living space flows directly into a private backyard for seamless indoor/outdoor living and entertaining.  Two bedrooms, one located off the living room and the other located off the kitchen each with a great sized walk in closet and a full hallway bath complete the lower level of this stunning, oversized duplex. The upper level of this duplex offers an oversized master bedroom with over 9 feet high ceilings and ensuite for total privacy, complete with built in custom floor-to-ceiling wardrobe, beautiful modern finishes, double vanity, extra storage closet inside the bathroom and large size stand in shower. There is also a separate entrance on the upper level going straight to the master suite to maintain total privacy. Some notable mentions include: hardwood flooring throughout, the video intercom / doorbell system in place is an “iPhone GT video intercom” system, tankless hot water heater, central A/C and heat, hook up for stackable w/d, one car parking and beautiful backyard space perfect for entertaining or just some quiet time to relax outdoors."
220003264,SOLD,"JC, Heights",82 RESERVOIR AVE,Condominium,1105,5845,"$590,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,3,"JC, Heights",07307-2478,,,,,,,,3,0,2,6,,"$590,000","$599,500",$533.94,$533.94,2/24/2022,6/28/2022,10/30/2022,124,124,,11/3/2022,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Webster and Lineau Place,"Welcome home to 82 Reservoir. This 3 unit building was meticulously renovated with an eye to providing everything today's discerning buyer needs. Unit #3 offers 3 bedrooms 2 full bathrooms and a separate den/office room , perfect for our current work from home lifestyle. This top floor unit has soaring 11ft high ceilings and is simply flooded with light. The chefs kitchen is complete with maple cabinetry, quartz countertops and stainless steel appliances. The open concept living area has ample space for a separate dining area. The primary bedroom features an enu-site bathroom. Beautiful oak floors throughout, brand new Anderson windows, central a/c and in home laundry. The building offers a separate storage unit and a common roof deck with sweeping views of NYC. Perfectly situated in one of the most sought after areas in Jersey City Heights, only minutes to shopping, restaurants, Pershing field park and recreation and offering an easy commute to NYC"
210001066,SOLD,"JC, Heights",302 PALISADE AVE,Condominium,1000,1702,"$590,000",CONDO-COOP,,4,402,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,Palisade Heights,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$590,000","$599,000",$590.00,$590.00,1/13/2021,3/12/2021,5/3/2021,58,58,,5/5/2021,,,,"$6,167",2020,$401,2020,Conventional,,,,,,Ferry and Cuneo,"Exceptional turn key 2 bedroom 2 bathroom with parking! This top floor home offers a large living and dining room combination flooded with natural light. The designer kitchen includes high-end Jenn-Air appliances, quartz counters, and a breakfast bar. Two well appointed bedrooms including an over sized master bedroom with en-suite bathroom, two closets and plenty of room for a home office. Additional features include an in-unit washer/dryer, central air, and a dedicated parking space in the onsite garage with room for additional storage. Palisade Heights Condominiums is a professionally managed 12-unit building with a shared backyard located steps to NYC transportation, Choc-O-Pain, Lo-Fi, Corto, Riverview Park, supermarkets and a quick walk down to Hoboken."
210026524,SOLD,"JC, Heights",83 ZABRISKIE ST,Condominium,1338,1691,"$591,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,6,,"$591,000","$575,000",$441.70,$441.70,12/2/2021,12/30/2021,3/14/2022,26,26,,3/14/2022,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Sanford Place & Summit Ave,"Refresh your lifestyle with this beautifully refinished three bedroom two bath condo plus balcony. The modern grey brick building is situated in the sweet spot of Jersey City Heights, walking distance to parks, shops and community.  Walk into gleaming wide plank hardwood floors with classic crown molding and thoughtful finishes. Eat-in kitchen boasts dark cherry custom cabinetry with gleaming quartz counters, tile backsplash and stylish pendant lighting. Light flows into the generous bedrooms with oversized windows on either end of the split-plan layout. Primary ensuite hosts access to private balcony plus a large walk in closet. Stylish bathrooms bring sophistication with black porcelain counters, dark wood vanity, slab tile to the ceiling and glass showers plus soaker tub.  One block from bustling Central Avenue or peaceful Pershing Field and Leonard Gordon Parks, this location brings the best of both worlds for urban living. Jersey City Heights offers eclectic essential shops, vibrant community, excellent schools and easy NYC access."
250025928,SOLD,"JC, Heights",184 CENTRAL AVE,Condominium,915,1597,"$592,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1A,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$592,000","$599,000",$646.99,$646.99,1/6/2026,2/2/2026,3/16/2026,27,27,,3/17/2026,,,,,,$304,,Conventional,,,,,,Reservoir and Booraem,"Perched above peaceful Pershing Field Park, this newly renovated residence brings a rare blend of modern indoor-outdoor living—this time, with a private backyard oasis. Brought to you by renowned local builder, this 2 bedroom, 2 bath home offers a front-row seat to parkside living, plus modern design and unbeatable location in Jersey City Heights.  A wall of floor-to-ceiling windows floods the park-facing living space with light and highlights the light oak hardwood floors. The kitchen is thoughtfully composed with sleek deep navy lower cabinets, white uppers, quartz counters and eat-in peninsula, herringbone tile, and stainless appliances.   Each bedroom offers double glass door access to the beautifully landscaped, fully fenced backyard complete with new pavers, offering a sanctuary away from city life. Bathrooms bring elegant extras—one with a soaking tub, the other with an oversized shower and a multi-spray system—plus tile finished to the ceiling, smart mirrors and sizable vanities keep things clean and contemporary.  Tucked on a tree-lined street in the heart of Jersey City Heights, this residence is moments from Central Ave shops, Reservoir #3, and Pershing Field Park, with nearby access to the 2nd Street Light Rail, PATH, and Hoboken ferry. It’s parkside living—rooted in comfort and curated with care."
210025661,SOLD,"JC, Heights",287 WEBSTER AVE,Condominium,1231,1691,"$592,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,3,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$592,000","$599,000",$480.91,$480.91,11/15/2021,12/3/2021,12/23/2021,18,18,,12/23/2021,,,,,,$250,,Cash,,,,,,Congress & South St.,"Now offering up to $10K in closing costs for buyers! Inquire for more details.   Stately and palatial on the outside, luminous and modern on the inside, this freshly refinished 3-unit building is perfectly positioned in Jersey City Heights just blocks to Central Avenue, Washington Park and Riverview Fisk Park. This spacious 2 bedroom 2 bathroom offers private storage and private roofdeck.   Interior elements like soaring 10' ceilings with exposed industrial elements combine with wide plank white maple flooring and large bay windows to create a design-lovers dream. Kitchens impress clean white custom cabinets with matte black hardware, sparkling white quartz counters and island, grey tile backsplash and eye-popping pendant lighting. Bathrooms wow with carrera marble tile from top to bottom, white floating vanities, shower niche and super sleek design. Oversized windows give impeccable natural light, while the large private backyard provides excellent outdoor escape.  Positioned in a sweet spot within Jersey City Heights, these homes are nestled into a tree lined street steps away from Congress Street Light Rail, 22-acre Washington Park, cityscape views of Riverview Fisk and a few local favorites like Fox & Crow and The Cliff.  "
220006773,SOLD,"JC, Heights",176 GRIFFITH ST,Condominium,1008,1526,"$594,500",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07307,2801,38,Heights,,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$594,500","$575,000",$589.78,$589.78,4/18/2022,4/29/2022,7/29/2022,11,10,,8/2/2022,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Central & Summit,"Picture yourself as you run up your stairs to your WOWWW!  New, never-lived in home, open layout, drenched with light, huge windows, high ceilings, skylights galore, decorative fireplace …Drop your baggage, saunder and zen out in your master bedroom that opens to a terrace overlooking serene, backyard canopied by overhanging branches of swaying leaves. Grab a glass. YOU. HAVE. ARRIVED! Tasteful design, modern finishes and appliances; smart layout giving way to bright, light and open space you call home! Soaring high ceilings, recessed lighting throughout, beautiful light hardwood floors, skylights, decorative fireplace, terrace, central A/C, energy efficient tankless water heater and in-unit washer/dryer.  UNBEATABLE location in the heart of much-sough-after thriving Heights District of Jersey City, a vibrant community of JC proud residents.  Central to all essentials and city amenities, near Pershing Field, Mosquito and Riverview Parks.  Bus service on Central, Summit, Kennedy and Palisade Ave nearby, and with easy access to Light Rail and PATH Stations."
250019025,SOLD,"JC, Heights",433 CENTRAL AVE,Condominium,857,6638,"$595,000",CONDO-COOP,,3rd,3B,"JC, Heights",07307,,,,The James,,,,2,0,1,5,,"$595,000","$595,000",$694.28,$694.28,9/15/2025,10/15/2025,12/8/2025,30,30,,12/12/2025,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Bleeker & South St,"Introducing The James, a boutique condominium of 6 designer residences in Jersey City Heights. Crafted by Hampton Hill and walkTHIShouse, these homes blend modern elegance with timeless detail and direct Manhattan skyline views.  Each residence offers private, keyless elevator entry, open-concept layouts, oversized windows, and wide-plank white oak floors. Kitchens are outfitted with quartz counters and premium stainless appliances, while spa-inspired baths feature matte black fixtures and porcelain tile. Smart home tech, including Swiftlane video intercom and keyless access, enhances daily convenience.  Amenities include a panoramic rooftop terrace, landscaped rear patio, bike storage, and a package room. Located steps from neighborhood shops, cafés, restaurants, and just minutes to the 9th Street Light Rail, The James delivers boutique luxury and effortless connectivity in one of Jersey City’s most vibrant communities. *Photos are of  similar model unit 3B*- Please reach out to our preferred lender Jackie koven at cross co mortgage for grant options from 15-22 k and interest rates at 5.875"
230004258,SOLD,"JC, Heights",3464 KENNEDY BLVD,Condominium,1006,1692,"$595,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,3C,"JC, Heights",07307,,,,,,,,2,0,1,4,,"$595,000","$595,000",$591.45,$591.45,3/16/2023,4/6/2023,8/25/2023,21,21,,8/30/2023,,,,$0,,$433,,Conventional,,,,,,Charles Street and Thorne Street,"A Historic Icon in The Heights.   The Packard JC was once the Packard Motor Car Company’s premiere showroom, which produced American luxury automobiles from 1899 through 1956. Today, The Packard JC has been revitalized into 14 new luxury condominiums while preserving the coveted Neo-Classical architectural details from its early 20th century past. Residential upgrades include Latch keyless entry system, Younity high speed internet, secure WiFi included in the maintenance, and a dedicated package room for every day convenience.   Residence 3C, 1,006 square foot two bedroom one bathroom has a stylish kitchen with stainless steel appliances, under-mount sinks, breakfast bars and leathered granite countertops with a waterfall edge.  Central AC, Navian on-demand tankless water heater and an in-unit washer-dryer ensure absolute comfort plus there’s a host of dramatic features including 12 ft ceilings, concrete beams, exposed ductwork and engineered hardwood herringbone flooring.   The Packard JC is an elevator building with a 5 year tax abatement available. Storage units may be available upon request.  This steel and concrete construction, loft-style building is located close to the bustling Central Avenue with restaurants, shopping, cafes and parks nearby.  Transportation is effortless; bus 125 at the corner and bus 119 to Port Authority/Congress Street Light Rail connecting you to NYC with easy links to the Journal Square transportation hub."
230011304,SOLD,"JC, Heights",360 PALISADE AVE,Condominium,1010,1597,"$595,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,3,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,2,1,2,5,,"$595,000","$599,000",$589.11,$589.11,7/7/2023,8/2/2023,9/15/2023,26,26,,9/15/2023,,,,,,$333,,Conventional,,,,,,Ferry St & Franklin St,"Built in 2020, this ground-up new construction two bedroom and two and a half bath home offers spacious interior & thoughtful upgrades! Stylish modern exterior gives way to classic design within, featuring light wood tile floors, neutral color palette and ceiling fans. Eat-in kitchen offers peninsula island with gleaming white quartz counters, tile backsplash, custom white cabinets and stainless appliances.   Large bedrooms offer plentiful closet space, while the back bedroom hosts double glass sliding doors to the private balcony. Bathrooms offer floor to ceiling tile, soaker tub and shower with sizable vanity and updated design. Home features dedicated laundry area for convenience.   Modern facade gives great curb apparel on this tree-lined street of one of The Heights most coveted streets. Home offers walkability to Riverview Fisk Park Jersey City is known for its vibrant community and close proximity to excellent schools, expansive parks and easy NYC access."
240011678,SOLD,"JC, Heights",71 NORTH ST,Condominium,1173,1653,"$595,000",CONDO-COOP,,5,503,"JC, Heights",07307,001602,0001,Heights,,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$595,000","$600,000",$507.25,$507.25,6/18/2024,6/28/2024,7/29/2024,10,10,,7/31/2024,,,,"$9,581",2022,$500,,Cash,,,,,,Corner of Cambridge and North Street,"Indulge in Urban Serenity! Elevate your lifestyle with this breathtaking top-floor sanctuary boasting 2 bedrooms, 2 bathrooms, and a generous 1130 square feet of blissful living space. Nestled directly across from the picturesque Washington Park in the thriving Heights neighborhood of Jersey City, this apartment is the epitome of modern urban living. The expansive open-concept living area, adorned with gleaming hardwood floors, effortlessly blends living and dining spaces, perfect for entertaining or unwinding in style. As the day winds down, retreat to your private balcony and soak in the breathtaking partial views of the iconic New York City skyline, while the lush greenery of Washington Park provides a serene backdrop, ensuring the privacy and tranquility you deserve in the heart of the city. The bright galley style kitchen features stainless steel appliances, granite countertops and herringbone backsplash. Embrace the vibrant energy of the neighborhood, where a plethora of activities awaits – from seasonal Farmers Markets to local fairs, eclectic dining experiences, vibrant nightlife, and abundant shopping options, all within arm's reach. Explore the charm of Central Avenue or hop on an express bus for a seamless journey into Manhattan. Commuting is a breeze with multiple bus routes conveniently located nearby, and the Congress St elevator granting swift access to the 9th Street light rail station in Hoboken, just a leisurely stroll away. Rarely does an opportunity arise to live in such an idyllic setting, offering unparalleled convenience and accessibility at an irresistible price point. Seize the moment and make this urban oasis your own!"
220012083,SOLD,"JC, Heights",185 COLUMBIA AVE,Condominium,1576,6078,"$595,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07307,01203,00051,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,6,,"$595,000","$599,000",$377.54,$377.54,7/2/2022,8/15/2022,9/29/2022,44,44,,9/29/2022,,,,"$11,882",,$199,,VA,,,,,,North & Bleecker,"NEW CONSTRUCTION! Welcome to 185 Columbia Ave, an exquisite brand new property constructed by Jersey City's one of the premier builders, where no detail has been spared. The house features stunning and unique façade with charcoal board & batten paneling combined with red brick siding, delivering modern yet traditional look to the property, sitting on a 25’x100’ lot.   The quintessential brand new 3 bedroom 2 bathroom condominium, offers extra large 1,576 square feet of open-concept living space, with state of the art Chef's Kitchen. This immaculate condominium features 9' ceilings, gorgeous 7 Amaro European White Oak hardwood flooring and oversized Anderson casement & picture windows, allowing abundant natural light throughout the day. The impeccable kitchen features white shaker cabinetry, luxury stainless steel Samsung appliances, and beautiful white subway tiles. The open concept living and dining space leads to a captivating approx. 95' of private terrace with unbeatable city views. The massive 13.6' X 13.5' master bedroom offers an ensuite spa-like bathroom, and an expansive walk-in closet. This magnificent condo with carefully considered floor plan that rivals Manhattan standard luxury, also provides large second bedroom, a dedicated Home Office space and a second bathroom featuring clean design, porcelain tiles, and a soaking tub. The encompassed approx. 413 SQFT. of private rooftop deck and outdoor space with stunning panoramic views is perfect for entertaining! This Home creates ease of living and efficiency through a central HVAC system regulated by Nest thermostat. This unit also comes fully equipped with Samsung washer and dryer.  185 Columbia is surrounded by tons of options for shopping, dining, entertaining, and transportation.  Located on a quiet tree-lined street in the highly sought-after Jersey City Heights section known as The Western Slope. Short distance from all transportation to NYC, buses, major highways, shopping, parks, restaurants and more! An ideal location for commuters!  Developer is offering a 10 year new home warranty, and has applied for a 5 year tax abatement. Lock in this property at an incredibly below market price today while the mortgage rates are still on the rise! "
220004808,SOLD,"JC, Heights",47 HANCOCK AVE,Condominium,975,6494,"$596,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,202,"JC, Heights",07307,03802,00015 01,Heights,The Baxter,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$596,000","$596,000",$611.28,$611.28,3/21/2022,4/7/2022,6/17/2022,17,17,,6/17/2022,,,,"$7,755",2021,$214,,Conventional,,,,,,Hutton & Griffith St,"Enjoy modern luxury living at The Baxter! This beautiful building was reconstructed by one of Jersey City's top developers. This 2 Bedroom, 2 Bath unit features a modern design and open floor plan, with bright white oak floors throughout and oversized windows with plentiful sunlight. Stylish, semi-custom kitchens with maple cabinets, Quartz countertops, large waterfall island, white vintage brick backsplash and high-end Dacor appliances. Designer bathrooms include Bella Royale mosaic and herringbone tiling paired with matte black and brass Delta fixtures. Located in the heart of The Heights, The Baxter is close to shopping, schools, parks and transportation to NYC."
260004435,ACTIVE,"JC, Heights",142 CHARLES ST,Condominium,1021,1713,"$599,000",CONDO-COOP,,4,403,"JC, Heights",07307,2603,51,Heights,,,,,2,0,2,6,,,"$599,000",$586.68,,3/13/2026,,,27,,,3/13/2026,,,,"$8,838",2026,$440,,,,,,,,Summit Ave. & JFK Boulevard,"Rare opportunity to own a piece of Heights history at The Packard Jersey City. This boutique collection of just 14 luxury condominiums is housed in a gorgeous converted Packard Motor Car Company showroom. This 1928 building offers a striking blend of modern finishes and preserved industrial character. The steel-and-concrete construction, loft-style building, delivers timeless architecture reimagined for contemporary living. Penthouse 3 is a thoughtfully designed, South facing, two-bedroom two-bath residence featuring an open layout and high-end finishes throughout. The kitchen is equipped with stainless steel appliances, under-mount sink, breakfast bar, and leathered granite waterfall countertop—ideal for everyday living and entertaining. Two outdoor spaces, both a private terrace off the primary bedroom and a larger terrace off the 2nd bedroom shared with four other penthouse units. Additional highlights include central air conditioning, Navien on-demand tankless water heater, in-unit washer-dryer, soaring 12-foot ceilings, exposed concrete beams, visible ductwork, and engineered herringbone hardwood flooring. Conveniently located in the center of everything Jersey City Heights has to offer, including restaurants, shopping, cafés, and parks. Easy access in 40 minutes to either midtown or downtown Manhattan."
250009504,SOLD,"JC, Heights",103 FERRY ST,Condominium,926,6176,"$599,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2L,"JC, Heights",07307,4401,16,Heights,,,,,2,0,2,6,,"$599,000","$599,000",$646.87,$646.87,5/14/2025,5/23/2025,5/27/2025,9,10,,7/10/2025,,,,"$10,066",2024,$204,Mo,Conventional,,,,,,Central Ave & Abbett St.,"Welcome to 103 Ferry St, Unit 2L - where modern design meets boutique-style living in the heart of Jersey City Heights. This chic and sun-drenched 2-bedroom, 2-bath condo is part of Le Navire, a fully renovated 4-unit building offering privacy, charm, and a truly elevated lifestyle. Located on the second floor, Unit 2L features soaring 12 ft. ceilings, custom oak flooring, oversized bay windows, and an open concept layout with no wasted square footage. The gourmet kitchen is equipped with Bosch stainless steel appliances, quartz countertops, double-stacked cabinetry, a breakfast bar, and designer lighting. Both bedrooms offer generous closet space, while the bathrooms boast custom tile work, frameless glass shower doors and modern vanities. Additional upgrades include in-unit laundry, tankless hot water heater, smart storage nooks, recessed lighting, Pella windows, hardwired Sonos sound system, and premium finishes throughout. The crown jewel of this home is the expansive 400+ sq ft private rooftop deck with jaw-dropping NYC skyline views and designated gas line - perfect for lounging, grilling or entertaining under the stars. Just one block from Pershing Field Park, and minutes to neighborhood favorites like Choc O Pain, Bread and Salt, and Busy Bee Organics, plus NYC transit access at your corner and available parking nearby. This is truly a rare opportunity to enjoy modern, low-maintenance living with all that Jersey City Heights has to offer."
210025050,SOLD,"JC, Heights",142 CHARLES ST,Condominium,996,1653,"$599,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,203,"JC, Heights",07307,2603,51,Heights,The Packard,,,,2,0,1,5,,"$599,000","$599,000",$601.41,$601.41,11/4/2021,2/7/2022,4/22/2022,95,95,,4/22/2022,,,,,,$372,,Conventional,,,,,,John F Kennedy & Summit Blvd,"This is a rare and sought-after opportunity to secure your very own slice of history in booming Jersey City Heights. The Packard JC boasts 14 new luxury condominiums that combine the very best in contemporary comfort with original details from this building’s industrial past.  Once the Packard Motor Car Company showroom, this steel and concrete construction, loft-style building is located close to the bustling Central Avenue with restaurants, shopping, cafes and parks nearby.  There is a selection of one and two-bedroom condos on offer that promise a life of elegance. Cooking will be a pleasure in the stylish kitchens with stainless steel appliances, under-mount sinks, breakfast bars and leathered granite countertops with a waterfall edge.  Central AC, Navian on-demand tankless water heaters and an in-unit washer-dryer ensure absolute comfort plus there’s a host of dramatic features including 12 ft ceilings, concrete beams, exposed ductwork and engineered hardwood herringbone flooring. Nearby buses connect you to NYC with easy links to the Journal Square transportation hub."
260005531,ACTIVE,"JC, Heights",85 OAKLAND AVE,Condominium,1200,1526,"$599,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07306,5702,15,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,6,,,"$599,000",$499.17,,3/29/2026,,,11,,,3/30/2026,,"$360,700",2024,"$8,105",2023,$0,,,No,No,No,,,Ferry and Hwy 139,"Lovely 1200 + ft 3 bedroom 2 full bath 2nd floor condo with backyard just in time for your summer entertaining, 2 blocks to Journal Square Path Train and all JC's Journal Square has to offer! New whole foods and additional Path entrance with all the restaurants and shoppes opening now. Perfect time to settle in to NJ award winning school district. This unit has hardwood floors & all new style lighting."
240007297,SOLD,"JC, Heights",933A SUMMIT AVE,Condominium,1327,1724,"$599,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,3,"JC, Heights",07307,3601,44,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,6,,"$599,000","$599,000",$451.39,$451.39,4/19/2024,5/28/2024,7/24/2024,39,39,,7/25/2024,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,ZABRISKIE & HUTTON,"Welcome to this stunning 3-bedroom, 2-bathroom residence in Jersey City Heights. Bathed in natural light, the spacious living area cultivates a cozy and inviting atmosphere perfect for relaxation or hosting guests.  The kitchen boasts stainless steel appliances and generous counter space, ideal for culinary adventures. Whether you're hosting a gathering or enjoying a quiet meal, this kitchen will surely ignite your culinary imagination.  Complete with a washer and dryer conveniently tucked away in the unit, laundry day becomes effortless, providing unparalleled convenience.  Nestled in a highly sought-after locale, this unit offers more than just a place to reside—it offers a lifestyle. With effortless access to shopping, dining, and entertainment options, everything you desire is within reach."
210024220,SOLD,"JC, Heights",99 SHERMAN PL,Condominium,1200,1691,"$599,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1,"JC, Heights",07307,3603,7,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,6,,"$599,000","$599,000",$499.17,$499.17,10/22/2021,1/14/2022,3/25/2022,84,84,,3/25/2022,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Summit Ave & Sanford Pl,"Classic elegance and grandeur extend through these beautifully re-constructed condominiums in one of the sweetest spots of Jersey City Heights. The garden-level floor-through condo offers thoughtful three-bedroom layout with two full bath and timeless finishes, bringing a modern edge to an ideally located space with open floorplan. Kitchen opens to oversized living and dining area with classic shaker cabinets and subway backsplash plus modern fixtures and stainless appliances.  The stylish street view shows beautiful dark grey siding and classic white gable cornice settled into the tree-lined residential street. Sherman Place is walking distance to Central Avenue with essential shops and vibrant community, as well as Riverview Fisk Park with sports facilities, play areas, walking paths and excellent NYC skyline vistas."
210009555,SOLD,"JC, Heights",22 LINCOLN ST,Condominium,,1691,"$599,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,6,,"$599,000","$599,000",,,4/22/2021,4/29/2021,6/9/2021,7,7,,6/10/2021,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Summit and Central,"Say hello to thoughtful modern luxury in the Heights. This beautifully renovated floor-through 3 bedroom 2 bath condominium brings elegance and sophistication to a quiet tree-lined street just off Central Avenue.  Simple, clean design delights upon entry with bright, open floor plan.  Contemporary kitchens impress with custom charcoal grey lower cabinets, clean white uppers and marbled quartz counters. Bathrooms bring interest and enviable design with elements such as floating custom vanities, pocket doors, oversized slab tile and complementary brass and black fixtures.  Master en-suite boasts sliding French doors leading to private balcony (perfect for al fresco coffee or cocktails).   Part of a completely renovated 3-unit building, all three homes offer ideal walkability to surrounding Central & Palisade Avenue for all essential shopping needs, plus Pershing Field, Washington or Riverview Fisk Parks. The Heights is a thriving community with excellent schools, award-winning restaurants & businesses plus easy NYC access!   Rental parking available nearby!!"
220017532,SOLD,"JC, Heights",3568 KENNEDY BLVD,Condominium,1030,6199,"$599,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,4,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,2,0,2,4,,"$599,000","$599,000",$581.55,$581.55,9/30/2022,11/28/2022,1/13/2023,59,59,,1/13/2023,,,,,,$164,,Conventional,No,No,Yes,,,Graham & Congress,"SPECIAL LOW INTEREST RATE FROM MID 5%’s PROGRAM AVAILABLE, NO PMI, LOW DOWNPAYMENT, SAVING THOUSANDS OF DOLLARS: Part of census tract mortgage program which features below market interest rate with 30 year fix option from mid 4%’s.  Featuring Another Signature Luxury brand new Construction by Blue Chip Living from the pages of Architectural Digest to the heart of booming Jersey City Heights, a business district, residential area, and transportation hub. Open your private entry door to this captivating condo featuring 2 bedrooms, 2 bathroom, with private Roof Deck, open concept living space with LED electric fireplace and oversized wrap around windows that flood the space with natural light. The chef’s kitchen boasts impeccable white high-gloss European Style cabinetry, stainless steel premium smart appliances, modern porcelain backsplash, central island with a waterfall quartz, pot filler, pendant lighting, and drawer microwave. The 2 bedrooms share a spa–like bathroom with matte black hardware, luxurious vanity. This unit has access to a large picturesque private yard. Other perks include West Elm lighting, laundry room hook ups, central/heat/air, 8’ solid-core doors & designated storage area. Full smart home technology creates ease of living with ButterflyMX Video Intercom System, Nest thermostat, Smart Lighting Dimmer Switches accessible via smart phone. Private Storage Are included. All major transportation at your fingertips. Make this your Dream Home Oasis today! Maintenance includes cold water, sewer, snow removal, trash removal, common area utilities.  *Eligible for 5 year tax abatement."
210017130,SOLD,"JC, Heights",99 BEACON AVE,Condominium,0,1691,"$599,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1,"JC, Heights",07307,,,,,,,,3,0,2,6,,"$599,000","$599,000",,,7/16/2021,8/3/2021,12/8/2021,18,18,,12/10/2021,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Oakland and Central,"Gorgeous ground-floor walk up beams with natural light and luxury finishes in Jersey City Heights. The new construction 3-bedroom and 2-bath home offers a secure entrance and breathtaking modern glass-front building.   Inside, the stunning 5-panel wall of windows illuminates the rich hardwood floors, neutral palette and classic crown molding throughout. Kitchen showcases seamless style with custom stained cabinets, gleaming white quartz counters, polished linear glass tile backsplash, stainless Frigidaire appliances, and glass pendant lighting accents.  Traditional layout leads to large bedrooms with central air and plenty of closet space, while bathrooms bring floor to ceiling tile, medicine cabinet mirrors for added storage, plus glass shower in the master bathroom, or soaker tub and shower combo in shared bathroom. Owners enjoy the separate laundry / utility room for ultimate convenience.  Ideally located on an excellent corner of The Heights, just one block from Central Avenue and walkable to Journal Square PATH plus Pershing Field Park and Reservoir."
