250007357,SOLD,"JC, Heights",116 OGDEN AVE,Condominium,1150,5010,"$600,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2A,"JC, Heights",07307,5202,18,Heights,,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$600,000","$600,000",$521.74,$521.74,4/15/2025,5/1/2025,6/30/2025,16,16,,6/30/2025,,,,"$11,592",2023,$662,2023,Conventional,No,No,No,,,Cuneo Pl & Wood Pl,"2-Bedroom Condo with City Views in Jersey City Heights   Located on one of the most desirable streets in Jersey City Heights, this 2-bedroom, 2-bathroom condo offers a fantastic opportunity with gorgeous city views. With its prime location just steps from local parks and conveniences, this condo has amazing potential for the right buyer.   Key Features: City Views: Enjoy stunning city views right from your living room, offering an ideal backdrop to urban life in Jersey City.   Location, Location, Location: Steps from a community park and dog park, this condo is situated on the most sought-after street of Jersey City Heights. Whether you're walking your dog or relaxing outdoors, you'll love the nearby green spaces and access to all the Heights has to offer.   Convenient Living: Just a short walk from Palisade Avenue, you'll have easy access to a variety of restaurants, shops, and local amenities. The area offers a true blend of urban convenience and neighborhood charm.   Commuter-Friendly: Perfect for NYC commuters, with public transportation options just a few blocks away, making the city easily accessible while still enjoying the perks of Jersey City living.   Additional Highlights: Spacious Layout: With two bedrooms and two bathrooms, this condo offers space to create a comfortable home. The master bedroom includes an ensuite bath, offering privacy and convenience.   Potential for Personal Touch: The condo is ready for your vision. Whether you're looking to renovate or simply update certain areas, there’s plenty of potential to make this space truly your own.   Great Community: Jersey City Heights is known for its welcoming community, with plenty of neighborhood events, parks, and local shops to explore.   An Opportunity Not to Miss This is your chance to secure a well-located condo in Jersey City Heights. With its incredible views and proximity to parks and transportation, it's a great canvas for someone looking to add their personal touch. If you're seeking a property with potential in a fantastic location, this condo is worth a look."
250001292,SOLD,"JC, Heights",179 LINCOLN ST,Condominium,1374,1597,"$600,000",CONDO-COOP,,2&3,2,"JC, Heights",07307,2504,19,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,8,,"$600,000","$625,000",$436.68,$436.68,1/20/2025,1/31/2025,2/25/2025,11,11,,2/25/2025,,,,"$5,930",2024,$200,,Cash,No,No,,,,Terrace & Liberty,"This North & South facing 1,374sf 3 bedroom, 2 bathroom condominium is flooded with natural light featuring high ceilings, hardwood floors, in-unit laundry room, central A/C and plentiful storage. The first level private entryway leads upstairs to the impressively spacious open concept living area with vaulted ceilings, skylights and balcony. The kitchen features custom cabinetry, stainless steel appliances, vented stove exhaust, sink disposal & wine fridge overlooking the dedicated dining area. The identical first and second bedrooms are perfect for guests or a spacious work from home setup. Across the hall is a beautifully tiled guest bathroom with bathtub and a laundry room with storage. The primary suite features a massive California king bedroom with two walk-in closets and en-suite bathroom with walk-in rainfall shower. Perched on a quiet block of the Western Slope in The Heights, this home offers walkability to both Leonard Gordon and Pershing Field Parks, the recently renovated Reservoir, restaurants and shops along Kennedy Blvd, easy access to bus service to PATH & NYC and immediate access to major highways."
