250006823,SOLD,"JC, Heights",360 PALISADE AVE,Condominium,1000,6451,"$600,000",CONDO-COOP,,4,4A,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,2,1,2,5,,"$600,000","$599,000",$600.00,$600.00,4/8/2025,5/6/2025,6/27/2025,28,28,,7/9/2025,,,,"$10,957",2024,$338,,Conventional,,,,,,Franklin and Ferry,"Welcome to contemporary living at its finest in the heart of Jersey City! This stunning, fully renovated condo at 360 Palisade Ave offers a perfect blend of modern design and comfortable living. Spanning 1,000 square feet, this spacious residence features 2 bedrooms and 2.5 bathrooms.  Upon entering, you're greeted by an open-concept space accentuated by oversized dual pane windows that bathe the home in natural light from both northern and eastern exposures. The expansive hardwood floors and recessed lighting create a warm and inviting atmosphere throughout.  The gourmet kitchen is a chef's dream, boasting stainless steel appliances, a gas stove, dishwasher, and a large island that doubles as a perfect spot for casual dining. The primary ensuite bathroom offers a luxurious retreat with marble finishes and an attached full bathroom for convenience.  Step outside to your private balcony, an ideal space for relaxation or entertaining. The unit is equipped with central heating and cooling for year-round comfort, and the convenience of an in-unit washer and dryer adds to the appeal.  Security is top-notch with an intercom and video intercom system, and the walk-up building style ensures a sense of privacy and exclusivity. This condo is a true gem, offering a contemporary lifestyle with all the modern amenities you desire. Don’t miss the opportunity to make this exceptional residence your new home! "
220013294,SOLD,"JC, Heights",11 JEFFERSON AVE,Condominium,1008,1713,"$600,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,3,"JC, Heights",07306,05902,00016,,,,,,2,0,1,5,,"$600,000","$575,000",$595.24,$595.24,7/21/2022,8/9/2022,9/15/2022,19,19,,9/16/2022,,,,"$7,442",,$232,,Conventional,,,,,,Baldwin Ave & Palisade Ave,"Bright and beautiful newly renovated 2 bed 1 bath condo in a great Jersey City Heights location. This stylish home features white oak hardwood floors, Anderson windows,  exposed brick with a fireplace, Nest thermostat , custom made cabinetry, quartz countertops, stainless steel appliances, and imported Italian tile in the bathroom. It also includes high ceilings, and a stunning architecturally designed staircase and huge roof deck with amazing NYC views. All this and a storage unit in the basement which could also be used as a home gym! Close to Palisade Ave  buses for easy commuting and walking distance to Path. Great restaurants, bars and shops nearby."
230010089,SOLD,"JC, Heights",684 SUMMIT AVE,Condominium,1653,1653,"$600,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,2,"JC, Heights",07306,5603,67,Heights,,,,,3,0,3,7,,"$600,000","$599,000",$362.98,$362.98,6/17/2023,7/3/2023,8/29/2023,16,16,,8/29/2023,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Hopkins & Beacon,"Welcome to Summit Lodge, a meticulously curated condominium building in the Jersey City heights. With its classically ornamental brick facade exterior, 684 Summit Avenue imparts a completely reimagined contemporary design on the interior to create harmonious, lavish, condominiums. Every square-inch of the property has been intricately designed with the end-user in mind. The lower-level duplex units each will consist of roughly 1600 sqft of living space, spanning across 2 solid oak hardwood floors and boasting 3 bedrooms and 3 baths leading to a private backyard space. This unit will come with a custom chef’s kitchen, including designer quartz countertops, Porcelanosa tile and fixtures, Nest thermostats, central air, a Ring Doorbell Intercom, vibrant LED lighting throughout the entire space, and more! The ground level of this unit will also possess a separate entrance and a kitchenette, creating a private and functional space for extended family or guests. Additionally, all units have been upgraded with new plumbing, a new electrical system, and fire protection as well as top of the line sound proofing. The developer spared no costs to sound proof all the units in this building. This includes using open cell foam insulation, QuietWalk floor underlayment, and QuietRock ceiling panels between the floors to dampen the sound. Additionally, using sound clips and sound channels enabled to provide an unmatched level of peace and privacy. Topping this off, the property is located one block away from Highway 139, where you can access many northbound major highways such as Route 3 and Route 1 & 9 or maybe head southbound towards Pulaski Skyway or Route 440. The building is also only 6 minutes away from the Holland Tunnel via driving, and 13 minutes walking distance to the Journal Square PATH station, making travel to and from Manhattan incredibly easy. Other perks include a plethora of options for restaurants and entertainment for all ages, being that this property is located so close to both Downtown Jersey City and the Journal Square section of Jersey City while having the residential neighborhood feeling of the Jersey City Heights. This property’s location will cater to your every need. Schedule a viewing today!"
230000006,SOLD,"JC, Heights",20 RESERVOIR AVE,Condominium,1200,6078,"$600,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,3,"JC, Heights",07307,5005,30,,,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$600,000","$579,000",$500.00,$500.00,1/3/2023,1/26/2023,3/1/2023,23,23,,3/2/2023,,,,"$8,109",2022,$259,,Conventional,,,,,,Webster & Palisade,"Bright and sunny Jersey City Heights 2 bedroom condo inside a converted 1879 Queen Anne Victorian mansion.  Located 1/2 block from Palisade Avenue and the NYC bus stop.  Hoboken, the 2nd Street Light Rail, and the Supremo SuperMarket are within walking distance as well. Off-street parking spot included!  1200 sq. ft. of living space includes an eat-in kitchen, large living room and a terrific master bedroom with a walk-in closet and en suite bathroom.  Central A/C and laundry inside.  Extra storage downstairs and shared outdoor space.  Low HOA payment.  This one checks all of the boxes!  Schedule your tour today!  "
230008758,SOLD,"JC, Heights",152 BEACH ST,Condominium,1699,1597,"$600,000",CONDO-COOP,,1-2,1,"JC, Heights",07307,04201,00036,,,,,,3,1,2,8,,"$600,000","$640,000",$353.15,$353.15,5/30/2023,7/13/2023,8/4/2023,44,44,,8/5/2023,,,,"$9,961",2023,$165,,Cash,,,,,,Liberty & Tonnelle,"Expansive 3 bedroom, 2.5 bathroom duplex condominium with private backyard now available in Jersey City Heights.  This nearly new home was developed less than five years ago and is in pristine condition.  The chef’s kitchen is designed with beautiful modern quartz countertops, custom wood cabinetry, and stainless steel appliances. Bathrooms are equipped with modern vanities and Spanish/Italian Tiles. All three bedrooms are generously proportioned with large custom-built closets.  Additional features include 4” Red Oak hardwood floors, an abundance of storage space, a Juliet balcony in the living room that allows in natural light, central a/c and heat, and in-unit washer & dryer.  A tandem garage parking spot is included as well as several storage spaces within the garage.  Ideally located on a peaceful tree-lined street, this home is near the historic Leonard Gordon and Pershing Field Parks, local shops and restaurants, and provides easy commuting with nearby access to the 1&9, expressways and the Holland Tunnel."
220021583,SOLD,"JC, Heights",159 LIBERTY AVE,Condominium,1550,1603,"$600,000",CONDO-COOP,,"G,1,2",1,"JC, Heights",07306,05304,00020,Heights,,,,,2,1,2,4,,"$600,000","$599,000",$387.10,$387.10,12/16/2022,1/6/2023,3/9/2023,21,21,,3/11/2023,,,,$0,,$0,,Conventional,No,No,No,,,Spruce St and Stagg St,"Absolutely stunning ground-up new construction home, developed by Jersey City's highly reputable developers, GN Management. 159 Liberty Avenue is located on a dead end, private street on the Western Slope of Jersey City Heights. This 1550 sf open floor plan, three-story home includes 2 bedrooms, 2.5 bathrooms, a massive ground level with additional living space and front and rear entrances into your new home. Home features include white oak hardwood flooring through out, soaring 10' ceilings, 9' solid wood doors with black channels, oversized windows allowing for an abundant of natural lighting, central a/c, washer/dryer, recessed and custom lighting and sleek horizontal black railings. Amazing all white kitchen with breakfast island, slow closing shaker cabinetry, Quartz countertops, backsplash, stainless steel appliances and pot filler. Stunning baths with designer fittings and finishes including LED mirror lighting and glass enclosed showers. Master bedroom includes an ensuite and a large terrace with sunset views. 1 car parking included! This smart home includes built-in audio speakers, smart mirrors and ring doorbell. Located close to Rt 1&9, NJ Turnpike, Holland Tunnel, PATH train and the 125 bus to Port Authority; commuting has never been easier! Only a few short blocks from Pershing Field Park and the Central Ave shopping district as well as JSQ path and shopping district. A neighborhood that needs no introduction, Jersey City Heights has become one of Hudson County's most desirable places to live. 159 Liberty Ave includes a 10-year new home warranty and is eligible for 5-year tax abatement!"
210022612,SOLD,"JC, Heights",13 SHERMAN PL,Condominium,1265,1673,"$600,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,202,"JC, Heights",07307,03701,00029,Heights,King Edward Condominium,,,,2,0,2,6,,"$600,000","$615,000",$474.31,$474.31,9/29/2021,12/2/2021,12/31/2021,64,64,,2/3/2022,,,,"$7,816",2021,$337,2021,Conventional,No,No,,,,Central Ave. & Summit Ave.,"Your chance to own a Jersey City Heights Gem has just arrived! Nestled on the tree lined street of Sherman Pl., this 2 bedroom 2 bath condo is a one of a kind. Built in 2015, this condo has everything you need. Plenty of closet space, eat in kitchen, washer/dryer room, terrace and parking! Central Ave., is just around the corner with plenty of shopping and transportation to NYC."
220003066,SOLD,"JC, Heights",35 MANHATTAN AVE,Condominium,1350,1419,"$600,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1,"JC, Heights",07307,04402,00013,Heights,,,,,3,0,3,8,,"$600,000","$649,000",$444.44,$444.44,2/22/2022,4/25/2022,6/9/2022,62,62,,6/19/2022,,,,,,$384,2022,Conventional,,,,,,Ferry St. & Franklin St.,"Another gem reveals itself in the Jersey City Heights! There was no detail spared within these luxury units considering the 10 ft ceilings, outdoor space, high end appliances, vibrant LED lighting, and Pella windows throughout. This building was completely and meticulously gut renovated and upgraded with new plumbing and electric systems, a central sprinkler system, and fire protection. Your home will be equipped with central air, managed by Nest thermostats, a pair of pre-wired speakers in each room, high-end RING intercoms, operated from your phone, and in-unit washer/dryers! Offering custom-made chef's kitchens with designer quartz countertops, Bosch stoves, high-end Bosch appliances, and wide plank oak hardwood floorings makes this unit irresistible! The developer spared no cost on noise reduction and used sounds channels, sound clips, foam insulation, Rockwool, and SounFX sheetrock to keep your noise in and their noise out. Details aside being located in this Jersey City Heights neighborhood leaves you less than 100 feet from the Central Ave Shopping district and nearest bus stops to the PATH and NYC. There are an abundance of surrounding eateries including Pier 13, The Hutton Bar & Grill, Rumba’s Cafe, and two of the highest-rated locations, Dulce de Leche Bakery and Pampita Butcher Shop!"
230001438,SOLD,"JC, Heights",33 WAVERLY ST,Condominium,860,5678,"$600,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,Apt PH,"JC, Heights",07306,05803,00006,,,,,,2,0,2,7,,"$600,000","$600,000",$697.67,$697.67,1/25/2023,2/22/2023,4/7/2023,28,28,,4/7/2023,,,,"$9,588",,$285,,Conventional,No,No,,,,Baldwin Ave and Palisades,"Stunning PENTHOUSE TWO bedroom, TWO bathroom condo with over 650 SQ Ft of private outdoor space including a lower level Ipe deck off the living room and a rooftop terrace with NYC views! This south-facing residence is part of a newer reconstructed boutique building on a quiet tree-lined street in The Heights. High-end features include wide plank white oak floors, SS appliances, custom cabinetry, exposed brick walls, and central AC/Heat. Additional features include an open floor plan, spacious bedrooms, and an in-unit washer/dryer. Step out from the living room to your private outdoor space plus a rooftop with 360-degree views of Midtown/Hudson Yards, WTC, and the JS Skyline. High Walk Score and near all major amenities, groceries, and fantastic dining options on Palisade and Central Ave; Lo-Fi, The Franklin, Bread and Salt, and the farmer's market at Riverview-Fisk Park! Three parks within close walking distance (Pershing Field and the newly restored Reservoir, Riverview-Fisk Park, Leonard Gordon Park). Easy commute to NYC via JSQ Path, light rail, or buses just a short distance away.  HOA fees of $285 includes:  Water, trash & recycling pick-up, snow removal, and twice-a-month lobby/stairwell cleaning."
220000335,SOLD,"JC, Heights",99 BEACON AVE,Condominium,1245,1691,"$605,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,3,"JC, Heights",07307,,,,,,,,3,0,2,6,,"$605,000","$599,000",$485.94,$485.94,1/6/2022,1/13/2022,3/1/2022,7,7,,3/4/2022,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Oakland and Central,"Stylish new home shines with natural light and luxury finishes in Jersey City Heights. The newly refinished 3-bedroom and 2-bath condo offers a secure entrance and breathtaking modern glass-front building.  Inside, the stunning 5-panel wall of windows illuminates the rich hardwood floors, tray ceilings, neutral palette and classic crown molding throughout. Kitchen showcases seamless style with custom stained cabinets, gleaming white quartz counters, polished linear glass tile backsplash, stainless Frigidaire appliances, and glass pendant lighting accents. Open floorplan expands even further with an additional dining alcove ideal for entertaining or additional living space.  Traditional layout leads to large bedrooms with central air and plenty of closet space, while bathrooms bring floor to ceiling tile, medicine cabinet mirrors for added storage, plus glass shower in the master bathroom, or soaker tub and shower combo in shared bathroom. Owners enjoy the separate laundry / utility room for ultimate convenience.  Ideally located on an excellent corner of The Heights, just one block from Central Avenue and walkable to Journal Square PATH plus Pershing Field Park and Reservoir, this home is poised with potential for the ultimate urban living."
210009183,SOLD,"JC, Heights",341 NEW YORK AVE,Condominium,977,1673,"$606,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07307,2306,35,Heights,,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$606,000","$579,000",$620.27,$620.27,4/18/2021,4/28/2021,6/8/2021,10,10,,6/11/2021,,,,$0,,$300,,Conventional,,,,,,Bowers & South St.,"Just what you've been looking for! A gorgeous newly renovated 2 bed, 2 bath condo in the buzzing Jersey City Heights. Private porch, Close to shopping, transportation, and NYC. Look no further now that you can finally park not just one vehicle, but two- in your deeded driveway. Contact us today for a private showing!"
220020728,SOLD,"JC, Heights",210 CAMBRIDGE AVE,Condominium,1161,1597,"$610,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2A,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,6,,"$610,000","$625,000",$525.41,$525.41,11/28/2022,12/23/2022,2/23/2023,25,24,,2/24/2023,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Congress & South St,"Step on into this luxurious and newly refinished parisian-style three bedroom and two bath home in Jersey City Heights. Stunning Haussmann architecture exterior shines with stone walls, square roof, wrought iron Juliet balconies and dormer windows.   Classic elegance stretches throughout with gleaming hardwood floors, crown molding, ceiling fans and oversized windows. Open floorplan living is great for entertaining, plus eat-in kitchen offers oversized island with pendant lighting, quartz counters, cherry custom cabinets, tile backsplash and stainless appliances.   Spacious bedrooms bring plenty of natural light with primary ensuite offering extra large walk-in closet. Bathrooms offer both bathtub and shower with sizable vanity and medicine cabinet mirror for additional storage.   One block from both Washington Park and Central Avenue, this home is situated for ideal access to both urban and outdoor living. Jersey City Heights is the fastest growing part of this eclectic community, offering boutique shops and restaurants, expansive parks, excellent schools and easy access to NYC and surrounding neighborhoods."
