240020102,SOLD,"JC, Heights",116 HUTTON ST,Condominium,850,6078,"$610,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07307,3703,36,,,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$610,000","$625,000",$717.65,$717.65,10/11/2024,12/18/2024,2/18/2025,68,68,,2/19/2025,,,,"$12,583",,$155,,Conventional,,,,,,Sherman Place & Zabriski Street,"Discover this beautifully renovated 2 bedroom, 2 bath condo with a private, professionally installed roof deck offering stunning NYC skyline views. Located just off Central Ave in the desirable JC Heights, this building was fully renovated less than 4 years ago. The sunlit, south-facing living room offers abundant natural light, creating a warm and welcoming atmosphere throughout the day. The chef’s kitchen is a standout, complete with white quartz countertops, high-end stainless steel appliances, and a vented hood. The kitchen opens to a dining area perfect for hosting. The private roof deck is an outdoor oasis with a custom cabana for shade and privacy. Smart home technology is integrated throughout, controlling lights, locks, window shades, and thermostat. Both bedrooms are spacious with ample closet space, and the primary suite offers a luxurious ensuite bath with modern finishes and a floating vanity. Central A/C, LED lighting, and hardwood floors. Low HOA charges with a self-managed HOA. Easy access to NYC transportation via bus or walk to light rail. Steps to the best restaurants and shops."
250002211,SOLD,"JC, Heights",207 OGDEN AVE,Condominium,890,1597,"$612,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,Unit 5 (3R),"JC, Heights",07307,3903,71,,,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$612,000","$599,000",$687.64,$687.64,2/3/2025,3/20/2025,5/16/2025,45,45,,5/19/2025,,,,"$10,491",2023,$339,,Conventional,,,,,,Franklin & Griffith,"Welcome to your future home at 207 Ogden Ave #3R.   A delightful top-floor condo nestled on one of Jersey City Heights' most coveted tree-lined streets. This charming residence offers two spacious bedrooms and two full baths, situated on opposite ends and perfectly with 890 square feet of thoughtfully designed space. Step into a beautifully renovated pre-war building, where modern comforts blend seamlessly with historic charm. Central air conditioning and in-unit washer and dryer add a convenience often sought but seldom found in historic buildings. Access your private locked storage unit in the basement, perfect for extra space. Enjoy the shared backyard with a grill for outdoor cooking. Enjoy the short walk to Hoboken via the 100 Steps, easy access to the 2nd Street Light Rail, leading to Hoboken, Downtown Jersey City, and NYC. Nearby, explore the best shopping, dining spots like LoFi, Choc o Pain, and Mod Cup, as well as art galleries, parks, and farmers markets. Rental parking is available nearby, and the property is pet-friendly. The neighborhood has a vibrant community atmosphere."
240007859,SOLD,"JC, Heights",3464 KENNEDY BLVD,Condominium,1073,1692,"$615,000",CONDO-COOP,,PH,PH6,"JC, Heights",07307,,,,The Packard,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$615,000","$649,000",$573.16,$573.16,4/28/2024,5/6/2024,6/28/2024,8,8,,9/23/2024,,,,$0,,$461,,Conventional,,,,,,Charles Street and Thorne Street,"A Historic Icon in The Heights. The Packard JC was once the Packard Motor Car Company’s premiere showroom, which produced American luxury automobiles from 1899 through 1956.   Today, The Packard JC has been revitalized into 14 new luxury condominiums while preserving the coveted Neo-Classical architectural details from its early 20th century past. Residential upgrades include Latch keyless entry system, Younity* high speed internet, secure WiFi included in the maintenance, and a dedicated package room for every day convenience. PH6, 1,073 square foot duplex two bedroom two bathroom has a stylish kitchen with stainless steel appliances, under-mount sinks, breakfast bars and leathered granite countertops with a waterfall edge. Central AC, Navian on-demand tankless water heater and an in-unit washer-dryer ensure absolute comfort plus there’s a host of dramatic features including 12 ft ceilings, concrete beams, exposed ductwork and engineered hardwood herringbone flooring. This residence also features a 79 square foot private terrace off the primary bedroom and additional storage space for your everyday needs.   The Packard JC is an elevator building with a 5 year tax abatement available. Storage units may be available upon request. This steel and concrete construction, loft-style building is located close to the bustling Central Avenue with restaurants, shopping, cafes and parks nearby. Transportation is effortless; bus 125 at the corner and bus 119 to Port Authority/Congress Street Light Rail connecting you to NYC with easy links to the Journal Square transportation hub. *Younity is not only high speed internet but it is the most economical, prewired highest speed internet available in a residential building, at a cost that is lower than the major carriers, while offering 24/7 customer support. Younity is pre-existing and available upon move-in for all residences.    "
230004409,SOLD,"JC, Heights",236 PALISADE AVE,Condominium,1160,1653,"$615,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,3,"JC, Heights",07306,6001,15,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,6,,"$615,000","$615,000",$530.17,$530.17,3/20/2023,3/20/2023,5/10/2023,0,0,,5/12/2023,,,,,,$252,,Conventional,,,,,,Prospect St. & Waverly St.,"Welcome home to this spacious 1,160 sq.ft. duplex condo with stunning views of Hoboken and NYC. With three bedrooms and two bathrooms, this brand new, fully renovated condo offers plenty of space to satisfy all your lifestyle needs.  The kitchen is stylish and spacious, with ample cabinetry, stainless steel appliances, and Calcutta quartz countertops. It flows seamlessly into the open-plan living/dining area, filled with natural light. You'll also find three bedrooms, one of which is an expansive primary bedroom with en-suite bathroom. There is also a second bathroom to service the other two bedrooms. Other key features of the home include central heat/AC, hardwood floors throughout & in-unit washer dryer.  Located on prime Palisade Avenue, this building is a few blocks away from Pershing Field Park & 2nd Street Light Rail, not to mention the multitude of local shops, restaurants, cafes, parks and all the conveniences of a vibrant neighborhood. All this while still having easy access to the city via public transit or car. Parking is available nearby at an additional cost."
220019112,SOLD,"JC, Heights",111 COLLARD ST,Condominium,1260,1598,"$615,000",CONDO-COOP,,1&2,3,"JC, Heights",07306,04701,00009,,111 Collard St Condos,,,,3,1,2,8,,"$615,000","$635,000",$488.10,$488.10,10/27/2022,1/10/2023,2/13/2023,75,74,,2/14/2023,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Kennedy Blvd & Spruce St,"Welcome to the spectacular brand new construction condos at 111 Collard St. 111 Collard Street offers 4 unique duplexes - residences 1 & 2 feature 2 bedrooms + den and 2 bathrooms duplexes with a small outdoor space. Residences 3 & 4 feature 3 bedrooms and 2.5 bathrooms with 2 private roof decks for each condo that offer beautiful panoramic NYC views. Each duplex offers central heating/cooling, beautiful oak flooring with sleek contemporary railings, designer kitchens equipped with custom white shaker cabinets , Carrera quartz countertops, Samsung stainless steel appliance package includes a 5 burner range, french door refrigerator, dishwasher & microwave oven. Enjoy movies & entertaining in your living room with built-in surround sound ceiling speakers, recessed lighting, Andersen  windows, Washer/dryer and more. Generous bedrooms and beautiful bathrooms. These condos are also integrated with the latest smart technology including touch screen security system, outdoor security cameras, smart video intercom system and sprinkler system. Across the street from Franklin Williams Middle School, next to PershingFields Park & Playground.  A block away from JFK and bus to/from NYC and short distance to JSQ PATH."
220003825,SOLD,"JC, Heights",103 FERRY ST,Condominium,1535,1419,"$615,000",CONDO-COOP,,G & 1,1R,"JC, Heights",07307,04401,00016,Heights,Le Navire,,,,4,0,2,8,,"$615,000","$599,000",$400.65,$400.65,3/4/2022,3/17/2022,5/26/2022,13,13,,6/13/2022,,,,,,$356,,Conventional,,,,,,Central Ave & Abbett St,"Welcome to Le Navire on Ferry St. in The Jersey City Heights! These immaculate homes are less than 100 feet from the Central Ave Shopping district and the nearest bus stops to the PATH and NYC. There are various eateries in the area like Cocoa Bakery, Rumba’s Cafe, The Franklin, and some of the highest-rated locations including the famous Dulce de Leche Bakery and Pampita Butcher Shop! The options are endless when you reside at The Navire on Ferry St. This home is approximately 1,535 sf, comprised of 4 bedrooms and 2 full bathrooms. What makes this duplex even better is that there are two separate entrances to give each floor additional privacy and functionality which enables it to be used for extended family or guests! The unit boasts 10ft ceilings, solid oak hardwood flooring, Pella windows, and vibrant LED lighting throughout.This beautiful home offers custom-made chef's kitchens with designer quartz countertops, Bosch stoves, high-end Bosch appliances, and extra storage above your kitchen cabinets. Not only is it equipped with central air, managed by Nest thermostats, high-end RING intercoms, and an in-unit washer/dryer, there is a pair of pre-wired speakers in each room that are operated from your phone! The seller spared no cost on noise reduction by incorporating foam insulation, sound channels, sound clips, Rockwool, and SounFX sheetrock. The Navire is an opportunity that you do not want to pass up. Between the private backyard location, neighborhood atmosphere, and great amount of detail that was put into these units, it will surely make anyone fall in love!  - One parking is still available! - Seller can build an L-shaped island upon request or provide a $1,000 credit."
