210002250,SOLD,"JC, Heights",195 BOWERS ST,Condominium,,1653,"$616,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07307,,,,195 Bowers LLC,,,,3,0,2,7,,"$616,000","$619,000",,,1/26/2021,3/3/2021,4/22/2021,36,36,,4/23/2021,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Milton & Summit,"Welcome to this luxury condo in Jersey City Heights. This unit has 3 bedrooms & 2 full bathrooms, with a large private rooftop terrace and is located only 1 block over from Central Ave Shopping District.  Designed with an open layout concept with tons of natural sunlight, high ceilings, and a state of the art kitchen designed to entertain. This unit has all the bells and whistles including hardwood floors, quartz countertops, tons of closet space including a true chef's pantry, and stainless steel appliances. Outdoor space has never been more important! This unit comes with its own private rooftop terrace with beautiful NYC views. One car parking rental spot secured nearby. Close to all public transportation, 15 minutes into NYC, Central Ave Shopping District 5 minutes away.  Schedule a tour today!"
210008313,SOLD,"JC, Heights",974 SUMMIT AVE,Condominium,,1691,"$619,000",CONDO-COOP,,4,408,"JC, Heights",07037,2801,5.01,,,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$619,000","$589,000",,,4/8/2021,7/19/2021,8/10/2021,102,102,,8/10/2021,,,,,,$412,,Conventional,,,,,,Griffith & Licoln,"Welcome to THE SUMMIT in the heart of Jersey City Heights; New Construction, Boutique Condo building with open floor plans & amazing amenities, including:  a shared over-sized roof deck with stunning, 360 panoramic views, elevator, Peloton exercise bike room, bicycle storage. Deeded parking also available. Unit 408 is a modern open layout home with 2 large bedrooms, 2 full bathrooms and ample storage on both level. Elegantly built with modern, high-end finishes, quartz counter tops, hardwood floors, high end GE Cafe appliances (including smart tech induction vented range with Wi-Fi cooking access). Additional smart home features include Yale smart digital locks, Nest thermostat, Verizon FiOS ready,  tankless water heater, Central AC, full size washer/vented dryer. This impressive brick building at the corner of Summit Ave and Lincoln Street is ideally located in Jersey City Heights, near Central Avenue’s Restaurant row, NYC transit and steps away from all of JC Heights parks. Available for Immediate Occupancy and is eligible for 5 year tax abatement!"
250012712,SOLD,"JC, Heights",314 PALISADE AVE,Condominium,1106,6199,"$619,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,#3,"JC, Heights",07307,,,,,,,,3,0,1,5,,"$619,000","$619,000",$559.67,$559.67,6/23/2025,8/4/2025,10/10/2025,42,42,,10/14/2025,,,,"$9,827",2024,$228,,Conventional,,,,,,Across from Supremo,"Three-Bedroom Corner Unit with Roof Rights! Soaring ceilings and an abundance of natural light set the tone for this beautifully designed home. The open floor plan features a full pantry, ample in-unit storage, and additional dedicated storage in the basement. Enjoy the convenience of rental parking just steps away, and a bus to and from Manhattan that stops right next door.  Unit 3 is part of an attractive, 3-unit condominium building located in an ideal Jersey City Heights neighborhood that overlooks the Greatest City in the World.  Bonus: This unit comes with roof rights, offering the potential to create your own private rooftop oasis."
210011708,SOLD,"JC, Heights",391 PALISADE AVE,Condominium,1144,1653,"$619,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,202,"JC, Heights",07307,3901,24.01,Heights,Gallery Lofts,,,,2,0,2,6,,"$619,000","$619,000",$541.08,$541.08,5/14/2021,5/18/2021,6/30/2021,4,4,,7/7/2021,,,,,,$383,,Conventional,,,,,,Franklin St. & Hutton St.,"Perched above bustling Palisade Avenue and overlooking the city, Gallery Lofts is perfectly situated footsteps away from local shops, restaurants, cafes, parks and all the conveniences of a vibrant neighborhood. All this while still having easy access to the city via public transit or car. With a thoughtful approach to design, Gallery Lofts has an air of sophistication and elegance not seen in new construction these days. Each unit is outfitted with timeless selections that have a touch of European Flair.Bertazzoni appliances, porcelain countertops, Imported porcelain tile, Mittel Cucine cabinets, Kohler fixtures; that’s just the start of a long list of materials used on this project."
250002207,SOLD,"JC, Heights",47 HANCOCK AVE,Condominium,975,1186,"$620,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2-02,"JC, Heights",07307,3802,15.01,Heights,,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$620,000","$620,000",$635.90,$635.90,2/3/2025,2/5/2025,5/28/2025,2,2,,5/28/2025,,,,,,,,Conventional,No,No,No,,,Sherman & Cambridge,"Situated in the heart of Jersey City Heights, this exquisite 2-bedroom, 2-bathroom apartment offers an ideal blend of modern comfort and convenience. Boasting an open layout, the unit features a spacious living area that flows seamlessly into the dining room and kitchen, creating a perfect space for relaxation and entertainment. Central air and heating systems ensure optimal comfort throughout the year, while the in-unit washer and dryer offer added convenience for your laundry needs. Enjoy breathtaking views and outdoor relaxation on the common rooftop area, providing an inviting retreat after a long day. Ideally located, this property is in close proximity to various amenities and attractions. Just steps away, you'll find a bus stop for easy commuting, as well as a Stop and Shop for all your grocery needs. For coffee enthusiasts, Froth on Franklin is a local favorite for specialty drinks and treats, while the nearby Riverview Park Farmers Market provides fresh produce and local goods in a vibrant community setting. Don't miss this opportunity to experience the ultimate Jersey City Heights living experience."
210013277,SOLD,"JC, Heights",302 PALISADE AVE,Condominium,1156,1603,"$622,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,303,"JC, Heights",07307-1797,05201,00013,,Palisade Heights,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$622,000","$629,000",$538.06,$538.06,6/2/2021,7/2/2021,8/27/2021,30,30,,12/2/2021,,,,"$6,471",2020,$465,,Conventional,,,,,,Ravine Ave & Cuneo Place,"Welcome to Palisade Heights. Located right in the heartbeat of the Jersey City Heights neighborhood, this beautifully crafted building was just built from the ground up in 2016. Home 303 features the largest floorplan the building offers. Two bedrooms and two full baths, just over 1,150 sqft of space with hardwood floors spread throughout. From the spacious entryway foyer, you enter right into the gorgeous kitchen. The kitchen features bright quartz countertops, a farm-style sink, top-of-the-line JennAir stainless steel appliances, subway-tile backsplash and industrial style pendant lighting over the breakfast bar. The wide-open layout then leads right into an expansive living space. In the living room are east-facing sliding glass doors that lead out to your Juliette balcony with partial views of the Freedom Tower and great morning sunlight. In the first bedroom, you can easily fit a Queen bedroom set and still have enough space for your home office. In the oversized master bedroom, you will find plenty of room for a California king bed, great closet space and en-suite master bath with a glass-enclosed spa-style shower. Additional conveniences include an in-unit washer & dryer, central a/c powered by Nest, video intercom, recessed lighting, industrial-style light fixtures, and garage parking. The building also features a large shared back patio. Close to all major transportation, shops restaurants and access to major highway & the Holland Tunnel. No need to compromise here!"
250015497,SOLD,"JC, Heights",42 PROSPECT ST,Condominium,1354,5678,"$625,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1C,"JC, Heights",07307,,,,The Juliette,,,,3,0,2,6,,"$625,000","$630,000",$461.60,$461.60,7/30/2025,8/5/2025,9/19/2025,6,6,,9/22/2025,,,,"$10,046",2024,$440,Mo,Conventional,,,,,,Palisade Ave and Reservoir Ave,"Welcome to this stunning 3-bedroom, 2-bath duplex, perfectly blending classic charm with modern upgrades in the heart of Jersey City Heights. Spanning two spacious levels, this residence has high ceilings, hardwood floors throughout, and an abundance of natural light. The inviting living room features an exposed brick accent wall, creating the ideal backdrop for stylish city living.  Cook and entertain in the beautifully updated kitchen, complete with custom cabinetry, granite countertops, stainless steel appliances.   Retreat to your private backyard, creating your very own outdoor oasis, perfect for relaxation or entertaining. Additional highlights include central air with NEST thermostat, smart lock, in-unit washer/dryer, custom closets, recessed lighting, and generous storage.  Located just minutes from vibrant Palisade Avenue, you’ll be within easy reach of local dining, shopping, parks, and playgrounds. Commuting is a breeze, with easy access to PATH, Light Rail, and express buses to NYC and Hoboken.   Located conveniently to different shops on Central Ave and beloved hotspots in Jersey City such as Busy Bee Organics, Bread & Salt, and Corto, while Riverview-Fisk Park beckons with its farmer’s markets, playgrounds and breathtaking skyline views.  This exceptional duplex is truly a rare find and a perfect place to call home in one of Jersey City’s most sought-after neighborhoods!"
250016564,SOLD,"JC, Heights",172 SOUTH ST,Condominium,997,1713,"$625,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,B,"JC, Heights",07307,2103,20,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,6,,"$625,000","$599,000",$626.88,$626.88,8/13/2025,9/12/2025,11/3/2025,30,30,,11/5/2025,,,,"$9,896",2023,$395,,Conventional,,,,,,Congress St & Summit Ave,"  Located just steps from Summit and Central Avenues, this stylishly renovated three-bedroom, two-bath home offers an unbeatable location paired with one of the most coveted features in the area: an expansive private backyard that elevates your outdoor living experience. Set on the garden level of a classic brick building, the home opens to a nicely finished backyard retreat—complete with a built-in firepit—perfect for relaxing, entertaining, or enjoying al fresco evenings under the stars.  Inside, character-rich details like reclaimed wood barn doors and exposed brick accents meet modern comforts including a peninsula for casual dining, quartz countertops, and stainless steel appliances. A bright bay window brings natural light into the open-concept living, dining, and kitchen area, all enhanced by warm hardwood floors.  The primary suite is a true retreat with a walk-in closet and direct access to the backyard, making indoor-outdoor living effortless. En suite bathroom is beautifully appointed with full-height tile, mosaic accents, and a glass shower.  This home blends tranquility and city energy in one of Jersey City’s most vibrant neighborhoods—just moments from parks, shops, dining, and transit.  As a bonus, nearby parking is available for an additional fee, offering extra convenience in this sought-after location."
250018469,SOLD,"JC, Heights",70 BOWERS ST,Condominium,1000,1526,"$625,000",CONDO-COOP,,2nd,3,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$625,000","$599,000",$625.00,$625.00,9/9/2025,12/23/2025,1/28/2026,105,105,,1/28/2026,,,,"$10,000",Est.,$300,,Conventional,,,,,,Palisade and Central,"Welcome to Your New Favorite Place (You Just Don’t Know It Yet)  Hey there, future homeowner/hero/urban legend. Feast your eyes on this freshly remodeled 2-bed, 2-bath gem in the Heights of Jersey City — because your current place just isn’t cutting it, is it?  Perfectly sandwiched between Central Avenue and Palisade Ave (like a location panini), you get the best of both worlds: shopping sprees in one direction, scenic park strolls in the other. Boom — nature and retail therapy. Balance.  Inside? You’ve got the goods: gas stove (because food tastes better with flames), microwave (because let’s be honest, you’re gonna reheat a lot of pizza), central air (bye sweat), and yes — an in-unit washer/dryer. That’s right. Laundry. Without the weird basement vibes.  Want more? There’s an option to add parking and/or outdoor space, so your car and your plants can also live their best lives.  Bottom line: this place is great. Call, text, send a carrier pigeon — just make your appointment today."
230009026,SOLD,"JC, Heights",165 MANHATTAN AVE,Condominium,1164,6005,"$625,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,1,"JC, Heights",07307,,,,,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$625,000","$649,000",$536.94,$536.94,6/1/2023,6/9/2023,7/20/2023,8,8,,8/1/2023,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Kennedy & Summit,Unique opportunity to own a new 2 bed 2 bath (1164 Sq Ft approx) condo with a private roof deck. Parking available around the corner Sherman Place and Summit Ave for $250 per month.
220012622,SOLD,"JC, Heights",245 OGDEN AVE,Condominium,1496,1713,"$625,000",CONDO-COOP,,1st&2,1,"JC, Heights",07307,03903,00052,Heights,,,,,1,1,2,5,,"$625,000","$699,000",$417.78,$417.78,7/12/2022,8/4/2022,9/30/2022,23,23,,10/3/2022,,,,"$8,915",2021,$215,,Conventional,,,,,,Griffith & Franklin St,"This loft style duplex is located on one of the most desirable streets in Jersey City Heights, just a few blocks away from the 2nd Street Light Rail Station and just one stop to the Hoboken Bus, Train and Ferry Terminal. Easy commute to New York City!  This unit features almost 1500sqft of living space and a private backyard with a beautiful garden ready to bloom. Currently utilized as a one bedroom with living and dining area on first level, this blank canvas first level with a full bath and tile flooring can be used as a 2nd bedroom, home office, gym and so much more.   Head upstairs to your bright and airy second level with 9ft ceilings, natural sunlight from all the windows and stunning 4” Brazilian cherry hardwood floors throughout. Enjoy your large kitchen that features stainless steel appliances including a dishwasher, Kohler fixtures, granite countertops with breakfast-bar/island and custom cabinetry. Next you have 1 ½ bath and generously sized bedroom with two custom closets. Additional features are ADT, Ring bell and washer/dryer always a plus!  Near Parks, Restaurants, Boutique shops, New Port Centre Mall, Jersey City Downtown and Hoboken nightlife. A Must See!"
250003278,SOLD,"JC, Heights",16 TROY ST,Condominium,1000,1654,"$625,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,101,"JC, Heights",07307,,,,,,,,2,0,2,4,,"$625,000","$640,000",$625.00,$625.00,2/20/2025,4/3/2025,6/30/2025,42,42,,6/30/2025,,,,"$11,000",2025,$300,,Conventional,No,No,,,,Summit and Manhatten,"New major Price Drop!! Parking, parking parking!!! Welcome Home to this chic private modern condo in the heart of JC Heights. Set back off the street for added privacy, this nearly new (just 2 years young!) condo offers a boutique feel and an impressive array of features. The 2 bedrooms, 2 full bathrooms offer  almost 1,000 square feet of living space Step inside to discover high ceilings, recessed lighting, and a Sonos surround sound system wired for Alexa. The open-concept kitchen boasts quartz countertops, Frigidaire stainless steel appliances and kitchen island. Enjoy the convenience of an in-unit washer/dryer and tiled floors that add a modern touch. The condo includes one covered parking space, a shared outdoor space, and bike storage for active lifestyles. Stay connected with the Wi-Fi visual intercom system. Located just a 12-minute walk to the Journal Square PATH, with a bus stop only a block away, commuting is a breeze. You'll also be steps from the lush greenery of Pershing Field, along with nearby shopping, restaurants, and more.   "
230018688,SOLD,"JC, Heights",25 ST PAULS AVE,Condominium,1109,1597,"$625,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1A,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,6,,"$625,000","$650,000",$563.57,$563.57,11/6/2023,1/16/2024,2/9/2024,71,71,,2/9/2024,,,,,,$374,,Conventional,,,,,,Concord and Baldwin,"Tucked into a quiet corner of The Heights, this freshly renovated home offers traditional elegance with modern upgrades galore. The floorplan showcases excellent square footage with 3 bedrooms, 2 baths plus formal dining room or flex space.   Entering into the open plan kitchen and living area, beautiful details like crown molding, gleaming stained hardwood floors, ceiling fans and pendant lighting shine throughout. Bright white eat-in kitchen showcases custom shaker cabinets, quartz counters, subway tile backsplash and stainless appliances. Bathrooms are tiled to ceiling with convenient soaker tubs and shower plus vanity and oversized medicine cabinet mirror. Master en-suite impresses with two large windows, two closets plus additional walk-in closet with window for natural light for ultimate storage.   Settled on a private tree-lined street, the vibrant community, eclectic shops, excellent schools and easy NYC access are no wonder why Jersey City Heights is one of the hottest neighborhoods."
240005027,SOLD,"JC, Heights",34 GRACE ST,Condominium,1600,6078,"$625,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1L,"JC, Heights",07307,,,,,,,,4,0,3,9,,"$625,000","$625,000",$390.63,$390.63,3/16/2024,4/8/2024,5/20/2024,23,23,,5/29/2024,,,,,,$350,,Conventional,,,,,,Summit & Central,"Here is your opportunity to house hack and live virtually mortgage free in a brand new condo in Jersey City Heights! Welcome to Home 1 at The Grace Residences, a boutique project of 4 high-end homes in the Heights. Home 1 is a brand new duplex condo featuring a bonus unit downstairs that you can legally lease for short term rentals. Property includes high-end appliances, in-unit washer/dryer, Pella Architect Series Windows, custom-built closets, quartz countertops, custom designed bathrooms, cove lighting through-out, and high quality soundproofing between all homes. Free downpayment assistance credit for first time homebuyers of up to 22k through preferred mortgage lender. To learn more about this purchase opportunity please inquire within. *Short walking distance to the light rail train*"
250018154,SOLD,"JC, Heights",84 MANHATTAN AVE,Condominium,1000,1713,"$625,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07307,3701,51,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,7,,"$625,000","$650,000",$625.00,$625.00,9/4/2025,10/21/2025,12/1/2025,47,47,,12/1/2025,,,,"$13,145",2023,,,Conventional,,,,,,Central & Summit,"Welcome to 84 Manhattan Ave, Unit 2 – a stunning 3-bedroom, 2-bathroom condo offering modern luxury in the heart of Jersey City Heights. This exceptional residence has been thoughtfully updated and is ready to impress.  Step inside and be greeted by an abundance of natural light cascading across beautiful hardwood floors that flow throughout most of the home. The recently redone façade adds to the building's curb appeal, making a striking first impression.  The heart of the home is the open-concept kitchen, designed for both style and functionality. It features sleek stainless steel appliances, a chic gray tile backsplash, and elegant two-tone cabinetry. A large center island provides a perfect spot for meal prep or casual dining.  Enjoy your morning coffee or evening cocktail on your very own private balcony, conveniently located just off the kitchen – a peaceful retreat from the hustle and bustle of city life.  The primary bedroom is a true sanctuary, boasting a spacious walk-in closet and a luxurious ensuite bathroom. Pamper yourself in the spa-like setting with a double vanity and a sleek, glass-enclosed shower. The second full bathroom is equally well-appointed and features a relaxing tub.  For added convenience, this home includes an in-unit washer and dryer and comes with a nearby rental parking spot that can be transferred to the new owners.  With its prime location and sophisticated design, this condo offers the perfect blend of comfort and style. Don't miss your chance to own a piece of this vibrant neighborhood—schedule your private tour today! Parking available nearby for an additional fee"
240022668,SOLD,"JC, Heights",146 NELSON AVE,Condominium,1959,1597,"$625,000",CONDO-COOP,,1&2,1,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,7,,"$625,000","$649,000",$319.04,$319.04,11/21/2024,12/16/2024,1/17/2025,25,25,,1/31/2025,,,,,,$315,,Conventional,,,,,,Grace & Leonard,"Redefine modern comfort and convenience with this newly renovated, two-story home in the Western Slope neighborhood of Jersey City Heights with one car driveway parking. First impressions are everything with fresh siding, elegant brick accents, and Dutch colonial architecture. Industrial chic design echos throughout the interior with bright white oak flooring, white crown molding and black window trim, and all the modern conveniences.   Beautiful bay windows offer extra natural light, plus super spacious open concept living. This unit features a three bedroom, two bath layout, plus a generous family room or den, secluded downstairs ensuite, luxurious entertainment space and a sizable private backyard, perfect for personalization.   The contemporary kitchen hosts a spacious eat-in island with white waterfall quartz countertops. Finishes include modern gray cabinets including custom touches like wine storage over the refrigerator, brass fixtures and stainless appliances. Bathrooms offer style with beautiful porcelain tile, spacious vanities, bathtub and shower combos and continued brass fixtures. Downstairs you will find the perfect combination of luxury and relaxation as you enjoy your very own private entertainment room.   This home is nestled in the peaceful neighborhood of Western Slope in The Heights, walking distance to Washington Park, 9th Street Lightrail and Hoboken, Central Avenue and more. The Heights is known for its vibrant community, great shops, restaurants and cafes, excellent schools and easy NYC access.   *Backyard is an artistic visual rendering*"
210026268,SOLD,"JC, Heights",73 IRVING ST,Condominium,950,1468,"$625,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,302,"JC, Heights",07307,00805,00001,Heights,,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$625,000","$636,500",$657.89,$657.89,11/28/2021,12/9/2021,3/30/2022,11,10,,4/4/2022,,,,$0,,$0,,Conventional,,,,,,Corner of Kennedy Blvd,"Welcome to 73 Irving Street! This 4-story new construction boutique building sits on a corner lot and clears every neighboring building in a multi-block radius, allowing for an overflowing of afternoon amber glow into the unit through its numerous floor-to-ceiling windows. You will enter onto beautiful 8” white oak floors into an open layout concept. The kitchen was uniquely designed with custom cabinetry, custom, uniquely ribboned quartz countertops and backsplash, Samsung SS appliances and a wine fridge. A true split-plan, the master bedroom is surrounded by windows, offers a large walk-in closet and an en-suite bathroom with a big window, custom granite vanity sink and floating storage. On the other end of the unit is a second, bright room that is perfect for a 2nd bedroom, home office or nursery. The cherry on top is the gorgeous, large tree that sits outside the living/dining area for added tranquility. Pella Lifestyle Series windows cement-fiber structural 3/4 tongue and groove sub flooring complete this home for added durability. One deeded garage parking space is included. HOA TBD and taxes TBD/should be independently verified by tax assessor.  "
220000535,SOLD,"JC, Heights",73 IRVING ST,Condominium,950,1468,"$625,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,202,"JC, Heights",07307,00805,00001,Heights,,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$625,000","$631,750",$657.89,$657.89,1/10/2022,1/21/2022,3/4/2022,11,11,,3/10/2022,,,,$0,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Corner of Kennedy Blvd,"Welcome to unit 202 at 73 Irving Street! This 4-story new construction boutique building sits on a corner lot and clears every neighboring building in a multi-block radius, allowing for an overflowing of afternoon amber glow into the unit through its numerous floor-to-ceiling windows. You will enter onto beautiful 8” white oak floors into an open layout concept. The kitchen was uniquely designed with custom cabinetry, custom, uniquely ribboned quartz countertops, continuing as backsplash, Samsung SS appliances and a wine fridge. A true split-plan, the master bedroom is surrounded by windows, offers a large walk-in closet and an en-suite bathroom with a large window, custom granite vanity sink and floating storage. On the other end of the unit is a second, bright room that is perfect for a 2nd bedroom, home office or nursery! The cherry on top is the gorgeous, large tree that sits outside the living/dining area for added tranquility. Pella Lifestyle Series windows cement-fiber structural 3/4 tongue and groove sub flooring complete this home for added durability. One deeded garage parking space is included. HOA approximations are vetted estimates and taxes are TBD/should be independently verified by JC tax assessor.  "
210006714,SOLD,"JC, Heights",302 PALISADE AVE,Condominium,1004,1568,"$625,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,304,"JC, Heights",07307,05201,00013,Heights,,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$625,000","$629,000",$622.51,$622.51,3/22/2021,5/7/2021,6/29/2021,46,46,,6/29/2021,,,,"$6,232",2020,$405,,Conventional,,,,,,Palisade and Cuneo,"OPEN HOUSE 12-2, SATURDAY 4/3  Welcome to JC Heights- Beautiful 2 Bedroom 2 Bathroom home at the Palisades Heights Condominiums. This young home boasts an open layout featuring hardwood floors throughout, crown molding, recessed lighting, upgraded washer/dryer, ample closet space, central air, dining room, and a Juliet balcony  off of the living room. Modern kitchen with Jennair appliances, large cabinets with custom lighting underneath, and a breakfast bar with quartz countertops. The master bedroom has a spacious ensuite bathroom. Both bedrooms have custom closets with recessed lighting in each, and ample light. This turn key home is located in a boutique building and comes with indoor garage parking and a beautiful shared yard. A wonderful neighborhood walking distance to parks, restaurants, transportation, farmers market, and more!  "
260000116,SOLD,"JC, Heights",201 ZABRISKIE ST,Condominium,1782,1713,"$625,000",CONDO-COOP,,1-2,1,"JC, Heights",07307,3303,15,Heights,,,,,3,1,2,6,,"$625,000","$625,000",$350.73,$350.73,1/8/2026,2/2/2026,3/11/2026,25,25,,3/13/2026,,,,"$11,093",2023,$416,,Cash,,,,,,Terrace & Western Ave,"**PRIVATE BACKYARD + PARKING** Your next chapter begins at 201 Zabriskie #1, a beautifully redesigned two-story home in the heart of Jersey City Heights. Spanning nearly 1,800 square feet, this spacious 3-bedroom, 2.5-bath residence perfectly blends smart function, design, character, and comfort. This is true modern city living, complete with a fully finished private backyard and valuable private, off-street parking. Tucked away just moments from Leonard Gordon Park, Tonnelle Avenue, and the Holland Tunnel, this peaceful retreat offers quick access to the energy and amenities of the Heights and NYC. Step inside to a bright, open-concept main level. The living area is instantly inviting, centered around a cozy fireplace featuring a custom wood mantle and shiplap detail. Wood tile floors and custom lighting flow seamlessly into the full-size dining area and the gourmet kitchen, designed equally for everyday living and stylish entertainment. The kitchen is a sleek contemporary dream with Calcutta Bellow white quartz waterfall countertops and matching backsplash, custom cabinetry, and black stainless steel appliances and fixtures. It also boasts a large eat-in island, perfect for casual meals or larger gatherings. While the main level hosts two sizable bedrooms, each with a walk-in closet, the upper level is dedicated entirely to the private primary ensuite, offering a secluded sanctuary. Throughout the home, excellent built-in cabinets and closet space provide function and ease for daily living. The bathrooms feature luxurious touches, including a gorgeous glass shower with floor-to-ceiling herringbone tile, a spacious double vanity, and warm brass fixtures. Modern upgrades include central heating and air, a stacking LG washer & dryer, and a state-of-the-art video intercom system. Situated on a quiet, tree-lined street, this home delivers the best of modern city living in a prime location. Owners enjoy recently renovated Leonard Gordon Park with walking paths, playgrounds, farmers’ markets, and gardens. Jersey City Heights is known for its vibrant community, eclectic art scene, excellent schools, beautiful parks, and remarkably easy access to NYC. This is more than a home—it’s where smart luxury meets prime location. Welcome home to 201 Zabriskie #1."
210000936,SOLD,"JC, Heights",99 LEONARD ST,Condominium,1238,1419,"$625,000",CONDO-COOP,,1 & 2,1,"JC, Heights",07307,00403,00021,,,,,,2,1,2,6,,"$625,000","$669,000",$504.85,$504.85,1/8/2021,4/25/2021,5/18/2021,107,104,,5/19/2021,,,,"$6,718",2020,$159,,Conventional,,,,,,Nelson Ave & Pierce Ave,"This luxurious 2 bed plus 2.5 bath duplex in a newly built Townhome is located in the highly desirable Western Slope area of Jersey City Heights! This gorgeous 1238 sf' home boasts 2 spacious bedrooms, including a master suite with ample closet space and an en suite, a spacious kitchen, living room and a family room on the second level. Other features include granite counter tops, stainless steel appliances, a brick kitchen island, water purifier separate from the fridge, dishwasher, washer/dryer, gas fireplace, central HVAC + central vacuum, Nest thermostats, patio furniture, a private attached garage, and front and backyard Nest security (DVR subscription not included). Enjoy relaxing in the private and landscaped backyard!   One block away from transportation to NYC and Journal Square PATH via bus and minutes from Rt. 1-9 and Rt. 3. A few blocks to Washington Park and all the local eateries and shops on Central Ave."
230010625,SOLD,"JC, Heights",258 SHERMAN AVE,Condominium,854,1597,"$625,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,3,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$625,000","$599,000",$731.85,$731.85,6/26/2023,7/10/2023,8/16/2023,14,14,,8/16/2023,,,,,,$256,,Conventional,,,,,,South St & Congress,"Light, bright and modern, this newly finished two bedroom home is one block to either Washington or Riverview Fisk Park in Jersey City Heights. Elegant design shines with loads of light illuminating hardwood floors and stylish contrasting matte back doors throughout.    Eat-in kitchen gleams with white quartz counters, exposed shelves, custom cabinets, tile backsplash and stainless appliances. Bedrooms boast ample closet space, while bathrooms host finishes like traditional penny tile shower floors, large vanities and polished chrome fixtures. Home features dedicated laundry area for added convenience.   Ideally located in the heart of The Heights, this home is perfectly positioned walking distance to major thoroughfares, great parks, and easy NYC access. Jersey City Heights is known for its excellent community and parks, great schools, eclectic shops and restaurants, and proximity to surrounding urban areas."
210007586,SOLD,"JC, Heights",47 NELSON AVE,Condominium,1585,1653,"$625,000",CONDO-COOP,,G & 1,1,"JC, Heights",07307,,,,,,,,4,1,2,8,,"$625,000","$625,000",$394.32,$394.32,4/1/2021,5/7/2021,6/22/2021,36,36,,6/25/2021,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Bleeker & North st - Off Kennedy blvd,"Welcome home to one of Jersey City Heights most unique and special offerings on the market right now!  Brand new construction with 4Beds & 2.5Baths featuring 1585sqft of interior living space, 189sqft terrace off the master suite, a private yard, and a huge Storage area in the basement.  This home can accommodate the largest of families or a multitude of opportunities, think home business/storage solutions!   Property features 10 ceilings adding to the ambiance of extra space and one of the homes most special features is a private ground floor main living level entrance, offering a super unique no stair comfort access with endless possibilities.   Other than these great features the property boasts everything you would expect from new construction as in a chef inspired kitchen with soft close cabinets, quartz countertops, recessed lighting, beautiful natural hardwood floors, Anderson windows, Solid core doors, central ac, and much much more.  Round it off with a 10year builder warranty and a potential builder applied for post-closing tax abatement could be the perfect home for you?  Call now for more information or to arrange a private showing! "
250011919,SOLD,"JC, Heights",20 RESERVOIR AVE,Condominium,1197,1741,"$625,000",CONDO-COOP,,GR,1,"JC, Heights",07307,05005,00030,Heights,,,,,2,0,2,7,,"$625,000","$589,999",$522.14,$522.14,6/12/2025,6/17/2025,8/5/2025,5,5,,8/5/2025,,,,"$8,202",2024,$292,,Conventional,,,,,,Baldwin & Palisade Ave,"Discover the perfect blend of luxury and convenience at 20 Reservoir Avenue, Apt 1, nestled on one of the most desirable tree-lined streets in The Heights of Jersey City. Enjoy the rare convenience of deeded parking and the comfort of your own private patio—an ideal space for morning coffee, evening relaxation, or outdoor entertaining. Inside, a brand new in-unit washer and dryer adds ease to your daily routine, while the expansive living area is elevated by recessed lighting and an electric fireplace, creating a warm and welcoming atmosphere.  Take advantage of close proximity to green spaces like Pershing Field Park, the brand-new Jersey City Reservoir Walking Trail, and the iconic Riverview Fisk Park—home to Sunday farmers markets. The 100 Steps to Hoboken are just around the corner, offering easy access to Hoboken in minutes. Surrounded by local hotspots including Low Fidelity, The Alps, The Franklin, and Alessio’s, this home combines comfort, convenience, and community.  The state-of-the-art kitchen is outfitted with brand new appliances, perfect for any home chef. The primary bedroom includes a gut-renovated en-suite bathroom that exudes modern luxury, while both bedrooms are generously sized to accommodate your lifestyle needs. Nearly the entire unit has been recently renovated, offering a fresh and contemporary feel throughout.  Additional features include central A/C and heating, a smart thermostat, a thoughtfully designed foyer/mudroom, ample storage, and a ButterflyMX video intercom system for added security. The building is pet-friendly, and both property taxes and HOA fees are low, making this home as practical as it is stylish.  Experience the best of city living in a home that offers comfort, modern amenities, and an unbeatable location in the heart of The Heights—all with the added perks of deeded PARKING and a PRIVATE PATIO that truly set this residence apart."
220002623,SOLD,"JC, Heights",54 SHERMAN AVE,Condominium,1249,1603,"$625,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,3,"JC, Heights",07307,04502,004-C03,,,,,,2,0,2,4,,"$625,000","$620,000",$500.40,$500.40,2/15/2022,3/1/2022,4/7/2022,13,13,,4/7/2022,,,,"$8,421",,$325,,Conventional,,,,,,Franklin & Hutton,"Sunny and spacious top floor 2 bed/ 2 bath unit *with parking* in the heart of the Riverview Arts section of Jersey City Heights. This dazzling condo was gut renovated in 2018 and boasts high ceilings, hardwood floors throughout, stainless steel appliances, quartz countertops, central air, and in-unit laundry. Custom Elfa closets from Container Store and handmade shelving from Ninja Bear Woodworks make storage a breeze. The primary bedroom features a walk-in closet and oversized bath. Juliet balconies in the front *and* back create a serene living space in the middle of a bustling neighborhood. Situated between Riverview and Manhattan Parks, you’ll have easy access to Palisade and Central Avenue bus routes and the 2nd Street Light Rail Station in Hoboken. One block from great coffee and restaurants on Franklin Street, come enjoy all the Heights has to offer. Welcome home!"
240015219,SOLD,"JC, Heights",155 LAIDLAW AVE,Condominium,1250,298,"$627,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1,"JC, Heights",07306,,,,,,,,2,1,2,5,,"$627,000","$629,000",$501.60,$501.60,8/5/2024,8/30/2024,9/27/2024,25,25,,10/14/2024,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Jefferson Ave and Beacon Ave,"Experience the best of urban living with this beautifully designed duplex condo located in the vibrant Jersey City Heights. This spacious home features two generous bedrooms perfect for relaxation, 2.5 bathrooms, and an open-concept living area ideal for entertaining. The finished basement provides additional space for a home office or playroom, while the private backyard offers your own outdoor oasis for relaxation and gatherings. Situated in a prime location, this condo offers easy access to local amenities, trendy restaurants, parks, and public transportation, making commuting to Manhattan a breeze. Whether you're a first-time homebuyer or looking to upgrade, this home provides the perfect blend of style, space, and convenience. Don't miss out on this fantastic opportunity—contact us today to schedule a viewing and make this dream home yours."
210001170,SOLD,"JC, Heights",22 LINCOLN ST,Condominium,,1691,"$630,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,3,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,6,,"$630,000","$639,000",,,1/13/2021,1/20/2021,3/24/2021,7,7,,4/15/2021,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Summit and Central,"Say hello to thoughtful modern luxury in the Heights. This beautifully renovated top floor, 3 bedroom 2 bath condominium brings elegance and sophistication to a quiet tree-lined street just off Central Avenue.  Simple, clean design delights upon entry with bright, open floor plan.  Contemporary kitchens impress with custom charcoal grey lower cabinets, clean white uppers and marbled quartz counters. Bathrooms bring interest and enviable design with elements such as floating custom vanities, pocket doors, oversized slab tile and complementary brass and black fixtures.  Master en-suite boasts sliding French doors leading to private balcony (perfect for al fresco coffee or cocktails). Step out onto your private outdoor roof deck for breathtaking 360 degree city-scape and NYC views.  Part of a completely renovated 3-unit building, all three homes offer additional storage and ideal walkability to surrounding Central & Palisade Avenue for all essential shopping needs, plus Pershing Field, Washington or Riverview Fisk Parks. The Heights is a thriving community with excellent schools, award-winning restaurants & businesses plus easy NYC access!  Rental parking available nearby!!"
220006279,SOLD,"JC, Heights",124 NEW YORK AVE,Condominium,875,1419,"$630,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,203,"JC, Heights",07307,04504,1,Heights,The York,,,,1,0,1,4,,"$630,000","$599,000",$720.00,$720.00,4/11/2022,4/29/2022,10/21/2022,18,18,,11/9/2022,,,,,,$276,,Conventional,,,,,,Ferry St & Franklin St,"A serene escape is located in the Jersey City Height with unobstructed Manhattan views. The peaceful private terraces and direct elevator access to a huge communal deck will provide you with an immediate escape. There is endless opportunity in this spacious condominium entailing 1 bedroom and 1 bathroom with 875 sq ft of living space. This is one of only two one bedrooms here at the York and it's equipped with chef's kitchen, Bosch stainless steel appliances, modernized cabinetry, in-unit washer/dryer, and in-ceiling speakers managed by Sonos amplifier. 5 wide plank oak hardwood floors throughout, Porcelanosa tile and plumbing fixtures, LED lighting and heated bathroom floors create a true luxurious experience. The builder spared no cost in making this home sound proofed by using sound channels and sound clips, Quietrock, green/noise proofing compound, and even foam insulation, dampening the noise. This unbeatable Heights location is easily commutable and accessible to public transportation being only 1 block from Palisade Ave; with direct bus lines to NYC Port Authority, Hoboken, and Downtown JC. The Hudson Light Rail Stations are only minutes away as well as Pershing Field's indoor pool and ice skating rink being only 3 blocks away. Riverview Park with its amazing views offers Farmers Market, movie nights, and neighborhood events. Don't miss this opportunity to see The Jersey City Heights newest development - The York! This elevator building optimizes every square foot of the floor plan and includes two communal rooftop decks, a large garage, and a bike rack on the 1st floor. Garage parking available. 5 year new construction tax abatement."
