210007029,SOLD,"JC, Heights",69 CHARLES ST,Condominium,1233,1691,"$635,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1,"JC, Heights",07307,2704,13,,,,,,3,0,2,7,,"$635,000","$640,000",$515.00,$515.00,3/25/2021,4/23/2021,6/10/2021,29,29,,6/10/2021,,,,,,$210,,Conventional,,,,,,Summit Ave & Milton Ave,"Clean design and contemporary finishes encompass this newly renovated 3-bedroom home on enchanting Charles Street in The Heights. Opening to a flowing floorplan, the bright bay windows and intricate hardwood flooring throughout showcase the spacious design, while crown molding and tall 10.5 foot ceilings create a bright airy feeling to the property.   Quartz counters gleam on the oversized eat-in island, with kitchen finishes like white tile backsplash, neutral custom cabinets and inlay stainless sink plus appliances. Master bedroom bathes in light with windows on the south and west-facing walls, plus exclusive access to the beautiful big private backyard. Ensuite also enjoys spacious walk-in closet and enviable bath hosting large glass shower plus seat, niche and rainhead. Extra bedrooms offer excellent storage plus standard LED lighting, with the additional bathroom showcasing double vanity and convenient shower plus bathtub combo.    Constructed with confidence by accomplished local builders, this home is settled into a beautiful residential street walking distance to thriving Central Avenue, coveted Washington and Leonard Gordan Parks, plus excellent schools and easy NYC access."
220003293,SOLD,"JC, Heights",176 SHERMAN AVE,Condominium,1331,64,"$635,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,201,"JC, Heights",07307,02301,00002,,BAKERY LOFTS,,,,2,0,1,5,,"$635,000","$632,500",$477.08,$477.08,2/25/2022,3/8/2022,5/6/2022,11,11,,5/9/2022,,,,"$8,611",21,$420,,Cash,,,,,,Bowers & South,"What better way to start the year off than moving into your new home at the factory converted Bakery Lofts in the booming Riverview Arts District of Jersey City Heights. This 2 Bedroom Gem offers soaring 10ft high ceilings, boasting 1,330 square feet of beautifully crafted lofted interior space. With its western exposure and oversized windows, you'll enjoy the afternoon sun filling your home with soothing natural light. Designer setting features exposed brick and duct work to set the tone of NYC style lofts.  Complemented by the granite kitchen countertops, brand new kitchen cabinets, wide plank red oak hardwood floors and GE stainless steel appliances. Other features include a spacious bathroom with double vanity, deluxe expansive shower, central heat and AC, in-unit washer/ dryer and a deeded-garage parking spot. Condo converted and completely gut renovated in 2006, The Bakery Lofts is a Boutique elevator building conveniently located on a quiet tree-lined street just steps away to the Heights' best shopping, dining (LoFi, Corto, Choc-o-Pain, Mod Cup), art galleries, parks and easy transportation into Hoboken, Downtown Jersey City or NYC."
