210009098,SOLD,"JC, Heights",126 WEBSTER AVE,Condominium,1387,5845,"$635,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,3D,"JC, Heights",07307,04503,00017,,Hugo Pronti Artist Loft,,,,1,0,1,8,,"$635,000","$628,000",$457.82,$457.82,4/16/2021,4/26/2021,6/15/2021,10,10,,6/16/2021,,,,"$9,660",2020,$536,,Conventional,,,,,,Hutton and Franklin,"Living where you love means coming home to this one-of-a-kind large Soho-style true loft residence with one bedroom and a sleeping loft at the Hugo Pronti Artist Loft Building. This former suitcase factory is located in one of the hottest neighborhoods in Jersey City. The home astounds with 1,387 square feet of living space, and a large shared 17’8” X 13’3” terrace with partial views of New York City! This best-in-class loft features: oak hardwood floors throughout; soaring 13 foot ceilings highlighted by original timber beams; enviable exposed brick and seven oversize windows that bathe the home in natural light aided by it’s southeast exposures. The residence offers a wide open living area with a gas fireplace, a spacious dining area and an open chef’s kitchen featuring: mosaic tiles; breakfast bar and stainless appliances. Other highlights: Washer/ Dryer in unit; central gas heating and cooling; a jetted soaking tub; 5’2 x 16’ assigned gated storage; southeast exposures and one private parking space!  This is a pet friendly 28-unit loft building with elevator, bike area, additional laundry area for residences in the building and a video entrance/security system. Located 2 blocks to NYC bus service, 3 blocks to Riverview Fisk Park and 8 minutes to Hoboken’s 2nd St. Light Rail station. ( See alternative floor plan and add a 2nd bedroom!)."
