240014859,SOLD,"JC, Heights",155 LAIDLAW AVE,Condominium,1,298,"$635,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07306,,,,,,,,2,1,2,5,,"$635,000","$649,000","$635,000.00","$635,000.00",7/31/2024,8/12/2024,9/20/2024,12,12,,9/26/2024,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Summit Ave and Central Ave,"PRIVATE ROOF DECK AND NYC VIEW. Experience the best of urban living with this beautifully designed duplex condo located in the vibrant Jersey City Heights. This spacious home features two generous bedrooms perfect for relaxation, 2.5 modern bathrooms, and an open-concept living area ideal for entertaining. While the private roof deck offers your own outdoor oasis for relaxation and gatherings. Situated in a prime location, this condo offers easy access to local amenities, trendy restaurants, parks, and public transportation, making commuting to Manhattan a breeze. Whether you're a first-time homebuyer or looking to upgrade, this home provides the perfect blend of style, space, and convenience. Don't miss out on this fantastic opportunity—contact us today to schedule a viewing and make this dream home yours."
260000245,SOLD,"JC, Heights",25 ST PAULS AVE,Condominium,1250,1597,"$637,500",CONDO-COOP,,3,3,"JC, Heights",07306,,,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,7,,"$637,500","$649,000",$510.00,$510.00,1/9/2026,2/6/2026,3/18/2026,28,28,,3/18/2026,,,,,,$411,,Conventional,,,,,,Concord and Baldwin,"Tucked into a quiet corner of The Heights, this renovated home offers traditional elegance with modern upgrades galore. The floorplan showcases excellent square footage with 3 bedrooms, 2 baths plus formal dining room or flex space.   Entering into the open plan kitchen and living area, beautiful details like crown molding, gleaming stained hardwood floors, ceiling fans and pendant lighting shine throughout. Bright white eat-in kitchen showcases custom shaker cabinets, quartz counters, subway tile backsplash and stainless appliances. Bathrooms are tiled to ceiling with convenient soaker tubs and shower plus vanity and oversized medicine cabinet mirror. Master en-suite impresses with two large windows, two closets plus additional walk-in closet with window for natural light for ultimate storage.   Settled on a private tree-lined street, the vibrant community, eclectic shops, excellent schools and easy NYC access are no wonder why Jersey City Heights is one of the hottest neighborhoods."
240010194,SOLD,"JC, Heights",185 WEBSTER AVE,Condominium,1030,1713,"$640,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,1D,"JC, Heights",07307,2904,22,,Liberty View Condos,,,,2,1,1,5,,"$640,000","$650,000",$621.36,$621.36,5/29/2024,6/25/2024,8/20/2024,27,27,,8/23/2024,,,,"$9,480",,$615,,Conventional,,,,,,Griffith and Bowers,"Welcome to this gorgeous 2-bedroom, 1.5-bathroom condo nestled in the vibrant neighborhood of Jersey City Heights Riverview Arts District. As you step into the unit, you're greeted by an inviting living space filled with natural light streaming through large windows, soaring 12' ceilings and teak flooring. The open layout seamlessly connects the living room to the kitchen, creating a perfect space for entertaining guests. The kitchen boasts beautiful white cabinetry, granite countertops, and stainless steel appliances w/ breakfast bar. Two spacious bedrooms, each offering ample closet space. A full bathroom with modern fixtures and a half bath completes the living space, providing both style and functionality. Building offers a shared rooftop deck w/ breathtaking views of NYC and garage parking. Located in Jersey City Heights, enjoy easy access to a variety of dining and shopping options as well as convenient transportation to Manhattan and other parts of New Jersey."
220020183,SOLD,"JC, Heights",3316 KENNEDY BLVD,Condominium,1000,1702,"$640,000",CONDO-COOP,,4/5,402,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,Sherman Place,,,,2,0,2,6,,"$640,000","$699,900",$640.00,$640.00,11/14/2022,11/15/2022,12/28/2022,1,0,,12/30/2022,,,,$0,,$431,,Conventional,,,,,,MANHATTAN/SHERMAN PLACE,"New ground up construction, 14-unit luxury condos, This one-of-a-kind Haussmann inspired boutique, corner location with New York City skyline & River views. DEEDED indoor parking available for purchase, rooftop deck, indoor bike storage, tech-savvy homes,elevator, professional property management, secure package room. Convenient to all, 2 blocks to Central Ave -Restaurant Row, CitiBike & JSQ/NYC bus at your door.  1,000-2,200 Sq ft. Homes. Agents & Referrals Welcome. Private tours available.    "
210003011,SOLD,"JC, Heights",15 LEONARD ST,Condominium,1246,1681,"$640,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07307,00504,00018,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,8,,"$640,000","$599,900",$513.64,$513.64,2/5/2021,2/15/2021,4/9/2021,10,10,,4/9/2021,,,,"$6,845",,$249,,Conventional,No,No,,,,Summit & Central,"Welcome to the best value in JC Heights. This 3BR/2BTH condo built in 2019 features 1246 sq. feet of luxury, new living capped off with a 400 sq. ft. rooftop deck w/ NYC views! Condo boasts open floor plan w/ soaring cathedral ceilings & skylights in living room and a gourmet kitchen w/ granite countertops & stainless steel appliances. Relax in your large master suite w/ walk-in closet, master bath with radiant heat in floors and a terrace. Tandem garage parking included, great storage throughout unit and steps to Washington Park and NYC transportation."
230011909,SOLD,"JC, Heights",33 WAVERLY ST,Condominium,1128,1603,"$640,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,Unit 1,"JC, Heights",07306-1111,05803,00006,Heights,,,,,2,0,2,6,,"$640,000","$615,000",$567.38,$567.38,7/17/2023,7/25/2023,9/7/2023,8,8,,9/7/2023,,,,"$10,240",2022,$373,,Conventional,No,No,Yes,,,Palisade and Baldwin,"Welcome to the home that has it all in the heart of it all, 33 Waverly Street, a historic brick boutique building on a quiet tree-lined block in the booming south eastern side of Jersey City Heights. This thoughtfully re-designed southern-facing 2 bedroom, 2 bathroom, garden level unit welcomes you with its private entrance that expands into over 1100 sf of beautiful open concept living. Pella glass french doors off the living room lead out to your EXCLUSIVE landscaped BACKYARD that feels like an urban oasis-- complete with paver patio and slight views of NYC. Home features include central a/c, five-inch white oak floors throughout, ornate light fixtures as well as recessed lighting, in-unit stackable washer/ dryer, a fully equipped kitchen with custom cabinetry, stainless steel appliances, MOEN hardware and a wine fridge. Perfectly laid out with opposite end spacious bedrooms, including one as a primary with en-suite bathroom, a home ideal for those who WFH.  Other bonuses include smart home features such as app-controlled lighting, Nest thermostat, Ring video doorbell; storage space for a bike or oversized containers; and to top it all off— a transferable covered garage rental PARKING spot 1.5 blocks away. Ideally located within walking distance to parks, the Heights' best shopping, cafes, bars, restaurants, supermarket, and the steps into Hoboken. Easy commute to NYC via JSQ Path, light rail, or buses all just a short walkable distance away. HOA fees include water, trash & recycling pick-up, twice-a-month lobby and front yard cleaning, common area electric."
210002274,SOLD,"JC, Heights",127 SHERMAN PL,Condominium,1450,1653,"$640,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,127 Sherman Condos,,,,3,0,2,7,,"$640,000","$649,000",$441.38,$441.38,1/26/2021,2/24/2021,5/6/2021,29,29,,5/7/2021,,,,,,,,Cash,,,,,,Sanford Pl & Kennedy Blvd,"Welcome to Sherman Place - one of Jersey City's most desired tree lined blocks. This spacious Condo will surely impress you! Offering 3 bedrooms, 2 baths, dining room, a huge open living room with tons of natural sunlight and a kitchen designed to entertain. Gut renovated with all new electric, plumbing, HVAC, and a fire sprinkler system. This luxury condo has all the bells and whistles including hardwood floors, quartz countertops, stainless steel Samsung appliances including a smart fridge, and chic designer tiles throughout. Outdoor space has never been more important! This unit comes with its own private roof deck. Parking rental secured nearby. Steps away from Leonard Gordon Park & JFK BLVD. Citibike access on the corner of the block. Close to all public transportation, 15 minutes into NYC, Central Ave Shopping District 5 minutes away. Schedule a tour today!"
230011983,SOLD,"JC, Heights",56 RESERVOIR AVE,Condominium,1060,1597,"$642,500",CONDO-COOP,,1,1,"JC, Heights",07307,,,,,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$642,500","$649,000",$606.13,$606.13,7/18/2023,8/23/2023,10/13/2023,36,36,,10/13/2023,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Lienau & Webster,"Modern design and urban escape combine to bring this newly renovated home to Jersey City Heights. Presented with carefully curated finishes, private outdoor space and quality craftsmanship, this property is located just off Pershing Field Park and Reservoir, and nestled on a tree-lined street between Palisade and Central Avenue.  Gorgeous green siding, beautiful black trim plus soffits, and classic front porch lead the way to the impeccably designed interior. Featuring high ceilings and white oak floors, the two bedrooms, two bath floorplan offers style and spaciousness. Kitchen showcases custom gray cabinetry with under lighting, matching quartz counters, matte black fixtures, and stainless appliances. Sliding glass doors lead you to your own private patio & backyard. Black half-wall wainscotting offers timeless appeal in the primary ensuite, while bathrooms boast floor to ceiling tile, natural wood vanities and extras like a shower nook and bronze or black fixtures.  Nestled in a sweet spot of Jersey City Heights, owners enjoy nearby Pershing Field Park with swimming pool, tennis courts, sports facilities and more. Also within walking distance is bustling Central Avenue with shops, cafes and restaurants, and the 2nd Street stairs with direct access to Hoboken and Lightrail Station. The Heights is known for its tight-knit community, excellent parks, great schools and easy NYC access."
210020996,SOLD,"JC, Heights",94 ZABRISKIE ST,Condominium,1344,6192,"$644,500",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07307,02701,00046,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,6,,"$644,500","$649,000",$479.54,$479.54,9/8/2021,10/24/2021,12/6/2021,46,46,,12/9/2021,,"$476,900",,"$7,676",2020,$230,,Conventional,,,,,,Summit Ave and JFK Ave,"Sunlit and elegantly designed, this is a new building located in the heart of JC Heights. With 1344 SF, this home features 3 Bedrooms, 2 baths, a private Rooftop Terrace w/ coveted NYC views.  Open & flexible floorplan offers the best of generous living w/ high ceilings, oversized windows & brick accent wall, Central AC, in unit laundry, ample closet space, recessed lighting & hardwood floors.  Modern, sleek Kitchen w/ huge island, quartz counters, custom cabinetry, SS appliances flows seamlessly into the spacious living & dining area. Primary suite offers a large, custom closet, spacious balcony & a beautifully designed spa-like en-suite bathroom. This pet friendly home was completed in 2019. Proximity to restaurants, shopping, Leonard Gordon & Washington Parks. Jitney at JFK & Hutton to Journal Square Path."
220011533,SOLD,"JC, Heights",127 MOUNTAIN RD,Condominium,1100,1603,"$644,794",CONDO-COOP,,1,1,"JC, Heights",07307,00040,03904,Heights,,,,,2,0,2,4,,"$644,794","$625,000",$586.18,$586.18,6/23/2022,7/8/2022,8/23/2022,15,15,,8/23/2022,,,,"$7,933",2021,$255,,Conventional,,,,,,Franklin and Griffith,"Tucked behind Ogden Ave and overlooking Hoboken, Mountain Road is one of The Height's best kept secrets.  With extraordinary views, gorgeous shared outdoor space, and unique duplex living, 127 MOUNTAIN RD #1 truly sets itself apart!  Located on the first floor of a 3 unit, all owner-occupied condo building; 127 MOUNTAIN RD #1 offers its homeowners multiple outdoor spaces to enjoy, beautiful eastern and western exposure, and great indoor/outdoor flow thru both levels of the beautifully appointed home.   As you enter the home, note the oversized windows in the kitchen -  which frame the city skyline from midtown to the financial district.  A fully glass door leads out to a newly built terrace for your private use. Imagine sipping your morning coffee as the sun begins to peek over the city's buildings and sparkle on the Hudson River.  Stepping back inside, you will be greeted by the large and well designed kitchen - freshly painted cabinets with modern brushed gold hardware, excellent task lighting, and the first of three original marble fireplaces found throughout the home. Beyond the kitchen is the home's family room.  Previously the home's primary bedroom with ensuite, it now provides homeowners with a full level of living space to relax, enjoy, and entertain family and friends.    The lower level of the home leads to 2 bedrooms and a full bathroom.  There's also another beautiful fireplace with marble mantel, a full sized washer/dryer and tons of closet and storage space.  A door on this level leads directly to the beautifully manicured shared upper garden.  There is also a shared lower level garden past the wooden gate and fence; framed with high hedges for complete privacy. This is a one of a kind home in an excellent location with outdoor space to be envied Quiet and serene, you'll feel a million miles away from the city, yet NYC is right there in your backyard.  Video tour:<a href=https://vimeo.com/717348135>Click here</a>"
250011337,SOLD,"JC, Heights",13 MANHATTAN AVE,Condominium,1282,6078,"$645,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1,"JC, Heights",07307,4402,24,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,7,,"$645,000","$674,900",$503.12,$503.12,6/5/2025,6/27/2025,8/8/2025,22,22,,8/8/2025,,,,,,$139,,Conventional,,,,,,Central Ave,"Welcome to 13 Manhattan Ave #1, a brand-new construction condo in the heart of Jersey City Heights, offering modern elegance and high-end finishes. This spacious three-bedroom, two-bath home is designed for both comfort and convenience, featuring 9.5 ft ceilings and an open-concept layout that seamlessly connects the kitchen, dining, and living area—perfect for entertaining. The kitchen is equipped with custom shaker cabinetry, quartz countertops, and a GE stainless steel appliance package, including a gas range and a wine fridge. New Anderson windows provide natural light that floods the space, highlighting the hardwood floors throughout. Thoughtfully designed custom closets provide optimal organization, and there is plenty of storage within the home. An in-unit washer and dryer adds everyday convenience, while central air and heat with Nest smart thermostats ensure year-round comfort. The master suite is generously sized and includes its own private outdoor patio. A 10-year builder’s warranty offers peace of mind, making this an excellent opportunity for modern urban living. Located within walking distance to Pershing Field Park, this home is perfectly situated between Central and Palisade Avenue, offering easy access to shops, restaurants, and everyday conveniences. Commuters will appreciate the proximity to NJ Transit bus lines into Manhattan, with bus stops just a block away on Ferry St and Central Ave, as well as the 2nd Street Light Rail station. Reach out to schedule your private tour today!"
230006463,SOLD,"JC, Heights",974 SUMMIT AVE,Condominium,1090,1419,"$645,000",CONDO-COOP,,4,401,"JC, Heights",07307,2801,5.01,Heights,,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$645,000","$649,000",$591.74,$591.74,4/21/2023,6/1/2023,8/4/2023,41,41,,10/17/2023,,,,"$8,569",2022,$490,2023,Conventional,,,,,,Lincoln St. And Summit Ave.,"Welcome home to this spacious and sunlit new construction condominium! Located in the heart of the Jersey City Heights, this corner unit 2 bedroom and 2 full bathroom duplex was built with sleek and modern finishes, hardwood floors, quartz countertops, high end GE cafe appliances, Yale smart digital locks, Nest thermostat, central AC, full size washer/dryer and multiple windows allowing in an abundance of natural light. Amazing amenities that complete this elevator building include a large shared roof deck with captivating views, Peloton exercise bike room, bicycle storage, and deeded parking! Once you step outside of this modern brick building you will find yourself in proximity to Central Avenue’s restaurant row, transportation connecting you to NYC, Downtown JC, and Hoboken, and all the beautiful parks that the JC Heights has to offer! ~3 years left on the tax abatement and ~8 years left of the builder warranty."
210002300,SOLD,"JC, Heights",494 LIBERTY AVE,Condominium,1600,207,"$645,000",CONDO-COOP,,1-2,1,"JC, Heights",07307,01203,00007,,,,,,3,1,2,6,,"$645,000","$674,999",$403.13,$403.13,1/27/2021,3/26/2021,6/18/2021,90,90,,6/21/2021,,,,,TBD,,TBD,Conventional,,,,,,Bleecker St & North St,"**OPEN HOUSE 3/13/2021 1-3PM** NEW CONSTRUCTION! 494 Liberty Ave was constructed by one of Jersey City's premier builders where no detail has been spared. This duplex unit boasts a beautiful open floor plan, large kitchen outfitted with top of the line Samsung stainless steel appliances and quartz countertops, hardwood floors throughout, Andersen windows and slider doors, spacious modern bathrooms, a herringbone-tiled family room on the lower level, and a beautiful backyard perfect for entertaining. This home also features two private balconies and tons of natural light. Unit 1 also has shared use of the tandem garage parking. Developer is offering a 10 year new home warranty, and will be applying for a 5 year tax abatement. 494 Liberty Ave is surrounded by tons of options for shopping, dining, entertaining, and transportation."
220000465,SOLD,"JC, Heights",201 NEW YORK AVE,Condominium,1050,1685,"$645,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1,"JC, Heights",07307,03805,00019,,,,,,2,0,2,4,,"$645,000","$645,000",$614.29,$614.29,1/8/2022,1/13/2022,3/11/2022,5,5,,3/13/2022,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Hutton St. & Griffith St.,"New Construction luxury at its finest. This elegant open floorplan features 9 ft ceiling, semi- custom kitchen with floating shelves, along with beautiful gold brass finishes and a beautiful waterfall quartz countertop, along with the appliances that feature GE Profile 30” smart slide in range, Sharp Stainless Steel Microwave Draw oven, GE Profile Counter Depth fingerprint resistant French Door Refrigerator, GE Profile Dishwasher. Walk into your efficient bedrooms featuring Custom made closets designed by “Closets by Design”, Master bathroom with sleek matte black bathroom hardware, Hexagon polished Marble with Mosaic backsplash tiles, frameless glass shower door. The apartment is ready to go “smart home”, wired with interior speakers in the master bath & living room areas, network and cable installation, Honeywell security system that communicates & notifies authorities if alarm is set off and Video intercom accessible through your phone & system. Builder took extra step for noise reduction & sound attenuation between apartments by adding Resilient J channels, purple sound break sheetrock & Serenity mat under hardwood floors, easy commute to NYC and Hoboken via 9th/Congress, 2nd Street light rail, quick bus ride, or a quick 10-minute walk. You'll love being seconds from all the best restaurants and shops that the Riverview Arts District has to offer. Riverview-Fisk Park undergoing a $2M renovation. Come see what this thriving neighborhood has to offer. **5-year tax abatement as per Jersey City Tax assessor, subject to sales price**Images are renderings. This unique & spacious Approx. 1,050 sq ft 2 bedrooms/2 full features, Wide Plank elegant Porcelain floors throughout, in home office area/nook, an exclusive privately fenced in backyard space of approx. 685 sq ft along with beautifully hardscaped pavers and outdoor speakers for outdoor entertainment or after a long day, just relax & enjoy your beautiful outdoor oasis."
260004291,ACTIVE,"JC, Heights",291 NEW YORK AVE,Condominium,840,5876,"$649,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,4,"JC, Heights",07307,,,,,,,,2,0,2,4,,,"$649,000",$772.62,,3/11/2026,,,29,,,3/11/2026,,,,"$14,472",,,,,,,,,,Bowers and South,"Be the first to live in this brand-new 2-bedroom, 2-bathroom residence, thoughtfully designed for modern city living in one of the Jersey City Heights' most convenient and desirable locations.   This sun-filled home features all new construction and finishes throughout, offering a clean, contemporary feel from top to bottom. The open living space flows seamlessly into a sleek, modern kitchen with new appliances, stylish cabinetry, and quality finishes perfect for everyday living and entertaining.A true highlight of the home is the private roof deck, offering sweeping skyline views and an ideal outdoor retreat for relaxing, hosting guests, or enjoying warm summer evenings above the city.  Location sets this apartment apart. Just steps away is the neighborhood park, home to a vibrant seasonal farmers market, green space, and a strong community vibe. Hoboken is only minutes away, giving you easy access to its waterfront, dining, nightlife, and shopping.Commuting is effortless with quick access to Hoboken Terminal and PATH trains, providing direct routes to Midtown and Downtown Manhattan. Multiple nearby bus options make getting around even easier.   Surrounded by local cafes, restaurants, and everyday conveniences, this apartment delivers the perfect balance of modern comfort, outdoor space, and unmatched connectivity.Schedule your private showing today and experience elevated living in the Jersey City Heights."
210001940,SOLD,"JC, Heights",28 ST PAULS AVE,Condominium,,1691,"$649,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,2,"JC, Heights",07306,6802,16,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,6,,"$649,000","$649,000",,,1/22/2021,2/9/2021,3/25/2021,18,18,,3/26/2021,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,concord and baldwin,"The search for a more perfect home has been met with every must-have: space, luxury, outdoor and location. Your best luxury lifestyle awaits with this thoughtfully-planned, new construction home plotted in Jersey City’s hottest neighborhood. Steps from Journal Square PATH, tucked away on a tree-lined residential street, this brand new 3 bedroom, 2 bath offers superb spaciousness and a priceless private rooftop touting NYC views.   The classic ultra-wide floorplan offers oversized windows and light oak floors for bright and airy appeal. Modern kitchen impresses with quartz counters, herringbone backsplash, custom cabinetry, pendant lighting and dark stainless Samsung appliances. The master ensuite offers a private balcony while all bathrooms offer porcelain tiling, shower or soaker tub, matte black or brushed nickel fixtures and plenty of storage.   Ideally located less than a 10-minute walk to the Journal Square PATH train, the peaceful residential neighborhood is centrally located with easy access to downtown Jersey City, Hoboken and the Heights. Great parks in every direction with sport-haven Pershing Field Park, the nature reserve Reservoir and picturesque Hamilton Park, these homes equal the ultimate urban lifestyle with both vibrant community and the peaceful sanctuary of home."
220008379,SOLD,"JC, Heights",404 PALISADE AVE,Condominium,1229,5759,"$649,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07307,3903,18,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,5,,"$649,000","$649,000",$528.07,$528.07,5/11/2022,5/17/2022,7/8/2022,6,6,,7/12/2022,,,,"$7,805",2021,$202,,Conventional,No,No,,,,Franklin and  Hutton,"Welcome to this luxurious exquisitely designed and newly renovated 3 bed, 2 bath 1229 sf home Live in one of the best locations in Jersey City Heights! Open concept high-end design condo features modern kitchen with shaker cabinets,Statuarino Venato quartz countertop, white Carrara backsplash and Brass handles , stainless appliances. The modern home with classic layout includes expansive living, dining and kitchen area, with timeless 5 gleaming hardwood floors throughout. Attention to detail has not been spared, recessed lighting and sub-ceiling insulation between floors to minimize sounds and solid doors.   The oversized owners ensuite features sliding glass doors leading to a large private balcony, a stunning ensuite bath with upgraded fixtures, imported porcelain tile, “Kohler” faucets plus large walk – in closet with washer/dryer. Additional bedrooms include design elements like plantation shutters, build-out reading bench and plenty of closets for additional storage.  Settled into a tree-lined street on pristine Palisade Avenue, this home is located steps from Riverview Fisk Park with cliffside NYC views, plus walkable access to NJ and NY transit or Citi bike stations and Congress St light rail station nearby. Jersey City Heights is home to the perfect blend of urban and escape, including essential shops, , restaurants, nightlife, expansive parks and impressive lifestyle to value ratio. Low monthly fees add to the appeal of this impressive property. "
250021204,SOLD,"JC, Heights",549 PALISADE AVE,Condominium,1230,5836,"$649,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2-A,"JC, Heights",07307,2305,27,Heights,,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$649,000","$649,000",$527.64,$527.64,10/14/2025,10/20/2025,12/12/2025,6,6,,12/12/2025,,,,"$9,718",2023,$500,,Conventional,,,,,,Bowers & South,"Perfectly situated on Palisade Avenue between Riverview Park and the Congress Street Light Rail Station, this oversized 2 bed, 2 full bath offers a lifestyle in Jersey City Heights. Fully renovated in 2021, the timeless Tudor stone facade welcomes you with character and charm. The condo’s spacious entryway is home to Pottery Barn shelving, hooks, and seating, as well as a full bathroom. High ceilings and blonde oak hardwood floors lead you down the hall to the massive living/dining area where recessed lighting and crown molding provide style and comfort. The kitchen features stainless steel appliances, white quartz countertops, and chic gold hardware. The first bedroom is spacious and boasts a deep closet and ceiling fan. The serene primary is home to a custom California Closet, stylish full bathroom, and balconette. Other features include: a full-sized, champagne color Samsung washer and dryer, ceiling fans in each bedroom, custom shelving and wood slat wall details. In the building, a common storage room provides a place to leave your stroller, bike, or luggage. Enjoy the Sunday Farmer’s Market in Riverview Park, coffee at ModCup, lil dove, or the COMING SOON Hybrid on Palisade, brunch at The Cliff, dinner at Corto, wine from Riverview Wines, and all The Heights has to offer. Welcome home!"
250019914,SOLD,"JC, Heights",63 JEFFERSON AVE,Condominium,1200,6638,"$650,000",CONDO-COOP,,1-2,1-2 Duplex,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,3,1,2,6,,"$650,000","$650,000",$541.67,$541.67,9/26/2025,10/10/2025,12/2/2025,14,14,,12/19/2025,,,,,,$250,,Conventional,,,,,,Baldwin Ave. & Oakland Ave.,"**Special Financing, Community Lending Rates at 5.75%**  Discover the perfect blend of sophisticated design and urban convenience in this strikingly modern duplex condo, nestled on a quiet side street between Palisade and Central Avenues. Featuring dramatic architectural elements and sleek, clean lines, this home offers an expansive two-story layout designed for effortless living and entertaining.   The open-concept main level is anchored by an oversized double waterfall island, seamlessly integrating defined living and dining spaces. Contemporary aesthetic, with a stylish powder room on main floor. The chef’s kitchen boasts bold black quartz countertops, a tiled backsplash, stainless steel appliances, and custom cabinetry, with an oversized island offering seating for four.   Upstairs leads to three spacious bedrooms and two luxurious full baths. The king-sized primary suite features a spa-inspired ensuite with black and white marble tile, a glass-enclosed rain shower, and an oversized floating vanity. The second bath exudes tranquility with wood-toned tiles, an extra-deep soaking tub, and dual shower heads.   Perfectly positioned for commuters, this home is just steps from Hoboken Stairs, 2nd Street Light Rail, Congress Street Elevator, and Journal Square PATH. Enjoy the vibrant neighborhood with coffee shops, restaurants, farmer’s markets, Pershing Field, and Riverview-Fisk Park offering breathtaking  NYC skyline views.    **Special financing available with preferred lender Jackie Koven at Cross Country Mortgage. Grants ranging from $15,000 to $22,000 available for down payment and/or closing cost assistance. Interest rates as low as 5.75%**"
210004493,SOLD,"JC, Heights",135 PROSPECT ST,Condominium,1134,1653,"$650,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,#1,"JC, Heights",07307,04902,00013,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,7,,"$650,000","$669,000",$573.19,$573.19,2/25/2021,3/25/2021,5/10/2021,28,28,,5/11/2021,,,,"$9,916",,$352,,Conventional,,,,,,Central & Lienau,"Welcome home to your gorgeous new JC Heights Condo with a GIGANTIC 1,300+ SF PRIVATE BACKYARD!!! Oak floors, quartz counters, SS Appliances, 42 cabinets, W/D in unit, recessed LED lighting, 10-11' ceilings, a huge deeded storage room (13' x 12') and Central HVAC units. Steps from Pershing Field, and just blocks from Bread & Salt, Renato's Pizza Master and Stop & Shop."
240012270,SOLD,"JC, Heights",234 WEBSTER AVE,Condominium,1442,6078,"$650,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1R,"JC, Heights",07307,2306,5,,,,,,4,0,2,8,,"$650,000","$675,000",$450.76,$450.76,6/25/2024,8/29/2024,11/1/2024,65,65,,11/1/2024,,,,$0,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Bowers and South,"Welcome to this fully renovated duplex-style 4-bedroom, 2-bathroom condo, perfectly situated in the heart of Jersey City Heights. This modern residence boasts 12 foot ceilings and recessed lighting giving the space a lofty feel and creating a bright and inviting atmosphere throughout. The primary bedroom is bathed in natural light, offering a serene retreat. Enjoy the luxury of a private 529 sq. ft. backyard featuring a firepit, ideal for relaxing or entertaining. The first-floor kitchen is a chef's delight with stainless steel appliances and elegant quartz countertops. Both bathrooms feature ultra modern finishes, including Cove lighting and a frameless shower door in the main level bathroom. The lower level, perfect for an in-law suite, includes a kitchenette, two bedrooms, a full bath, a den/work from home space, and an in-unit washer and dryer. Energy efficiency is a priority with the state-of-the-art HVAC system. Just four blocks from Central Avenue, you'll have access to a vibrant array of eateries and shops, making this location unbeatable. Don't miss out on this exceptional home in a prime location! The Jersey City Heights neighborhood boasts close proximity to the Holland Tunnel, Home Depot, and Newport Center Mall, ensuring effortless access to major bus lines as well as the Congress Street and Second Street light rail stations. This prime location offers residents a convenient and direct route to New York City."
220010456,SOLD,"JC, Heights",310 PALISADE AVE,Condominium,1137,1597,"$650,000",CONDO-COOP,,5,11,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,6,,"$650,000","$599,000",$571.68,$571.68,6/8/2022,6/10/2022,8/16/2022,2,2,,8/16/2022,,,,,9362,$473,,Conventional,,,,,,Ravine Ave & Cuneo Pl,"Perched on coveted Palisade Ave in the Heights, this freshly renovated three bedroom, penthouse duplex home comes with both parking AND incredible NYC views from each floor (as well as the private rooftop!), and offers easy walkability to nearby Riverview Fisk Park, light rail and more.  Light floods in through the large windows with full NYC views, illuminating the classic hardwood floors and wide open floor plan. Kitchen is finished with white quartz counters, shaker cabinets, mosaic tile backsplash and stainless appliances. Large bathrooms offer tile finished to ceiling, bathtub and shower, and spacious vanity with medicine cabinet for added storage. Upstairs loft-style bedroom provides excellent multi-purpose space, and gives great access to the private rooftop. Owners enjoy brand new full-size Maytag washer and dryer as well.  Beautiful, historic brick building is settled in the heart of Jersey City Heights, a neighborhood known for its eclectic shops and restaurants, close-knit community, excellent parks and proximity to nearby Hoboken, Downtown and NYC. "
210012258,SOLD,"JC, Heights",214 SHERMAN AVE,Condominium,,1691,"$650,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,6,,"$650,000","$649,000",,,5/20/2021,6/3/2021,7/6/2021,14,14,,7/7/2021,,,,,,$150,,Conventional,,,,,,Bowers & South St,"Upgraded living plus location equal the ultimate property pair in this 3-bedroom with backyard in the heart of The Heights. Settled into a tree-lined street blocks from the main thoroughfare and major parks, this beautiful brick building with 2 car non-tandem garage parking offers high ceilings, high-end finishes and outdoor access to meet all the must-haves.  The white and natural wood banister stairwell lead up to loft-style vaulted ceilings and illuminated open floorplan. Light pours in through the large arched windows onto the light oak floors, classic crown molding and stylish chandelier and pendant lighting throughout. Eat-in kitchen showcases a peninsula island plus natural granite counters, mosaic tile backsplash, custom wood cabinets, spill-proof wood tile floors and Samsung stainless appliances.  Master ensuite offers ethereal tray ceiling, lots of natural light plus ceiling fan and companion closets. Additional bedrooms and separate laundry room give ideal layout, while both bathrooms showcase continued granite counters, excellent storage and soaker tub plus shower for design and utility.  Big beautiful shared backyard wows with wall-to-wall grass and high exposed brick walls for privacy. Right off Central Avenue with access to vibrant shops and community, and equidistant to both Washington Park with amenities and Riverview-Fisk Park with views, this home sweet home truly has it all."
210008314,SOLD,"JC, Heights",974 SUMMIT AVE,Condominium,,1691,"$650,000",CONDO-COOP,,4,410,"JC, Heights",07037,2801,5.01,,,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$650,000","$630,000",,,4/8/2021,5/11/2021,7/22/2021,33,33,,8/10/2021,,,,,,$412,,Conventional,,,,,,Griffith & Licoln,"Welcome to THE SUMMIT in the heart of Jersey City Heights; New Construction, Boutique Condo building with open floor plans & amazing amenities, including:  a shared over-sized roof deck with stunning, 360 panoramic views, elevator, Peloton exercise bike room, bicycle storage. Deeded parking also available. Unit 410 is a modern open layout home with 2 large bedrooms, 2 full bathrooms and ample storage on both level. Elegantly built with modern, high-end finishes, quartz counter tops, hardwood floors, high end GE Cafe appliances (including smart tech induction vented range with Wi-Fi cooking access). Additional smart home features include Yale smart digital locks, Nest thermostat, Verizon FiOS ready,  tankless water heater, Central AC, full size washer/vented dryer. This impressive brick building at the corner of Summit Ave and Lincoln Street is ideally located in Jersey City Heights, near Central Avenue’s Restaurant row, NYC transit and steps away from all of JC Heights parks. Available for Immediate Occupancy and is eligible for 5 year tax abatement!"
230000329,SOLD,"JC, Heights",210 CAMBRIDGE AVE,Condominium,1146,1597,"$650,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1A,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,6,,"$650,000","$650,000",$567.19,$567.19,1/6/2023,1/13/2023,3/9/2023,7,7,,3/9/2023,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Congress & South St,"Garden level brings grandeur in this luxurious and newly refinished parisian-style home. Step inside to the three bedroom and two bath home plus beautiful backyard in Jersey City Heights. Stunning Haussmann architecture exterior shines with stone walls, square roof, wrought iron Juliet balconies and dormer windows.   Classic elegance stretches throughout with gleaming hardwood floors, crown molding, ceiling fans and oversized windows. Open floorplan living offers access to the private backyard directly from the living area, ideal for extended outdoor living and entertainment. Eat-in kitchen offers oversized island with pendant lighting, quartz counters, cherry custom cabinets, tile backsplash and stainless appliances.   Spacious bedrooms bring plenty of natural light with primary ensuite offering extra large walk-in closet. Bathrooms offer both bathtub and shower with sizable vanity and medicine cabinet mirror for additional storage.   One block from both Washington Park and Central Avenue, this home is situated for ideal access to both urban and outdoor living. Jersey City Heights is the fastest growing part of this eclectic community, offering boutique shops and restaurants, expansive parks, excellent schools and easy access to NYC and surrounding neighborhoods."
