230013415,SOLD,"JC, Heights",139 SHERMAN PL,Condominium,1050,1713,"$674,900",CONDO-COOP,,2,203,"JC, Heights",07307,03503,00001,,Sherman Place,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$674,900","$649,900",$642.76,$642.76,8/10/2023,9/21/2023,11/13/2023,42,42,,11/14/2023,,,,$0,,$431,,Conventional,,,,,,Kennedy and Sanford,"Presenting an exquisite condominium nestled in the heart of Jersey City Heights. This splendid residence boasts two generously proportioned bedrooms and two elegant bathrooms, providing a perfect blend of comfort and luxury. Just over 1000 square feet, the condo offers a well-thought-out layout that maximizes both space and functionality. Upon entering, you are greeted by a sophisticated and modern interior design that sets the tone for the entire unit. The open-concept living area seamlessly transitions from the inviting living room to the well-appointed kitchen, creating a harmonious space for relaxation and entertainment. The kitchen features top-of-the-line appliances, sleek cabinetry, and ample countertop space, catering to the needs of culinary enthusiasts and hosts alike. The two spacious bedrooms are designed to offer tranquility and privacy. The primary bedroom comes complete with an en-suite bathroom, providing a serene retreat after a long day. The second bedroom, equally spacious, offers versatility for use as a guest room, home office, or personal sanctuary. Both bathrooms are adorned with contemporary finishes and fixtures, evoking a spa-like ambiance. Natural light floods the living spaces through large windows, creating an airy and inviting atmosphere. The condo also features thoughtfully integrated storage solutions, ensuring a clutter-free living environment and in-unit Washer and Dryer. Commuting to Manhattan and other parts of Jersey City is a breeze, thanks to the well-connected transportation options in the vicinity. Parking is also available for purchase! This building truly caters to a sophisticated urban lifestyle. A unique opportunity to own a slice of modern elegance and urban convenience. A must-see!"
210010768,SOLD,"JC, Heights",34 LIENAU PL,Condominium,1250,1186,"$675,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07307,05007,00035,,,,,,3,0,2,6,,"$675,000","$675,000",$540.00,$540.00,5/5/2021,5/22/2021,7/6/2021,17,17,,7/6/2021,,,,"$9,268",,$189,,Conventional,,,,,,Reservoir Ave & Booraem Ave,"Enjoy outdoor living at it's finest with this spectacular 700 sq. ft. PRIVATE rooftop with Trex decking and DuPont Foreverlawn high performance grass! This renovated and sunlit 3 bedroom, 2 bathroom, 1250 sq. ft. unit features a glamorous gourmet kitchen with top of the line Bosch stainless steel appliances, Alusso Cuccina cabinetry and Cashmere Carrera quartz countertops. Retreat to your spa-like master bathroom complete with a soaking tub and standing shower with Porcelanosa tile, double vanities and Hansgrohe plumbing. This smart home also boasts a range of high tech gadgets such as Nest thermostats, Nest protect (smoke / CO detectors) in every room, Ring doorbell, Sonos AMP, Sonance speakers and is pre-wired with HDMI. Gorgeous oak hardwood flooring throughout, LED lighting, Central AC and Samsung washer/dry round out the amenities of this fantastic unit.  Located in the heart of Jersey City Heights you will find a vibrant and artistic community close to parks, farmers market and coffee shops and steps to transportation into Hoboken and NYC. Don't miss out!"
240012291,SOLD,"JC, Heights",90 WEBSTER AVE,Condominium,1150,1597,"$675,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,2,0,2,6,,"$675,000","$699,000",$586.96,$586.96,6/25/2024,8/2/2024,9/25/2024,38,38,,9/26/2024,,,,,,$295,,Conventional,,,,,,Franklin and Ferry,"Get the best of both worlds in this new construction garden-level home featuring private outdoor space, modern design and ideal location in Jersey City Heights. The front space offers street access, serving as an ideal live/work area, perfect for a home office, workout room, or art studio. Inside, the home features two bedrooms and two bathrooms, along with modern design and functional features like smarthome upgrades or classic wood tile flooring throughout.   The open concept kitchen boasts contemporary white cabinets, quartz counters, herringbone subway tile backsplash, and stainless fixtures and appliances. Bathrooms are beautifully designed with floor-to-ceiling tile, spacious vanities, and options for either a bathtub or a shower. The primary ensuite stands out with a stunning onyx accent wall and wainscoting, as well as beautiful glass door access to the backyard. The private outdoor space is complete with pavers and landscaping, offering a secluded sanctuary for daily relaxation and entertaining. Finally, the dedicated laundry room offers added convenience with a brand-new LG washer and dryer.  Situated in a classic red brick building on a tree-lined street, this home is just blocks to the 2nd Street Light Rail and the Hoboken stairs, providing easy commutes and access to surrounding areas and NYC. Residents enjoy nearby Riverview Fisk Park and Pershing Field Parks, with stunning city views and playgrounds, or nature spaces, farmer’s markets and swimming! Jersey City Heights is known for its vibrant community, excellent schools, peaceful parks and central location."
260004489,ACTIVE,"JC, Heights",37 SPRUCE ST,Condominium,1180,6078,"$675,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,5,"JC, Heights",07306,5404,8,Heights,Spruce Hill Condo,,,,3,0,2,6,,,"$675,000",$572.03,,3/13/2026,,,27,,,3/13/2026,,,,,,$265,,,,,,,,Off of JFK Blvd between Floyd & Stagg,"3 Bed | 2 Bath | Deeded Garage + Driveway | Private balcony | Top Floor  In Jersey City Heights, a home at this price point with these amenities isn't a typo—it’s a rare find where style, comfort, and location come together perfectly. This sun-drenched top-floor residence delivers the expansive space, soaring light, and premium parking that city buyers dream about but rarely find in one package. Pets are welcome, making this the perfect long-term sanctuary for your entire family.  THE RESIDENCE | From the moment you step inside, you're greeted by a bright, open layout filled with natural light. The oversized living room flows seamlessly into the kitchen, anchored by soaring 12-foot ceilings and four skylights that create a dramatic, airy atmosphere. Oversized Pella windows frame stunning Meadowlands sunsets, which you can enjoy from the peace of your private balcony.  The kitchen is both timeless and functional, pairing crisp quartz countertops and stainless steel appliances with classic subway tile. Whether you're hosting a dinner party or enjoying a quiet morning, the open living and dining area flexes effortlessly to suit your lifestyle.  A HOME TO GROW INTO |  All three bedrooms are generously proportioned and equipped with custom closet systems, but it is the versatile layout that truly shines for a growing family:  The Primary Suite: A true retreat featuring double closets and a spa-inspired en-suite bath.  The 2ND Bedroom: Perfectly sized to create a dream 5 or 6-year-old’s room, with plenty of space for a full bed, desk, and play area.  The 3RD Bedroom: An ideal, sun-lit nursery or baby room, situated to provide a quiet and cozy environment for the littlest member of the family.  An oversized hall walk-in storage/coat closet solves the perennial city-living storage challenge, keeping your living space organized and serene.  THE PARKING ADVANTAGE |  Forget the daily parking hunt. This home includes a deeded private garage plus an additional driveway space—a combination that is genuinely rare in the Heights and adds incredible value and convenience to your daily routine.  PREMIER LOCATION |  Tucked away on a quiet, one-way street, easy accesst to Journal Square PATH and buses (stop is on Spruce & JFK), putting Manhattan less than 20 minutes away. With parks, top-rated schools, and vibrant neighborhood dining just steps from your front door, this is the urban oasis you've been waiting for.  Offered at Under $800K. Schedule your private tour today to experience this unique Heights gem."
210003615,SOLD,"JC, Heights",204 CAMBRIDGE AVE,Condominium,1200,6069,"$675,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07307,02203/0000,00009/0000,Heights,204 Cambridge Avenue,,,,2,0,2,7,,"$675,000","$699,000",$562.50,$562.50,2/12/2021,3/17/2021,4/30/2021,33,33,,5/1/2021,,"$578,600",2020,"$9,350",2020,$200,2021,Conventional,No,No,No,,,CENTRAL AVENUE AND HANCOCK AVENUE,"Newly built in 2016 and smartly situated in 'The Heights' ~ this sleek and modern, 2 bed/2 full bath upper-level townhome boasts two levels of living space with tons of natural light and a massive rooftop offering spectacular NYC skyline views. Beautiful hardwood floors throughout, the main level also features nineteen (19') foot ceilings with a wall of oversized, brilliant windows which operate with the 'touch of a finger' courtesy of an electronic wand. Prepare meals in the beautifully-equipped kitchen outfitted with professional-grade appliances, miles of stunning counter-space, a wine/beverage fridge, a subway-styled back-splash, recessed illumination and a center island with bar seating. Directly opposite the working kitchen lies a generous soft-seating area sizable enough to accommodate a dining table. A coat closet/pantry complete the winning first level.   Level ll offers a large (15' x 17') family/great room and cabinetry to accommodate a TV and components. Again ~ hardwood flooring runs throughout the entire level with the singular exception of the two, full baths. The generously-sized, master suite (13' x 17') offers a full, private bath with a walk-in shower. The suite also features recessed illumination, a lighted paddle fan, a fully-outfitted walk-in closet and a set of sliding glass doors leading to a private balcony. The second bedroom is nicely sized at 12' x 13' offering two closets, overhead lighting and yet another illuminated paddle fan. The full, hall bath with a shower positioned over a tub nicely services the second bedroom.  A fabulous rooftop retreat awaits you as you step out and experience a panoramic perspective of lower Manhattan ~ which seems so close one can almost reach out and touch the iconic structures which make up the world's most recognizable skyline."
220020967,SOLD,"JC, Heights",124 TERRACE AVE,Condominium,1555,6078,"$675,000",CONDO-COOP,,1 & B,201,"JC, Heights",07307,02503,00005-02,Heights,,,,,3,1,2,6,,"$675,000","$675,000",$434.08,$434.08,12/3/2022,12/15/2022,2/24/2023,12,12,,2/25/2023,,,,"$9,500",2022,$225,,FHA,No,No,,,,Thorne & Lincoln,"Welcome to the Terrace Development, one of the finest quality ground-up new construction property, developed by one of the highly reputable Jersey City Developers, GN Management. 124 Terrace Avenue Unit 201 duplex of this property offers 3 bedrooms 2.5 full bathrooms with 1,555 SQFT. of living space and 286 SQFT. of Rooftop Deck. This immaculate condominium features 10' ceilings, 9' solid doors, white oak hardwood flooring with classic grey finish, recessed and pendant lighting, electric fireplaces, oversized Anderson windows allowing abundant natural sunlight throughout the day. White eat-in kitchen shows style with waterfall quartz counters & backsplash, custom shaker cabinets, pot-filler, drawer microwave, stainless steel appliances and a massive pantry. Spacious bedrooms offer plenty of closet space, with the primary en-suite featuring spa-like modern bathroom and extra-large custom walk-in-closet. Each bathroom is meticulously designed with high end finishes, floating vanities and smart mirrors. A tech-lover’s dream wired for plenty of mod cons, including 9 built-in audio speakers, smart mirrors, smart lighting, ring doorbell, security cameras with mobile-app connectivity, sonos amplifiers, yale locks and nest thermostat, rival Manhattan standard luxury.  Location is very convenient for NYC commuters with a multitude of public transportation options commute to NYC PORT AUTHORITY, JSQ PATH, Downtown JC and Hoboken. Centrally located between the Lincoln and Holland Tunnel, drive to Manhattan in less than 15 mins. Walking distance to Washington Park, Central Avenue and 9th St Light Rail station, makes this location even more desirable for sports, shopping, dining and commuting.  This neighborhood is known for great community and excellent schools. 124 Terrace unit 201 comes with 1 deeded car parking in the garage. In a competitive new development market, quality and affordability is what separates the Terrace Development from the rest! Come check it out before its gone and begin your new year in your brand new home!  10-year new home warranty, 5-year Tax Abatement! Some finishes may differ from these photos/copy. Contact listing agent today for private showing! "
260006156,ACTIVE,"JC, Heights",684 SUMMIT AVE,Condominium,1653,1724,"$675,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1,"JC, Heights",07306,5603,67,Heights,,,,,3,0,3,7,,,"$675,000",$408.35,,4/7/2026,,,2,,,4/7/2026,,,,"$11,037",2025,,,,,,,,,Beacon and Hopkins,"Welcome to Summit Lodge, where classic charm meets modern luxury in this expansive, sun-drenched 3-bedroom, 3-full-bathroom duplex. Boasting over 1,600 square feet of meticulously renovated (2023) living space, this bright and airy residence is designed for a seamless indoor-outdoor lifestyle. The main level features a custom chef’s kitchen with designer quartz countertops and Porcelanosa finishes, while the versatile lower level—complete with its own private entrance and kitchenette—serves as the perfect guest suite or quiet work-from-home retreat.  Enjoy ultimate privacy with advanced sound-dampening products used throughout and step outside to your own private backyard, a rare urban oasis perfect for entertaining or relaxing. With a second private entrance, smart-home technology, and a prime location just minutes from the Journal Square PATH for a quick 20-minute NYC commute, this home offers the perfect balance of scale, sophistication, and convenience."
220020850,SOLD,"JC, Heights",218 HANCOCK AVE,Condominium,1162,1597,"$675,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,6,,"$675,000","$699,000",$580.90,$580.90,12/1/2022,12/22/2022,2/2/2023,21,21,,2/3/2023,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,South St & Congress,"Make your next move to this beautifully renovated home with private backyard, storage and EV charger parking from Nkay Construction. Set one block from Washington Park in Jersey City Heights, the three bedroom layout is classically finished with crown molding, hardwood floors and large Pella windows.   White kitchen shines with sparkling waterfall quartz counters, stainless farm sink, shaker cabinets, blue accent shiplap, and black Samsung appliances. Smarthome features include ring doorbell, camera and security system, and nest thermostat.   The spacious private backyard offers an ideal urban escape with pavers, landscaping and vibrant mural wall. Bathrooms boast beautiful marble double vanity, glass shower or bathtub combo and polished chrome fixtures. Owners enjoy a dedicated utility area with Samsung washer and dryer, plus private basement storage area and side-by-side, EV charger, compact car parking.  Modern gray brick building is settled on a tree-lined street just around the corner from expansive Washington Park with sports facilities, playground and walking paths. Jersey City Heights is known for its great community, excellent schools and easy NYC access, with vibrant shops, restaurants and parks!   "
240001116,SOLD,"JC, Heights",3464 KENNEDY BLVD,Condominium,1142,1692,"$675,000",CONDO-COOP,,PH,PH1,"JC, Heights",07307,,,,The Packard,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$675,000","$679,000",$591.07,$591.07,1/19/2024,2/11/2024,3/29/2024,23,23,,4/12/2024,,,,$0,,$496,,Conventional,,,,,,Charles Street and Thorne Street,"A Historic Icon in The Heights.   The Packard JC was once the Packard Motor Car Company’s premiere showroom, which produced American luxury automobiles from 1899 through 1956. Today, The Packard JC has been revitalized into 14 new luxury condominiums while preserving the coveted Neo-Classical architectural details from its early 20th century past. Residential upgrades include Latch keyless entry system, Younity* high speed internet, secure WiFi included in the maintenance, and a dedicated package room for every day convenience.   PH1, 1,142 square foot duplex two bedroom two bathroom has a stylish kitchen with stainless steel appliances, under-mount sinks, breakfast bars and leathered granite countertops with a waterfall edge. Central AC, Navian on-demand tankless water heater and an in-unit washer-dryer ensure absolute comfort plus there’s a host of dramatic features including 12 ft ceilings, concrete beams, exposed ductwork and engineered hardwood herringbone flooring. This residence also features a wraparound private terrace with amazing city views off the primary bedroom and additional storage space for everyday needs. Pre-wired for Younity highest speed internet at a cost lower than major carriers with 24/7 customer support and available upon move-in!  The Packard JC is an elevator building with a 5 year tax abatement available. Storage units available.  This steel and concrete construction, loft-style building is located close to the bustling Central Avenue with restaurants, shopping, cafes and parks nearby.  Transportation is effortless; bus 125 at the corner and bus 119 to Port Authority/Congress Street Light Rail connecting you to NYC with easy links to the Journal Square transportation hub.   *Younity is not only high speed internet but it is the most economical, prewired highest speed internet available in a residential building, at a cost that is lower than the major carriers, while offering 24/7 customer support. Younity is pre-existing and available upon move-in for all residences. "
220004997,SOLD,"JC, Heights",483 PALISADE AVE,Condominium,945,1691,"$675,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,3,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$675,000","$650,000",$714.29,$714.29,3/23/2022,4/18/2022,5/27/2022,26,26,,5/31/2022,,,,,,$250,,Conventional,,,,,,Griffith & Bowers,"Soak in the sights with wall-to-wall windows and juliet balcony giving crystal clear views of the NYC skyline and overlooking park. This perfectly located, high-end condo is situated right on Riverview Fisk Park for lavish luxury and an incomparable vantage point.   Loads of natural light flood the classic design and beautiful hardwood floors with details like window casings and tray ceilings. Open floorplan offers outdoor access and abundant space big enough for living, kitchen and full dining area. Kitchen showcases quartz counters, tile backsplash, custom cherry cabinets and stainless appliances with room for an added island or eat-in dining.   Primary ensuite offers double-glass doors leading out to the private balcony terrace. Bathrooms offer neutral tones, plus soaker tub or shower and vanity for additional storage. Ample closet space and separate utility room offer added convenience and value.  Beautiful brick building is newly finished with great curb appeal and even better location with walkability to 9th Street LightRail, PATH train, vibrant neighborhood and Riverview Fisk Park as your permanent playground."
220000958,SOLD,"JC, Heights",210 CAMBRIDGE AVE,Condominium,1300,1691,"$675,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,3,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,6,,"$675,000","$675,000",$519.23,$519.23,1/17/2022,3/10/2022,5/11/2022,52,52,,5/12/2022,,,,$0,,$0,,Conventional,,,,,,south and congress,"Make resolutions a reality with this newly refurbished three bedroom and two bath home plus beautiful balcony in Jersey City Heights. Stunning exterior Haussmann architecture shines with stone exterior, square roof, wrought iron Juliet balconies and dormer windows. One block from both Washington Park and Central Avenue, this home is situated for ideal access to both urban and outdoor living.  Classic elegance stretches throughout with gleaming hardwood floors, crown molding, ceiling fans and oversized windows. Walk into this wide open floor plan with backyard balcony directly off the living area, ideal for exterior square footage and entertainment. Eat-in kitchen offers oversized island with pendant lighting, with quartz counters, cherry custom cabinets, tile backsplash and stainless appliances.   Spacious bedrooms bring plenty of natural light with primary suite offering extra large walk-in closet. Bathrooms offer both bathtub and shower with sizable vanity and medicine cabinet mirror for additional storage. Jersey City Heights is the fastest growing part of this eclectic community, offering boutique shops and restaurants, expansive parks, excellent schools and easy access to NYC and surrounding neighborhoods. "
210009482,SOLD,"JC, Heights",278.5 SHERMAN AVE,Condominium,,1691,"$675,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1,"JC, Heights",07307,1604,35,Heights,,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$675,000","$675,000",,,4/21/2021,5/3/2021,6/14/2021,12,12,,6/16/2021,,,,,,,,Cash,,,,,,Congress & North,"Do a double-take with this dazzling two bedroom duplex, with over 1,200 square feet and priceless private outdoor. Feel the spaciousness in this newly constructed home, and truly trade up with the high-end finishes and quality upgrades prevalent by this coveted Jersey City developer.   Glide through the white oak floors into the ample living, dining and kitchen areas and into your beautiful backyard. Kitchen features waterfall white quartz counters, stone tile accents, farmhouse sink with pull-down faucet and black Samsung appliances. Home brings both a classic and modern appeal with classic crown molding, recess lighting and excellent smart-home extras.   Steps from enormous Washington Park with tennis, baseball, soccer, splash pad, soft play, dog run and more, this home is settled on a quiet residential street in the heart of Jersey City Heights. Enjoy access to essential shops on Central Avenue, excellent schools, vibrant community and easy NYC access. "
210014575,SOLD,"JC, Heights",103 THORNE ST,Condominium,1517,5678,"$675,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07307,02603,00023,Heights,,,,,3,1,2,6,,"$675,000","$699,000",$444.96,$444.96,6/16/2021,8/23/2021,10/14/2021,68,68,,10/21/2021,,,,,,,,Conventional,No,No,,,,JFK Blvd & Summit Ave,"New construction in the vibrant Heights neighborhood in Jersey City.  This home is located directly off the major commercial hub of Central Ave with plenty of shopping and dining options along with bus routes directly to Manhattan.  The building itself is on a 25x100 lot size, however since it is attached on one side there is additional interior width.  Importantly, this building offers NON-TANDEM parking for both upper and lower level owners (unit 2 has additional storage closet in garage as well).  The upper level features vaulted ceilings, a rear balcony, and craftfully designed kitchen with Samsung appliances and quartz counters.  This home will be bright all year long with no obstructions on the second floor.  This is a great move-in ready opportunity to take advantage of the long term benefits of the Heights and Jersey City magnet schools.  Seller to provide credit of $2000 for buyer to purchase washer / dryer."
240017900,SOLD,"JC, Heights",234 WEBSTER AVE,Condominium,1300,6078,"$675,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1L,"JC, Heights",07307,2306,5,,,,,,3,0,2,9,,"$675,000","$679,000",$519.23,$519.23,9/10/2024,9/30/2024,11/15/2024,20,19,,11/18/2024,,,,,,$250,,Conventional,,,,,,Palisade and Central,"***ONLY 2 UNITS LEFT! SELLER OFFERING 1 YEAR OF PARKING CREDIT!*** Recently constructed duplex condo with a boutique-style ambiance and private backyard! Boasting three bedrooms, 2 baths, 2 levels of entertainment areas, and a second kitchenette on the lower level. Situated in the coveted Jersey City Heights neighborhood, 234 Webster offers top-notch appliances and finishes including washer/dryer in unit and stainless steel appliances. With impressive 12-foot ceilings and modern black custom architect windows, the home is flooded with natural light. Thoughtful design is evident, with custom-built Chanel-inspired closets, elegant quartz one-piece backsplash and countertops in the kitchens, and real oak wood European-style stairs. The bathrooms feature innovative three-way plumbing fixtures, upgraded hardware. Cove lighting adds a touch of sophistication, complemented by upgraded tile finishes, floor-to-ceiling tiling, and a clean coat of high-end frameless shower glass doors. Experience tranquility with exceptional soundproofing, minimizing noise transmission between floors. The prime location is nestled between Palisade Ave and Central Avenue. Enjoy your neighbors of Corto, Riverview Wine and Spirits, The Franklin, Bread & Salt, Low Fi Bar, and Dulce De Leche Bakery. Close to great attractions such as Jersey City Mural, Hudson River Waterfront Walkway, Trader Joes, and shopping along Central Avenue. The Jersey City Heights neighborhood is very close to the Holland Tunnel, Home Depot, and Newport Center Mall, providing easy access to major bus lines and the Congress St light rail and 2nd St light rail, offering a convenient and direct route to NYC."
210021570,SOLD,"JC, Heights",15 GRAHAM ST,Condominium,1316,1691,"$680,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,2,1,2,5,,"$680,000","$695,000",$516.72,$516.72,9/15/2021,10/8/2021,11/23/2021,23,23,,11/23/2021,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Central Ave & Summit Ave,"Expand your lifestyle with this beautiful duplex in the heart of the Heights. Two floors, one-car garage tandem parking and a big beautiful backyard only accentuate the modern finishes and smart home features in this oversized two bed, two-and-a-half bath layout.  Downstairs features the modern eat-in kitchen with ample quartz counters and backsplash, gleaming custom soft close cabinets and Samsung smart appliances. Double glass doors open wide to the fully finished private backyard with maintenance-free lawn and paver patio, perfect for pets, family and outdoor entertaining.  Stylish chandelier and skylit stairwell leads upstairs to high ceilings and living area featuring juliet balcony for added outdoor access and fresh air.  Wide plank hardwood floors and white trim throughout give a timeless touch to the modern home.  Bathrooms host large slab tile and sliding glass shower or soaker tub plus shower combo. All closets boast built-in organization systems, including the primary bedroom ensuite walk-in. Additional urban comforts include a dedicated downstairs laundry area and private one-car garage.  Less than 1 block from Central Avenue, and steps to spacious Washington Park and Congress Street Light Rail station, the location of this spacious home is second to none. Jersey City Heights is known for it’s vibrant community, eclectic arts scene, excellent schools and proximity to NYC and surrounding urban areas."
210025058,SOLD,"JC, Heights",93 IRVING ST,Condominium,1759,1603,"$680,000",CONDO-COOP,,2&3,2,"JC, Heights",07307,00704,00022,Heights,,,,,2,0,2,6,,"$680,000","$675,000",$386.58,$386.58,11/4/2021,11/18/2021,2/4/2022,14,14,,2/7/2022,,,,"$7,047",2021,$250,,Conventional,,,,,,JFK Blvd & Nelson Ave,"Simply stunning lofted 2 Bedroom, 2 full bathroom home with cathedral ceilings in the Heart of Jersey City Heights. This recently constructed loft-style condo boasts over-size windows, double height cathedral style living/dining space with skylights and custom lighting. Fully equipped kitchen features top-of-the-line stainless steel appliances, quartz counters/island and an abundance of cabinet storage.  Primary bedroom offers a spacious walk-in closet, spa-like bathroom, and a juliet balcony. Second bedroom is spacious and bright and offers plenty of closet space. Direct access roof deck with panoramic views of the Manhattan and Jersey City skylines. Additional highlights include central A/C, NEST smart home technology, custom lighting throughout, full size laundry room and so much more!  Located centrally to parks, shopping, dining and all that Jersey City Heights has to offer. Convenient access to NYC transportation, NJ Transit Light Rail to the PATH and busses to Port Authority.OPEN HOUSE CANCELLED SUNDAY NOVEMBER !4"
240017407,SOLD,"JC, Heights",85 BOWERS ST,Condominium,1200,1597,"$680,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07307,2903,4,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,5,,"$680,000","$699,000",$566.67,$566.67,9/5/2024,9/19/2024,11/4/2024,14,14,,11/4/2024,,,,"$12,639",2023,$160,,Conventional,,,,,,Sherman Ave & Hancock,"Built in 2018 and located in the highly desirable Riverview Arts District, this picturesque home has a charming facade with a shared porch. This North & South facing 3 bedroom, 2 bath condominium is flooded with natural light featuring high ceilings, in-unit washer/dryer, central A/C, and plentiful storage. Perfect for entertaining, the open concept living area includes a kitchen with stainless-steel appliances, custom cabinetry, and an island that overlooks the incredibly spacious living room with a beautiful electric fireplace. The first bedroom is currently used as a work-from-home space, but can fit a full-sized bed and the second bedroom can fit a king-sized bed. The guest bathroom with bathtub and bidet is located across the hall. The incredibly massive primary bedroom features 4 large windows, a walk-in closet with built-ins and an en-suite bathroom with walk-in shower & linen closet. Conveniently located near bus service to NYC, light rail stations, Riverview Park with its panoramic views of NYC and farmer’s markets, Washington Park with playgrounds, sports fields and dog runs, and some of the city's most beloved cafes, restaurants & bars."
250007653,SOLD,"JC, Heights",256 WEBSTER AVE,Condominium,1380,1597,"$680,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,2,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,6,,"$680,000","$680,000",$492.75,$492.75,4/18/2025,4/18/2025,4/18/2025,0,0,,4/18/2025,,,,,,$389,,Conventional,,,,,,Bowers and South St,"This newly refinished grey brick building blends modern design with classic details. Offering three thoughtfully designed residences, each feature light oak hardwood floors, crown molding, and - In Unit 3 - sliding glass doors, allowing for an abundance of natural light. The open-concept living areas are spacious enough for a full-size dining table, creating a comfortable and functional layout.  The kitchens are finished with waterfall quartz countertops, a herringbone tile backsplash, and a striking combination of white upper and dark indigo lower custom cabinetry. Brass fixtures add warmth, while LG stainless steel appliances complete the space with a sleek, modern touch. The primary suite in each unit is designed as a peaceful retreat, accented by a tranquil feature wall. Bathrooms showcase floor-to-ceiling tile, double vanities, matte black fixtures, and either a glass-enclosed shower or a deep soaking tub with a built-in niche. Each unit includes a full-size laundry room with a Samsung champagne washer and dryer for added convenience.  Unit 3 features three bedrooms, two bathrooms, and a vaulted ceiling with sliding glass doors leading to a private balcony.  Set in the heart of Jersey City Heights, this location is just blocks from Riverview Fisk Park, where residents can take in sweeping views of the Manhattan skyline and enjoy local farmers' markets and community events. The 9th Street elevator provides easy access to Hoboken, while the nearby Light Rail connects directly to the PATH train and ferry, making commuting into New York City seamless."
240004947,SOLD,"JC, Heights",83 ZABRISKIE ST,Condominium,1375,1597,"$680,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,3,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,4,0,2,7,,"$680,000","$649,000",$494.55,$494.55,3/15/2024,3/28/2024,5/16/2024,13,13,,5/20/2024,,,,,,$373,,Conventional,,,,,,Summit & JFK,"Modern living meets classic style with this beautifully refinished four bedroom two bath condo plus balcony. The contemporary grey brick building is situated in the sweet spot of Jersey City Heights, walking distance to parks, shops and community.   Walk through the secure private entrance and into natural hardwood floors with classic crown molding and thoughtful finishes. Eat-in kitchen boasts custom shaker cabinetry with sleek quartz counters, tile backsplash, plus brass fixtures and fittings. Light flows into the generous bedrooms with oversized windows on either end of the split-plan layout.    Primary ensuite hosts access to private balcony plus an oversized walk in closet. Stylish bathrooms bring sophistication with floor to ceiling tile, spacious vanities, glass showers or soaker tub, and matching brass fixtures.    Two blocks from bustling Central Avenue or peaceful Pershing Field and Leonard Gordon Parks, this location brings the best of both worlds for urban living. Jersey City Heights offers eclectic essential shops, vibrant community, excellent schools and easy NYC access."
230001949,SOLD,"JC, Heights",302 PALISADE AVE,Condominium,1156,6199,"$681,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,303,"JC, Heights",07302,05201,00013,,,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$681,000","$645,000",$589.10,$589.10,2/3/2023,2/10/2023,3/24/2023,7,7,,3/24/2023,,,,"$12,032",,$465,,Conventional,,,,,,Ravine Ave & Cuneo Place,"Welcome to Palisade Heights!  Located in the heart of the Jersey City Heights neighborhood, this beautifully crafted building was just built from the ground up in 2016. This unit features the largest floorplan the building offers. Two bedrooms and two full baths, just over 1,150 sqft of space with hardwood floors spread throughout. From the spacious entryway foyer, you enter right into the gorgeous kitchen which features bright quartz countertops, a farm-style sink, top-of-the-line JennAir stainless steel appliances, subway-tile backsplash and industrial style pendant lighting over the breakfast bar. The wide-open layout leads right into an expansive living space. In the living room are east-facing sliding glass doors that lead out to your Juliette balcony with partial views of the Freedom Tower and great morning sunlight. The oversized main bedroom, you will find plenty of room for a California king bed, great closet space and en-suite master bath with a glass-enclosed spa-style shower. Additional conveniences include an in-unit washer & dryer, central a/c powered by Nest, video intercom, recessed lighting, industrial-style light fixtures, and garage parking. The building also features a large shared back patio. Close to all major transportation, shops restaurants and access to major highway & the Holland Tunnel. There is nothing like it currently on market in this perfectly appointed neighborhood, just half a mile to Hoboken and 2nd St Light Rail Station - don’t miss out on making this yours!"
220001229,SOLD,"JC, Heights",70 SHERMAN PL,Condominium,1500,283,"$685,000",CONDO-COOP,,2&3,3,"JC, Heights",07307,03602,00042,Heights,,,,,3,0,3,8,,"$685,000","$697,000",$456.67,$456.67,1/20/2022,1/6/2022,3/25/2022,0,0,,3/31/2022,,,,$0,,,,Conventional,,,,,, Summit Ave & Sanford Pl,"Newly renovated luxury condo in the Victorian mansion located on a desirable Sherman Place in the heart of Jersey City Heights. This Unit #3 is an amazing 1500 sqft duplex condo, has 3 bedrooms and 3 full baths, with high ceilings, ample closets, oversized windows, and basement storage. It has stainless steel appliances, includes gas-range oven, refrigerator with a built-in TV Screen, Microwave, and dishwasher. It also features tankless water heater, laundry room, and deeded parking. Close to all major commutes, shopping, schools and parks. For showing appt. 24hrs advance notice Please"
210007402,SOLD,"JC, Heights",40 THORNE ST,Condominium,1351,1603,"$685,000",CONDO-COOP,,1&2,1,"JC, Heights",07307,2805,50,,,,,,3,0,3,8,,"$685,000","$699,000",$507.03,$507.03,3/30/2021,5/7/2021,6/21/2021,38,38,,6/22/2021,,,,"$9,902",20,$330,,Conventional,,,,,,Central & Summit,"Welcome to 40 Thorne St, a newly renovated duplex condo that feels like a true suburban home in the center of Jersey City Heights! From the moment you walk into this stunning home, you are immediately greeted with an abundance of natural light, open floor plan and an airy feel to your next home. The eat-in kitchen features white quartz countertops, white subway tile backsplash, shaker style cabinets and stainless steel appliances. Opposite the kitchen island, there is enough room for a family-style dining table. Walk down the hall, you will find 2 bedrooms and 2 full bathrooms. The master bedroom can comfortably fit a king size bed and offers a walk-in closet in addition to a reach-in closet. En-suite bathroom offers dual sinks and a glass enclosed shower. Down the stairs of this thoughtfully designed duplex, there is a family room large enough for everyone with an additional half bath for convenience. The third bedroom is located downstairs with an additional walk-in closet for even more storage. Smart features include Ring Doorbell, Nest Thermostat and energy-efficient tankless water heater. Private backyard includes a tiered deck that walks down to your own manicured lawn. Current owners installed a standalone hot tub, perfect for relaxing and entertaining. Nestled into Jersey City's rapidly growing neighborhood, this home is steps from restaurants, shops and local business in this thriving community. Walking distance to Washington Park and Riverview Fisk Park and easy access to bus directly into Midtown NYC."
250003171,SOLD,"JC, Heights",77 WEBSTER AVE,Condominium,1500,6494,"$685,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,2,"JC, Heights",07307,4501,28,,,,,,3,0,2,7,,"$685,000","$675,000",$456.67,$456.67,2/18/2025,3/3/2025,4/17/2025,13,13,,4/17/2025,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Ferry & Franklin,"Spacious & Bright 3-Bedroom Condo in Jersey City Heights – Parking, NYC Access & More!  Welcome to 1500 square feet of bright, airy living in the heart of Jersey City Heights! This stunning 3-bedroom, 2-bathroom condo offers the perfect blend of space, convenience, and city vibes—all with a deeded parking spot included!  What You’ll Love: Expansive Layout – Spread out in 1500 sq. ft. of sunlit living space with high ceilings skylights and an open living dining layout PLUS an additional office or storage space off the living room area Eat-In Kitchen – Stainless steel appliances with new finishes, quartz countertops, providing ample space for meals, entertaining, and morning coffee. Deeded Parking Spot – Say goodbye to parking headaches in this sought-after neighborhood! NYC Commuter’s Dream – Quick access to Port Authority via bus just blocks away, plus easy access to NYC Port Authority via Bus or PATH, Hoboken, Citi Bike connections aplenty Recreation at Your Doorstep – Enjoy outdoor adventures at the newly renovated Jersey City Reservoir Park or take a dip in the swimming pool at Pershing Field. Endless Shopping & Dining – Surrounded by incredible restaurants, coffee shops, and boutiques that make The Heights one of Jersey City’s coolest neighborhoods. Enjoy the Riverview Fisk Park farmers market that runs every Sunday from May-November  This is more than just a condo—it’s a lifestyle upgrade!  "
