210017039,SOLD,"JC, Heights",88 POPLAR ST,Condominium,1437,1702,"$685,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,7,,"$685,000","$675,000",$476.69,$476.69,7/16/2021,8/5/2021,9/30/2021,20,21,,10/7/2021,,,,"$7,000",2021,$150,,Conventional,,,,,,Grace St. and Irving St.,"Welcome to 88 Poplar St., a luxury 2-unit new construction brownstone in Jersey City Heights. Residence #2 has been thoughtfully designed offering 3 Bedrooms/2 Bathrooms and 1437 SF of open-concept floor plan. The primary bedroom has a beautiful balcony, a five-star en-suite bath, and large walk-in closet. In addition to two other properly sized bedrooms and another full bath, the home has a stunning private rooftop with NYC Views from the Empire State, to One World Trade, and the most amazing western sunset views. All of this with and 1 car tandem garage parking with tons of storage. This turn-key property has been appointed with high-end finishes and is smart home enabled. 88 Poplar is situated closely to Bus transportation to NYC, schools, and the amazing Washington Park. Do not miss the opportunity to tour this incredible opportunity!"
210004255,SOLD,"JC, Heights",366 NEW YORK AVE,Condominium,1180,1724,"$685,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1,"JC, Heights",07307,02304,00009,Heights,,,,,2,1,1,6,,"$685,000","$649,999",$580.51,$580.51,2/19/2021,3/14/2021,6/10/2021,23,20,,6/10/2021,,,,,,,,Conventional,No,No,,,,South St. & Congress St.,"New construction luxury at it's finest. Welcome home to 366 New York Ave a three unit boutique and the epitome of luxury and convenience. Explore this exceptional 2bed/1.5 bath home boasting 10 high ceilings and solid 5 hard wood floors  through out the entire home. Your sleek and modern chef's kitchen features high end digital Samsung stainless steel appliances, 42 cabinets, quartz countertops, Sharp microwave, and a country style farmer sink. This home features 2 bedrooms, one large office space, and access to your very own private back yard for a private out door oasis. Finishes include home entertainment wiring with speakers, video intercom security system, Nest thermostat, custom closets, and an electric 50 stainless steel fire place for those cozy nights. Just the pure luxury of this home will make it an enjoyable place to call home. You could hear a button drop in this ultra-peaceful atmosphere, thanks to the extra-thick soundproofing, subfloor and insulation. This neighborhood is known for great schools and easy NYC access, all amid the eclectic and vibrant scene of Jersey City Heights. Nearby attractions include Hoboken’s Trader Joe’s, Bow Tie Cinemas, an array of revered diverse restaurants, bakeries, coffee houses and bars. NYC and metro area transportation on the corner, the expansive Washington park 1 block away, and Lightrail and Citibikes just a few blocks away. Your new urban home oasis awaits you!! **eligible for 5 year tax abatement** "
240002894,SOLD,"JC, Heights",361 OGDEN AVE,Condominium,1800,1605,"$686,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1,"JC, Heights",07307,,,,,,,,3,0,2,10,,"$686,000","$650,000",$381.11,$381.11,2/15/2024,2/27/2024,4/19/2024,12,12,,4/19/2024,,,,"$13,305",2022,$300,,Conventional,,,,,,Bowers & South,"Amazing location on one of the most desirable blocks in JC Heights! Great potential for house hackers as this 1800s/f duplex condo with a private yard consists of two separate apartments. The parlor level features an updated kitchen featuring stainless steel appliances, ample cabinet and counter space with a ceiling fan and reclaimed wood on the ceiling, giving it a rustic vibe. With hardwood floors throughout, the high ceilings make the two large bedrooms, living room and dining room feel very spacious; an updated bathroom, large pantry and lots of closet storage space complete the top floor. Parlor level also has central air/heating. The basement level has a private entrance from the private backyard and offers a large tiled bedroom and kitchen/living room condo, several closets and a full bathroom along with a washer/dryer that is accessible for both units. Neighborhood features Riverview Fisk Park with sweeping NYC views, Sunday farmer's markets, coffee shops, restaurants, including local favorites, Corto, Mod Cup & Bread & Salt! Just a short distance to the elevator leading to Hoboken and the NJ Transit Light Rail and Bus to Port Authority."
210016334,SOLD,"JC, Heights",72 COLUMBIA AVE,Condominium,1909,1419,"$689,000",CONDO-COOP,,1&2,1,"JC, Heights",07307,02602,00047,Heights,,,,,4,0,3,8,,"$689,000","$698,000",$360.92,$360.92,7/7/2021,10/29/2021,11/30/2021,114,114,,12/1/2021,,,,,,$318,,Conventional,,,,,,Lincoln & Thorne,"This home will take your breathe away! When you walk in you're greeted with high ceiling heights, oversized Pella windows, lavish entertainment space, and sunlit rooms. This huge duplex condominium with a massive backyard for grilling and entertainment has been outfitted to perfection! There is over 1,909 square feet consisting of 4 bedrooms with an abundance of custom closet space and 3 full bathrooms with porcelanosa tile and fixtures. On top of that this duplex has the benefit of another entrance into your ground floor sanctuary and kitchenette in the basement. This smart home is equipped with New speakers managed with Sonos amplifier, video door bell, and Nest Thermostats operable with your smartphone, connecting you with your home even when you're on the go. Custom Italian kitchens with Bertazonni, Bosch stainless steel appliances  Oak hardwood flooring throughout, quartz countertops, and a center island with a built-in wine refrigerator. The space also has a built-in outdoor sound/entertainment system and water and gas connections. Less than 2 blocks to JFK bus stops, under 10 minutes to Journal Square, and there is easy access to Tonnelle Ave and 1&9. You’ll also be located less than 3 blocks to the Leonard Gordon Park Conservancy and The Hutton, one of the Height's premier eateries. 1 car parking included!  "
