230009117,SOLD,"JC, Heights",56 RESERVOIR AVE,Condominium,1164,1597,"$700,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,3,"JC, Heights",07307,,,,,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$700,000","$699,000",$601.37,$601.37,6/2/2023,6/22/2023,8/24/2023,20,20,,8/24/2023,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Lienau & Webster,"Modern design and urban escape combine to bring this newly renovated home to Jersey City Heights. Presented with carefully curated finishes, private outdoor space and quality craftsmanship, this property is located just off Pershing Field Park and Reservoir, and nestled on a tree-lined street between Palisade and Central Avenue.  Gorgeous green siding, beautiful black trim plus soffits, and classic front porch lead the way to the impeccably designed interior. Featuring high ceilings and white oak floors, the two bedrooms, two bath floorplan offers style and spaciousness. Kitchen showcases custom gray cabinetry with under lighting, matching quartz counters, matte black fixtures, and stainless appliances. Sliding glass doors lead you to your own private deck and backyard, and also feature access to the quintessential front porch, perfect for watching the world go by. Black half-wall wainscotting offers timeless appeal in the primary ensuite, while bathrooms boast floor to ceiling tile, natural wood vanities and extras like a shower nook and bronze or black fixtures.  Nestled in a sweet spot of Jersey City Heights, owners enjoy nearby Pershing Field Park with swimming pool, tennis courts, sports facilities and more. Also within walking distance is bustling Central Avenue with shops, cafes and restaurants, and the 2nd Street stairs with direct access to Hoboken and Lightrail Station. The Heights is known for its tight-knit community, excellent parks, great schools and easy NYC access."
