220000078,SOLD,"JC, Heights",483 PALISADE AVE,Condominium,945,1691,"$700,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$700,000","$675,000",$740.74,$740.74,1/3/2022,1/13/2022,3/11/2022,10,10,,3/14/2022,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Griffith & Bowers,"Uniquely situated high-end condo directly on Riverview Fisk Park offers lavish luxury and an incomparable vantage point. Wall-to-wall windows sparkle upon entry giving crystal clear views of the park plus NYC skyline. Loads of natural light flood the classic design and beautiful hardwood floors throughout with details like window casings and tray ceilings.  Kitchen showcases quartz counters, tile backsplash, custom cabinets and stainless appliances with plenty of room for an added island or eat-in dining.   Primary ensuite gives another wow-worthy element with double-glass doors leading out onto the extra large backyard patio terrace. Bathrooms offer neutral tones, plus soaker tub or shower and vanity for additional storage. Extra storage and separate utility room offer added convenience and value.  Beautiful brick building is newly finished with great curb appeal and even better location with walkability to 9th Street LightRail, PATH train, vibrant neighborhood and Riverview Fisk Park as your permanent playground."
240001539,SOLD,"JC, Heights",277 SHERMAN AVE,Condominium,1250,6078,"$700,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1F,"JC, Heights",07307,1603,23,,,,,,2,0,2,6,,"$700,000","$689,000",$560.00,$560.00,1/26/2024,1/30/2024,3/11/2024,4,4,,3/12/2024,,,,"$10,323",,$0,,Conventional,No,No,No,,,Webster and Hancock,"Welcome home to 277 Sherman Avenue, in the heart of the hottest neighborhood in JC, Jersey City Heights. This unique 2 bedroom, 2 bath condo is spacious at 1250 square feet, features 2 private outdoor spaces and 2 deeded parking spots! The open concept main floor has a designated dining area large enough to fit a table for 10, an updated kitchen with bar seating, beautiful hardwood floors, and a large living room area with access to a huge private deck perfect for entertaining. Downstairs you’ll find a master bedroom with an oversized walk-in closet, ensuite bathroom and an entrance to a private, covered outdoor patio. A second bedroom, additional full bath and laundry/storage room round out the lower level. Located in one of the most desirable areas of Jersey City just 3 blocks from the 9th street lightrail, and steps from the 119 bus to NYC. Don't miss this one."
210002273,SOLD,"JC, Heights",127 SHERMAN PL,Condominium,,1653,"$702,500",CONDO-COOP,,1,1,"JC, Heights",07307,,,,127 Sherman Condos,,,,3,1,2,7,,"$702,500","$675,000",,,1/26/2021,2/15/2021,4/7/2021,20,20,,4/9/2021,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Sanford Place & Kennedy Blvd,"This beautifully designed condo on one of the most desired tree lined blocks of Jersey City Heights Sherman Place offers 3 bedrooms, 2.5 baths with a formal dining area and large open basement great for additional space. Gut renovated with all new electric, plumbing, HVAC, & fire sprinkler system - this one of a kind home stands out with a larger than normal living room, ample closet space throughout, and a generous size kitchen designed for entertaining. This luxury condo has all the bells and whistles including hardwood floors, quartz countertops, stainless steel Samsung appliances including a smart fridge, and chic designer tiles throughout. Outdoor space has never been more important! Relax in your personal oasis - a private fenced in backyard beautifully landscaped. Car parking rental secured nearby.  Steps away from Leonard Gordon Park, and JFK Blvd. Citibike access on the corner of the block. Close to all public transportation, 15 minutes into NYC, Central Ave Shopping district 5 minutes away. Schedule a tour today!"
240000771,SOLD,"JC, Heights",589 CENTRAL AVE,Condominium,1500,6078,"$705,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07307,00503,00023,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,5,,"$705,000","$715,000",$470.00,$470.00,1/11/2024,1/26/2024,4/26/2024,15,14,,5/10/2024,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Leonard St. & Paterson Plank Rd.,"Welcome to The 589 Quantum Residence, a newly constructed boutique community of an exquisite home. Nestled just across the street from the picturesque Washington Park, this is urban living at its finest. One standout feature is the home's breathtaking views of the iconic New York City skyline, and private parking. This property draws its inspiration from the legendary Quantum Sound music studio, located only a couple of doors down, where some of the biggest stars of the 80s and 90s, including Madonna, recorded major hits. Moreover, situated on Jersey City Heights' renowned Restaurant Row, Central Ave, you're just a quick walk away from award-winning restaurants and shops. Add to that the convenience of extremely quick transportation into NYC, and you have a residence that truly encapsulates the best of city living. Experience luxury, history, parkside tranquility, and an epicurean paradise all in one exceptional address."
250023434,SOLD,"JC, Heights",10 SOUTH ST,Condominium,898,1597,"$705,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,201,"JC, Heights",07307,,,,,,,,1,0,1,4,,"$705,000","$699,000",$785.08,$785.08,11/14/2025,3/2/2026,4/1/2026,108,108,,4/1/2026,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Palisade Ave and Ogden Avenue,"Discover an exceptional new collection of homes where historic character meets modern design. Rising up to four stories, these thoughtfully crafted residences capture the energy and sophistication of city living while offering a serene retreat at home.  Enjoy the convenience of a full-service elevator building with a secure lobby, intercom access, available on-site heated garage and handicap-accessible parking, and EV charging stations. Just three blocks from the Hoboken Light Rail, residents enjoy effortless access to Manhattan and beyond.  Inside, every detail has been considered—from European floor-to-ceiling windows and wide-plank white oak flooring to Gyp-Crete soundproofing that ensures quiet and comfort. Select homes include private balconies, dens, or roof decks designed for seamless indoor-outdoor living.  The interiors reflect a mid-century modern aesthetic with timeless craftsmanship, highlighted by granite waterfall islands, European cabinetry, Kohler fixtures, GE Café and Fisher & Paykel panel-door appliances, smart mirrors, and imported glass lighting. Open-concept kitchens flow into airy living spaces, creating the perfect backdrop for sophisticated urban life.  Private roof decks with full kitchens provide a refined setting for entertaining, complete with surround sound and green roof features.  For those seeking style, convenience, and connection, these residences reimagine Jersey City Heights living with an inspired blend of design, comfort, and modern amenities.   This home represents one of three, 1 bedroom plus den and balcony. 10SouthSt.com.  Available On -Site Garage Parking (heated) w/ HC & EV options."
250010720,SOLD,"JC, Heights",102 OGDEN AVE,Condominium,1150,6706,"$705,000",CONDO-COOP,,1st,104,"JC, Heights",07307,5202,23,Heights,Ogden Parkview Condo,,,,3,1,1,8,,"$705,000","$739,000",$613.04,$613.04,5/29/2025,6/16/2025,8/1/2025,18,18,,8/1/2025,,,,"$9,870",,$421,,Cash,No,No,,,,end of Ogden Ave.,"This stunning 3bd, 1.5bath condo is located at the Ogden's End--the BEST location in The Heights! The two-level unit boasts an open concept kitchen, a balcony with stunning Manhattan Views, and plenty of natural light. With lots of storage space and a deeded yard, this condo is perfect for comfortable living. The location is unbeatable with Janet Moore playground and dog park across the street, next door to Ogden's end community garden, and near Riverview Fisk park and Pershing Field park!! It is also just one block away from supermarkets, medical facilities, restaurants and public transportation. Don't miss out on this chance to secure a home in one of the most sought-after residences in The Heights!"
240002885,SOLD,"JC, Heights",431 PALISADE AVE,Condominium,1000,1597,"$707,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,3,"JC, Heights",07307,03902,00028,,,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$707,000","$699,000",$707.00,$707.00,2/15/2024,3/8/2024,6/6/2024,22,22,,6/6/2024,,,,$0,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Griffith st. and Hutton st.,"Experience luxury living with this brand new renovated 2 bedrooms, 2 bathrooms apartment nestled within a charming boutique brick building on Palisade Ave. Just few steps from Riverview Fisk Park and one block away from the 2nd Street Light Rail station and stairs to Hoboken. The open concept living space, enhanced with high-end finished and natural light, includes a large terrace accessible from the living room, provides ideal setting for entertaining and relaxation and a great outdoor space to enjoy. The apartment features 2 spacious bedrooms and 2 full modern sleek bathrooms including a master suite. Enjoy the vibrant community and easy access to cafes, restaurants, shops and services. Additional dedicated storage place in the basement."
210000603,SOLD,"JC, Heights",129 CONGRESS ST,Condominium,1325,66,"$707,500",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07307,01506,00017,Heights,129 Congress Residences,,,,3,0,2,7,,"$707,500","$719,899",$533.96,$533.96,1/7/2021,2/3/2021,3/16/2021,27,27,,3/17/2021,,,,$0,,$265,2021,Conventional,No,No,No,,,Central Ave & Passaic Ave,"A beautiful new take on a quintessential Heights property!  New construction penthouse condo boasting a spacious sunlit floor plan, great room w/ cathedral ceilings, impeccable finishes, private roof deck w/ NYC views, garage parking, storage and a full home warranty! Distinguished by a combination of contemporary design, luxury finishes, craftsmanship and value. Details include hardwood floors throughout, custom trim work, solid core doors, custom Hardi facade and upgraded Andersen 400 series windows & doors. Three bedrooms culminate in the master suite w/ balcony, en-suite bath w/ dual-vanity and large walk-in closet. The bathrooms are adorned with custom tile, floating vanities, seamless glass showers, full-width mirrors & abundant lighting. The open kitchen has Quartz waterfall counters, SS appliances, tiled backsplash eat-in island w/ built-in microwave, & tons of storage in the Shaker cabinets. From the great room, full-size stairs lead to the private roof deck w/ NYC views!  Central A/C, in-unit washer/dryer & expansive closets round out the myriad of features meticulously incorporated into this home. Steps to the Central Ave business district & express NYC transportation. New home warranty & 5-year tax abatement application included. Immediate Occupancy Available!"
220010819,SOLD,"JC, Heights",580 PALISADE AVE,Condominium,1038,1692,"$710,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,403,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,The Riveview,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$710,000","$710,000",$684.01,$684.01,11/1/2021,2/11/2022,6/8/2022,102,0,,6/13/2022,,,,,,$343,,Conventional,,,,,,Congress and South,"Step inside and immediately feel at ease in this unit. BRAND NEW GROUND UP CONSTRUCTION at The Riverview offers impeccable comfort and convenience, situated on Palisade Avenue, at the heart of the neighborhood’s exciting retail/dining corridor. Choose from two- and three-bedroom residences in this intimate 13-unit building, crafted to meet your every need. The well-proportioned units are carefully constructed with today’s most in-demand elements. Flow-through rooms and thoughtful appointments combine for luxurious comfort. Expansive energy-efficient insulated windows frame the interiors with abundant natural light. Elegant top-line finishes include wide plank flooring, granite countertops and premium Fischer-Paykel appliances. Thoughtfully curated amenities bring ease to today’s busy lifestyles. A package room, 12-car parking garage with electric chargers and ground-level bike storage are among the building’s many essential comforts designed to enhance your lifestyle. Make this inspired collection of pet-friendly condominiums home. 10-year New Home Warranty, Manufacturer’s Warranty on all appliances and systems, and tax abatement. Photos are of model unit."
220020966,SOLD,"JC, Heights",124 TERRACE AVE,Condominium,1831,6078,"$710,000",CONDO-COOP,,1 & B,101,"JC, Heights",07307,02503,00005-02,Heights,,,,,3,1,2,7,,"$710,000","$699,000",$387.77,$387.77,12/3/2022,12/15/2022,2/3/2023,12,12,,2/3/2023,,,,"$11,000",2022,$300,,Conventional,No,No,,,,Thorne & Lincoln,"Welcome to the Terrace Development, one of the finest quality ground-up new construction property, developed by one of the highly reputable Jersey City Developers, GN Management. 124 Terrace Avenue unit 101 spans over 1831 SQFT of living space, including 1340 SQFT. of open-concept living and dining, 3 bedrooms, 2.5 bathrooms, in-unit laundry, European kitchen, 491 SQFT. of private bright and glossy entertainment space featuring a gorgeous wet bar. This immaculate condominium features 10' ceilings, 9' solid doors, white oak hardwood flooring with classic grey finish, recessed and pendant lighting, electric fireplaces, oversized Anderson windows, allowing abundant natural sunlight throughout the day. White eat-in kitchen shows style with waterfall quartz counters & backsplash, custom shaker cabinets, pot-filler, drawer microwave, stainless steel appliances and a massive pantry. Spacious bedrooms offer plenty of closet space, with the primary en-suite featuring spa-like modern bathroom, extra-large custom walk-in-closet and double glass doors to the 592 SQFT. of private yard. Each bathroom is meticulously designed with high end finishes, floating vanities and smart mirrors. A tech-lover’s dream wired for plenty of mod cons, including 9 built-in audio speakers, smart mirrors, smart lighting, ring doorbell, security cameras with mobile-app connectivity, sonos amplifiers, yale locks and nest thermostat, rival Manhattan standard luxury.  Location is very convenient for NYC commuters with a multitude of public transportation options commute to NYC PORT AUTHORITY, JSQ PATH, Downtown JC and Hoboken. Centrally located between the Lincoln and Holland Tunnel, drive to Manhattan in less than 15 mins. Walking distance to Washington Park, Central Avenue and 9th St Light Rail station, makes this location even more desirable for sports, shopping, dining and commuting.  This neighborhood is known for great community and excellent schools. 124 Terrace unit 101 comes with 1 deeded car parking in the massive garage. In a competitive new development market, quality and affordability is what separates the Terrace Development from the rest! Come check it out before its gone and begin your new year in your brand new home!  10-year new home warranty, 5-year Tax Abatement! Some finishes may differ from these photos/copy. Contact listing agent today for private showing! "
250000399,SOLD,"JC, Heights",489 LIBERTY AVE,Condominium,1356,1526,"$710,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07307,,,,,,,,3,0,2,6,,"$710,000","$725,000",$523.60,$523.60,1/7/2025,4/8/2025,5/20/2025,91,91,,6/17/2025,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,North St & Bleeker St,"Discover your perfect sanctuary in one of Jersey City's most desirable neighborhoods, JC Heights/Western Slope! This beautifully designed, recently built condo features 3 bedrooms and 2 baths. Step inside to find gleaming red oak hardwood floors throughout, setting the stage for a sophisticated and inviting ambiance. Sunlight pours through expansive windows, creating a bright and uplifting atmosphere. The kitchen features sleek quartz countertops paired with stylish blue cabinetry for a contemporary and refined look. Each of the three spacious bedrooms offers ample room for rest and relaxation. The primary suite elevates comfort with its luxurious en-suite bathroom and private balcony—perfect for enjoying your morning coffee or unwinding in the evening. Head upstairs to the crowning jewel of this home: a sprawling PRIVATE roof deck with panoramic views. This outdoor space is ideal for entertaining, relaxing, or simply soaking in the beauty of the surroundings. Practicality meets peace of mind with a long-term homeowner warranty and a tax abatement still in effect, providing ongoing financial benefits. (Please confirm property taxes with the Jersey City Tax Office.) Opportunities like this don't last—secure your place in this breathtaking property that combines contemporary luxury and smart investment potential. Make your move today and experience the best of modern living in the heart of Jersey City!"
240000238,SOLD,"JC, Heights",139 SHERMAN PL,Condominium,1050,1713,"$710,000",CONDO-COOP,,4,403,"JC, Heights",07307,03503,00001,,Sherman Place,,,,2,0,2,6,,"$710,000","$684,900",$676.19,$676.19,1/4/2024,2/1/2024,3/11/2024,28,28,,3/12/2024,,,,$0,,$431,,Cash,,,,,,Kennedy and Sanford,"Presenting an exquisite condominium nestled in the heart of Jersey City Heights. This splendid residence boasts two generously proportioned bedrooms and two elegant bathrooms, providing a perfect blend of comfort and luxury. Just over 1000 square feet, the condo offers a well-thought-out layout that maximizes both space and functionality. Upon entering, you are greeted by a sophisticated and modern interior design that sets the tone for the entire unit. The open-concept living area seamlessly transitions from the inviting living room to the well-appointed kitchen, creating a harmonious space for relaxation and entertainment. The kitchen features top-of-the-line appliances, sleek cabinetry, and ample countertop space, catering to the needs of culinary enthusiasts and hosts alike. The two spacious bedrooms are designed to offer tranquility and privacy. The primary bedroom comes complete with an en-suite bathroom, providing a serene retreat after a long day. The second bedroom, equally spacious, offers versatility for use as a guest room, home office, or personal sanctuary. Both bathrooms are adorned with contemporary finishes and fixtures, evoking a spa-like ambiance. Natural light floods the living spaces through large windows, creating an airy and inviting atmosphere. The condo also features thoughtfully integrated storage solutions, ensuring a clutter-free living environment and in-unit Washer and Dryer. Commuting to Manhattan and other parts of Jersey City is a breeze, thanks to the well-connected transportation options in the vicinity. Parking is also available for purchase! This building truly caters to a sophisticated urban lifestyle. A unique opportunity to own a slice of modern elegance and urban convenience. A must-see!"
210025094,SOLD,"JC, Heights",580 PALISADE AVE,Condominium,1192,1692,"$710,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,302,"JC, Heights",07307,,,,The Riverview,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$710,000","$710,000",$595.64,$595.64,11/4/2021,11/15/2021,4/18/2022,11,10,,6/13/2022,,,,,,$394,,Conventional,,,,,,Congress and South,"Step inside and immediately feel at ease. BRAND NEW GROUND UP CONSTRUCTION at The Riverview offers impeccable comfort and convenience, situated on Palisade Avenue, at the heart of the neighborhood’s exciting retail/dining corridor. Choose from two- and three-bedroom residences in this intimate 13-unit building, crafted to meet your every need. The well-proportioned units are carefully constructed with today’s most in-demand elements. Flow-through rooms and thoughtful appointments combine for luxurious comfort. Expansive energy-efficient insulated windows frame the interiors with abundant natural light. Elegant top-line finishes include wide plank flooring, and premium Fischer-Paykel appliances. Thoughtfully curated amenities bring ease to today’s busy lifestyles. A package room, 12-car parking garage with electric chargers and ground-level bike storage are among the building’s many essential comforts designed to enhance your lifestyle. Make this inspired collection of pet-friendly condominiums your home. 10-year New Home Warranty, Manufacturer’s Warranty on all appliances and systems, and tax abatement. Photos are of model unit."
220020554,SOLD,"JC, Heights",27 RAVINE AVE,Condominium,1200,6199,"$710,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07307,05009,00001 03,Heights,,,,,2,0,2,6,,"$710,000","$699,000",$591.67,$591.67,11/23/2022,11/30/2022,1/13/2023,7,7,,1/14/2023,,,,"$9,900",2021,$330,2022,Conventional,No,No,No,,,New York Ave & Webster Ave,"The ideal location you've been looking for with the modern finishes you deserve. Enjoy sophisticated urban living in this well-appointed 2 bed 2 full bath home in the most desirable section of the Heights...close to Light Rail, bus, and all of the best nightlife & convenient hot spots. This distinctive home boasts 1200 square feet of living space and includes a private & spacious roof deck...perfect for grilling and entertaining. Every detail has been thoughtfully considered in this custom built home, originally constructed in 2016. Features include roof deck, parking, beautiful wide plank light oak floors, floor to ceiling windows, gourmet kitchen with top of the line stainless steel appliances & white quartz countertops, gas fireplace, central heat & air, high ceilings with an abundance of natural light, lots of bonus closet & storage space throughout, top of the line washer & dryer, and the walk in closet of your dreams. The bedrooms are spacious, and what used to be a full third bedroom, was converted to an enormous walk in closet...easy to convert back if desired. 27 Ravine, with it's boutique contemporary feel, has it all...as well as very low monthly maintenance. Come, see, and fall in love..."
210011474,SOLD,"JC, Heights",133 NEW YORK AVE,Condominium,1300,1419,"$710,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07307,4505,33,,,,,,3,0,2,7,,"$710,000","$710,000",$546.15,$546.15,5/12/2021,5/17/2021,8/18/2021,5,5,,9/10/2021,,,,"$8,485",2020,$300,,Conventional,,,,,,Franklin & Ferry,"Welcome to this elegant open layout 3bed/2bath with a massive rooftop deck located in a charming tree lined block near Riverview Park in Jersey City Heights. As you step in, notice the well-appointed hard wood floors, crown molding and recess lighting throughout.  Relish in your fully customized chefs’ kitchen with stainless steel appliances, quartz countertops and wine cooler to savor your most delightful bottles. After your long days, indulge in your massive rooftop deck with NYC views. Conveniently located near bus stop that routes you to NYC Port Authority, Journal Square Path, Grove St Path and much more."
210026212,SOLD,"JC, Heights",241 SOUTH ST,Condominium,1511,6199,"$715,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07307,02104,00005,,,,,,3,0,2,6,,"$715,000","$729,000",$473.20,$473.20,11/28/2021,12/13/2021,2/3/2022,15,15,,2/4/2022,,,,,,$270,2021,Conventional,,,,,,Off Kennedy Blvd,"Check out this brand new construction that spares no expense in the heart of booming Jersey City Heights. Open your private entry door to this captivating condo featuring 3 bedrooms, 2 bath, modern open concept living, fully equipped kitchen with stainless steel appliances, custom cabinets, quartz counter tops with breakfast bar. Main bedroom with private en-suite bath and sliding glass doors that lead to your balcony, 2 generous sized bedrooms. Private roof top deck. Features include hardwood floors throughout, central air/heat, washer and dryer and LED lighting. 1 car shared tandem spot included. Minutes to Journal Square PATH and bus station, restaurants, shops and all major highways and tunnels. Come and see for yourself why Jersey City was named the Sixth Borough of New York City. This property is eligible for a 5 year tax abatement."
220015188,SOLD,"JC, Heights",276 GRIFFITH ST,Condominium,2669,1725,"$715,000",CONDO-COOP,,1&2,1,"JC, Heights",07307,03403,00036,,,,,,5,0,3,9,,"$715,000","$715,000",$267.89,$267.89,8/19/2022,8/26/2022,11/11/2022,7,7,,11/14/2022,,,,"$10,160",2021,$300,,Conventional,,,,,,JFK & Milton Blvd,"Don't miss this huge 5 bedroom 3 bathroom duplex! This 2,669 sq. ft. apartment features 3 bedrooms, 2 full bathrooms, a beautifully renovated kitchen, plus a living/dining space all on the parlor level. In addition, the ground level offers a fully functional in-law suite with 2 bedrooms, a large living space and kitchenette. All of this, plus private garage parking space make 276 Griffith Street a uniquely ideal space for large families or the savvy investor. Nestled on a quite street between JFK Blvd. and Summit, this fantastic space has easy transportation options, great food and shopping, and parks practically on it's doorstep! Don't let this superb home pass you by!"
240015361,SOLD,"JC, Heights",90 WEBSTER AVE,Condominium,1280,1597,"$715,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,6,,"$715,000","$725,000",$558.59,$558.59,8/6/2024,8/23/2024,9/26/2024,17,17,,9/26/2024,,,,,,$329,,Conventional,,,,,,Franklin & Ferry,"Experience elevated living with this newly constructed 3 bed, 2 bath home in Jersey City Heights. Oversized windows and a Juliet balcony bring the natural light and a treetop breeze into the super spacious open concept living, kitchen and formal dining area. Crown molding and gleaming red oak hardwood floors add elegance to the classic design, while the full private roof deck is the real showstopper with NYC views, hookups for gas, electric, and water, plus a refreshing living garden space.  The kitchen boasts contemporary white cabinets, quartz counters, herringbone subway tile backsplash, and stainless fixtures and appliances. Bathrooms are beautifully designed with floor-to-ceiling tile, spacious vanities, and options for either a bathtub or a shower. The primary ensuite stands out with a stunning onyx accent wall and wainscoting, as well a substantial walk-in closet. Finally, the dedicated laundry room offers a brand-new LG washer and dryer plus central location for added convenience.  Situated in a classic red brick building on a tree-lined street, this home is just blocks to the 2nd Street Light Rail and the Hoboken stairs, providing easy commutes and access to surrounding areas and NYC. Residents enjoy nearby Riverview Fisk Park and Pershing Field Parks, with stunning city views and playgrounds, or nature spaces, farmer’s markets and swimming! Jersey City Heights is known for its vibrant community, excellent schools, peaceful parks and central location."
240011878,SOLD,"JC, Heights",573 PALISADE AVE,Condominium,941,1603,"$715,000",CONDO-COOP,,4,4B,"JC, Heights",07307,02304,00024,Heights,,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$715,000","$729,000",$759.83,$759.83,6/19/2024,6/24/2024,10/11/2024,3,3,,10/14/2024,,,,$0,,,,Conventional,No,No,No,,,Congress St & South St,"TOP FLOOR!  New construction home in elevator building with two private terraces!  Welcome to 573 Palisade Avenue, where unparalleled sophistication meets breathtaking views in an exclusive collection of seven condominium homes in a boutique-style elevator building.  Each two-bedroom, two-bathroom condominium home features spacious open floor plans of meticulously designed living space and private outdoor spaces. 10 - 14 ft ceilings soar above engineered hardwood floors, creating an airy sanctuary illuminated by recessed and custom light fixtures. The expansive triple pane Pella windows frame stunning vistas of the Manhattan skyline, inviting you to unwind against a backdrop of urban splendor. Kitchens feature custom 2-toned cabinetry, Samsung stainless steel appliances, Calacatta Laza Quartz countertops, wine cooler and direct vent exhaust hood. Bathrooms include Porcelanosa tiles with Kohler fixtures, deep soaking tubs and dual flush toilets.  You'll love the convenience of having in-home laundry, integrated intercom and security system and a home that is prewired for home automation.  Unwind and socialize on our exclusive residents rooftop lounge offering sweeping NYC views, providing an extraordinary backdrop for relaxation or entertaining guests. This property boasts unparalleled ease of access to New York City, making your commute as breezy as a walk in the adjacent Fisk Park. Whether you prefer the NJ Transit buses or the convenience of the 9th Street-Congress Street Light Rail Station right at your doorstep, your connection to the city has never been smoother. And with breathtaking views of the Manhattan skyline from your window, every day feels like a picturesque escape. This prime Jersey City Heights location offers you not just a home, but a lifestyle. Seller will apply for 5 year tax abatement."
220017483,SOLD,"JC, Heights",84 FERRY ST,Condominium,1400,1597,"$715,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,3,"JC, Heights",07307,04402,00040,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,7,,"$715,000","$729,000",$510.71,$510.71,9/29/2022,11/18/2022,6/9/2023,50,50,,6/12/2023,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Central Ave and Sherman Ave,"Situated in the heart of Jersey City Heights between Central and Sherman Avenue and a stone’s throw to Pershing Field Park, this impeccably designed new boutique condominium residence feature approximately 1400sf of generous indoor living space, 3 Bedrooms, 2 Bathrooms and windows on three sides. This sprawling residence is equipped with two serene bathrooms with Porcelanosa tiles and fixtures and a stunning chef’s kitchen featuring custom white cabinets, Samsung appliances, Quartz Calcutta countertop and backsplash, and sizable waterfall peninsula. The sumptuous primary bedroom suite includes a walk-in closet, en-suite bathroom and sliding glass doors. Further, this artfully constructed condominium is furnished with washer and dryer, Central AC & Heat and recessed lighting. Unit #3 boasts a private roof terrace with unobstructed views for miles, hardwood floors and bay windows. This beautifully proportioned residence is 22ft wide and centrally located convenient to restaurants, shops, markets, public transportations to NYC and parks. All buyers must contact Donald Matia @NJ Lenders 201-783-4397 for pre-approval."
220000765,SOLD,"JC, Heights",69 HANCOCK AVE,Condominium,1200,1691,"$715,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,6,,"$715,000","$699,000",$595.83,$595.83,1/13/2022,2/10/2022,4/1/2022,28,28,,4/6/2022,,,,,,$366,,Conventional,,,,,,Hutton & Griffith,"Magnificent and modern, this brand new, bright and airy, custom home shines with space and sophistication in the heart of Jersey City Heights. High ceilings & high-end finishes in this 3-bedroom, 2-bathroom unit elevates luxury lifestyle to the next level.   Finished with light oak floors plus matte black pendant lighting and trim throughout, each home features wide open windows along the back wall with western-exposure for excellent sunsets and seclusion. Kitchens excite with sleek light wood or matte black custom cabinetry, finished with waterfall quartz counters, tile backsplash, brass fixtures and high-end Bertazzoni appliance package. Freshly designed bathrooms feature ribbon gray porcelain tile, glass shower with niche and rain head faucet, floating vanity and contrasting matte black fixtures.  Settled into a tree-lined street just off Central Avenue with essential shops and award-winning restaurants, this home is located blocks from both Riverview Fisk and Pershing Field Park, plus walkable access to NJ and NY transit or Citi bike stations. Jersey City Heights is home to the perfect blend of urban and escape, including vibrant community, excellent schools and impressive lifestyle to value ratio."
