le."
220003791,SOLD,"JC, Heights",250 WEBSTER AVE,Condominium,1010,1691,"$715,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$715,000","$725,000",$707.92,$707.92,3/4/2022,4/20/2022,6/2/2022,47,47,,6/2/2022,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Bowers & South St,"Bright white interiors and brand new, ground-up construction, this two unit building in The Heights offers a private roofdeck, garage parking and individual storage for each luxury home. The two bedroom and two baths are designed with thoughtful split plan layout, each with modern style and up-to-date tech.   Dark hardwood floors meet with clean palette white walls, extra large windows with black trim and carefully curated designer pendant lighting throughout. Kitchens showcase beautiful white quartz counters with herringbone backsplash, stainless appliances and ample cabinet space with wall pantry and built-in coffee bar.   Primary ensuite showcases private balcony and walk-in closet. Oversized bathrooms boast natural light plus double panel glass shower including niche and multi system showerhead.   Owners enjoy several must-have amenities including their own private roofdeck with impressive NYC views and invaluable outdoor living. In addition, each home has access to tandem garage parking and their own ground-level storage area.  Set on a quiet street in the heart of Jersey City Heights, this location offers walkability to beautiful Riverview Fisk Parks with panoramic NYC and Hudson River views, plus 9th street elevator Light Rail for easy NYC and Hoboken access."
