250015262,SOLD,"JC, Heights",126 WEBSTER AVE,Condominium,1339,5957,"$747,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1G,"JC, Heights",07307,,,,Hugo Pronti Loft Building,,,,2,0,1,5,,"$747,000","$685,000",$557.88,$557.88,7/25/2025,7/29/2025,8/27/2025,4,4,,11/28/2025,,,,"$13,103",2024,$690,,Conventional,,,,,,SHERMAN AVE AND NEW YORK AVE,"Welcome to 126 Webster Avenue – a beautifully updated apartment located in the heart of Jersey City Heights, offering a rare blend of historic charm, modern living, and unbeatable convenience.  Situated in a classic brick building on a quiet, tree-lined street, this sun-filled unit features high ceilings, hardwood floors, oversized windows, and a cozy fireplace that adds warmth and character to the open living space. The layout includes open-concept living and dining areas, creating a seamless flow that’s ideal for both daily living and entertaining.  The apartment is equipped with WiFi-enabled heating, cooling, and lighting systems, allowing smart-home control for comfort and energy efficiency at your fingertips.  The bathroom features clean, modern tilework, a soaking tub or walk-in shower, and a contemporary vanity. Additional highlights include in-unit laundry, ample closet space, updated mechanicals, and a Dedicated storage area in the basement  **A private parking spot is included**—a rare and highly valuable feature in Jersey City Heights, where parking is limited and often expensive. This adds both convenience and long-term value to the home.  **For investors**, this unit offers excellent rental potential in a high-demand area. Whether you're looking to generate passive income or secure a long-term asset, the location and features of this home make it a smart addition to any portfolio * Just blocks from Congress St. Light Rail for fast access to Hoboken and NYC **Steps from Palisade Avenue and NJ Transit Bus Route 119**, offering direct service to NYC’s Port Authority * Minutes to Riverview-Fisk Park and Washington Park * Walkable to Central Avenue shops, cafes, restaurants, and farmers markets * Easy access to Route 1&9, the Holland Tunnel, and major highways * Surrounded by a growing arts scene and nightlife  Jersey City Heights continues to attract buyers and renters alike with its vibrant community, excellent transit options, and close proximity to New York City. Don’t miss your opportunity to own this move-in ready, smart-enabled apartment with a fireplace and private parking in one of Jersey City’s most desirable neighborhoods. Schedule your private tour today!  "
220015301,SOLD,"JC, Heights",201 COLUMBIA AVE,Condominium,1349,1597,"$749,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,2,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,6,,"$749,000","$749,000",$555.23,$555.23,8/23/2022,9/28/2022,10/25/2022,36,36,,10/31/2022,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,North St & Bleecker St,"Elevate your living standards with these high-end, high tech, new construction homes in The Heights. Each home – with at least 3 beds & 2 baths - includes private outdoor and garage parking with electric charging station.  Light streams in through the oversized Pella windows illuminating the open floorplan with classic crown molding and gleaming hardwood flooring throughout. White eat-in kitchen shows style with waterfall quartz counters & backsplash, custom shaker cabinets, pot-filler, apron sink, black Samsung appliances and wine fridge. A tech-lover’s dream wired for plenty of mod cons, including smart doorbell, smart thermostat, camera, security system and central vacuum.  Unit 2 gives way to a full-floor private roofdeck with 360 degree views ideal for entertaining or daily sightseeing! Bathrooms bring coveted upgrades like double-vanities, herringbone tile in soaker tub with multi-system shower and niche, and glass shower with pennytile accents. Primary ensuite hosts spacious built-out walk-in-closet for optimal storage and organization.  On a quiet tree-lined street of The Heights, and walking distance to JFK Blvd, Washington Park and 9th St Light Rail station, this neighborhood is known for great community, excellent schools and easy NYC access, all amid the eclectic and vibrant scene of Jersey City Heights."
260001410,ACTIVE,"JC, Heights",85 BLEECKER ST,Condominium,1184,1724,"$749,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,6,,,"$749,000",$632.60,,1/27/2026,,,72,,,1/27/2026,,,,,,,,,,,,,,summit,"Welcome to this exceptional brand-new construction residence situated on one of Jersey City Heights’ most sought-after streets. An impressive 1,184 square feet, this thoughtfully crafted three-bedroom, two-bathroom home perfectly blends modern elegance with everyday comfort.  Step inside to an open-concept living and dining area, light-finished 6 wide-plank hardwood floors, oversized Anderson windows, and an 8-foot custom entry door package create an immediate sense of style and sophistication. Anchoring the space is a bespoke electric fireplace, offering warmth and ambiance for both relaxing evenings and lively gatherings.  The chef’s kitchen is a true showpiece, designed for both function and flair. Outfitted with custom soft-close cabinetry, a walk-in pantry, quartz countertops, and a designer quartz backsplash, it is centered around a generous island perfect for casual dining and entertaining. A full suite of premium VIKING appliances completes the space, providing professional-grade quality for culinary enthusiasts.  Retreat to the primary suite oasis, featuring a custom walk-in closet and a spa-inspired en-suite bath with a contemporary rain shower and sleek designer finishes. Two additional well-proportioned bedrooms offer oversized custom closets, ideal for guests, family, or a home office.  Additional highlights include garage parking availability, central heating and cooling, and premium finishes throughout.  Perfectly located, this home places you within moments of NYC transportation, neighborhood parks, local cafés, dining destinations, and cultural hot spots that define the vibrant Jersey City Heights lifestyle.  This is more than a residence—it’s an opportunity to experience elevated living in one of Jersey City’s most desirable neighborhoods.  GARAGE PARKING AVAILABLE."
220002695,SOLD,"JC, Heights",20 THORNE ST,Condominium,1500,156,"$749,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07307,02805,00041,,,,,,3,1,2,7,,"$749,000","$749,000",$499.33,$499.33,2/16/2022,2/24/2022,5/9/2022,8,8,,5/11/2022,,,,"$7,983",2021,$110,2021,Conventional,,,,,,Central Ave and Summit Ave,"Welcome to this modern, bright and spacious duplex condo with a private rooftop located just off Central Avenue in the Jersey City Heights. This newer constructed custom build features generous sized 3 bedrooms, 2.5 baths with beautiful brick work, and majestic windows. On the interior, clean and modern design opens with two-story high soaring windows in the eat-in kitchen plus dining area and powder room. Sleek tile flooring and crown molding highlight the custom white shaker style cabinetry, waterfall quartz counters, tile backsplash and stainless steel appliances. Upstairs leads to the airy and open loft-space living area, plus three bedrooms and two full baths. Master ensuite offers quartz counter, great storage and glass shower with contemporary tile floor. Other notable features include; Central air, central vacuum system, recessed lighting, full washer and dryer and beautiful hardwood floors to name a few. Step up to the stunning roof deck with spectacular NYC views and endless fresh air. Accessible to Central Avenue, for dining, shopping, cafes, parks, schools and easy metro transportation."
210023319,SOLD,"JC, Heights",83 WAVERLY ST,Condominium,0,5745,"$749,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,F,"JC, Heights",07306,04901,00027,,,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$749,000","$749,000",,,10/9/2021,4/18/2022,7/13/2022,41,41,,8/22/2022,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Oakland and Central,"Get in early on this Eco friendly/environmentally sustainable new construction on a quiet street in the booming Heights section of Jersey City.  Just blocks whatever you need - from the plethora of diverse activities at Pershing Field Park, shopping, groceries, farmer’s market, schools, day care, old and new eateries from cafes & pubs to 5 star restaurants.  A real community feel with modern amenities!!  Let’s start with the heart of a home – the chef designed dream kitchen w/ marbled stone countertops, SS Energy Star appliances w/ exhaust fan vented outside for improved air quality, herringbone subway tile backsplash.  Although incredibly convenient for walking, biking or public transportation, throw in/provided indoor parking with electric vehicle charging station, bicycle & stroller storage.  Stuck inside or need some fresh air head out to your private outdoor space.  Help your wallet and the environment with high efficiency insulation on the interior of all exterior walls and the roof, triple pane windows, high efficiency multi-zone heating & cooling system with programmable thermostats, high efficiency LED lighting, EnergyStar rated white roof and a vegetated “green’ roof, water conserving dual flush toilets and a rain water harvesting and recycling system used for flushing toilets.  A little more peace & quiet provided by sound attenuating insulation on interior wall partitions while you work from home, read or just relax in your Kohler deep soaking tub.  Security conscious, need at home deliveries, let a baby or dog sitter in without giving them a key, no problem – you control access to your place remotely with smart access entry system to the building and residences.  Low or non-toxic building materials were used for construction and approximately 90% of all construction waste diverted from a landfill & recycled.   Proximity to Journal Square, Hoboken and Downtown Jersey City.  83 Waverly has it all: location, community, diverse activities, quiet nights with family and friends or a night on the town, stop in and check it out for yourself!   Estimated completion date is 10/31/2021. Photos are Virtually Staged, finishes are subject to change.   1, 2 and 3 Bedroom Units Available!"
