210003018,SOLD,"JC, Heights",72 LINCOLN ST,Condominium,,1691,"$761,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07307,2703,28,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,6,,"$761,000","$749,000",,,2/5/2021,2/19/2021,4/12/2021,14,14,,4/12/2021,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Summit and Milton,"Created with exquisite taste and intelligent design, one of Jersey City Height’s top developers have completed two freshly renovated homes. This elevated penthouse with high ceilings, skylights and panoramic rooftop, three bedroom home levels up daily lifestyle with ease and sophistication.  Experience ultimate curb appeal with alluring white brick facade, dark trim and protective enclosed front porch. Step inside to thoughtful finishes and top quality throughout -- wide plank hardwood floors, exposed brick walls, beautiful bay windows and elegant arched built-in dry bar to open the spacious floorplans. Chef-inspired kitchens impress with striking green custom cabinetry, black quartz waterfall countertops, built-in stainless appliances, brass fixtures and natural wood hood.   Massive master en-suite showcases seductive dark panelled accent wall plus sweeping french doors to private balcony perfect for al fresco coffee or cocktails. Distinctive zen-inspired bathrooms feature unique elements like black tile and floor-to-ceiling glass shower and faux wood or pattern tile floors. Head upstairs to enjoy unobstructed cityscape and NYC rooftop views.  Settled into a quiet, tree-lined street equidistant to Pershing Field, Leonard Gordon, Riverview Fiske and Washington Parks, this location also offers walkability to surrounding Central & Palisade Avenue for essential shopping needs. The Heights is a vibrant community with excellent schools, award-winning restaurants and shops plus easy NYC access!"
220008575,SOLD,"JC, Heights",9 STAGG ST,Condominium,1841,1597,"$762,000",CONDO-COOP,,1 & 2,1,"JC, Heights",07306,,,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,6,,"$762,000","$799,000",$413.91,$413.91,5/12/2022,6/29/2022,8/19/2022,48,48,,8/29/2022,,,,,,$234,,Cash,,,,,,Liberty Ave & JFK,"Set your sights on these completely renovated homes with private outdoor and storage from one of Jersey City’s top builders, Nkay Construction, now available in a quiet corner of The Heights. Both duplexes offer three bedrooms plus added living area and expansive roof deck or backyard with patio.  Built-in floating gas fireplace is the show-stopping centerpiece, beautifully encased in a classic custom mantle in the wide-open living area. Modern yet classic finishes include crown molding, hardwood floors, Pella windows and ceiling fans throughout. Open floorplan kitchen includes sparkling quartz waterfall eat-in peninsula including eye-catching blue kick plate, tile backsplash, custom shaker cabinets, stainless farm sink and matte black Samsung appliances including much-needed wine fridge, plus Kohler fixtures and modern pendant lighting. Tech upgrades include ring doorbell, camera and wired for security system, and nest thermostat. Bathroom finishes include marble double vanity, glass shower or bathtub combo with polished chrome fixtures.  Unit one hosts an expansive primary ensuite with gorgeous etched french doors leading to a private back balcony, as well as coveted private patio and backyard.   Modern gray brick building on idyllic tree-lined street in a quiet corner of The Heights Western Slope is blocks from Leonard Gordon Park, and easy access to the JSQ PATH station, 2nd St  Light Rail, and all major roads. Jersey City Heights is known for its great community, excellent schools and easy NYC access, with vibrant shops, restaurants and parks!"
240019055,SOLD,"JC, Heights",307 NEW YORK AVE,Condominium,1134,1603,"$762,500",CONDO-COOP,,2,B,"JC, Heights",07307,02306,00049,,,,,,3,0,2,6,,"$762,500","$775,000",$672.40,$672.40,9/26/2024,10/17/2024,11/25/2024,21,21,,11/26/2024,,,,"$10,558",,$200,,Conventional,,,,,,Bowers and South,"Welcome to 307 New York Avenue! Constructed in 2019, this top floor residence has it all: 3 bedrooms, 2 full bathrooms, an exclusive full-length roof deck, and garage parking, all within two blocks of Riverview Park! A private entrance leads to the sun-drenched open-concept living space where high ceilings and gleaming oak floors welcome you in. The kitchen is home to KitchenAid stainless steel appliances, stunning white quartz waterfall countertops, crisp white shaker cabinets, and a slate tile backsplash. Up the steps you’ll find a jaw-dropping, full-length, nearly 1,000 sq ft roof deck adorned with string lights and city views, perfect for entertaining! The primary bedroom boasts a large walk-in closet, a sleek and modern en-suite, and a lovely terrace where you can relax and enjoy your morning coffee or a glass of wine in the evening. Two additional bedrooms feature ample closet space and stylish ceiling fans. Both bathrooms boast spa-inspired tile layouts, floating vanities, and mirrored medicine cabinets for sleek and sophisticated storage. The garage is home to your parking space as well as a large private storage closet. Additional features and upgrades include: central A/C controlled by Nest, recessed, dimmable LED lighting and ceiling fans all operated by Lutron smart switches, Ring Security System, smart meters for utilities and a garage door opener that links to your phone for added convenience! Enjoy Riverview Park, home to the best Farmers Market around, dining at Corto, coffee at Mod Cup, music at Fox & Crow, grab and go from Busy Bee Organics, shopping at Lucky Honeybee, and so much more."
230013734,SOLD,"JC, Heights",108 IRVING ST,Condominium,1470,1597,"$765,000",CONDO-COOP,,1 & 2,1,"JC, Heights",07307,00703,00049,,,,,,2,1,2,6,,"$765,000","$749,000",$520.41,$520.41,8/16/2023,8/21/2023,10/16/2023,5,5,,10/16/2023,,,,"$12,367",2022,$200,,Conventional,,,,,,JFK & Nelson,"Enjoy the townhouse-feel in this duplex condominium home that features over 1,400 sf of living space, central AC, extra soundproofing, in-unit laundry, 2-car parking, abundant storage with custom shelving and a private backyard oasis. The first level features a massive living room that leads to the chef’s kitchen with island, quartz countertops, stainless steel appliances, exhaust hood over gas stove and plentiful custom cabinetry and shelving. Located directly off the kitchen is a spacious two-tiered low maintenance backyard that is lush with mature plantings and a beautiful backdrop of green ivy. Completing the first level is a convenient powder room. The stairs lead to an additional living room that can also be used as a large office, fitness room or can easily be converted into a 3rd bedroom. The large primary bedroom features a walk-in closet and en-suite bathroom with walk-in shower. The second bedroom can comfortably fit a queen-sized bed and is located next to the full bathroom with bathtub in the hallway. The deeded garage with incredible storage and driveway are included with this perfect home. Conveniently located close to Washington Park (sports courts, playground, splash pad and dog runs), bus lines to NYC, easy access to Route 1 & 9 and Central Ave’s shops, restaurants and cafes."
260000160,SOLD,"JC, Heights",63 WEBSTER AVE,Condominium,1246,6494,"$765,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,3,"JC, Heights",07307,4501,35,Heights,,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$765,000","$789,000",$613.96,$613.96,1/8/2026,1/16/2026,3/26/2026,8,8,,3/26/2026,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Franklin St & Ferry St,"Elevated Living Starts Here!! Nestled in the heart of The Heights, the fully renovated 63 Webster Ave offers three luxurious condos. Unit 3 features 2 bedrooms, 2 baths, and a glass enclosed Office/Den space, designed with sleek modern finishes and smart layouts. Enjoy access to the roof deck—perfect for relaxing, working outdoors, or hosting casual get-togethers with a view. The Heights neighborhood of Jersey City boasts vibrant energy and is commuter-friendly, just a few blocks from Pershing Field Park and Riverview-Fisk Park. Enjoy top-rated restaurants, cozy cafés, and local markets all within reach. *virtually staged rooftop photos *preliminary floor plans on architectural drawings. Final floor plans to come"
230008174,SOLD,"JC, Heights",73 BLEECKER ST,Condominium,1529,1597,"$765,000",CONDO-COOP,,2&R,2,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,6,,"$765,000","$775,000",$500.33,$500.33,5/18/2023,6/16/2023,8/3/2023,29,29,,8/3/2023,,,,,,$160,,Conventional,,,,,,Pierce Ave & Summit Ave,"Upgrade your every day with elegance in this three bed, two bath with private roofdeck and garage in Jersey City Heights. Beautifully constructed in 2018, classic design incorporates crown molding, 4.25”  hardwood floors, recess and stylish pendant lighting, plus large Pella windows on three sides of the home allowing for loads of natural light.  State-of-the-art amenities include surround sound in the living room, outdoor speakers on the rooftop, keyless Schlage entry, security camera and video intercom, plus Tesla EV car charger in tandem garage. Open concept eat-in kitchen showcases white quartz counters, herringbone backsplash, shaker cabinets with glass display accents, stainless appliances including hood, and timeless farm sink. Head up to the serenading full-floor private rooftop complete with built-in shade umbrella and 360 cityscape views. Spa-inspired bathrooms boast features like floor to ceiling tile with beautiful black hexagonal tile accents, glass shower with cutout niche or spacious soaker tub and polished chrome multi system fixtures.   Settled on tree-lined street in the heart of The Heights, this home offers direct access to beautiful Washington Park with playgrounds, track fields, baseball fields, and tennis courts, both Central Ave and Summit Ave with excellent shops and restaurants, and the 9th street elevator to Hoboken, Lightrail or PATH. Jersey City Heights is known for its artistic vibe, excellent community, great schools, parks and easy NYC access."
210013082,SOLD,"JC, Heights",40 MILTON AVE,Condominium,1925,1419,"$765,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1,"JC, Heights",07307,02704,00002,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,8,,"$765,000","$750,000",$397.40,$397.40,6/1/2021,6/15/2021,7/21/2021,14,14,,7/22/2021,,,,"$9,684",2020,$200,,Conventional,No,No,Yes,,,Charles & Bowers,"Welcome to 40 Milton, a one of a kind 3 bedroom, 2 bathroom recently built condo in the heart of Jersey City Heights. This captivating condo offers over 1,900 sq ft of living space with two deeded covered parking spots. The home boasts 10’ ceilings and hardwood floors with an open concept living room and kitchen with a large island built with quartz countertops, beautiful backsplash and stainless steel premium appliances perfect for those who love to cook and entertaining. The main bedroom includes an en-suite bathroom with a double vanity, an expansive walk–in closet, and a large balcony. The two other bedrooms are also spacious with large closets. The home also has an outdoor patio with a gas line for a grill and a bonus den room that can be used as an office, gym or additional family fun space. Everything will be easy to organize with the ample amount of storage space. The home also features a central vacuum, an HVAC system controlled by a Nest thermostat, a Ring doorbell, and laundry closet with washer / dryer.  The home is close to public transportation, PATH, ferry, major highway, parks, markets and a ton of amazing restaurants. Call us today for a private showing!"
250019619,SOLD,"JC, Heights",214 SHERMAN AVE,Condominium,1185,1686,"$765,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,1,"JC, Heights",07307,2301,18,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,6,,"$765,000","$750,000",$645.57,$645.57,9/23/2025,9/29/2025,11/17/2025,6,6,,11/17/2025,,,,"$11,841",,$250,,Conventional,,,,,,Bowers and South,"Discover your next home just two blocks from vibrant Washington Park in Jersey City Heights. This spacious 3 bedroom, 2 bathroom residence offers the perfect blend of modern comfort and urban convenience.  Step inside to find a thoughtfully designed layout featuring central air conditioning, an in-unit washer and dryer, and a custom chef’s kitchen that’s truly the heart of the home. The kitchen boasts handmade terracotta backsplash tiles, quartz countertops, a waterfall island, and custom cabinet lighting. Ideal for both everyday living and entertaining.  Enjoy the convenience of garage parking for two cars, plus access to a shared yard, providing a private outdoor retreat in the city. With just a short commute to Hoboken or Manhattan, this home combines neighborhood charm with unbeatable accessibility.  More than a home, it’s a lifestyle, offering comfort, convenience, and character in one of Jersey City’s most sought-after neighborhoods."
220021748,SOLD,"JC, Heights",58 GARRISON AVE,Condominium,2312,6199,"$765,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1,"JC, Heights",07306,,,,,,,,3,1,2,7,,"$765,000","$749,000",$330.88,$330.88,12/21/2022,1/11/2022,2/28/2023,0,0,,3/1/2023,,,,$0,,$125,,Conventional,,,,,,SIP & PAVONIA,"Open the door into this luxurious, newly restored 3 bedroom 2.5 bath duplex unit gleaming with natural light and a huge, unique open concept layout designed by Blue Chip Living. This modern farmhouse style home is located within walking distance to Journal Square! The home features a dining area accented by an electric linear LED fireplace which flows into the beautiful chef’s kitchen with two tone shaker cabinets, pot filler, smart stainless-steel appliances, and a spacious waterfall quartz center island. Oversized primary bedroom consists of 8 ft sliding glass door to paver patio, a barn door walk-in closet, and ensuite bath detailing spa like features. Two additional bedrooms with closet space and stunning bathroom with a double vanity and high-end porcelain tile complete the main floor. Lower-level room can be utilized as home office, or extended family and half bath. Other key features in this stunning home are hardwood floors throughout, an in-unit laundry hook up, and a paver patio to the backyard. Full smart home technology creates ease of living complete with Ring doorbell, Nest thermostat, Lighting Dimmer Switches accessible via smart phone. One car shared parking is included. All major transportation at your fingertips Close to all conveniences, major highways, minutes to Journal Square PATH terminal for a quick commute to NYC. Make this your Dream Home today! Special LOW RATES in 5% RANGE, CONV With 5% Down Payment NO PMI AND BANK FEES. Eligible for 5 year tax abatement."
210018528,SOLD,"JC, Heights",193 BOWERS ST,Condominium,,1691,"$765,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,6,,"$765,000","$769,000",,,8/4/2021,9/7/2021,11/3/2021,34,34,,11/3/2021,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Summit Ave and Milton Ave,"Quality crafted by one of Jersey City’s top developers, this newly renovated home offers ultimate sophistication and stylish finishes with an abundance of spaciousness both inside and out. With striking curb appeal, the modern matte black siding with oversized glazed window exterior welcomes owners into their private entrance and beyond to these transformative three bedroom homes.   Head upstairs to this ethereal penthouse with soaring vaulted ceilings and two-story high windows, architectural design elements like the slatted peekaboo staircase wall and, of course, a panoramic rooftop with NYC views.  This trophy home showcases ultra modern, clean kitchens with elements like waterfall quartz counters, exposed shelves on tile backsplash, natural wood accents and matte black fixtures. Finish it off with custom cabinetry finished to the ceiling, built-in stainless appliances, and unique pendant lighting throughout for an everyday chef’s dream.   Light pours into the luxury bathrooms giving natural light to the double vanity, tall glass showers including crafted niche and matte black rainhead and hand fixtures and floor to ceiling porcelain tile. Beautiful master suite boasts sliding glass doors to balcony for additional private outdoor access.  Settled into an ideal tree-lined street one block from Central Avenue, this location also offers walkability to Leonard Gordon and surrounding parks, plus vibrant community, excellent schools, award-winning restaurants and shops plus easy NYC access!"
210009594,SOLD,"JC, Heights",28 SOUTH ST,Condominium,1282,1656,"$765,000",CONDO-COOP,,1&2,1,"JC, Heights",07307,02304,00030.02,Heights,The Warwick,,,,3,1,2,6,,"$765,000","$784,000",$596.72,$596.72,4/22/2021,5/29/2021,7/27/2021,37,37,,7/27/2021,,,,"$8,769",2020,$190,,Conventional,No,No,No,,,Palisade & New York Ave.,"The Warwick, professionally designed w/high end finishes & newly built in 2018. Spacious 3 bedroom 2.5 bath duplex w/family room and backyard. Chef's kitchen has Carrera marble counters & matching herringbone backsplash, stainless steel appliances, Shaker cabinets, industrial-grade faucet & breakfast bar w/pendant lights. Bright south-facing living area, recessed & custom lighting, 8 wide oak floors throughout, crown moldings, Andersen 400 Series windows & doors & solid core interior doors. Primary bedroom with walk-in closet & private terrace. Bathrooms feature Porcelanosa tile & fixtures. Family room for sports fans w/adjoining 1/2 bath leads to your deeded backyard w/new pavers. Central air and washer/dryer in the home. Garage tandem parking with storage. Quality construction w/transferable home warranty. 25% Tax abatement until June 2023. Excellent location, close to bus and light rail access."
210009141,SOLD,"JC, Heights",31 ZABRISKIE ST,Condominium,1707,6078,"$769,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,6,,"$769,000","$769,000",$450.50,$450.50,4/16/2021,4/30/2021,6/11/2021,14,14,,6/11/2021,,,,"$10,200",2020,,,Conventional,No,No,,,,Central Ave and Summit Ave,"Welcome to 31 Zabriskie Street, Jersey City, an exquisite brand new property where modern meets traditional. This captivating Victorian style home, with beautifully restored antique exterior is a rare find, in the heart of Jersey City Heights. Custom quality, thoughtful design, state-of-the-art modern finishes, built by one of Jersey City's finest developers, is elevating the standards of sophisticated and modern living. This brand new 3 bedroom 2 bathroom smart home spans over a 25’x107’ lot, offering 1707 square feet of open-concept living, with a state of the art Chef's Kitchen. This immaculate condominium features 10' ceilings, 7' solid-core doors, white oak hardwood flooring and oversized bay windows to allow abundant natural light.   The impeccable white high gloss European Style kitchen cabinetry with soft close, luxury stainless steel appliances, a wifi & bluetooth enabled refrigerator, central island featuring waterfall quartz countertop, a wine cooler and drawer microwave, spares no expense in the intricate design kitchen. The master bedroom includes an ensuite spa-like bathroom with dual rain showers, and an expansive walk-in closet. This magnificent condo with carefully considered floor plan that rivals Manhattan standard luxury, also provides large second bedroom, a dedicated Home Office space and a second bathroom featuring clean design, waterfall mosaic tiles, floating vanity and a soaking tub. The encompassed 451 sqft. of private rooftop deck and outdoor space with stunning panoramic NYC views is unbeatable. This Smart Home creates ease of living and efficiency through a central HVAC sys regulated by the Nest thermostat, Wi-Fi enabled lights, Smart doorbell, all integrated via a Smart home hub. This unit also comes fully equipped with washer and dryer and includes 1 car driveway parking.   Set in the heart of Jersey City Heights, enjoy walkability to vibrant Central Avenue, where you will find the neighboring grocery stores, supermarket, major banks, public library, pharmacy, famous café and restaurants, that make routine shopping trips a breeze. Located at 2 mins walk from Hutton ST bus stop, 119 bus to NYC takes you to Port Authority within 25 mins. Close to Washington and Leonard Gordon parks, excellent schools and easy NYC access makes this property quintessential.  "
230001256,SOLD,"JC, Heights",176 SHERMAN AVE,Condominium,1716,1597,"$770,000",CONDO-COOP,,1 & 2,101,"JC, Heights",07307,02301,00002,Heights,,,,,2,0,2,6,,"$770,000","$799,000",$448.72,$448.72,1/23/2023,3/30/2023,5/19/2023,66,66,,5/19/2023,,,,"$13,255",2022,$640,,Conventional,,,,,,Bowers & South,"Situated in the coveted Bakery Lofts building in the Riverview Arts District of The Heights, this voluminous and beautifully appointed loft residence offers over 1,700sf of living space, soaring 12ft ceilings and an incredible amount of storage. This duplex condominium features its very own private entrance, central air conditioning, in-unit washer/dryer, and two heated garage parking spaces. Enter the residence to be greeted by the impressive open space with the kitchen and dining area overlooking the living room and private outdoor space. The kitchen features an oversized natural stone waterfall island, stainless steel appliances and bar with wine fridge. The large dining area is perfect for entertaining. The first bedroom and full bathroom with a massive shower are tucked away in the rear. Moving down to the lower level you will find the enormous primary suite featuring plentiful wardrobe space, work from home office area, laundry closet and bathroom with double vanity and deep soaking tub. The Bakery Lofts is a 17-unit elevator building conveniently located on a quiet tree-lined street near bus service to NYC, light rail, Riverview Park, shops and restaurants. "
