210022283,SOLD,"JC, Heights",192 CONGRESS ST,Condominium,1707,1605,"$799,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1,"JC, Heights",07307,01402,00034,,,,,,3,1,2,9,,"$799,000","$825,000",$468.07,$468.07,9/24/2021,11/3/2021,12/17/2021,40,40,,12/19/2021,,,,"$2,401",2020,$295,2021,Conventional,,,,,,Summit & Pierce,"Welcome home to this one year young high end unit in the heart of booming Jersey City Heights. This stunning 3 bedroom, 2.5 bath home stretches over 1700 square feet with a private backyard and garage parking. Wide open floor plan with 10 foot ceilings, oversized windows-allowing for tremendous natural sunlight-and a smart home package with tons of upgrades added to make this the perfect place to call home. An amazing chef’s kitchen awaits its new owner, detailed with high gloss modern style cabinetry, stainless steel Premium Samsung Appliance package that includes a smart refrigerator with digital screen, built in drawer microwave, and a full center island with waterfall Quartz countertops. Large open living room which provides space for a separate dining area. Spacious master bedroom suite with a private terrace, fully outfitted designer walk in closet with a sliding barn door and a gorgeous bathroom with wall mounted vanity, luxurious full body multi jet digital glass enclosed shower with Porcelain tiles and West Elm fixtures. Two generously sized guest bedrooms, each fitted with built in closet systems. Guest bath features a full sized soaking tub and dual vanity with Quartz countertops. Access the lower level by a custom designed interior staircase and step into an oversized custom family room/den with wet bar, wine fridge and a lovely half bath. From here, glass sliders will lead you to a private yard with pavers and grass-this is the perfect spot to entertain, garden or just enjoy the outdoors. Other features not to be missed are in home laundry with additional storage, hardwood floors throughout main level, beautiful custom tile on lower level, central A/C & heat controlled by Nest, 7 foot solid doors and an indoor garage parking spot. Full smart home technology includes Nest thermostat and security doorbell, smart light fixtures, Google Home Hub and My Q Smart garage door opener. Close to all shopping and major highways with easy transportation into NYC via bus or Congress Street light rail to Hoboken’s Path station. Take advantage of the 4 years left on the tax abatement & make this home yours today!"
240010235,SOLD,"JC, Heights",573 PALISADE AVE,Condominium,941,1603,"$799,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2B,"JC, Heights",07307,02304,00024,Heights,,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$799,000","$799,000",$849.10,$849.10,5/30/2024,6/17/2024,10/3/2024,18,18,,10/3/2024,,,,$0,,,,Conventional,No,No,No,,,Congress St & South St,"New construction home in elevator building with 554 sf private terrace!  Welcome to 573 Palisade Avenue, where unparalleled sophistication meets breathtaking views in an exclusive collection of seven condominium homes in a boutique-style elevator building.  Each two-bedroom, two-bathroom condominium home features spacious open floor plans of meticulously designed living space and private outdoor spaces. 10 - 14 ft ceilings soar above engineered hardwood floors, creating an airy sanctuary illuminated by recessed and custom light fixtures. The expansive triple pane Pella windows frame stunning vistas of the Manhattan skyline, inviting you to unwind against a backdrop of urban splendor. Kitchens feature custom 2-toned cabinetry, Samsung stainless steel appliances, Calacatta Laza Quartz countertops, wine cooler and direct vent exhaust hood. Bathrooms include Porcelanosa tiles with Kohler fixtures, deep soaking tubs and dual flush toilets.  You'll love the convenience of having in-home laundry, integrated intercom and security system and a home that is prewired for home automation.  Unwind and socialize on our exclusive residents rooftop lounge offering sweeping NYC views, providing an extraordinary backdrop for relaxation or entertaining guests. This property boasts unparalleled ease of access to New York City, making your commute as breezy as a walk in the adjacent Fisk Park. Whether you prefer the NJ Transit buses or the convenience of the 9th Street-Congress Street Light Rail Station right at your doorstep, your connection to the city has never been smoother. And with breathtaking views of the Manhattan skyline from your window, every day feels like a picturesque escape. This prime Jersey City Heights location offers you not just a home, but a lifestyle."
230002023,SOLD,"JC, Heights",97 LAIDLAW AVE,Condominium,1313,1603,"$799,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,2,"JC, Heights",07306,05705,00014,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,7,,"$799,000","$795,000",$608.53,$608.53,2/5/2023,2/16/2023,4/4/2023,11,11,,4/4/2023,,,,$0,,$489,,Conventional,No,No,No,,,Central Ave & Oakland Ave,"97 Laidlaw Ave is a collection of five timeless new construction condominium homes consisting of three and four bedrooms, two and three bath homes. Unit 2 is a three bedroom, two bath home and includes a private backyard. Full-service kitchen designed to flow smoothly into and out of the living area features Graphite Steel LG and Frigidaire appliances, two-toned matte cabinetry with custom integrated cabinet lighting, Himalayan White Granite waterfall countertops and floating wall shelves. This elegant space with dining area is perfectly suited for casual dining as well as entertaining. Luxurious bathrooms offering you a spa-like retreat with an assortment of carefully selected materials and textures that are exceptional including Roca Piasentina silver polished large format tiles throughout, 60'' double vessel sink on a floating vanity, 30'' natural oak vanities, showers with horizontal niche and integrated led lighting, fixed glass enclosed shower with rain shower head and more. Every home offers unparalleled detail from expansive open floor plan living spaces and high-end finishes to massive private balconies, exclusive backyards, elevator, garage parking and deeded rooftop spaces with NYC views.  97 Laidlaw Ave sits in prime location only a few short blocks from Pershing Field Park and only one block to the Central Ave shopping district. Commute with ease to NYC via NJ Transit buses right on Central Ave or a quick 15 minute walk to the JSQ PATH train. City-bikes located one block from the property. Offering you larger living spaces at desirable price points while maintaining close proximity to NYC, these one-of-a-kind new construction homes are so luxurious you’ll never want to leave!  Property eligible for 5 year tax abatement."
230003841,SOLD,"JC, Heights",39 MONTROSE AVE,Condominium,1356,1419,"$799,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07307,04307,00020,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,6,,"$799,000","$799,000",$589.23,$589.23,12/3/2022,12/19/2022,1/27/2023,16,0,,3/9/2023,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Carlton Ave. & Beach St.,"The Jersey City Heights welcomes its newest construction! This modern 3 bed and 2 bath boasts hardwood floors throughout, 8ft custom doors, high ceilings, crown molding, in unit washer dryer, LED lighting, built in speaker wiring, and a private roof deck! Marble counters, custom cabinets, stainless steel appliance, luxurious finishes provides an elevated ambiance in your home. Located in an unbeatable area of the Heights that is easily commutable and accessible to public transportation with direct bus lines to NYC Port Authority, Hoboken, and Downtown JC. The Hudson Light Rail Stations are also nearby as well as Pershing Field's indoor pool and ice skating rink being only a few blocks away. Riverview Park with its amazing views offers Farmers Market, movie nights, and neighborhood events! 1 car garage parking included! Call us for a private tour today, move in ready by January 2023!"
220010867,SOLD,"JC, Heights",63 SOUTH ST,Condominium,1020,1691,"$799,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,3,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,2,1,2,5,,"$799,000","$799,000",$783.33,$783.33,6/14/2022,6/14/2022,6/14/2022,0,0,,6/14/2022,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Sherman Ave & Webster Ave,"Make this modern marvel home in The Heights! Local builders, Nkay Construction, have done it again with this super smart floor through 2 bed, 2.5 bath complete with parking (equipped with eCharging stations for each unit!).  Situated on the corner of a tree-lined street, this impressive home offers oversized windows with sunlight streaming in on three sides of the 2 bed and 2.5 bath layout. Beautiful bay windows open to the spacious upstairs with flowing kitchen, living and dining area complete with pewter oak hardwood floors and crown molding.   Gorgeous navy blue accents in island highlight the bright eat-in kitchen with waterfall quartz counters, tile backsplash and custom shaker cabinets. Additional features include apron sink, black stainless Samsung appliances and matte black fixtures including wall mounted pot filler faucet. Stylish bathrooms offer highlights such as herringbone grey porcelain tile, smart mirrors and glass shower with penny tile floor pattern plus multi head rain shower system. Primary ensuite offers a must-have double vanity and built-out walk-in closet.   Additional tech upgrades include smart doorbell, smart thermostat, camera and security system and central vacuum. Situated walking distance to bustling Central Avenue, expansive Washington Park or Riverview Fisk Park with NYC views and light rail access, this home is the ideal combination of location and modern luxury."
260005123,ACTIVE,"JC, Heights",183 ZABRISKIE ST,Condominium,1277,1750,"$799,999",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07307-1111,3304,31,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,6,,,"$799,999",$626.47,,3/24/2026,,,16,,,3/24/2026,,,,,,$75,2026,,No,No,Yes,,,liberty and terrace,"Welcome to Unit 2 at 183 Zabriskie Street, a beautifully designed 3-bedroom, 2-bath residence offering approximately 1,280 square feet of refined living within a newly built boutique development in Jersey City Heights. This light-filled home showcases a seamless open-concept layout complemented by wide-plank flooring, elevated finishes, and a sleek contemporary kitchen featuring custom cabinetry, stainless steel appliances, generous workspace, and a dedicated wine bar area for added sophistication. The well-proportioned primary suite and versatile secondary bedrooms provide flexibility for modern living, while elegantly appointed bathrooms and thoughtfully integrated storage enhance both comfort and functionality. Additional highlights include in-unit washer/dryer, dishwasher, and meticulous attention to detail throughout. Perfectly positioned for effortless access to transportation, neighborhood favorites, and vibrant city life, this residence offers a polished blend of style, convenience, and contemporary design."
220018236,SOLD,"JC, Heights",24 THORNE ST,Condominium,1607,6494,"$800,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1,"JC, Heights",07307,02805,00042,,,,,,3,1,2,6,,"$800,000","$800,000",$497.82,$497.82,10/13/2022,10/26/2022,12/16/2022,13,13,,12/16/2022,,,,"$7,994",2021,$272,,Conventional,,,,,,Central Ave and Summit Ave,"Recently constructed and centrally located 1607 square foot duplex condo with coveted landscaped yard and garage parking located in the thriving Heights area of Jersey City. This warm and inviting home has it all including an abundance of natural light, 3 bedrooms, 2.5 bath, tandem garage parking, private backyard and balcony, sleek chef's kitchen with statement island, quartz countertops and wine fridge, a south-facing sunlit living room with oversized windows, in-unit washer dryer, central air and recessed lighting and beautiful plank oak floors throughout. Serene main bedroom has a custom walk-in closet, a balcony overlooking your lush backyard and ensuite bathroom with a step-in shower. Two additional bedrooms with ample storage are on the same level. Lower level has a spacious bonus room, half bath and direct access to the tandem garage (with added storage) and your large backyard with a porcelain paver patio, grass and shrubs perfect for entertaining, gardening, barbecuing or just relaxing. Living here will also give you the added advantage of being just steps to the NYC bus and to all the restaurants and shops in the burgeoning and lively Central Ave district which is currently undergoing major renovations. Convenient to parks, playground, tennis and basketball courts, pool, dog run and a 10 minute walk to the elevator/steps to Hoboken, the 9th St Lightrail (which connects to the Path train) and Riverview Park offering amazing NYC skyline views and an impressive weekend farmer's market. The 2 unit building completed construction in 2020. If you are seeking a spacious and stylish condo primely located with garage parking and private outdoor space this is the perfect home for you!"
230001078,SOLD,"JC, Heights",199 GRIFFITH ST,Condominium,1376,1713,"$800,000",CONDO-COOP,,1 &2,2,"JC, Heights",07307,03704,00011,,,,,,3,0,2,7,,"$800,000","$800,000",$581.40,$581.40,1/19/2023,2/17/2023,4/20/2023,29,29,,4/21/2023,,,,,,$275,,Conventional,,,,,,Summit Ave & Central Ave,"Welcome to this luxurious 1300+ sq foot condo in the highly sought-after Jersey City Heights! This 3 bed 2 bath condo is all new construction and features a beautiful and serene private rooftop patio that is fully equipped with an outdoor kitchen and grill and has beautiful NYC views! The custom chef’s kitchen is complete with stainless steel appliances and the open floor plan in the kitchen and bright spacious living room allow for great entertainment space. The primary bedroom boasts a large walk-in closet as well as an en suite with double sink vanity. This unit features a modern design throughout, a separate private entrance, additional private storage, and a parking spot in the attached garage! Don’t miss the opportunity to own this beautiful unit!"
220002798,SOLD,"JC, Heights",234 CAMBRIDGE AVE,Condominium,2127,5111,"$800,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1,"JC, Heights",07307,01602,00040,,,,,,4,0,3,9,,"$800,000","$725,000",$376.12,$376.12,2/17/2022,2/22/2022,4/4/2022,5,5,,4/4/2022,,,,,,$235,,Conventional,,,,,,Congress and North Street,"Beautiful and spacious 2-floor condominium home, steps from Washington Park and bustling Central Avenue in Jersey City's booming Heights neighborhood. The main floor features 3 bedrooms, 2 full bathrooms, laundry room with full sized washer/dryer and a large, open kitchen/dining/living area with balcony. The kitchen includes custom cabinets, a large island, stainless steel appliances and a walk-in pantry. The main bedroom suite has a large walk-in closet, custom built-ins and an en-suite bathroom. This home's amenities include hardwood floors, recessed lighting, central air with smart thermostat. The ground floor features a huge 515 sq ft (approx) living space with separate entrance, wet bar, full bathroom, and bonus room that has been used as a home office. This space has endless possibilities, it can we used as a large fourth bedroom, recreation room, art/music/photo studio, media room, guest room or in-law suite. Also on this level is a private, deeded one-car garage and a door to the shared back yard. Easy commute to NYC, steps away from mass transit. Close to the Congress Street elevator to the Hoboken Light Rail Station. Direct bus to Manhattan on the corner. VIA to Journal Square PATH. Pet friendly!"
