his prime Jersey City Heights location offers you not just a home, but a lifestyle."
240001867,SOLD,"JC, Heights",89 LINCOLN ST,Condominium,1466,6199,"$800,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1,"JC, Heights",07307,02702,00003,Heights,,,,,3,1,3,7,,"$800,000","$845,000",$545.70,$545.70,1/31/2024,2/23/2024,4/9/2024,23,23,,4/9/2024,,,,,,$125,2023,Conventional,No,No,Yes,,,GPS,"Brand New Unique Triplex Condo Townhouse, located in the heart of the highly desirable Jersey City Heights! Featuring 3 bedrooms, 3.5 baths, corner unit with an abundance of large windows drenched in natural sun light. Main living area with custom design metal railing, high ceilings with LED strip lighting make for a luxurious modern feel, sliding glass doors leading to balcony, contemporary fully equipped kitchen, with stainless steel appliances, high gloss white cabinetry, white quartz countertops and waterfall center island for additional storage, 3rd bedroom with a beautiful modern full bath and stand-up shower completes the floor. Lower-level flex room with private entrance, built-in wet bar, half bath perfect for family/living or home office, top floors main bedroom with a private balcony, wall to wall closet, generous 2nd bedroom, and 2 full baths, one with a tub and the other with a stand-up shower, bonus home office area. Hardwood floors, central A/C, washer and dryer room, private rooftop deck with adjacent wet bar and breathtaking views. 1 private parking garage (not tandem), exclusive use of the front yard, and plenty of storage! All major transportation at your fingertips, Close to all conveniences, parks, schools, library, restaurants, and more! Unpack and move in! Property is eligible for a 5 year tax abatement!"
230016659,SOLD,"JC, Heights",18 THORNE ST,Condominium,1500,1597,"$802,000",CONDO-COOP,,2&3,2,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,3,1,2,6,,"$802,000","$785,000",$534.67,$534.67,10/4/2023,11/2/2023,12/15/2023,29,29,,12/15/2023,,,,"$10,974",,,,Conventional,,,,,,Central & Summit,"Get that much-needed upgrade in living with this two-story, 3 bedroom, 2.5 bath home including private rooftop in sought-after Jersey City. Newer construction with incredible upgrades, this modern home compliments the beautiful brick facade and classic style throughout.  Light streams in through the two-story windows and onto the open concept kitchen and dining or living room finished with sparkling marble floors. Finishes include waterfall quartz counters at the breakfast bar, plus mosaic backsplash, custom cabinetry with under cabinet lighting, stainless appliances and hood. Head upstairs to the beautiful loft living area finished with gorgeous built-in, including a wine drawer, and overlooking the downstairs and oversized windows finished with remote-controlled shades for privacy and ease.  The upstairs is finished with gleaming hardwood floors, plus crown molding throughout, and elegant accents like wallpaper walls and tray ceilings. Bathrooms feature extras like wood tile, rainhead and mult-system showers, soaker tubs and a window for natural light.  Owners take advantage of the extended private roofdeck with cityscape views, ideal for daily enjoyment or excellent entertainment. Smarthome features include video security entrance, climate control and emergency water heater shut off.  Located just off Central Avenue, this home is positioned on a beautiful tree-lined street in the heart of The Heights. Jersey City Heights is known for its vibrant community, great schools, beautiful parks and easy access to NYC and surrounding areas.  "
240015524,SOLD,"JC, Heights",126 WEBSTER AVE,Condominium,1550,1713,"$802,500",CONDO-COOP,,3,3c,"JC, Heights",07307,04503,00017,Heights,Hugo Pronti Lofts,,,,2,0,1,6,,"$802,500","$825,000",$517.74,$517.74,8/8/2024,8/22/2024,10/23/2024,14,14,,10/24/2024,,,,"$13,682",2022,$552,,Conventional,,,,,,HUTTON AND FRANKLIN,"Discover an unparalleled loft living experience in the heart of Jersey City Heights! This remarkable home offers 1550 square feet of space, soaring 12-foot ceilings, a private garage, and a secured storage area. As you step inside, you're greeted by hardwood floors, exposed brick, massive original timber beams, exposed ductwork, and industrial steel braces. Currently configured as an open-plan one-bedroom loft, this space can easily be converted into a two-bedroom layout. The chef's kitchen features granite countertops, Bosch stove, microwave, and dishwasher, under-cabinet lighting, and plenty of storage. The living and dining area, complete with a gas fireplace, custom built-ins, and direct patio access, is ideal for both large parties and intimate gatherings. The bathroom boasts custom Kohler fixtures and a deep soaking Jacuzzi tub. Additional highlights include upgraded light fixtures, central A/C, washer/dryer hookups, and ample closet space. Situated in the vibrant Riverview Arts District of Jersey City's Heights, you'll enjoy new restaurants, farmers markets, shopping, community events, parks, and easy access to NYC via NJ Transit bus to Port Authority or the Hoboken 2nd Street Light Rail Station to the PATH. Don't miss the chance to make this extraordinary loft your new home!"
230003911,SOLD,"JC, Heights",51 SANFORD PL,Condominium,1641,1597,"$803,000",CONDO-COOP,,2&3,2,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,3,1,2,6,,"$803,000","$799,000",$489.34,$489.34,3/10/2023,3/29/2023,5/16/2023,19,19,,5/17/2023,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Mahattan Ave & Sanford Pl,"Stylish and spacious, this brand new home is move-in ready and nestled between Pershing Field and Leonard Gordon Parks in The Heights. Two-story, expansive layouts include three bedrooms, two and a half baths, and all the modern must-haves. Plus, the upstairs unit hosts a fully finished rooftop with exquisite 360 degree views.   Angled corner building adds both extra square footage and extra light showcasing finishes like crown molding, light oak or walnut hardwood floors. Kitchens wow with white shaker cabinets with matte black shiplap island, waterfall quartz counters, stainless farm sink, black Samsung appliances and wine refrigerator.  In addition to the private rooftop, this upstairs unit hosts an absolutely enormous primary ensuite, allowing ultimate opportunities for usage. Bathrooms feature elements like herringbone tile finished to the ceiling, or black penny tile floors and glass shower.  Set on a special corner ideally located between two great parks, and two main thoroughfares, this home is positioned to provide the best of urban living. Jersey CIty Heights is known for great community, picturesque parks, excellent schools and easy NYC access."
220016218,SOLD,"JC, Heights",11 IRVING ST,Condominium,1400,6199,"$803,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,6,,"$803,000","$779,000",$573.57,$573.57,9/9/2022,2/9/2023,3/24/2023,153,153,,3/24/2023,,,,,,$250,,Conventional,No,No,Yes,,,Summit Ave and John F. Kennedy Blvd,"Brand-new construction - spares no expense! Located in the heart of booming Jersey City Heights. Features include 3 bedrooms, 2 bathrooms, modern open concept living, a fully equipped kitchen with state-of-the-art stainless steel appliances, a 5 burner stove, a convection oven, custom cabinets, and quartz countertops with a breakfast bar. The main bedroom with private en-suite bath and sliding glass doors that lead to your balcony, 2 generous sized bedrooms. Features include hardwood floors throughout, central air/heat, washer and dryer, and LED lighting. Minutes to Congress St. Light Rail, Journal Square PATH and bus station, restaurants, shops, and all major highways and tunnels. Come and see for yourself why Jersey City was named the Sixth Borough of New York City. 1 year free parking paid by seller."
230000901,SOLD,"JC, Heights",87 LEONARD ST,Condominium,1658,1707,"$805,000",CONDO-COOP,,1/2,#1,"JC, Heights",07307,00403,00028,Heights,,,,,3,1,2,9,,"$805,000","$822,000",$485.52,$485.52,1/16/2023,1/17/2023,4/11/2023,1,1,,4/12/2023,,,,,,$275,,Conventional,,,,,,*off JFK Blvd.,"New NKAY Construction in a spectacular tree lined and prime location; Jersey City Heights (steps away to NY transportation)!  *BUYERS CONCESSION:  $10,000 CREDIT AT CLOSING FOR ALLOWABLE CLOSING COSTS*  This superior quality 3 bed, 2.5 bath condo features: 1658 square foot of living space with deeded parking (Electric Charging Station) and private back yard space (gas-water-electric connections), modern white kitchen containing quartz counter tops with waterfall island and Samsung black stainless steel appliances, wine fridge, Kohler plumbing fixtures, custom closets, high end finishes including crown moldings, aluminum railings, low voltage system (burglar alarm, video door bell, 5.1 channel home theater), elevated framing materials used for improved insulation and sound proof penetration, garage parking and much more! *10 years builders warranty & 5 year tax abatement included. Very close to NY transportation, shopping, restaurants, parks and schools.  Schedule now!"
230007944,SOLD,"JC, Heights",31 ZABRISKIE ST,Condominium,1707,1739,"$805,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07307,03703,00012,,,,,,3,0,2,9,,"$805,000","$799,000",$471.59,$471.59,5/15/2023,5/30/2023,7/6/2023,15,15,,7/6/2023,,,,"$13,532",2022,$180,,Conventional,,,,,,Central Ave and Summit Ave,"Private Driveway and Park Spot, Private Rooftop, Private Entrance. Welcome to 31 Zabriskie Street, Residence 2, which feels more like a townhome than a condominium in Jersey City Heights! A Victorian style home that has been fully restored, enjoy incredibly high-ceilings (10ft) and open living space (1,707 square feet). A blend of modern finishes with Jersey City charm, this 3 bedroom, 2 full bath home starts as you enter your own entry foyer right off the driveway, perfect for coats, shoes, strollers, groceries, and more. From the foyer, up the staircase, enter your main living space with the state-of-the-art chef’s kitchen overlooking an incredible living/dining room space, with built in fireplace adding warmth to the entire area. On the main living floor, you have all three bedrooms, including the primary with ensuite and walk in closet, as well as the second full bath. Each room is tremendous in size, giving you the space to grow in to, as opposed to grow out of. From the living room, continuing up the interior staircase, enter to your own private rooftop outfit with a roof deck, and artificial turf, which maximizes the space when entertaining and staring off to your unobstructed NYC views stretching from Hudson Yars to the World Trade Center. The home finishes include a waterfall quartz countertop island, white oak hardwood flooring, bay windows, European white high gloss kitchen cabinetry with soft close, luxury appliances, wine cooler, and drawer microwave. The biggest amenity however is your private driveway with single car parking. Avoid the hassle of shared parking and save time by pulling into your own driveway when coming home. The location is as good as it gets in The Heights, immediately located off Central Ave with walking accessibility to supermarkets, banks, restaurants, cafes, and more. The 119 bus stop to NYC is less than 1 minute walk, and unmatched proximity to renowned Pershing Park and soon to be complete Reservoir walk and trails, which only adds to the quickly growing neighborhood. With all the access you could want in Jersey City, 31 Zabriskie Street is the opportunity you have been waiting for. Schedule a private showing today and see why this home puts you at the height of Jersey City living."
230018828,SOLD,"JC, Heights",126 WEBSTER AVE,Condominium,1288,1597,"$805,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,3F,"JC, Heights",07307,04503,00017,Heights,,,,,2,0,1,6,,"$805,000","$799,000",$625.00,$625.00,11/8/2023,11/28/2023,1/8/2024,20,20,,1/8/2024,,,,"$14,389",2023,$552,,Conventional,No,No,,,,Franklin & Hutton,"Situated in the coveted Hugo Pronti Loft building in the Riverview Arts District of The Heights, this voluminous and beautifully appointed loft residence offers 1,288sf of living space, soaring 14ft ceilings, hardwood floors, gas fireplace, in-unit washer dryer, Central AC, in-building storage locker and private 1-car garage. This corner unit is flooded with natural light featuring 2 bedrooms and 1 bathroom. The enormous living and dining room is sprawled out with the picturesque backdrop of exposed brick with southern and western exposures. The renovated chef’s kitchen boasts plentiful cabinetry, open shelving, beautiful quartzite natural stone counter tops, stainless steel appliances including Wolf range and a massive island perfect for entertaining. The two bedrooms are in excellent proportions and have plentiful closet space with custom built-ins. The bathroom is spacious and has a large bathtub. Soak in the southern light and open skies from the private large balcony. Conveniently located near bus service to NYC, light rail stations, Riverview Park with its panoramic views of NYC and farmer’s markets, Washington Park with playgrounds, sports fields and dog runs, and some of the city's most beloved cafes, restaurants & bars."
220002631,SOLD,"JC, Heights",126 WEBSTER AVE,Condominium,1687,1686,"$805,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2C,"JC, Heights",07307,04503,00017,Heights,,,,,1,0,1,3,,"$805,000","$750,000",$477.18,$477.18,2/15/2022,2/28/2022,3/31/2022,13,13,,4/1/2022,,,,"$10,997",2021,$551,2021,Conventional,,,,,,Hutton and Franklin St,"Tired of the typical white box condo layout that plagues the market currently? Well look no further than residence 2C at the sought after 126 Webster building in Jersey City Heights. This one bedroom stunner is the true definition of loft living with all the conveniences of a well placed layout and luxury design. Enter the home and let your eyes widen as you attempt to take in the soaring ceilings, original exposed wood and brick and massive windows. Walk past the recently renovated chefs kitchen boasting stainless steel appliances, abundant storage and large center island. Open to the living space this place just begs to host a cocktail party with walls perfect for the large art display that hugs your senses as you move throughout the room. Completely renovated with a designers eye, the space beckons you to move through it to the private dining space bursting with light and easily accommodating a massive dining table and statement chandelier (included in sale). This dining space is easily converted to a second bedroom with architect and building approval. On the right a bedroom space fit for a Queen with walk in closet, exposed brick and more of that piercing natural light. Summer afternoons take on a whole new purpose with your attached semi private covered deck off the living room and with laundry and fireplace in the unit you really don’t need to leave. Don’t forget the large walk in storage cage in the basement and your own private garage across the street both included in the sale. All this in one of Hudson County’s hottest neighborhoods minutes to Hoboken and New York City. Creativity lives here. So should you."
210007442,SOLD,"JC, Heights",36 LINCOLN ST,Condominium,,1592,"$805,500",CONDO-COOP,,1,1,"JC, Heights",07307,02802,00042,,,,,,3,1,2,7,,"$805,500","$799,000",,,3/30/2021,4/26/2021,6/30/2021,27,27,,7/7/2021,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,SUMMIT AVE & CENTRAL AVE,"Perfect location! Luxurious modern condos in desirable JC Heights. Custom quality, thoughtful design, built by one of Jersey City's finest developers, is elevating the standards of sophisticated and modern living. The immaculate condo features spacious large 3 bdrms, 2 full bthrms and 1/2 bthrm, laundry room, hardwood floors, marble titled bath, quartz waterfall kitchen counter tops, double vanity with led light mirror and walk–in closets, efficiency through a central HVAC sys regulated by the Nest thermostat and Smart Ring doorbell. This unit is built on an oversized lot includes 1 car garage parking. Enjoy walking vibrant Central Ave. where you will find the neighboring grocery stores, major banks, pharmacy, famous café, and restaurants. Nearby easy NYC access, close to Pershing Field and Leonard Gordon parks, excellent schools makes this property quintessential. Pictures aren't actual they are renderings. Only unit available hurry won't last call for an appointment ASAP !!"
210004253,SOLD,"JC, Heights",366 NEW YORK AVE,Condominium,1348,1724,"$806,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,3,"JC, Heights",07307,02304,00009,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,6,,"$806,000","$749,999",$597.92,$597.92,2/22/2021,3/1/2021,4/15/2021,7,7,,6/9/2021,,,,,,,,Conventional,No,No,,,,South st. & Congress,"New construction luxury at it's finest. Welcome home to 366 New York Ave a three unit boutique and the epitome of luxury and convenience. Explore this exceptional 3 bed/ 2bath home boasting 10 high ceilings, and solid 5 hard wood floors through out the entire home. Your sleek and modern chef's kitchen features high end digital Samsung stainless steel appliances, a wine cooler, 42 cabinets, quartz countertops, Sharp microwave, and a country style farmer sink. The master en-suite boasts a 55 sq ft balcony, and an installed Alexa system. Travel upstairs to your own expansive roof deck with speakers, gas and water access for entertainment. High end Finishes include home entertainment wiring with speakers, video intercom security system, Nest thermostat, custom closets, and an electric 50 stainless steel fire place for those cozy nights. Just the pure luxury of this home will make it an enjoyable place to call home. You could hear a button drop in this ultra-peaceful atmosphere, thanks to the extra-thick soundproofing, subfloor and insulation. This neighborhood is known for great schools and easy NYC access, all amid the eclectic and vibrant scene of Jersey City Heights. Nearby attractions include Hoboken’s Trader Joe’s, Bow Tie Cinemas, an array of revered diverse restaurants, bakeries, coffee houses and bars. NYC and metro area transportation on the corner, the expansive Washington park 1 block away, and Lightrail and Citibikes just a few blocks away. Your new urban home oasis awaits you!! ** eligible for a 5 year tax abatement** "
230002637,SOLD,"JC, Heights",50 COLUMBIA AVE,Condominium,1750,1623,"$810,000",CONDO-COOP,,1 & 2,1,"JC, Heights",07307,02602,00036,Heights,,,,,3,1,2,7,,"$810,000","$798,000",$462.86,$462.86,2/16/2023,4/7/2023,5/4/2023,50,50,,5/5/2023,,,,"$9,750",2022,,,Conventional,No,No,No,,,Lincoln & Thorne,"This stunning Duplex situated on a quiet block in The Heights is what you've been waiting for. With 1,750 sq.ft. of living space, a 25' x 25' sq.ft. private yard, shared tandem parking in garage and 2 spots in the driveway, this home ticks all the boxes. Featuring 3 bedrooms, 2.5 baths and an additional bonus room leading to the private backyard, this home blends modern luxury with timeless design. It has surround sound in the living room & backyard, a Honeywell security system, Nest thermostats, Ring video doorbell, built-out closets, 9' ceilings, hardwood floors and recessed lighting throughout. The wall of windows are a bright backdrop to the open concept living area complete with sleek electric fireplace. The crisp white kitchen has a breakfast bar, stainless Frigidaire Gallery appliances, wine fridge, disposal, and quartz countertops. Bathrooms are styled with modern vessel sink vanities, floor-to-ceiling porcelain tile and rain shower heads. As the warm weather approaches, imagine hosting family and friends al fresco under the dramatic cedar pergola. Located close to Washington Park, Pershing Field Park, and Leonard Park?, the friendly neighborhood is home to many eclectic shops, cafes and markets. Only 1 block to JFK Blvd buses to NYC or Journal Square PATH and NJ Transit hub. Easy access to RT 1/9, Lincoln and Holland Tunnels, as well as the NJ Turnpike.    "
230005909,SOLD,"JC, Heights",204 CAMBRIDGE AVE,Condominium,1250,5894,"$810,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1,"JC, Heights",07307,02203,00009,Heights,,,,,3,1,2,6,,"$810,000","$820,000",$648.00,$648.00,4/12/2023,4/26/2023,7/7/2023,14,13,,7/11/2023,,,,"$11,998",,,,Conventional,,,,,,Congress Street and South Street,"Welcome to 204 Cambridge Avenue, in the heart of the highly sought-after Washington Village in Jersey City Heights.  Just a block from Washington Park and the NYC direct bus, this prime location has everything you need.    Built in 2016, you appreciate the young age of all the appliances, heating and air conditioning!  This stunning 3 bedroom, 2 1/2 bath home features a much desirable one-car garage with convenient storage space. As you step inside, you’ll be greeted by an inviting open concept floor plan, with a modern white quartz countertop kitchen overlooking the dining and living areas. This layout is ideal for entertaining. A slider from the main level leads you to the fenced in rear yard with a maintenance free deck, a paver patio and turf grass you’ll never need to cut!  Heading upstairs you’ll notice the beautiful wood flooring and the natural lighting which continues throughout. The spacious primary bedroom features an ensuite bath and a large walk-in closet. Two additional bedrooms and the second full bath offer ample space for family and guests. With the direct bus to New York just a block away and an easy walk to Congress Street Light Rail, commuting is a breeze.  Plus, you’ll be just steps away from the variety of shops and restaurants on Central Ave and the Riverview Arts District, ensuring that you’ll always have plenty of entertainment options close at hand. Don’t miss your chance to call this incredible property your own – schedule a tour today!"
230014815,SOLD,"JC, Heights",56 SHERMAN AVE,Condominium,1300,1603,"$810,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1,"JC, Heights",07307,4502,5,,,,,,3,0,2,6,,"$810,000","$775,000",$623.08,$623.08,9/6/2023,9/14/2023,11/8/2023,8,8,,11/8/2023,,,,"$10,265",,$229,,Conventional,,,,,,Franklin & Hutton,"An open concept living space welcomes you into this lovely 3 bed, 2 bath with two garage parking spaces per unit and a beautiful shared yard in the heart of the vibrant Riverview Arts District in Jersey City Heights. The newly renovated gleaming white kitchen features quartz countertops with bar seating, a herringbone backsplash, and stainless steel appliances. The oversized primary bedroom boasts an en-suite and two closets complete with ELFA organization systems. Two additional bedrooms are perfect for offices, guest rooms, or nurseries. The garage features 2 tandem parking spaces per unit and can be used for additional storage. The lovely grass yard is home to a producing fig tree, hydrangeas, and a patio for entertaining. Other features include: hardwood floors throughout, a full laundry room with a folding table and ample storage, central air, Nest thermostat & smoke detectors, and a Level 2 EV car charger. Situated between Riverview and Manhattan Parks, you’ll have easy access to Palisade and Central Avenue bus routes and the 2nd Street Light Rail Station in Hoboken. Less than a block from Froth on Franklin, Alessio’s Cafe, and Green Pear Heights, come enjoy all the Heights has to offer. Welcome home! "
250009776,SOLD,"JC, Heights",378-380 CENTRAL AVE,Condominium,2324,1603,"$810,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,3,"JC, Heights",07306,2201,3,,,,,,3,0,1,7,,"$810,000","$899,000",$348.54,$348.54,5/15/2025,6/30/2025,8/15/2025,46,46,,8/15/2025,,,,"$9,327",,$355,,Conventional,,,,,,Bowers & Charles,"Step into a world of light, space, and timeless character at 380 Central Avenue #3, a rare and expansive 2,324 sq ft penthouse loft in the heart of Jersey City Heights. This top-floor stunner offers dramatic proportions and an abundance of natural light, making it the perfect home for creatives, visionaries, and anyone who craves something truly unique.  Designed for live/work artist use, this one-of-a-kind home features a wall of oversized windows and striking, upgraded skylights (2021) that pour sunlight into every corner. Original stained-glass accents and warm hardwood floors bring texture and charm to the expansive layout, which includes three true bedrooms, an airy open-concept living and dining space, a spa-like bathroom with soaking tub, and an extra storage room.  Upgrades include a full-size in-unit washer and dryer, central air and heat (2021), a Navien tankless water heater (2021), and an upgraded roof (2021). Roof rights are included for future expansion or your private outdoor vision.  Located in a prime Central Avenue location, with low monthly HOA fees, rental parking available across the street, and easy access to parks, cafés, and NYC-bound buses, this penthouse isn’t just a place to live — it’s a place to create, dream, and thrive.  Explore beloved neighborhood spots like Dulce de Leche Bakery, Pampita Meat Shop, The Franklin, Modcup Coffee, and Corto, or unwind at Pershing Field Park or Riverview-Fisk Park, where skyline views and community energy meet.  This is your chance to own a piece of architectural soul in one of Jersey City’s most vibrant, evolving neighborhoods!"
240021253,SOLD,"JC, Heights",74 THORNE ST,Condominium,1585,1597,"$810,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2A,"JC, Heights",07307,2104,52,,,,,,4,1,2,8,,"$810,000","$839,000",$511.04,$511.04,10/30/2024,11/18/2024,12/23/2024,19,19,,12/23/2024,,,,"$14,043",2023,$222,,Conventional,,,,,,Summit Ave & JFK,"Built in 2018, this thoroughly unique duplex features unparalleled quality and finishes abound. Five inch wide walnut floors are throughout the property, we begin our tour in the kitchen offering custom Shaker cabinets, quartz counter tops, Bertazoni appliances and brass accents. The kitchen is complete with a walk in pantry closet. The dining room leads into your living area which is outfitted with floor to ceiling Anderson windows hosting custom window treatments, a powder room completes this first floor of 74 Thorne St. The second level hosts all four bedrooms which are in excellent proportion containing substantial closets within each and a balcony off the primary bedroom. The primary bedroom not only offers a balcony but also has a walk in closet and en suite bathroom featuring Kohler fixtures and Spanish Dozze vanities. The second, third and fourth guest rooms reside on the same level as the primary, as well as the second bathroom with bathtub and full sized laundry room. Head on up to the over 400 square foot private roof top terrace with NYC skyline views, complete with gas and water lines. Shared storage in basement is available as well! Centrally located near bus lines to NYC, as well as the light rail service. Central Avenue offers an abundance of restaurants, coffee shops and grocery shops. Riverview Park offers stunning views of NYC and a weekly seasonal farmer's market for all your needs. Sellers have pre-paid for garage parking at 139 Thorne St at the end of the block, lease is for 18 months, space can be transferred to buyers.     "
250003380,SOLD,"JC, Heights",33 SHERMAN PL,Condominium,2101,1741,"$810,000",CONDO-COOP,,G&1,1,"JC, Heights",07307,3701,17,,,,,,3,1,2,7,,"$810,000","$850,000",$385.53,$385.53,2/21/2025,4/15/2025,5/16/2025,53,53,,5/17/2025,,,,"$12,563",,$490,,Cash,No,No,,,,Central,"Live on one of Jersey City's most coveted & historic blocks, Sherman Place. This two-level condo is larger than your average unit, at over 2100sf. The upper level features 10ft ceilings, 5-inch espresso hardwood floors, a custom designed under the stairs “pet suite”, two large bedrooms and two full baths. The primary bedroom has an en-suite luxury bathroom, and spacious closets. Kohler fixtures, floor-to-ceiling tiles, white shaker vanities with quartz tops compliment both full baths. The bright open concept kitchen & dining room features an exposed brick fireplace, 42” white shaker cabinets, quartz countertops, herringbone marble backsplash, & ss appliances. The lower level has an enormous amount of open space. It includes a walk-out bedroom, kitchenette w/ seating area, half bath, walk-in laundry room and a large living/rec room which can be used in many ways. Other home features included a Nest controlled central AC & heat throughout, LED lighting, Anderson windows, a tankless on-demand water heater, and a private 600sf backyard oasis. Super convenient location, just a half block from Central Ave shopping district including supermarkets, cafe’s, shops, restaurants, and with bus access to both NYC Port Authority as well as Journal Square PATH. Parking available for only $150/mo just behind the property!"
230013654,SOLD,"JC, Heights",102 POPLAR ST,Condominium,1803,1603,"$812,000",CONDO-COOP,,Grd&1,1,"JC, Heights",07307-1111,00702,00045,Heights,,,,,3,1,2,10,,"$812,000","$799,000",$450.36,$450.36,8/14/2023,8/23/2023,10/23/2023,9,8,,11/2/2023,,,,"$13,835",2023,$250,2023,Conventional,No,No,Yes,,,Nelson and JFK Blvd,"Welcome to the home that has it all in the heart of it all, 102 Poplar Street, a thoughtfully designed 3 bedroom + den, 2.5 bathroom duplex built from the ground up in 2017 and located on a quiet tree-lined block in the booming Jersey City Heights. Using the keyless entry keypads, head up one flight and enter into southern-facing open concept living boasting over 1800 square feet of space. Home features include central a/c, in-unit stackable washer/ dryer, built-in surround sound both inside and outside; central vacuum system; Evolve Series Water Filtration System; automated Hunter Douglas blinds, including blackout blinds in the primary suite, beautifully crafted Pella oversized windows which flood the home with natural light; spa-like bathtubs; and a fully equipped kitchen with custom cabinetry, island with quartz countertops, a farmhouse sink, a wine fridge and stainless steel appliances. Other bonuses include an intercom; smart home features such as app-controlled lighting, Honeywell thermostat and home security system (cameras, motion detectors, door sensors).  Also to note are the hardwood floors throughout, a walk-in closet in the primary bedroom with en-suite spa-like bathroom; and extra storage in both the garage and a dedicated area in the downstairs suite. Finally, begin and end your day by heading downstairs and through the Pella glass french doors that lead out to your EXCLUSIVE landscaped BACKYARD that feels like an urban oasis-- complete with paver patio and built-in surround sound speakers perfect for entertaining.  The downstairs area is now a home gym but can dub as a rec room or even an extra bedroom, especially having the ½ bathroom which can be easily converted to a full bathroom. Lastly, a home of this stature would not be complete without DEEDED PARKING; one garage spot and one driveway spot. All the bells and whistles and ideally located within walking distance to parks, the Heights' best shopping, cafes, bars, restaurants, supermarkets, and more. Easy commute to NYC via JSQ Path, light rail, or buses all just a short walkable distance away."
250023134,SOLD,"JC, Heights",545 PALISADE AVE,Condominium,1080,1724,"$812,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,3,"JC, Heights",07307,02305,00029,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,6,,"$812,000","$819,000",$751.85,$751.85,11/10/2025,12/3/2025,2/2/2026,23,23,,2/2/2026,,,,,,$380,,Conventional,,,,,,South St. & Bowers,"Direct in unit elevator accessible condos situated on Palisade Ave in the Jersey City Heights less then one block from Riverview Park. This spacious 2-bedroom, 2 bathroom residence, with a flexible 3rd bedroom option, boasts 10' ceilings, solid 5 wide plank hardwood oak flooring, solid doors, an open floor plan, an abundance of natural light, and high-end finishes that are sure to impress.  Custom kitchen cabinets designed with both style and functionality, adorned in Calcutta quartz counter tops, provide ample storage space and a sleek, modern look. High end stainless steel appliances complete this modern kitchen, making it a dream for any home chef.   Both bathrooms are designed with elegant finishes, offering a spa-like retreat within your own home.  The seller is willing to customize the size of the 3rd bedroom to the buyer's specific dimensions or give the buyer a credit at closing. Customized closets/shelving can also be requested by the buyer.   ~650 sqft of additional entertainment space located in the carriage home behind the property is available to be deeded to this unit. This space may be able to be converted into an ADU."
240016034,SOLD,"JC, Heights",88 TERRACE AVE,Condominium,1382,5671,"$815,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07307,2504,8,,,,,,3,0,2,6,,"$815,000","$825,000",$589.73,$589.73,8/15/2024,8/19/2024,10/11/2024,4,4,,10/14/2024,,,,$1,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Lincoln St & Zabriskie St,"Welcome to your new home! This beautifully renovated 3-bedroom, 2-bathroom condo offers modern living with an urban edge. Step into an open-concept living space, featuring a spacious living room that flows seamlessly into a contemporary kitchen equipped with high-end appliances, sleek countertops, and ample storage. The master bedroom is a serene retreat with an en-suite bathroom and generous closet space, while the additional bedrooms are perfect for family, guests, or a home office. The highlight of this unit is the private rooftop, where you can relax and entertain with stunning views of the city skyline. It’s an ideal spot for enjoying your morning coffee, hosting summer BBQs, or simply unwinding after a long day. Additional features include in-unit laundry, central air/heat, and designated parking, ensuring you have all the comforts and convenience you need. Located in a vibrant neighborhood with easy access to public transportation, shopping, dining, and entertainment, this condo offers the perfect blend of luxury and practicality. Best of all take advantage of a 5-year tax abatement. Don’t miss the chance to make this exceptional property your own. Schedule a viewing today and experience all that this wonderful condo has to offer!"
220015881,SOLD,"JC, Heights",294 GRIFFITH ST,Condominium,1439,1623,"$815,000",CONDO-COOP,,3-4,2,"JC, Heights",07037,3403,45,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,8,,"$815,000","$839,000",$566.37,$566.37,9/6/2022,10/21/2022,12/12/2022,45,45,,12/22/2022,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,JFK & Milton Ave,"Seller to pay $10,000 toward closing costs! *Must close by 12/31/22. Welcome to 294 Griffith St! Don’t wait to get into this brand new luxury condominium in Jersey City Heights! This new construction condo offers 3 bedrooms, 2 full baths, one side-by-side garage parking space with electric vehicle charging stations, and a private rooftop deck. The open floor layout boasts 10 ft ceilings and floor-to-ceiling windows that will drench the living areas with sunlight all day. You’ll appreciate plenty of cabinet space in your state-of-the-art kitchen, with Samsung stainless steel appliances, and a quartz countertop. Features include in-unit laundry, Hardwood floors, stylish designer tiles, recessed lighting, coat closet, custom trim, a storage/office space, and modern fixtures. The Master bedroom offers a large walk-in closet, a master bathroom with a double sink vanity, and a sizable private balcony. Enjoy entertaining on your private rooftop deck constructed with Trex Decking. Conveniently located right off JFK Blvd and only two blocks from Central Ave for an easy commute to NYC and access to shopping, restaurants, schools, and daycare. The property is eligible for a 5-year tax abatement.  "
240020448,SOLD,"JC, Heights",67 PATERSON ST,Condominium,1510,1724,"$815,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1,"JC, Heights",07307,2102,2,Heights,,,,,3,1,2,9,,"$815,000","$849,000",$539.74,$539.74,10/17/2024,12/19/2024,1/31/2025,63,63,,2/3/2025,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Summit Avenue & Pierce Avenue,"Experience luxury living in this brand-new condominium, situated on one of the most desirable streets in JC Heights. With 1,510 square feet spread across two levels, this meticulously crafted home offers three bedrooms and 2.5 bathrooms.  Upon entry, you are welcomed into a bright, open-concept living and dining area, adorned with modern finishes. The interior showcases high ceilings, 6 wide plank hardwood floors, Anderson windows, a custom electric fireplace, and 8-foot custom entry doors, creating a warm and sophisticated ambiance.  The gourmet kitchen is a chef's delight, equipped with 60-inch custom soft-closing cabinets, quartz countertops, a chic backsplash, and a spacious center island. Complete with high-end VIKING appliances, it seamlessly blends style and functionality.  The expansive primary bedroom serves as a serene retreat, featuring two closets (including a walk-in), a private balcony, and an en-suite bathroom with floor-to-ceiling custom tile, a glass-enclosed rain shower, and double vanity sinks.  This beautifully crafted condo also offers two additional spacious bedrooms, each with generous living space and large closets.  On the lower level, you'll find a large rec room with a full wet bar kitchen, leading to the PRIVATE yard—an ideal space for entertaining and relaxing.  Set on a charming street, this home represents the pinnacle of urban living, with convenient access to NYC transportation, nearby districts, and a variety of shops, restaurants, and cultural attractions.  5 YEAR TAX ABATEMENT"
250006869,SOLD,"JC, Heights",88 PROSPECT ST,Condominium,2317,1724,"$815,000",CONDO-COOP,,1-2,1,"JC, Heights",07307,05006,00023,Heights,,,,,4,0,3,10,,"$815,000","$869,999",$351.75,$351.75,4/4/2025,4/5/2025,6/2/2025,1,0,,6/2/2025,,,,"$9,400",,$426,,Conventional,,,,,,Lienau Pl and Webster Ave.,"Luxurious 4 Bedroom 3 Bathroom Condo with Deeded Backyard in Jersey City's Heights Section! Rental parking is available nearby.  Welcome to your dream home at 88 Prospect St., where luxury meets convenience in the heart of Jersey City's vibrant Heights section. Step into this modern oasis, you'll be greeted by spacious living areas filled with natural light, offering ample room for both relaxation and entertainment. The gourmet kitchen is a chef's delight, featuring high-end appliances and sleek finishes. And through the sliding glass doors outside of your kitchen is the units private backyard, beautifully landscaped and easy to maintain.  This duplex offers family and friends a more comfortable stay than your regular home. With a second private entrance and exit into the backyard as well as a second kitchenette, full bathroom, and additional living room the downstairs can act as a private suite for guest, family or short term renters.  Located in the bustling Heights section, this condo puts you in the midst of Jersey City's finest attractions. Indulge in the local culinary scene with trendy bars and restaurants just steps away. From cozy cafes to upscale dining, there's something for every palate.  Long term rental parking is available.  *Builder can add a 4th bedroom within the downstairs living room space upon buyer request for no extra charge. Or the buyer can elect to leave the secondary living room more open*"
220013573,SOLD,"JC, Heights",4 SHERMAN AVE,Condominium,1800,1728,"$815,000",CONDO-COOP,,1&2,1,"JC, Heights",07307,04501,00001,Heights,,,,,3,0,3,9,,"$815,000","$799,000",$452.78,$452.78,7/26/2022,8/30/2022,9/23/2022,35,35,,10/17/2022,,,,"$9,464",2021,$175,,Conventional,,,,,,Corner of Ferry,"Welcome to 4 Sherman Ave in the heart of Jersey City Heights featuring a captivating blend of classic and modern design, quality craftsmanship and a rich selection of handpicked materials. This home has been lovingly maintained to include thoughtful upgrades to the living spaces. Located within an intimate and centrally located two-family house, this renovated 3 Bedroom 3 Bath duplex has over 1800 square feet of open floor plan living space with beautiful hardwood flooring throughout and oversized custom windows drenching the space in natural light. This elegant space is perfectly suited for casual dining as well as entertaining. Full-service chef’s kitchen features shaker style white cabinetry, quartz countertops, and stainless steel appliances. The large master bedroom contains large custom closets and a newly renovated en-suite bath with heated flooring. Also on the main floor are two more generous bedrooms, a second full bath and stackable front load washer dryer. The ground floor features a sizeable 600+ Sq Ft living space with private entrance, bonus rec room/bedroom, bathroom, kitchenette, washer/dryer. Endless possibilities to use as a home office, 4th bedroom /guest room or in-law suite. The unit comes with 1 Garage parking spot, and 1 bonus shared spot outside. This home has everything you need, including a central air/heating system, plenty of storage and a prime location just a block away from Pershing Field Park and  Central Ave shopping district. Commute with ease to NYC via the NJ Transit bus stop on the corner or a quick 12 minute walk to the 2nd Street Light Rail Station. City-bikes located one block from the property as well. Low HOA and pet friendly!  "
230007398,SOLD,"JC, Heights",31 GRACE ST,Condominium,1984,6158,"$815,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07307,,,,,,,,3,0,2,5,,"$815,000","$799,000",$410.79,$410.79,5/6/2023,5/19/2023,8/1/2023,13,13,,8/4/2023,,,,"$10,753",,,,Conventional,,,,,,Central Ave,"New Construction 3bed/2bath condo with private roof deck including gas & water hookups for an outdoor kitchen and parking space for 2 cars. High ceiling with in unit washer/dryer, plenty of closet storage, security system, smart home technology, built in surround sound speakers & more!   Beautiful modern apartment in desirable prime location Jersey City Heights. Just steps from Washington Park and only a short walk to Congress St. Light Rail Stunning large kitchen featuring a wine cooler, farm style kitchen sink and of-course stainless appliances open concept to a spacious dinning area and living room."
220020307,SOLD,"JC, Heights",147 TERRACE AVE,Condominium,3210,1685,"$815,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1,"JC, Heights",07307,02502,00039,Heights,,,,,4,2,3,9,,"$815,000","$799,000",$253.89,$253.89,11/17/2022,12/9/2022,3/22/2023,22,22,,3/23/2023,,,,,,$350,,Conventional,No,,,,,Lincoln Street & Thorne Street,"Brand new ONE OF A KIND LUXURY UNIT ! GN Management does it again , providing top of the line finishes and technology throughout this home! This triplex unit has all the features of a single family home including over 3,200 SQUARE FEET (that's about twice the size of many new units in Jersey City Heights). This unit boasts 4 bedrooms (2 of which are master suites with walk-in closets) 5 perfectly designed bathrooms, HUGE exercise/media room, recreation room with wet bar, open concept living room / dining room with eat-in kitchen with large quartz waterfall island, faucet over stove, built in cabinet microwave, farmhouse sink, washer/dryer closet, 2 electrical fireplaces, 2 balconies, deck & backyard, and garage parking. Each bathroom was designed meticulously with high end finishes, modern vanities & lights. This is a tech-lovers dream, built in audio speakers , cable ready, security system, and nest thermostat. This home truly provides peace of mind when it comes to noise and energy efficiency, thanks to the extra-thick soundproofing and great quality insulation. The developer truly went above & beyond with modern design, quality of material, number of bedrooms and bathrooms, and custom carpentry/trim. Transportation is very accessible making it an easy commute to NYC PORT AUTHORITY, JSQ PATH, Downtown JC and Hoboken. Also conveniently located near parks and schools. Developer is offering a 10 Year new home warranty! Eligible for a 5 year TAX ABATEMENT. Take advantage of the opportunity to purchase this unique one of a kind unit ! Unit has 1 car tandem garage spot."
240018482,SOLD,"JC, Heights",260 GRIFFITH ST,Condominium,2237,1623,"$815,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1,"JC, Heights",07307,03403,00028,Heights,,,,,4,0,3,11,,"$815,000","$850,000",$364.33,$364.33,7/22/2024,10/22/2024,11/21/2024,92,34,,11/21/2024,,,,"$15,124",,$437,,Conventional,,,,,,Kennedy to Griffith,"Welcome to 260 Griffith St, a thoughtfully designed 4-bedroom, 3-bath duplex condo in the vibrant Jersey City Heights neighborhood. This expansive 2,237 square foot unit offers an open-concept layout with high ceilings, solid oak hardwood floors and exposed brick walls creating a pleasant and soothing ambiance. The gourmet kitchen boasts Bosch stainless steel appliances, Cashmere Carrara quartz countertops and white Shaker cabinets accentuated by great natural lighting. The primary bedroom features a walk-in closet and a luxurious En-suite bathroom with double sink vanity and a huge walk-in shower. Both bathrooms are adorned in Porcelanosa tiles, toilets, and fixtures and Fresca vanities in the European fashion. The property includes exclusive use of a 1,000+ square foot private backyard, accessible from both the first floor and lower level. The lower level with a separate entrance offers an additional family room, wet bar/kitchenette, 2 additional bedrooms, a full bathroom and a large storage room. Enjoy modern conveniences like in-unit laundry, central air, Ring Intercom and Nest thermostats. Located just moments away from parks, restaurants and public transportation, this home offers the perfect blend of urban convenience and modern comfort. You won’t want to miss the opportunity to make this amazing condo your new home."
220018719,SOLD,"JC, Heights",151 WEBSTER AVE,Condominium,1638,1419,"$817,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2A,"JC, Heights",07307,03804,00014,Heights,,,,,3,0,3,6,,"$817,000","$845,000",$498.78,$498.78,10/20/2022,1/4/2023,3/9/2023,76,76,,3/9/2023,,,,,,$227,,Conventional,,,,,,Hutton St. & Griffith St.,"Seller is offering $4.5% APR financing on this ground up 1,638 sq ft new construction condominium bringing a new meaning to simple elegance! The Webster Flats provide you with an expansive space made up of 3 large bedrooms and 3 full bathrooms (2 master suits, one with its own private terrace). Ideal details like soaring 10 ft ceilings, built in bar area with wine cooler, high end stainless steel appliances, full sized WhirlPool washer/dryers, Resideo alarm system, Aiphone home intercom system, and the Honeywell Pro Series thermostat provide continuous comfort, convenience, and security to your home. The primary bedroom includes a custom walk in closet as well as a large custom bathroom, and private terrace. Entertainment is a breeze with your built in Sonos Ceiling speaker system prewired throughout the living room and master bedroom! Details like the solid oak hardwood floor in Herringbone pattern, Kohler fixtures, custom cabinets, chef's kitchen with ventilated hoods, black and white tiled bathrooms, and highly efficient recessed lighting throughout all create a tranquil atmosphere for you to relax, work, and have fun, all at the same time. Welcome home to The Webster Flats! Parking is in the next door gated and monitored lot. The Jersey City Heights gets even better with its newest addition, this package is complete with a 10 year new home warranty and a 5 year tax abatement to be filed with JC.  Please also check out unit 102 (1,634 sq ft) priced at $849,000 that comes with designated and zone work space! 4.5% apr seller direct financing is available with 20% down. Live in the lap of luxury for less than $5k with taxes, insurance, and home owners association included. Buy at todays prices with yesterday rates. Call today, live in your new home before the year ends."
210005278,SOLD,"JC, Heights",325 PALISADE AVE,Condominium,1343,6199,"$819,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,3C,"JC, Heights",07307,05003,00001,,Trolley House Lofts,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$819,000","$819,000",$609.83,$609.83,3/5/2021,3/11/2021,5/10/2021,6,6,,5/10/2021,,,,"$6,500",2020,$647,2020,Conventional,,,,,,Corner of Ferry St,"Historic Landmark boutique style “Trolley House Lofts” with soaring 14 feet concrete ceiling that features exposed ductwork, original polished concrete floors, 1343 sq feet of living space with Southwest exposure and oversized windows drenched with natural light. Unit features 2-bedroom 2 bath, stainless steel appliances along with a breakfast bar with quartz counters and opens to a spacious dining area. The large master bedroom features an accommodating square layout with double closets with extra storage on top. This chic loft features, original hardwood floors, central air conditioning and heat and an ideal layout. Washer and dryer on every floor.  One covered corner parking space included.  Located in the best Jersey Heights neighborhood that is brimming with activity. Additional features include a modern video intercom system, bike room, and a newly installed roof w/warranty. Palisade Ave is home to the Heights’ best local spots and groceries, shopping, parks & playgrounds, farmer’s market, music venues, restaurants and NYC transportation right on the corner. Tax abated until July 2032. Extremely low taxes. Seller will offer a $2000 credit towards a washer and dryer."
