230017051,SOLD,"JC, Heights",199 BOWERS ST,Condominium,1803,1568,"$830,000",CONDO-COOP,,1 &2,1,"JC, Heights",07307-3622,02703,00011,Heights,,,,,3,1,2,8,,"$830,000","$799,000",$460.34,$460.34,10/11/2023,10/17/2023,12/1/2023,6,6,,12/6/2023,,,,"$10,474",2022,,,Conventional,No,No,,,,summit and milton,"Luxury duplex in the heart of the Heights with private, deeded yard and parking. This home features hardwood floors throughout, open kitchen with center island and quartz countertops, along with SS appliances. True 3 bedroom, 2.5 modern baths and plenty of closet space throughout. Bright unit with high ceilings and a separate family room downstairs complete this elegant condo. Direct access from the garage to the home feels private and quiet. Perfect for entertaining and a true place to call home!"
260005533,ACTIVE,"JC, Heights",69 HANCOCK AVE,Condominium,1645,1186,"$830,000",CONDO-COOP,,0-1,1,"JC, Heights",07307,3802,5,,,,,,2,0,2,7,,,"$830,000",$504.56,,3/30/2026,,,10,,,3/30/2026,,,,"$14,771",2025,,,,,,,,,Griffith and Hutton St,"Finally, the space you have been looking for in the JC Heights is here! Incredible 1645 sq. ft. 2br 2ba duplex with huge recreation room and spacious private yard! As you walk into your home, you are greeted with high ceilings that make the space appear even larger! The open concept kitchen features high end appliances from Bertazzoni, waterfall quartz countertops, tiled backsplash, and sleek two-tone cabinets. Gorgeous light oak hardwood floors and plenty of sunlight add to the excellent ambiance of this condo. Large bedrooms with beautiful fixtures and functional closet space. The bathrooms feature ribbon gray porcelain tile, glass shower with niche and rain head faucet, floating vanity and contrasting matte black fixtures. The private backyard is massive with turf lawn for low maintenance and space to allow your dog and/or children to play! The backyard is perfect oasis for entertaining, summer BBQs, or gardening. The lower level features a huge recreation room with so many possibilities such as home gym, movie room, children's play area, or even create a 3rd bedroom and 3rd bathroom! Additional features include central AC/heat, storage, big walk-in closet that can be used as a pantry, large windows and in unit laundry. Prime Riverview Arts District location! Very close proximity to Riverview Park w/farmers market + playgrounds, Pershing Field Park, shops on Central Ave like Dulce De Leche Bakery, Pizza Masters, and so much more! All the favorites of the JC Heights right outside your door! Close proximity to NYC transportation via bus, light rail to Path, and Citi bike. Need to find parking? Parking lot just a block away behind the Burger King potentially has monthly rental options for only $72mo or leave car overnight and pay meter in the morning! Inquire now for more information on this wonderful JC Heights home!"
230001816,SOLD,"JC, Heights",236 PALISADE AVE,Condominium,2368,1653,"$830,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1,"JC, Heights",07306,6001,15,Heights,,,,,4,0,3,11,,"$830,000","$825,000",$350.51,$350.51,2/1/2023,3/2/2023,5/5/2023,29,29,,5/12/2023,,,,,,$515,,Conventional,,,,,,Prospect St. & Waverly St.,"Prepare to be blown away by this massive 2,386 sq.ft. duplex condo with its own private backyard!  With four bedrooms and three bathrooms, this brand new, fully renovated condo offers plenty of space to satisfy all your lifestyle needs.  The kitchen is stylish and spacious, with ample cabinetry, stainless steel appliances, and Calcutta quartz countertops. It flows seamlessly into the open-plan living/dining area, filled with natural light. On this floor, you'll also find three bedrooms, one of which is an expansive primary bedroom with en-suite bathroom. This floor also has a second bathroom and a garden-facing bonus room that would make a great office.  Heading downstairs to the ground floor, you'll find a huge living room/media room, a fourth bedroom, a full bathroom, a washer/dryer room, a home office, and plenty of space for storage. Other key features of the home include central heat/AC, hardwood and ceramic floors throughout & in-unit washer dryer.  Located on prime Palisade Avenue, this building is a few blocks away from Pershing Field Park & 2nd Street Light Rail, not to mention the multitude of local shops, restaurants, cafes, parks and all the conveniences of a vibrant neighborhood. All this while still having easy access to the city via public transit or car. Parking is available nearby at an additional cost."
