210012835,SOLD,"JC, Heights",107 JEFFERSON AVE,Condominium,1800,1659,"$830,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,2,"JC, Heights",07306,5706,11,Heights,TBD,,,,3,0,2,7,,"$830,000","$879,900",$461.11,$461.11,5/27/2021,8/9/2021,10/4/2021,74,74,,10/4/2021,,,,"$6,450",2021,,,Conventional,No,No,No,,,Central Ave and Oakland Ave,"As you enter this ultra-modern living space, you will forget you are in the City. The grand entry opens into an awe-inspiring living space fitted with all of today’s modern living arrangements. The polished Select 5 ¼ inch flooring with pre-fabbed hickory welcomes you to a living space where the wall mounted infrared fireplace and built-in surround sound system lets you tame any bad day and turn it into a celebration. The open floor concept is elevated to another level where the island with breakfast nook separates your guests from the passion flaming your inner chef as you carouse meals paired with wine safely stored in your built-in constant-temp wine chiller. 10-foot ceilings, floor-to-ceiling windows marries the unrestrictive light flow with any mood you wish to set. A liquor bar counter replaces the outdated pantry of the 70s and leads you to laundry room with energy efficient washer/dryer, bathroom drenched in pearl white Carrara marble, his and hers vanities, jacuzzi jets that will soothe all your troubles away, spacious rooms including a master’s with a walk-in closet and barn door on guard sets up a restful night for the hardworking Professional in any light. An iron baluster staircase leads you to a rooftop deck where you can play host to any/all events with panoramic views of Jersey City and Manhattan and plenty of space to entertain. Also inquire about the Tax Abatement."
210012071,SOLD,"JC, Heights",9 LIENAU PL,Condominium,1673,6005,"$830,000",CONDO-COOP,,1&2,1,"JC, Heights",07306,,,Heights,,,,,3,1,2,7,,"$830,000","$839,000",$496.11,$496.11,5/19/2021,7/12/2021,8/2/2021,54,54,,8/24/2021,,,,,TBD,,,Cash,,,,,,Waverly & Prospect,"GORGEOUS! New Construction Condominium home located on one of the nicest blocks in the Heights section of Jersey City, within walking distance to practically everything you need, including mass transit. Nothing will compare to pulling onto this beautiful, quiet, tree-lined street as you enter into the driveway, complete with a 1-car tandem parking garage for your new home. Amazing and well-thought-out construction details exist throughout the entire property. Luxury, high-end finishes are sure to delight you.Private Deeded yard. It's a must-see home that you won't want to miss. Luxury living deals like this won't last very long.Owner is an actively licensed NJ Real Estate Broker."
210000280,SOLD,"JC, Heights",139 SHERMAN AVE,Condominium,1892,1603,"$833,000",CONDO-COOP,,1 & 2,1,"JC, Heights",07307,2903,21,Heights,,,,,3,1,2,7,,"$833,000","$839,000",$440.27,$440.27,1/5/2021,1/29/2021,4/6/2021,24,24,,4/7/2021,,,,"$7,263",,$297,,Conventional,,,,,,Bowers & Griffith St,"Welcome to 139 Sherman Ave #1, a recently built 3-bedroom, 2.5 bath home with high-end features, outdoor living space, and garage parking. Located on one of the best blocks in Jersey City Heights, this stunning home spares no expense. Spread out over 2 levels and offering almost 1,900 square feet of luxurious space, this home was thoughtfully crafted and designed. Built for open concept living, the expertly outfitted kitchen includes a farm style sink, stainless steel appliances, gorgeous quartz countertops, custom-made cabinetry, recessed lighting, a wine fridge and opens up into the living and dining room. The expansive master bedroom offers 2 walk-in closets, bay style windows, high ceilings, and a beautiful en-suite bathroom.  Walk downstairs and you will find an additional spacious bonus room with attached half bathroom. Head outside the bonus room to an attached deeded patio, well-suited for entertaining. Equipped with water and gas, the patio can be an extension of your home and is perfect for enjoying the outdoors. You are just 3 short blocks to newly renovated Riverview-Fisk Park and Washington Park, and 3 blocks in the opposite direction to the Heights bustling Central Ave district. This home is at an unbeatable location and is at the center of everything Jersey City Heights. Close access to NYC via several NJ Transit bus lines just a few short blocks away."
220017144,SOLD,"JC, Heights",76 GRAHAM ST,Condominium,1888,1597,"$835,000",CONDO-COOP,,2 & 3,2,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,3,1,2,8,,"$835,000","$875,000",$442.27,$442.27,9/23/2022,10/15/2022,12/28/2022,22,22,,12/28/2022,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Summit & JFK,"High ceilings, oversized windows and modern upgrades brighten every turn in this new construction home in Jersey City Heights. Complete with classic grey hardwood floors, crown molding and a floating marble fireplace, this two-story, 3 bedroom plus office, 2.5 bath home with private rooftop and non-tandem parking promises to impress.  The modern brick exterior is accented with driveway pavers and tasteful landscaping. Step inside into a flowing open floorplan with spacious kitchen, living and dining, punctuated with stylish pendant lighting and exposed wrought-iron and wood banister. Kitchen offers gleaming white quartz countertops, striking tile backsplash, custom cabinetry with accent glass-front doors and stainless appliances including wine fridge.     Take a moment to marvel at the upstairs ensuite, which expands into a secluded sanctuary with large pained windows, massive walk-in closet, and a private office nook perfect for working, reading, meditation and more. Beautifully designed bathroom is tiled in floor to ceiling porcelain tile, and includes a spacious double vanity with smart mirror, plus stand alone glass shower and separate soaker tub for ultimate indulgence. Upstairs layout also includes separate stand-alone office space, plus additional bedrooms, one including a private balcony with sliding glass doors. To top it off, head to the top for a full-floor private roof deck with panoramic city views.  Walking distance to both Washington Park with sports facilities, dog run, playgrounds and walking trails, and Central Avenue for essential shops and vibrant community, this home offers ultimate urban living. Settled on a coveted street in The Heights, this neighborhood is known for its walkability to nearby parks, boutiques, schools and NYC access."
220011559,SOLD,"JC, Heights",42 GRACE ST,Condominium,1688,5845,"$835,000",CONDO-COOP,,1&2,1,"JC, Heights",07307,00504,00039,Heights,,,,,3,1,2,8,,"$835,000","$835,000",$494.67,$494.67,6/23/2022,7/22/2022,8/31/2022,29,29,,8/31/2022,,"$483,800",2021,"$7,760",2021,$49,,Conventional,,,,,,Summit Ave & Central Ave,"Welcome to your Urban Oasis! Convenience meets comfort in this Jersey City Heights newer construction condominium. This gorgeous duplex features three bedrooms, two and a half bathrooms, garage parking, storage, and a private backyard. Living here will make commuting in any direction feel like a day in the park. That being said, this property is located just next to Washington Park, which has all the essentials and more - a dog park, three softball fields, four basketball courts, a football field, eight tennis courts, a workout area, grills, gazebos, walking paths, and a large playground with splash pad. As if that is not enough, it is also close to shopping and restaurants, as well as a quick bus ride away from Manhattan. The open-concept kitchen features white cabinets, gleaming quartz countertops, ceramic tiles, Frigidaire Gallery stainless steel appliances, as well as a wine fridge. The rest of the home features hardwood floors, can lighting, surround speakers, and is controlled wirelessly with Nest thermostat. The fixtures blend modern luxury with timeless charm, while the bedrooms boast custom closets. The garage includes room for two cars, which are non-tandem spots with the neighboring unit. The private backyard patio is ready for your next gathering with artificial turf, speakers, and a locked gate. The home also has no shortage of security features, including a video doorbell with intercom, alarm system with sensors, and exterior cameras. There are three years left on a five-year tax abatement, and eight years left on the builder's home warranty. This condominium checks all the boxes. Don't miss out!"
210009135,SOLD,"JC, Heights",101 SOUTH ST,Condominium,1568,1603,"$835,000",CONDO-COOP,,1&2,1,"JC, Heights",07307,2201,26.01,,,,,,3,1,2,6,,"$835,000","$849,900",$532.53,$532.53,4/16/2021,5/13/2021,6/30/2021,27,27,,7/5/2021,,,,,,,,Conventional,No,No,,,,Central & Cambridge Ave,"Stunning new 3 Bedroom, 2.5 Bath homes. Perfect for family gatherings and entertaining. These duplexes feature huge open-concept floor plans with living room, dining, kitchen, 1/2 bath & direct access to the private 25’x15’ pavered back yard or rooftop deck. The kitchen features  Aria White Polished porcelain counter tops from Porcelanosa with breakfast bar and SS Samsung appliances. The 2nd floor has 3 generous bedrooms. The masters feature walk in showers, double sink vanities, and two walk-in closets. The building also features side by side Garage parking with direct access to first floor living space. https://vimeo.com/541048870"
