250025933,SOLD,"JC, Heights",100 WEBSTER AVE,Condominium,1389,1597,"$900,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,3,1,2,6,,"$900,000","$899,000",$647.95,$647.95,1/6/2026,2/3/2026,4/2/2026,28,28,,4/2/2026,,,,,,$427,,Conventional,,,,,,Franklin & Hutton,"   . Stay safe!   1 car rental spot pre-paid for 1 year!  Step into elevated design and modern convenience with this ground up new construction 3 bedroom, 2.5 bath unit with a private backyard over 700 sqft in the heart of Jersey City Heights. Set on Webster Avenue with a striking white brick exterior, this home boasts 10 foot ceilings & is bathed in natural light, highlighting a spacious open-concept layout with premium Legno Bastone wide-plank hardwood flooring and high-end finishes.  The oversized windows frame a beautifully designed kitchen featuring modern sage green and natural light oak custom cabinetry, white quartz waterfall countertops, and a matching backsplash. Premium Fisher & Paykel appliances bring both style and functionality, making this space perfect for cooking and entertaining.  The primary ensuite bathroom is a luxurious retreat with elegant gold accents, and a glass-enclosed shower with a multi-spray system and rain head. Additional features include ample closet space & brand-new washer and dryer.  Located just one block from popular cafés and restaurants like Froth on Franklin and The Franklin, the best of The Heights is at your doorstep. The 2nd Street stairs to Hoboken provide quick access to the Light Rail, PATH, and ferry, making commuting to NYC effortless. Known for its vibrant community, excellent parks and schools, and stunning skyline views, Jersey City Heights continues to be one of the most sought-after neighborhoods in the area."
240003310,SOLD,"JC, Heights",337 PALISADE AVE,Condominium,1450,5069,"$900,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07307,4503,31,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,6,,"$900,000","$925,000",$620.69,$620.69,2/21/2024,2/28/2024,5/17/2024,7,7,,5/18/2024,,,,$0,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Ferry St. and Franklin St.,"Presenting 337 Palisade Ave Unit 2, Palisade Ave's newest New Construction Luxury Condo. This 3 Bedroom, 2 Bathroom residence offers quality, high end interior design all located conveniently to transportation, Jersey City Restaurants and Riverview Fisk Park.       Your first floor enters to an open concept Living / Dining Room and Kitchen area. Your kitchen includes top line panel ready appliances, custom natural tone cabinetry, custom quartz countertops and waterfall island, designer pendant lights, pantry and plenty of storage space. Off of your living room is direct access to your private oversized deck.   Your Main Bedroom is filled with natural light and offers complete privacy. Complete with true custom walk in closet, your main bathroom offers double sink / vanity, matte black top of line shower fixtures and rainfall shower head.   Main floor is complete with 2 additional bedrooms and full bathroom. This home is perfectly fit for entertaining with your oversized deck. Property comes with 5 Year Tax Abatement and 10 Year warranty."
220009806,SOLD,"JC, Heights",101 SHERMAN AVE,Condominium,1619,5678,"$900,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07307,03803,00011,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,6,,"$900,000","$875,000",$555.90,$555.90,6/1/2022,6/8/2022,8/2/2022,7,7,,8/4/2022,,,,"$5,512",,$0,,Conventional,No,No,,,,Hutton and Griffith,"Welcome home to this 1-year young new construction property in a prime location of The Heights! Meticulously maintained, step into your open concept living/dining which flows directly into your high-end kitchen finished with a white quartz waterfall island, luxury black stainless steel appliances, farmhouse sink, and wine fridge. Heading down the hall you'll find two nice sized bedrooms with shared bath and full primary suite with two walk-in closets and en-suite bathroom. You'll be the envy of the town with your full-sized private Trex roof deck spanning the entire length of the home, perfect for entertaining this summer. This unit is complete with 2 tandem parking spaces, smart home light switches, and remaining 4 years of tax abatement and 9 years of builders warranty! Steps from Riverview Park, NYC Transit, shops, and restaurants - you won't want to miss this. Schedule your private showing today!"
250008615,SOLD,"JC, Heights",151 WEBSTER AVE,Condominium,1638,1724,"$900,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,201,"JC, Heights",07307,03804,00013,Heights,,,,,3,0,3,6,,"$900,000","$910,000",$549.45,$549.45,5/1/2025,6/6/2025,7/1/2025,36,36,,7/2/2025,,,,"$15,575",2024,$374,,Conventional,,,,,,Hutton St. & Griffith St.,"Step into a home that redefines modern sophistication. This sprawling 3-bedroom, 3-full bathroom, residence in a boutique 6-unit new construction condominium is designed for those who appreciate both beauty and function. With soaring 10-foot ceilings, a thoughtfully flexible open layout, 2 primary suits to choose from and uncompromising craftsmanship, this is more than a home—it’s an experience. Solid oak hardwood flooring in a striking Herringbone pattern, black-and-white tiled bathrooms, and premium Kohler fixtures set a tone of refined luxury. With its striking details, seamless functionality, and quiet sense of grandeur. Outfitted with top-tier stainless steel appliances, built to inspire culinary creativity. Two, gated & assigned parking spaces in a secure, monitored lot—an unparalleled luxury. Benefit from 7 years left on the builder’s warranty—a rare advantage in today’s market. The parking lot next door is owned by the building behind Sherman ave. Both parking spots are paid for for the next two years. After which spots will be rented at market rate."
220017918,SOLD,"JC, Heights",104 LINCOLN ST,Condominium,2013,1597,"$900,000",CONDO-COOP,,1&2,1,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,3,1,2,7,,"$900,000","$899,000",$447.09,$447.09,10/6/2022,10/11/2022,12/6/2022,5,5,,12/8/2022,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,JFK & Milton Ave,"Magazine-worthy modern marvel is move-in ready in The Heights. Brand new construction by one of Jersey City’s top builders offers three bedrooms, wide layout giving extra square footage, backyard, plus garage parking for the ultimate urban appeal.  Extra-high Pella windows shine loads of natural light through to the open concept floorplan finished with classic design and modern upgrades like fresh oak hardwood floors, crown molding, high ceilings, and smart home tech throughout. Downstairs duplex hosts bonus room with wet bar and half bath, plus double glass door access to your own fully finished private backyard.  Contemporary eat-in kitchens offer clean white quartz waterfall island, counters and backsplash, plus seamless custom cabinetry and stainless GE appliances including wine fridge. Primary ensuites host glass doors to private balcony plus large built-out walk-in closets. Bathrooms feature elements like double vanity with smart mirrors, glass shower with multihead system or soaker tub for added convenience. Designated utility area features stacking Samsung washer and dryer.  Modern brick building with 2-car non-tandem parking is less than one block from Summit Avenue, and walking distance to both Washington and Leonard Gordon Parks for ultimate urban escape. Jersey City Heights is known for its eclectic vibe, great community, excellent schools and accessibility to NYC and surrounding areas."
250005733,SOLD,"JC, Heights",12 IRVING ST,Condominium,1443,6199,"$900,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07307,00803,00030,,,,,,3,0,2,6,,"$900,000","$929,000",$623.70,$623.70,3/25/2025,5/14/2025,8/19/2025,50,50,,8/20/2025,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Central & Summit," Special Financing Available! This home qualifies for the Community Loan Program — an exclusive opportunity for first-time buyers featuring a low 5.6% interest rate, NO PMI, and low down payments starting at just 5%. A rare chance to make homeownership more affordable and within reach! rarely seen in today's market. Modern, sleek elegance is this 3-bedroom, 2 full bath condo with parking, where luxury living awaits its new owner in the booming Jersey City Heights close to Washington Park filled with tons of activities. This stunning new construction unit boasts an open concept layout where the spacious, brightly lit living expands into the dining room and chefs kitchen making for a seamless flow for entertaining and everyday living! The fully equipped kitchen with stainless steel appliances, quartz countertops, abundant cabinet space and a spacious island, making it the perfect hub for culinary creativity. The primary bedroom is generously sized with large windows, providing a private retreat where you can unwind and recharge. Ensuite bath that embodies spa-like elegance, complete with a separate glass-enclosed stand-up shower, contemporary vanity with sleek countertops, and premium fixtures and an Adjacent walk-in closet. Additional two bedrooms with large windows that flood the space with natural light, creating a bright and inviting atmosphere and a full modern bathroom with double vanity complete the main level. The bonus of a private roof deck with amazing views is another perk that this condo has to offer allowing for a tranquil oasis for relaxation, entertaining, and outdoor gatherings. Additional features include an in-unit washer and dryer, hardwood floors throughout, indoor non tandem parking ensuring you have peace of mind in this bustling setting. Location is key, ideally situated in the Heights, offering easy access to local dining, shopping, and entertainment. Commuting to Manhattan is a breeze with minutes to Congress St. Light Rail, Journal Square PATH and bus station all major highways and tunnels. Don't miss the opportunity to call this exquisite new construction condo your home. Contact today to schedule a viewing and experience urban luxury at its finest."
250007755,SOLD,"JC, Heights",93 TERRACE AVE,Condominium,0,6706,"$900,000",CONDO-COOP,,1 & 2,1,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,4,1,3,7,,"$900,000","$888,888",,,4/21/2025,6/2/2025,8/8/2025,42,42,,8/13/2025,,,,$0,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Lincoln and Zabriske St,"Brand new unique blend of modern living and timeless elegance is found in this never lived triplex condo. With its oversized windows facing East and western exposure the home boost plenty of natural lighting all year round. Located in the Western slope of Jersey City Heights with easy access to major highways and just 3 blocks from bus stops to Journal Square Path station within 10 minutes or NYC Port Authority within 30 mins. This home has approx.1950 square ft across 3 levels of living space, featuring 4 bedrooms, 3-1/2 baths, 10 ft high ceilings, hardwood floors, central air and heat, European solid wood cabinets, quartz counter tops, Samsung black stainless steel appliances, Home theater system, custom California closets, laundry room, 2 balconies a finished ground-level rec room with a wet bar and wine fridge leading out to your private backyard perfect for entertainment and relaxation. Also includes 1 indoor garage space with an electric car charger port.     "
220020011,SOLD,"JC, Heights",560 PALISADE AVE,Condominium,2521,1725,"$900,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,C,"JC, Heights",07307,02402,00002,,,,,,3,1,2,8,,"$900,000","$999,999",$357.00,$357.00,11/11/2022,2/4/2023,4/4/2023,85,85,,4/4/2023,,,,"$17,656",2022,$400,,VA,,,,,,Congress and South street,"A spectacular townhouse converted from an 1860s firehouse stands on coveted Palisade Avenue with its own parking garage and semi-private roof terrace! Spanning over 2500 sq ft with 4 floors of living space, this unique home includes a finished basement with an office, 2 or 3 bedrooms, 2 full baths and a new powder room. This spacious and move-in ready condominium is a unique piece of history to live in. From the outside, visitors are drawn to the stone archways that frame the garage doors and private entries to the three townhouses that comprise the entire building. Inside the newly renovated ground level, the soaring high ceilings lend a sense of grandeur with an expansive skylight that fills the space with natural light. The beautifully designed new kitchen is furnished with sleek modern two-tone cabinets, custom quartz countertops, a hand-made Luke Lamp sculptural lighting, large island and stainless-steel appliances by Bosch. New wide plank flooring spans the entire first floor with bookcases galore. The lower level accommodates a second living area, office, storage and in-home laundry. On the second level, the primary bedroom with high ceilings and wall of bookcases overlooks the treetops on Palisade Avenue. Street facing windows with custom Quiet Windows for noise isolation.The en-suite bath is adorned with a large shower, tumbled marble tiling and a pedestal sink. A spacious second bedroom is found on this level with additional storage and high ceilings with access to renovated bath with modern vanity and tub. The third level is an open and flexible space used as living area or 3rd bedroom. It comprises modern cabinets with sink, bookcases and expansive windows with access to a rare semi-private roof terrace, a true urban sanctuary. The enviably gorgeous house is further equipped with Central AC & Heat, ceiling fans and in-home laundry. This impressive residence is conveniently located just two blocks to the Light Rail corridor and two blocks to Riverview Park where the farmer’s market and music can be enjoyed all summer. Jersey City Heights is a vibrant and sought-after neighborhood filled with parks, shops and some of the city’s most beloved restaurants. This incredible townhouse converted from a historic firehouse with shared maintenance, a private garage and a roof terrace in one of the most desirable locations of Jersey City leaves nothing to be desired."
250022350,SOLD,"JC, Heights",425 NEW YORK AVE,Condominium,1358,5845,"$905,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07307,1705,6,,,,,,3,0,2,7,,"$905,000","$850,000",$666.42,$666.42,10/29/2025,11/5/2025,12/12/2025,7,7,,12/15/2025,,,,"$11,884",,$191,,Conventional,,,,,,North & Congress St,"Perfectly situated on one of the most desirable streets in Jersey City Heights, this stunning three-bedroom, two-bath residence offers 1,358 square feet of bright, contemporary living space with one-car parking. Soaring 12-foot ceilings and two skylights flood the home with natural light, while the East-facing orientation provides plenty of sunshine and sweeping skyline views from your private rooftop terrace. The open-concept living area flows seamlessly into a modern chef’s kitchen featuring a breakfast bar, elegant quartz countertops, sleek white cabinetry, pantry, and Samsung stainless-steel appliances—including a wine fridge. The spacious primary suite boasts a private balcony, walk-in closet, and luxurious en-suite bath. Two additional bedrooms are generously sized. Additional highlights include hardwood flooring throughout, central heating and cooling, in-unit washer/dryer, ceiling fans in every bedroom, ample closet space with custom built-ins, and bonus storage in the garage. Tandem parking is shared with Unit 1. Located just moments from NYC transportation (bus and rail), shopping, dining, parks, and top-rated schools—this exceptional home combines style, comfort, and convenience in one of the Heights’ most coveted locations."
230010273,SOLD,"JC, Heights",73 RESERVOIR AVE,Condominium,2035,1597,"$910,000",CONDO-COOP,,L&1,1,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,3,1,2,8,,"$910,000","$899,000",$447.17,$447.17,6/20/2023,6/30/2023,9/5/2023,10,9,,9/5/2023,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Lienau & Baldwin,"Settle into this newly renovated home sweet home in The Heights finished with modern upgrades, renovated historic details, plus a private backyard. Enter through the charming front porch and into the breathtaking exposed brick stairwell entryway with carefully preserved, striking stained glass window.  With two stories, three bedrooms and two and a half baths, this home hosts both classic design and modern style with elements like hardwood floors and timeless mint palette accents throughout. The open concept floorplan includes living and kitchen plus formal dining featuring beautiful bay windows. Contemporary kitchen showcases classic Euro-inspired aquamarine custom cabinetry, white quartz waterfall countertops and beautiful tile backsplash with exposed wood shelves for added style. The eat-in island offers excellent flexibility, while the brass fixtures and stainless appliances plus hood add functionality and polish.   Bathrooms boast finishes like floor to ceiling vertical ribbon or pattern tile, plus soaker tub, glass shower with multi-system sprayers. The primary ensuite glows with double glass doors to the private backyard finished with pavers and landscaping, ideal for relaxing and entertaining. A large, fully built-out walk-in closet and double vanity truly give this space a little something extra. Head downstairs to the oversized bonus room with additional half bath, separate utility area and added storage space.   The tan brick building is settled on a tree-lined street in the heart of Jersey City Heights. Enjoy walkability to nearby Pershing Field Park with indoor swimming, sports courts, playgrounds and dog walk, plus inspiring nature trails around the Reservoir. Central Avenue is less than a block away with boutique restaurants, cafes, shops and more. The Heights is known for its vibrant community, excellent schools, great views and easy NYC, Hoboken and surrounding area access."
220018716,SOLD,"JC, Heights",415 OGDEN AVE,Condominium,1500,1653,"$910,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1,"JC, Heights",07307,02402,00021,Heights,,,,,4,1,2,10,,"$910,000","$899,999",$606.67,$606.67,10/20/2022,11/23/2022,1/4/2023,34,34,,1/5/2023,,,,"$9,101",2021,$300,,Conventional,No,No,,,,South & Hobson,"OGDEN AVE is the most desirable block in Jersey City Heights. This welcoming newer built duplex with 4 bedrooms / 2.5 baths sits on a beautiful tree lined street that offers an expanded floor plan with exquisite wood floors throughout. You will enjoy cooking in your gourmet kitchen that boasts Quartz-Cursa Calcutta countertops, upgraded stainless steel appliances and a large storage pantry for entertaining . Along with countless days enjoying your professionally landscaped private backyard off your den. After a long day, you can sit down and relax in your sun drenched living room while you're looking out of your large bay windows. Your commute is a very short walk to the 9th Street Light Rail that gives you easy access to NYC as well as many fine restaurants in Hoboken and throughout Jersey City. Just a 2 minute walk, you can spend the day at Riverview-Fisk Park with its seasonal Farmers Market and sweeping views of NYC skyline. Included 1 car garage spot (tandem). Welcome Home !"
220001371,SOLD,"JC, Heights",65 HANCOCK AVE,Condominium,1100,6048,"$910,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07307,,,,,,,,3,0,2,6,,"$910,000","$910,000",$827.27,$827.27,1/24/2022,2/8/2022,3/30/2022,15,15,,5/10/2022,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,HUTTON AND GRIFFITH,"An absolute stunner! A one year old two unit building boasting with contemporary edge and spectacular rooftop views. This unit is endowed with 3 large bedrooms and abundant closet space. Custom closet systems in each bedroom. Hunter Douglas motorized shades in living room. Gorgeous skylights throughout allowing the sunlight to drench the entire unit. Tremendously high ceilings and high end finishes give a gallery-like feel! A masterpiece of a kitchen equipped with high gloss European style cabinetry, a suite of high end stainless steel appliances, quartz island and stunning quartz countertops end to end. The designer metal railings paired with exposed wood beams captivate you upon entry. The master-suite is complete with a walk in closet, full bathroom, and 8x8 full glass sliding doors leading out to a large balcony. The bathrooms are straight out of a catalogue featuring Carrara porcelain tile, floating vanities with under lighting, and a soaking tub. This is a full smart technology home including a Google Nest Doorbell, Google Nest Thermostat, August Smartlock, My Q Smart Garage door with Amazon Key, all streamlined via Google Nest Hub. A private tandem garage with covered parking takes this home up a notch. City living with the comfort of onsite parking. in unit washer/dryer. The private roof deck is breathtaking. Plenty of space to entertain with picturesque Manhattan views! Close proximity to the Congress Street light rail station, major highways, PATH stations, and ferry to Manhattan. Come by, seeing is believing!"
250012011,SOLD,"JC, Heights",141 SHERMAN AVE,Condominium,1300,6706,"$910,000",CONDO-COOP,,1/B,1,"JC, Heights",07307,2903,20,Heights,,,,,3,1,2,7,,"$910,000","$975,000",$700.00,$700.00,6/12/2025,8/1/2025,9/16/2025,50,50,,9/17/2025,,"$465,000",2024,,2023,$246,,Conventional,No,No,Yes,,,Bower and Griffith Street,"Welcome to Unit 1 at 141 Sherman Avenue — a stunning luxury duplex nestled in the desirable East Side of Jersey City Heights! Recently renovated down to the studs with a thoughtful new addition, this spacious residence offers approximately 2,500 square feet of modern living. The main level features three generously sized bedrooms and two full bathrooms. Enjoy a bright, open-concept layout enhanced by abundant natural light and a striking coffered ceiling in the living room. The state-of-the-art kitchen is a chef’s dream, outfitted with Samsung stainless steel appliances, including a smart fridge, and sleek two-tone European-style cabinetry. The quartz countertops extend to the backsplash for a seamless, elegant finish. The primary suite offers tranquil backyard views through a sliding glass door, inviting fresh air and natural light into the room. It also includes a walk-in closet and a luxurious en-suite bathroom with a double vanity. The lower level provides a flexible space that can serve as a home office, additional bedroom, playroom, or family room, complete with a half bath. Ideal for entertaining, this level connects beautifully to the private backyard, offering perfect indoor-outdoor flow. Features include hardwood floors, custom closet and trim work, recess lighting, chic designer tiles throughout, in unit laundry, and modern fixtures. Close to Parks, amazing restaurants on Central Ave, shopping centers, commuter friendly, close to NJ transit public transportation for quick access to the city."
250005148,SOLD,"JC, Heights",157 BOWERS ST,Condominium,3860,6199,"$910,000",CONDO-COOP,,1 & G,1,"JC, Heights",07307,02802,00015,Heights,,,,,6,1,4,13,,"$910,000","$929,000",$235.75,$235.75,3/18/2025,5/19/2025,7/15/2025,62,62,,7/16/2025,,,,$0,,$500,,Conventional,,,,,,Central and Summit Ave,"Welcome to this unique 5 Bedroom - 4.5 Bath duplex condo, 3,860 sqft. Perfect for large families or anyone looking for space that is like no other home. Could also work as mother and daughter set up with the Garden level 1,716 sq ft having its own entrance and second kitchen, 1.5 bath with the laundry room. The first floor features 2,144 sq ft- 4 bedrooms, 2 Master bedrooms with huge walk-in closets, and two 2 br's plus den/office area. Designed with the true “urbanite” in mind and meticulous attention to detail. This newly renovated home offers a Chef's kitchen with Samsung stainless steel appliance, quartz countertop, subway tile backsplash and designer cabinets. White oak hardwood floors though-out, Samsung washer and dryer, central air/forced hot air, high ceiling and windows on 3 sides with great natural light. Half a block to Central Ave, Heart of the shopping district with award-winning restaurants, plus easy NYC access.?  5 Year Tax abatement. "
240007469,SOLD,"JC, Heights",194 CAMBRIDGE AVE,Condominium,1378,5527,"$915,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1,"JC, Heights",07307,02203, 00004,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,6,,"$915,000","$915,000",$664.01,$664.01,4/22/2024,5/8/2024,6/28/2024,16,16,,7/1/2024,,,,"$10,238",,$200,,Conventional,,,,,,Congress st and South st,"Welcome to 194 CAMBRIDGE AVE unit 1. A beautiful boutique condo building, built in 2020. This unit features 3 spacious bedrooms and 2 full bathrooms, both with double vanities. Engineered hardwood floors throughout the unit and stainless steel LG and Samsung appliances. Quartz countertops, and plenty of cabinets and storage in the kitchen. Washer and dryer in unit. The scale of this unit is truly remarkable with 15-foot ceilings. The living room and master bedroom have sliding doors opening up to 500 sq feet of private backyard space. Two newly built decks in the backyard await, perfect for BBQs, and entertaining friends and family, as well as a perfect place for your kids to play. This unit is close to the main streets Central Avenue and Palisade Avenue, and close to all restaurants, coffee shops, and parks (2 blocks from  Washington Park and a 10-minute walk to either Riverview Park or Pershing Field Park), the New Jersey light rail, and an easy commute into NYC with the NJ Path train a 10-minute walk and bus stop less than 2-minute walk. Near public/private schools and daycares, including Park Prep Academy, Smart Start (3 locations nearby), and Kidz Inn. - perfect for a young family. This unit really is a must-see!!"
220004208,SOLD,"JC, Heights",43 BEACON AVE,Condominium,1530,1691,"$915,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,2,"JC, Heights",07306,,,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,6,,"$915,000","$899,000",$598.04,$598.04,3/10/2022,3/30/2022,6/24/2022,20,20,,6/2/2022,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Laidlaw & Palisade,"Welcome to the next generation of modern living with this new construction home with private outdoor and garage parking including EV charging station. Synonymous with quality, Jersey City’s Nkay Construction offer a brand new beautiful brick and glass building with classic design, modern must-haves and spacious three-bed, two-bath layout. Top unit gives way to a full-floor private roofdeck with 360 degree views ideal for entertaining or a daily respite.  Oversized Pella windows allow for loads of natural light on the classic crown molding, timeless wainscotting, and gleaming hardwood flooring throughout. White eat-in kitchen shows style with waterfall quartz counters plus painted blue wood accent. Tile backsplash, custom shaker cabinets, apron sink, and black stainless appliances plus wine fridge finish the space. A tech-lover’s dream with every mod con, including smart doorbell, smart thermostat, camera and security system and central vacuum.   Bathrooms bring coveted upgrades like double-vanities, herringbone tile in soaker tub with multi-system shower and niche, and glass shower with pennytile accents. Primary ensuite hosts spacious built-out walk-in-closet for optimal storage and organization. Tandem secure garage parking with electric vehicle hookups is the proverbial cherry on top.  On a quiet corner of The Heights, and walking distance to Pershing Field Park and Reservoir, or 2nd St Light Rail station - this neighborhood is known for great community, excellent schools and easy NYC access, all amid the eclectic and vibrant scene of Jersey City Heights."
230006686,SOLD,"JC, Heights",355 NEW YORK AVE,Condominium,1501,1581,"$915,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,2,"JC, Heights",07307,02303,00038,,,,,,3,0,2,6,,"$915,000","$949,000",$609.59,$609.59,4/26/2023,6/1/2023,7/20/2023,36,36,,7/20/2023,,,,,,$121,,Conventional,,,,,,Congress St & South St,"Welcome to Jersey City Heights 355 New York Ave, Unit #2, a high-end new construction 3 bedroom residence with exquisite finishes, with its own unique private roof deck. This 1,500 sq ft home is a 3 bedroom + roof deck featuring an open & bright floor plan with lush weathered oak flooring throughout, Anderson windows, chef's kitchen equipped with modern quartz countertops and luxurious pendant lights, built-in wine cooler, Samsung appliance package, custom linen finished cabinetry, along with smart video intercom and built-in speakers. As you walk throughout the home you’ll find three sizable bedrooms with private closets, built-in laundry. The master bedroom provides an in-suite bathroom finished with pastorelli porcelain tile and walk-in-closet. Head upstairs to enjoy a summertime bbq, night time cocktails, or relax with your favorite book on your 1,090 sq ft private roof deck with NYC views built with quality decking and built-in outdoor speakers. 355 New York is in a fantastic location in the Riverview Arts District of The Heights; steps to the vibrant Washington Park, minutes walk to the Hoboken Light Rail & local bus stops to and from NYC, shops & restaurants on Central/Palisade Avenue. Carefully crafted by one of Jersey City Height's most experienced developers! Additionally, you can also take advantage of Jersey City’s 5 Year ‘New Construction’ Tax Abatement. Parking space available for rent for $200 near by builder will pay for 1 year."
230006296,SOLD,"JC, Heights",489 LIBERTY AVE,Condominium,2338,6005,"$919,000",CONDO-COOP,,1&2&3,1,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,3,1,3,8,,"$919,000","$879,000",$393.07,$393.07,4/19/2023,4/27/2023,6/27/2023,8,8,,7/12/2023,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,/ /,"Luxury living awaits! Welcome to this expansive, gorgeously modern home located in one of Jersey City's hottest locations! This new construction triplex boasts so many features including red oak hardwood flooring, quartz countertops, private balconies and more! Don't wait! This property won't last long. Property comes with a 10 yr. new home owner warranty and 5 yr. tax abatement. Property taxes to be independently verified by the Jersey City Tax Office.  "
220020998,SOLD,"JC, Heights",183 SHERMAN AVE,Condominium,1445,6078,"$920,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,8,,"$920,000","$929,000",$636.68,$636.68,12/4/2022,12/30/2022,3/2/2023,26,26,,3/3/2023,,,,$0,2023,$150,,FHA,,,,,,South street and Bowers Street,"Welcome to 183 Sherman Avenue, a luxury new construction development built by one of Jersey City’s top local developers, Blue Chip Properties, a company known for their unique design esthetic, high end finishes and quality workmanship.  Unit Two is one of a kind custom condo featuring 12 ft ceilings, an open concept kitchen, living, and dining space that is illuminated with direct sunlight coming through the oversized Anderson windows.  The Chefs Kitchen features two tone high-gloss European Style cabinetry, premium stainless steel smart appliances, modern porcelain backsplash, central island with waterfall quartz countertop, pot filler, custom lighting, and hidden drawer microwave.  The primary bedroom is highlighted by a wooden feature wall with modern accent lighting, an en suite spa-like bathroom, walk-in closet and a large balcony overlooking the private backyard. This makes for a perfect place to relax after a busy day.  Other key features include custom 8 ft doors throughout the entire property, matte black hardware, hardwood floors, Washer and dryer hookups, Designer Lighting fixtures and Smart Home Technology. Ease of living is created using the Ring doorbell, Nest thermostat, Lighting Dimmer Switches, etc. (all accessible via smartphone).  There are 2 levels of living space for a total of 3 bedrooms and 2 full bathrooms, and a private Rooftop Deck with a custom wet bar. The spacious rooftop is an entertainer’s dream with picturesque NYC skyline views.  Non-tandem garage parking with a high voltage EV Charger outlet is included. Low HOA fees. Easy access into NYC via bus or train.  Congress street light rail station is a 5 min walk, walking distance to both Washington Park and Riverview- Fisk Park. The Ultimate Jersey City Heights Experience!  Property is eligible for a 5 year tax abatement. Schedule your appointment today."
220004210,SOLD,"JC, Heights",43 BEACON AVE,Condominium,1623,1691,"$920,000",CONDO-COOP,,1 & 2,1,"JC, Heights",07306,,,Heights,,,,,3,1,2,7,,"$920,000","$925,000",$566.85,$566.85,3/10/2022,3/31/2022,5/31/2022,21,21,,6/2/2022,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Baldwin & Palisade,"Welcome to the next generation of modern living with this new construction home with private outdoor and garage parking including EV charging station. Synonymous with quality, Jersey City’s Nkay Construction offer a brand new beautiful brick and glass building with classic design, modern must-haves and spacious three-bed, two and a half bath layout. Downstairs duplex offers extra den with wet bar, half bath and access to the private backyard. Vibrant mural highlights the outdoor space finished with pavers, landscaping and white picket fence.   Oversized Pella windows allow for loads of natural light on the classic crown molding, timeless wainscotting, and gleaming hardwood flooring throughout. White eat-in kitchen shows style with waterfall quartz counters plus painted blue wood accent. Tile backsplash, custom shaker cabinets, apron sink, and black stainless appliances plus wine fridge finish the space. A tech-lover’s dream with every mod con, including smart doorbell, smart thermostat, camera and security system and central vacuum.   Bathrooms bring coveted upgrades like double-vanities, herringbone tile in soaker tub with multi-system shower and niche, and glass shower with pennytile accents. Primary ensuite hosts spacious built-out walk-in-closet for optimal storage and organization. Tandem secure garage parking with electric vehicle hookups is the proverbial cherry on top.  On a quiet corner of The Heights, and walking distance to Pershing Field Park and Reservoir, or 2nd St Light Rail station - this neighborhood is known for great community, excellent schools and easy NYC access, all amid the eclectic and vibrant scene of Jersey City Heights."
240012486,SOLD,"JC, Heights",89 IRVING ST,Condominium,1772,6199,"$920,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1,"JC, Heights",07307,704,24,Heights,,,,,4,0,3,8,,"$920,000","$929,000",$519.19,$519.19,6/27/2024,8/16/2024,10/16/2024,50,50,,10/17/2024,,,,$0,,$150,2024,Conventional,,,,,,JFK and Nelson,"Nestled within the vibrant Jersey City Heights neighborhood, this spacious 4-bedroom, 3-bathroom with parking condo boasts an unparalleled blend of modern elegance and comfortable living.  Upon entering discover an open-concept layout, with the living room and dining room seamlessly flowing and filled with natural light from the wall of windows creating a bright atmosphere perfect to entertain. The sleek and contemporary kitchen is a culinary enthusiast's dream, equipped with stainless steel appliances, a quartz waterfall center island, ample storage, and stylish finishes. Retreat to the private quarters, where three generously sized bedrooms offer serene sanctuaries for rest and rejuvenation along with two modern baths. The master suite boasts a luxurious en-suite bathroom, providing a spa-like oasis with a stand-up shower, to unwind after a long day. Descend to the lower level, which can be used as an additional bedroom space and family room complete with a full bath perfect for guests, au pair, or extended family. A private yard to retreat to is an added bonus, where you can enjoy outdoor dining, gardening, or simply basking in the sunshine, ideal for hosting gatherings or simply unwinding. Additional highlights of this beautiful residence include hardwood floors, equipped with two HVAC units to provide independent temperature control for top and lower level, and in-unit laundry for added convenience. Conveniently located in Jersey City Heights, residents enjoy easy access to an array of trendy restaurants, shops, parks, and transportation options, ensuring a vibrant urban lifestyle. Eligible for 5 year tax abatement and special interest rate program 5.875% with no PMI and 5% down! Schedule your private tour today and discover the epitome of modern city living!"
240019260,SOLD,"JC, Heights",124 ZABRISKIE ST,Condominium,1552,1597,"$922,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,2,"JC, Heights",07307,,,,,,,,3,0,2,6,,"$922,000","$925,000",$594.07,$594.07,9/30/2024,10/8/2024,11/26/2024,8,8,,12/2/2024,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,JFK & Summit,"This property qualifies for a Temporary Interest Rate Buydown with an estimated savings to the buyer in excess of $10k. C  Step into sophisticated luxury with this stunning, brand-new home featuring three bedrooms, a private rooftop and garage parking in The Heights. Light streams in through the oversized windows bringing loads of natural light to the contemporary classic design. Features like the striking bamboo accent wall, crown molding and white oak floors help elevate the open floor plan.   Owners enjoy access to a full-floor private rooftop showcasing panoramic NYC views including the Freedom Tower. Inside, the kitchen is finished with waterfall black quartz counters and backsplash, modern custom cabinets in white or natural wood cabinets with under-lighting, high-end stainless appliances, including a wine fridge. Pendant lighting adds a touch of elegance, while matte black fixtures, including a pot filler, add sophistication and style.    The primary ensuite enamors with a white wainscotting feature wall with bedside sconce lighting. The side-by-side walk-in closets are fully finished offering ultimate storage and convenience. Bathrooms include extras like double vanity, smart mirror, glass shower, and black porcelain tile.    Situated on a quiet street in Jersey City Heights, this home is near the newly renovated Leonard Gordon Park and neighborhood favorites like The Hutton Restaurant and Bar and Dulce de Leche Bakery. The Heights is known for its eclectic arts scene, excellent community and schools, peaceful parks, and easy access to NYC and surrounding areas. "
210013422,SOLD,"JC, Heights",85 BOORAEM AVE,Condominium,2628,1691,"$922,000",CONDO-COOP,,1 & 2,1,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,4,1,2,9,,"$922,000","$925,000",$350.84,$350.84,6/3/2021,7/9/2021,8/16/2021,36,36,,8/16/2021,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Webster & Abbett,"Bright, light and altogether fresh, this beautifully constructed home feels like summertime all year round. Sunlight streams in through the matte black bay windows to illuminate the wide-plank oak flooring and classic 2-story layout. Each smartly designed home shines with flowing 2,000 (plus!) sq ft and four to five bedrooms plus bonus space! The bottom duplex showcases an extra large rec room, full sized laundry room and private backyard.  Designer kitchens beckon even the simplest chef with gleaming white quartz counters & backsplash, custom cabinets finished to the ceiling, brass hardware plus high-end GE appliances including wine fridge. Interior elements throughout impress like the matte black and brass pendant lighting, solid black wood closet double doors, and added drama to the master bedroom with the full-wall dark matte wainscotting. Bathrooms fully refresh with marbled porcelain tiles and mosaic accents, matte black fixtures, soaker tubs and glass showers. Abundant closet space and storage available throughout.  Set on a quiet tree-lined street just off Palisade Avenue, this breath of fresh air is walking distance to Pershing Field Park and Reservoir, vibrant shops on Central Avenue, excellent schools and easy NYC access via light rail or NJ Path."
240016134,SOLD,"JC, Heights",234 SOUTH ST,Condominium,1741,1597,"$925,000",CONDO-COOP,,1 & 2,1,"JC, Heights",07307,,,,,,,,3,1,2,7,,"$925,000","$950,000",$531.30,$531.30,8/15/2024,9/23/2024,11/21/2024,39,39,,11/21/2024,,,,,,$292,,Conventional,,,,,,JFK and Pierce,"Nestled on a tree-lined street in The Heights, this brand new construction home brings the very best of modern luxury and ultimate lifestyle. The beautiful red brick building boasts a three bedroom home with must-have private backyard and coveted garage parking.  Inside discover the epitome of modern elegance with red oak hardwood floors, high ceilings, oversized windows and crown molding throughout. Hosting a two-story floor plan, the downstairs bonus room is finished with herringbone flooring, custom wet bar and additional half bath. Step outside to the beautiful backyard oasis, where lush landscaping and pavers create an ideal retreat for both relaxation and entertainment.   The showpiece kitchen beckons with neutral wood and white cabinets finished to the ceiling, white quartz counters, gleaming tile backsplash and an eat-in island adorned with paneled-wood finish and extra storage. Finishing touches include beautiful brass fixtures complemented by stainless appliances, including convertible hood and must-have wine fridge.  Bedrooms bring ample space, light and storage, plus a walk-in closet with built-ins featured in the primary ensuite. Wow-worthy bathrooms include touches like resort-inspired floor to ceiling tile, glass showers with multi-system sprays, and not one, but two double vanities.   This unbeatable location is just one block from Summit Avenue with bustling shops, restaurants and boutiques. Jersey City Heights is known for its excellent community, great schools, beautiful parks and easy access to NYC and surrounding neighborhoods."
230015458,SOLD,"JC, Heights",245 OGDEN AVE,Condominium,1610,1568,"$925,000",CONDO-COOP,,1&2,1,"JC, Heights",07307,03903,00052,Heights,,,,,2,0,3,6,,"$925,000","$899,999",$574.53,$574.53,9/14/2023,9/16/2023,10/27/2023,2,2,,10/29/2023,,,,"$12,253",2023,$215,,Conventional,No,No,Yes,,,Griffith and Franklin,"Welcome to this beautifully renovated 2 bed/3 bath + Den, Custom Luxury Duplex home on the Desirable Ogden Ave in Jersey City! NO detail was spared. Enter through your ground level Private Entrance with warm terracotta tiles into a large open space with a completely custom kitchen, two bars, dining area and living room. The custom kitchen includes a Gaggenau Built-in Paneled Fridge, Kutch gas range stove, Vented 900CFM Range Hood, 32 Sink w/ Garbage Disposal, RO water filter, 8 ft island w/ spice rack, built-in microwave, extra drawers, extra seating and a separate coffee bar with mini fridge. Kitchen has under cabinet lighting as well as interior lighting in the upper glass cabinets. Included on this level is your walk-in laundry room, large coat closet, 2nd bar w/ built-in Kegerator and Pella sliding door leading you to your 925 SQFT Private Backyard w/ side gate access. Up the wainscot staircase w/ wool Zebra runner, you will walk into your loft style second living room/den that could be converted to a 3rd bedroom. Alongside is the 2nd bedroom w/ extra closet space and the master bedroom. The master includes a Walk-in Closet and ensuite bathroom. The bathroom is completed with Marble tile & vanity top, double sinks, wall-to-wall mirror, Heated Floors and Body Jets in the shower. Other details of this home include custom millwork/trim throughout, Built-in Surround-Sound Speakers in the kitchen and living room, Phillips Hue Smart Recessed Lights, Cat 6 Wiring, Verizon FIOS w/ Ubiquiti Wifi preinstalled, Benjamin Moore premium paint, and sound isolated drywall and floors. Low HOA of $215/MO and taxes $12,000/year."
260003114,ACTIVE,"JC, Heights",105 LAIDLAW AVE,Condominium,1774,1597,"$925,000",CONDO-COOP,,1 & L,1,"JC, Heights",07306,,,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,7,,,"$925,000",$521.42,,2/23/2026,,,45,,,2/23/2026,,,,,,,,,,,,,,Oakland & Central Ave,"Set amid a striking four-unit development in The Heights, this brand new residence redefines modern living, bold style and curated comfort. Spanning two levels and showcasing modern mood, elevated design and layered luxury, this 3 bedroom, 2 bath home also includes a bonus room and private backyard.  Floor-to-ceiling and wall-to-wall windows welcome you into the living space illuminating warm hardwood floors and the beautiful open floorplan. The kitchen commands attention with a waterfall white quartz island, seamless backsplash, matte black and natural wood custom cabinetry, and premium stainless appliances including a microwave drawer. Matte black pendant lighting and fixtures finish the look, including a pot filler for added style and functionality.  Retreat to the primary ensuite designed to impress with soft grey wood-panelling, striking chandelier, and spacious walk-in-closet. Glass doors allow secluded access to the private backyard finished with lush lawn and brand new white fencing. Bathroom finishes include elements like matte black vessel sinks, vertical tile to the ceiling, glass-enclosed multi-spray shower or soaker tub, and accent lighting in the shower niche.   Head downstairs to the flexible bonus space and endless opportunities, such as a playroom, studio, office, home gym or more. Additional upgrades abound with extras like Bose surround sound speakers throughout the home, plus an added laundry room with side-by-side brand new Samsung washer and dryer.  Two blocks to Reservoir #3 or Pershing Field Park, and easy access to Journal Square PATH, this location offers comfort, community and convenience. Set on a tree-lined street in Jersey City Heights, this quiet neighborhood is known for its creative, inclusive community, boutique shops and restaurants, excellent parks and schools and gorgeous skyline views."
260005661,ACTIVE,"JC, Heights",134 HANCOCK AVE,Condominium,1368,1597,"$925,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,6,,,"$925,000",$676.17,,3/31/2026,,,9,,,3/31/2026,,,,,,$202,,,,,,,,Bowers & South St,"High design meets everyday ease in this brand new home in The Heights. The impeccably styled 3 bed, 2 bath layout, features a fully finished private backyard, and is nestled in a coveted pocket of Jersey City Heights with access to shops, parks and NYC transport.  The entryway welcomes with wood-paneled walls and built-in hooks for function and warmth. Inside, the living area stuns with a wood-paneled fireplace feature wall, prepped for your oversized flatscreen. Tray ceilings provide intrigue above while sun-drenched light oak floors give continuity throughout.   The eat-in kitchen is a masterclass in contrast where crisp white quartz counters and backsplash meet matte black lower cabinets and light oak uppers. Top-tier Thermador appliances including a custom hood and microwave drawer create a chef-worthy space, while an added wine fridge and brass fixtures give the finishing touch.  Serenity awaits in the primary ensuite, where a paneled statement wall, nightstand sconces, and sliding glass doors to the backyard create a true retreat. Outside hosts a private retreat beautifully manicured with lush lawn, pavers and a customizable outdoor kitchen. An entertainer’s dream, the setup offers a sink, gas connections, and is prepped for a counter top grill installation.   Bathrooms elevate the everyday with gold rainhead fixtures, ribbon tile to the ceiling, a double vanity, and a lit wall niche for the glass shower or soaker tub. The thoughtfully appointed walk-in couple’s closet with custom built-ins completes the space.  Set just two blocks from the buzz of Central Avenue, this location brings the best of The Heights with boutique shops and cafés, Riverview Fisk Park with cinematic skyline views, and Washington Park’s sports facilities, farmer’s markets and community events. The 9th Street elevator and Light Rail offer a direct line to Hoboken, NYC ferries, and PATH connections.   Featuring a 10-year builder’s warranty, this home is modern, move-in ready and made for urban luxury dwellers."
260005662,ACTIVE,"JC, Heights",134 HANCOCK AVE,Condominium,1321,1597,"$925,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,6,,,"$925,000",$700.23,,3/31/2026,,,9,,,3/31/2026,,,,,,$195,,,,,,,,Bowers & South St,"High design meets everyday ease in this brand new home in The Heights. The impeccably styled 3 bed, 2 bath layout, features a private balcony, and is nestled in a coveted pocket of Jersey City Heights with access to shops, parks and NYC transport.  Inside, the living area stuns with a wood-paneled fireplace feature wall, prepped for your oversized flatscreen. Tray ceilings provide intrigue above while sun-drenched light oak floors give continuity throughout.   The eat-in kitchen is a masterclass in contrast where crisp white quartz counters and backsplash meet matte black lower cabinets and light oak uppers. Top-tier Thermador appliances including a custom hood and microwave drawer create a chef-worthy space, while an added wine fridge and brass fixtures give the finishing touch.  Serenity awaits in the primary ensuite, where a paneled statement wall, nightstand sconces, and sliding glass doors to the backyard create a true retreat. Step outside to the private balcony for treetop views and daily serenity. Bathrooms elevate the everyday with gold rainhead fixtures, ribbon tile to the ceiling, a double vanity, and a lit wall niche for the glass shower or soaker tub. The thoughtfully appointed walk-in closet with custom built-ins completes the space.  Set just two blocks from the buzz of Central Avenue, this location brings the best of The Heights with boutique shops and cafés, Riverview Fisk Park with cinematic skyline views, and Washington Park’s sports facilities, farmer’s markets and community events. The 9th Street elevator and Light Rail offer a direct line to Hoboken, NYC ferries, and PATH connections.   Featuring a 10-year builder’s warranty, this home is modern, move-in ready and made for urban luxury dwellers."
260005088,ACTIVE,"JC, Heights",183 ZABRISKIE ST,Condominium,1506,1750,"$925,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,3,"JC, Heights",07307-1111,3304,31,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,7,,,"$925,000",$614.21,,3/23/2026,,,17,,,3/23/2026,,,,,,$75,2026,,No,No,Yes,,,liberty and terrace,"Welcome to Unit 3 at the newly constructed Zabriskie Condos in Jersey City Heights, a striking 3-bedroom, 2-bath residence offering approximately 1,510 square feet of beautifully finished interior space plus a stunning private roof deck. This expansive home unfolds with a bright, dramatic open layout centered around a huge living room framed by floor-to-ceiling windows and a sleek fireplace, creating an impressive setting for both entertaining and everyday living. The sophisticated modern kitchen is equally compelling, featuring sleek cabinetry, stainless steel appliances, in-unit washer/dryer, and an oversized island with seating for eight that anchors the main living space. Thoughtfully designed throughout, the home offers well-proportioned bedrooms, elegant spa-inspired baths, custom storage, and generous walk-in closets. The spacious primary suite serves as a true retreat, complete with a Juliette balcony overlooking the lush backyard below for a serene and beautiful view. Upstairs, the private roof deck offers a rare outdoor escape ideal for dining, lounging, and entertaining under the open sky. Perfectly positioned near transportation, parks, and neighborhood conveniences, this remarkable residence delivers modern luxury and impressive indoor-outdoor living in the heart of Jersey City Heights."
220001781,SOLD,"JC, Heights",37 GRAHAM ST,Condominium,1590,1691,"$925,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1,"JC, Heights",07307,1504,12,Heights,,,,,4,1,2,8,,"$925,000","$899,000",$581.76,$581.76,2/1/2022,2/9/2022,7/18/2022,8,8,,7/19/2022,,,,$0,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Central & Summit,"Big on both beauty and size, this brand new dreamhome was reconstructed from the ground up with modern luxury living at the heart. Brought to you by revered local builder, M2M Development are known for their chic design, attention to detail and quality craftsmanship.  This home offers a generous two-story layout with 1,590sqft, four bedrooms, two and a half bathrooms, plus private storage and large private backyard. Settled on a tree-lined street just one block from either Washington Park or Central and Summit Avenue, initial impressions echo an aristocratic era with light brick and mansard roof with dormer windows and trim.  Inside, light and grandeur spill into the modern and bright living space with oversized Andersen windows, light oak wide plank hardwood floors, and all the smart home technology expected today. The thoughtful split-level floorplan hosts two bedrooms upstairs and two downstairs, plus direct access to a 575sqft private backyard ideal for outdoor living and entertaining.   Kitchen is finished with understated gray quartz counters, modern white custom cabinetry, brass fixtures, tile backsplash and pendant lighting. Primary bedrooms boast a large walk-in closet and sliding double glass doors to your own private balcony overlooking the backyard. Spa-inspired bathrooms offer elements such as floating double vanities, gorgeous glass showers, or blissful soaker tubs with matte black fixtures. Additional amenities include a dedicated utility area with new appliances, and bonus finished basement for rec room/ storage area (350sqft).   Located in the heart of Jersey City Heights, this home is poised to sell with all the luxury fittings in walking distance to beautiful parks, vibrant community, excellent schools and easy NYC access.  Unit is Pre-Construction. *Photos are artistic renderings of unit, for reference of style. Final finishes & fixtures are subject to differ from artwork.*"
230015437,SOLD,"JC, Heights",103 SOUTH ST,Condominium,1568,6494,"$925,000",CONDO-COOP,,1 & 2,1,"JC, Heights",07307,2201,26.02,Heights,,,,,3,1,2,6,,"$925,000","$925,000",$589.92,$589.92,9/14/2023,9/21/2023,11/15/2023,7,7,,11/15/2023,,,,"$12,996",,$200,,Conventional,,,,,,Central Ave & Cambridge Ave.,"Built in 2021, this gorgeous, 1,568 sq ft, 3 bedroom, 2.5 bathroom duplex, boasts an expansive open concept 1st floor which extends out to a private 24'x25' backyard. The upscale gourmet kitchen features quartz countertops, Porcelanosa backsplash, and black stainless steel Samsung appliances. Additional key kitchen details include: custom cabinets, built in wine refrigerator, microwave drawer, 5 burner stove with griddle and vented hood. The 1st floor is outfitted with a built-in 5 speaker system for surround sound, Minka Aire ceiling fan, Porcelanosa flooring, Elfa shelves in the pantry/storage room and half bathroom. Custom Serena shades and wood blinds on both levels. Energy efficient dual zone HVAC system on each floor and tankless water heater. The 2nd floor layout consists of; 3 bedrooms and 2 full bathrooms. The primary suite is appointed with 2 custom walk-in closets and heated floors in the bathroom. 2nd floor ceilings have additional sound proofing. Electrolux washer and dryer, in the laundry closet, adjacent to the bedrooms. Technology features include: Lutron light switches and dimmable LED throughout, EcoBee thermostats, Amazon key-delivery in garage door opener available and each room is wired with ethernet, high speed wifi hubs/direct connection. The shared garage with NON-tandem parking is convenient with direct access to the condo!"
240010375,SOLD,"JC, Heights",9 MANHATTAN AVE,Condominium,1520,1597,"$925,000",CONDO-COOP,,2&3,2F,"JC, Heights",07307,,,,,,,,3,1,2,6,,"$925,000","$949,000",$608.55,$608.55,5/31/2024,6/14/2024,7/31/2024,14,14,,8/2/2024,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Sherman and Central,"Located within a block to Pershing Field, the Reservoir, and close proximity to the best restaurants, shops and entertainments the treasured Jersey City Heights neighborhood has to offer, this newly constructed condominium residence leaves nothing to be desired. Built with the highest standards, the duplex home features 3 bedrooms, 2 bathrooms, a powder room, a private rooftop with spectacular views of NYC and a rarely attainable, non-tandem parking space in the back. The serene and spacious interior spaces boast select grade white oak floors throughout, a smart thermostat, and advanced pre-wiring for entertainment needs. The kitchen, designed by My House Kitchens, features opulent white Caesarstone quartz countertops, custom Shaker cabinets with under-cabinet lighting, matte black fixtures, a pot filler and Dacor appliances. The beautifully crafted staircase leads up to the private roof terrace with gorgeous NYC views all around and equipped with gas and water hookups. The bathrooms feature Turkish vanities, Italian porcelain tiles, glass-enclosed shower or deep soaker tubs with top-quality fixtures. Located near shops, restaurants, cafés, and parks, this home blends vibrant urban life with a peaceful retreat. Jersey City Heights offers a close-knit community, excellent schools, and easy access to NYC, ideal for modern city living. Offered at an outstanding value, don’t miss this opportunity to own a home that checks all the boxes."
250022032,SOLD,"JC, Heights",29 CARLTON AVE,Condominium,2600,1751,"$925,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,2,"JC, Heights",07307,,,,,,,,3,0,2,8,,"$925,000","$999,000",$355.77,$355.77,10/24/2025,11/28/2025,4/2/2026,35,35,,4/6/2026,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Montrose Ave & Summit Ave,"Discover the perfect blend of luxury, space, and convenience with this stunning new construction condominium, right in the heart of a vibrant Jersey City Heights neighborhood. This residence offers a truly upgraded living experience. Enjoy an open and airy interior with abundant natural light, complemented by sleek, contemporary finishes. Step out onto your private rooftop space, where you can unwind while soaking in panoramic views of the city skyline—an ideal retreat for peaceful mornings or evening gatherings. This unit features ample living space, making it perfect for comfortable everyday living and entertaining. Parking is included—an unbeatable advantage in this lively neighborhood—offering you convenience and peace of mind. As part of a brand-new construction, everything is fresh, modern, and built to last. Nestled in a friendly, lively community just minutes from local shops, dining, parks, and transportation, this condo offers everything you need for a dynamic and luxurious lifestyle. Don’t miss the opportunity to own this exceptional home—now ready for you to move in!"
240012161,SOLD,"JC, Heights",67 LAIDLAW AVE,Condominium,1400,1603,"$925,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07306,05906,00026,Heights,,,,,4,0,2,8,,"$925,000","$939,000",$660.71,$660.71,6/24/2024,8/5/2024,9/16/2024,42,42,,9/16/2024,,,,$0,,$225,,Conventional,No,No,No,,,Oakland Ave & Baldwin Ave,"Seller offering 3/2/1, 2/1 and 1/0 buy-down options to help lock in that lower rate for the duration of the buy-down term!  Welcome to the condos at 67 Laidlaw Ave, located on one of the most sought-after streets in Jersey City Heights perfectly situated between both Central and Palisade Ave and only 10 minutes to the JSQ path. Consisting of two luxuriously fully gut renovated units, each is bathed in light and features crisp modern design, serene outdoor spaces and 1 prepaid parking space located directly across the street for 1 year. Unit 2 is a sun-drenched 4 bedroom, 2 full bath top floor home with a large private roof-deck that boasts NYC views. The unit features a fully open-concept layout with soaring high ceilings and light-filled interiors framed by custom Pella Lifestyle casement windows. As you step in, your eye is drawn to the massive south-facing windows that let in tons of sunlight and the wide-plank white oak floors that run throughout the home. The kitchen wows with two-toned European-style oak veneer and matte gray cabinets. Kitchen islands feature Calacatta quartz countertops and waterfall edges. Pro-style luxury stainless steel appliances include a gas range with sleek vented hood, microwave drawer, large French door refrigerator and dishwasher. A cute bar niche with a must-have wine fridge makes this an impressive entertainment space. The massive light-filled primary bedroom features tall bay windows, an original marble Victorian fireplace, extra-large private en-suite bathroom and walk-in closet. Two spacious guest bedrooms, an additional office or 4th bedroom, large guest bathroom, and dedicated laundry-room provide all the space for today’s home-buyer. Both bathrooms feature elegant design, porcelain tiles, Delta shower fixtures and floating vanities; the master bath also provides an additional luxury with its heated floors. Take the party upstairs on your large private roof-deck which is fully equipped for entertaining with direct gas, water and electric connections. Other features include all new high efficiency central HVAC with Nest thermostat, tank-less water heater, superior noise suppression design, smart lighting, security cameras/Ring doorbell and brand new roof. A free secured parking space for a year makes this a must-see! Close to shopping, dining, parks and a range of transport options. Commute to NYC in under 30 minutes!"
220018777,SOLD,"JC, Heights",97 LAIDLAW AVE,Condominium,1456,1603,"$925,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1,"JC, Heights",07306,05705,00014,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,7,,"$925,000","$949,000",$635.30,$635.30,10/21/2022,1/15/2023,3/22/2023,86,86,,3/25/2023,,,,$0,,$542,,Conventional,,,,,,Central Ave & Oakland Ave,"97 Laidlaw Ave is a collection of five timeless new construction condominium homes consisting of three and four bedrooms, two and three bath homes. Unit 1 is a three bedroom, two bath home and includes a massive, over-sized, 427 sf private balcony that stretches across the entire width of the property accessible through the Anderson double sliding glass doors in the living room, master and second bedrooms. Full-service kitchen designed to flow smoothly into and out of the living area features Frigidaire appliances in slate, two-toned matte cabinetry with custom integrated cabinet lighting, Himalayan White Granite waterfall countertops and floating wall shelves. This elegant space with dining area is perfectly suited for casual dining as well as entertaining. Luxurious bathrooms offering you a spa-like retreat with an assortment of carefully selected materials and textures that are exceptional including Roca Piasentina silver polished large format tiles throughout, 60'' double vessel sink on a floating vanity, 30'' natural oak vanities, showers with horizontal niche and integrated led lighting, fixed glass enclosed shower with rain shower head and more. Every home offers unparalleled detail from expansive open floor plan living spaces and high-end finishes to massive private balconies, exclusive backyards, elevator, garage parking and deeded rooftop spaces with NYC views.  97 Laidlaw Ave sits in prime location only a few short blocks from Pershing Field Park and only one block to the Central Ave shopping district. Commute with ease to NYC via NJ Transit buses right on Central Ave or a quick 15 minute walk to the JSQ PATH train. City-bikes located one block from the property. Offering you larger living spaces at desirable price points while maintaining close proximity to NYC, these one-of-a-kind new construction homes are so luxurious you’ll never want to leave!  Property eligible for 5 year tax abatement. Open House 1/14 - 12pm-2pm! Open House 1/15 - 1pm-3pm!"
230020369,SOLD,"JC, Heights",197 GRIFFITH ST,Condominium,1375,1692,"$925,000",CONDO-COOP,,3 & 4,2,"JC, Heights",07307,,,,,,,,3,0,2,7,,"$925,000","$899,000",$672.73,$672.73,12/7/2023,12/15/2023,1/25/2024,8,8,,1/25/2024,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Summit Ave & Central Ave,"Jersey City Height’s own Blackstone Builders delivers another beautiful ground up new construction condo project! This one is a stunning two residence building, custom designed and carefully crafted, on a quiet block in the heart of this well-loved neighborhood. --- The upstairs condo welcomes you with its expansive open-concept kitchen, living room and dining room with a large bay of oversized double pane windows. The kitchen is a chef’s delight with high-end stainless-steel appliances, custom vented hood, well-made cabinets, waterfall quartz countertop, and subway backsplash. Down the hall are two spacious bedrooms and an elegant bathroom with a tub. Wide Red Oak Hardwood flooring and a full size washer dryer are just the small details in this gorgeous home. --- At the rear of the home, the third master bedroom is the cherry on top with its large walk-in closet, beautifully finished ensuite bathroom, and sizable balcony overlooking the backyard. --- Topping the unit off is a large expansive private rooftop with sweeping views of NYC and outdoor wet bar with cold and hot water. Garage parking completes the residence. Price reduction is available if the Buyer does not need parking. --- Loaded with Smart Home features such as a lighting system powered by ZWave technology controlled by SmartThings Hub, Yale W-Fi locks, Ring Elite Doorbells, Lift Master WiFi Garage Door Opener with Security Camera, and a custom designed speaker system that directly connects with streaming apps without being interrupted by phone calls. --- Situated just steps from Jersey City’s bustling Central Ave loaded with a myriad of shops, restaurants, bars, cafes, gyms, and yoga studios. Of course, there is the unparalleled access to Downtown Jersey City, Hoboken, New York City and points west in New Jersey bringing the best of the region within grasp. No better way to bring in the New Year than in your just built home!"
230015324,SOLD,"JC, Heights",339 PALISADE AVE,Condominium,1800,1597,"$925,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1A,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,6,,"$925,000","$925,000",$513.89,$513.89,9/13/2023,9/26/2023,11/17/2023,13,13,,11/17/2023,,,,,,$320,,Conventional,,,,,,Franklin & Ferry,"Rental parking available nearby!   Manhattan finishes and modern luxury are move-in ready in Jersey City Heights. No expense has been spared in these exquisite residences, where high-end finishes and top-of-the-line amenities await. Situated just one block away from the 2nd street lightrail station and stairs to Hoboken, and a mere two blocks from Riverview Fisk Park, you'll enjoy easy access to both The Heights and the vibrant neighborhood of Hoboken.  Step inside the three bed, two bath residences with warm hues emanating from the chestnut stained wide-plank oak flooring, high ceilings and private outdoor space. The flowing floorplan culminates with the designer kitchen showcasing natural wood themes and a large, eat-in island with waterfall white quartz counters. Features include matte black and ribbed glass custom cabinetry, quartz tile backsplash, stainless Bertazzoni appliances plus built-in wine fridge and pull out microwave, and polished off with matte black fixtures and carefully curated white and gold pendant lighting.  This layout includes a separate dining room or office space complete with sliding doors, plus your own private patio off the back bedroom, finished with decking and landscaping. Enjoy modern upgrades throughout, including built-in surround sound speakers and video entry. Bedrooms host stunning white wainscoting feature walls or exquisite gold foiled cherry blossom wallpaper for romantic detail. Bathroom design offers floor to ceiling tile with soaker tub and shower combo including disability access, or double vanity with smart mirrors, and glass shower with multi-system and marbled porcelain tile. Primary ensuite hosts a built-out walk-in closets while each unit includes a dedicated utility room with stacking LG washer and dryer.  This 2022 ground-up, new construction brick building offers a secure entrance on a perfectly positioned tree-lined street in Jersey City Heights. This area is known for its excellent community, boutique restaurants and shops, excellent schools, great parks and easy NYC access."
230007254,SOLD,"JC, Heights",38 CHARLES ST,TOWNHOUSE,1740,5164,"$925,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1,"JC, Heights",07307,2804,45,Heights,,,,,3,1,2,7,,"$925,000","$925,000",$531.61,$531.61,5/4/2023,6/26/2023,6/30/2023,53,53,,6/30/2023,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Central Avenue and Summit Avenue,"Welcome to luxury living with this brand new construction, 3-bedroom, 2 ½ bath townhome nestled within a prime location of Jersey City Heights! Beautiful red oak floors are accentuated by upgraded trim, ceiling moldings and modern lighting, exuding sophistication throughout the unit. The kitchen boasts custom cabinetry with top of the line SS appliances, quartz countertops and barstool seating space, and leads into an open concept living/dining room combo anchored by stunning woodwork. Large master bedroom is complete with an accent wall, walk-in closet and marble bathroom with a sliding glass shower door. Enhanced with a recreation room and 1/2 bath on the ground floor, it is perfect for entertainment and ample living space. The property is encased by white vinyl fencing, professional landscaping, and generously sized private patio, offering both privacy and beauty. Additional highlights include in-unit laundry room, 1 garage space with epoxy flooring, keyless entry, and intercom system. All within walking distance to convenient NYC transit access, vibrant shops, restaurants, parks, and schools! *Eligible for a 5 year tax abatement."
250011325,SOLD,"JC, Heights",129 CONGRESS ST,Condominium,1567,6199,"$925,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1,"JC, Heights",07307,01506,00015,Heights,,,,,3,1,2,9,,"$925,000","$925,000",$590.30,$590.30,6/5/2025,6/18/2025,8/4/2025,13,13,,8/7/2025,,,,"$11,376",2023,$230,2025,Conventional,,,,,,Central & Passaic Avenue,"Welcome to 129 Congress Street, Unit #1—a stunning modern condominium nestled in the heart of Jersey City Heights. This newly constructed residence, built in 2020, offers an ideal combination of contemporary finishes, thoughtfully designed living spaces, and coveted urban conveniences. With 1,567 square feet of living area, this three-bedroom, two-and-a-half–bath home exudes both style and functionality at every turn. Step inside to discover an inviting entertainment space bathed in natural light through oversized windows, perfect for formal gatherings or quiet mornings with coffee.  Enjoy an open chef’s kitchen where you’ll find sleek quartz countertops, custom shaker cabinetry, and top-of-the-line GE stainless steel appliances, including a gas range with hood, built-in microwave, and dishwasher. A spacious pantry ensures ample storage, while a large center island invites casual meals and entertaining. Hardwood floors run throughout the main living areas and bedrooms, lending warmth and continuity to the home’s contemporary palette. Smart-home enthusiasts will appreciate the Nest thermostat, WiFi-enabled Schlage front lock, and integrated smart switches, all of which can be controlled remotely for ultimate comfort and convenience. Practical amenities include an in-unit washer and dryer, a Ring security system for peace of mind, a private storage room and a shared garage parking spot—an invaluable commodity in Jersey City Heights. Retreat to the primary bedroom suite, where you’ll find a tranquil space with room for a king-size bed, spacious designer closet and an en-suite bathroom featuring a floating dual vanity, glass-enclosed walk-in shower, and designer tile finishes as well as a private rear facing balcony which provides a cozy spot to enjoy evening breezes. Two additional bedrooms share a full hall bathroom appointed with tasteful finishes & fixtures—ideal for guests or a home office setup. Downstairs you will find a perfect gathering space that will be the envy of every visitor and will be the place you can’t wait to come to after a long day. With direct access to your stunning private backyard which has been upgraded with synthetic turf creates a prime spot to host gatherings; perfect for grilling or simply soaking up the sun. A convenient powder room & laundry on the lower level rounds out the interior offering. Beyond your door, vibrant local life awaits: stroll to Washington Park for weekend recreation, enjoy nearby neighborhood cafés, or hop on the elevator to the light rail for an easy commute to downtown Jersey City and hop the Path to Manhattan. With its seamless blend of luxury finishes, smart-home technology, private outdoor space, and prime Heights location, 129 Congress Street #1 offers modern urban living at its best. Whether you’re a discerning buyer seeking move-in–ready comfort or an investor looking for a turnkey asset, this exceptional condo delivers on every level. Schedule your private showing today and experience all that Jersey City Heights has to offer. "
220007808,SOLD,"JC, Heights",90 FERRY ST,Condominium,1650,1719,"$925,000",CONDO-COOP,,1&2,1,"JC, Heights",07307,4402,43,,,,,,3,1,2,7,,"$925,000","$950,000",$560.61,$560.61,5/2/2022,5/25/2022,7/21/2022,23,22,,10/27/2022,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Sherman and central ave,"Step into contemporary style with this new construction airy and spacious duplex in the highly sought after Jersey City Heights. Enter into this beautiful duplex and look at the many top grade designer finishes. The kitchen is open concept to the living and dining room to make for a perfect entertaining area. Beautiful high end designer cabinets with quartz counters and backsplash make this kitchen a show stopper. There is no shortage of light with floor to ceiling Anderson windows. Gorgeous solid hardwood floors throughout with 3 bedrooms and 2 full baths on the main level. Primary bedroom has a stunning ensuite bath with upgraded fixtures and tiles and private patio with glass panels. The main bathroom is sophisticated and luxurious with floor to ceiling tile. Step downstairs to find an entire open second living space perfect for a living room equipped with a wet bar with 2 fridges and quartz countertops. Exit outside the oversized patio doors to your private oasis. Perfectly designed with pavers and grass, this backyard is welcoming and perfect of summertime fun. Large shared garage for storage and parking is just one more convenience this new home offers. NYC commuting is a breeze with bus access and nearby Journal Square Path Train. Shopping and amenities located right on the corner on Central Ave. Pershing Field park is an added bonus with track, outdoor playground, ice rink and swimming pool. Do not miss you opportunity to see this special one of a kind home. *squarefootage is approximate"
220000684,SOLD,"JC, Heights",104 LAIDLAW AVE,Condominium,1550,1653,"$925,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07306,05706,00037,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,7,,"$925,000","$925,000",$596.77,$596.77,1/12/2022,2/2/2022,6/10/2022,21,21,,6/14/2022,,,,,,,,Conventional,No,No,,,,Central & Oakland Avenue,"Location location location! Get in early on this new luxury condominium just steps away from Central Ave Shopping District. This ground up new construction offers 3 bedrooms, 2 full bathrooms, with a one car garage parking space. Experience an open floor layout drenched in natural lighting. The living room has floor to ceiling windows, along with skylight windows in the cathedral ceiling, adorned with exposed wooden beams. This unit stands out with larger bedrooms than your normal new construction with an additional space that can be used for an office. Enjoy the ample cabinet space in your state of the art kitchen, with Samsung stainless steel appliances and smart fridge, a wine fridge, and quartz countertop. Features include Hardwood floors, custom trim, recess lighting, chic designer tiles throughout, coat closet, pantry closet, in unit laundry, and modern fixtures. Master bedroom offers a sliding door to walk out to your private balcony, a large walk-in closet, and a master bathroom which includes a double sink vanity. Entertain in your large private roof top deck with outdoor sink and NYC Views. Steps away from Pershing Field Park, amazing restaurants on Central Ave, close to NYC transportation, new upcoming reservoir where you can enjoy water activities. Schedule a tour today!"
240007148,SOLD,"JC, Heights",112 WEBSTER AVE,Condominium,1358,1603,"$926,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07307,0008,04503,,,,,,3,0,2,6,,"$926,000","$899,000",$681.89,$681.89,4/17/2024,4/26/2024,5/29/2024,9,9,,5/29/2024,,,,"$12,637",,$220,,Conventional,,,,,,Franklin and Hutton,"Ready to enjoy summer in The Heights? Welcome home to 112 Webster Avenue. Constructed in 2019, this top floor residence boasts 3 bedrooms, 2 full bathrooms, a private roof deck with NYC views, and 1 car garage parking. Enter into an open-concept living/dining space with 16-foot ceilings and ample windows, flooding the home with sunlight. Hardwood floors, modern window treatments, and custom millwork run throughout. The kitchen features white soft-close cabinetry, waterfall countertops with seating for 4+, stainless steel appliances, built-in microwave and wine fridge, tasteful fixtures, and a beautiful gray tile backsplash. Off the kitchen are two rare finds - a full pantry and a full laundry room, adding extra comforts to this stunning home. The primary is home to an en-suite and walk-in closet, with custom shelving, as well as a lovely terrace, perfect for enjoying a morning coffee or glass of wine. Two additional bedrooms also feature custom closets and are ideal for offices, guest rooms, or nurseries. Up the stairs you’ll find a rooftop oasis, complete with views of the Empire State Building and Freedom Tower. Located in the coveted Riverview Arts neighborhood of Jersey City Heights, you’ll be mere blocks from the steps to Hoboken and the 2nd Street Light Rail, bus routes, restaurants, and businesses on Franklin Street and Palisade and Central Avenues, and beautiful Riverview Park. Additional features include: private entrance, bonus storage in the garage and on the roof, recessed lighting, and more. The Riverview Farmers Market and Jazz Festival kick off in May. Enjoy lunch at Alessio’s and become regulars at The Franklin and Busy Bee Organics. Green Pear Heights is a block away and La Milpa is coming soon. Enjoy all the Heights has to offer. Welcome home!"
220011285,SOLD,"JC, Heights",580 PALISADE AVE,Condominium,1157,1692,"$926,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,502,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,The Riveview,,,,2,0,2,5,,"$926,000","$926,000",$800.35,$800.35,2/24/2022,2/11/2022,6/17/2022,0,0,,6/20/2022,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Congress and South,"Step inside and immediately feel at ease in this unit. BRAND NEW GROUND UP CONSTRUCTION at The Riverview offers impeccable comfort and convenience, situated on Palisade Avenue, at the heart of the neighborhood’s exciting retail/dining corridor. Choose from two- and three-bedroom residences in this intimate 13-unit building, crafted to meet your every need. The well-proportioned units are carefully constructed with today’s most in-demand elements. Flow-through rooms and thoughtful appointments combine for luxurious comfort. Expansive energy-efficient insulated windows frame the interiors with abundant natural light. Elegant top-line finishes include wide plank flooring, granite countertops and premium Fischer-Paykel appliances. Thoughtfully curated amenities bring ease to today’s busy lifestyles. A package room, 12-car parking garage with electric chargers and ground-level bike storage are among the building’s many essential comforts designed to enhance your lifestyle. Make this inspired collection of pet-friendly condominiums home. 10-year New Home Warranty, Manufacturer’s Warranty on all appliances and systems, and tax abatement. Photos are of model unit."
220001412,SOLD,"JC, Heights",417 OGDEN AVE,Condominium,1246,1653,"$930,000",CONDO-COOP,,2/3,2,"JC, Heights",07307,2402,20,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,8,,"$930,000","$930,000",$746.39,$746.39,1/24/2022,1/25/2022,3/25/2022,1,1,,3/25/2022,,,,"$8,348",2021,,,Conventional,No,,,,,South & Hoboken,"Situated on the the most desirable Jersey City Heights tree lined street Ogden Ave, a short distance to Congress Street Light Rail Station. This stunning 3 bedroom/2 bath home features cathedral ceilings, Jacobean and gray custom stained hardwood floors throughout, open floor plan that can accommodate both the living area and a six-seater dining room table. Elegantly designed iron Balusters adorn this simplex condo with full height and width staircase to the outdoor roof top/ and seasonal lounge space with impressive views of NYC. The kitchen is well outfitted w/ many upgrades including but not limited to s/s appliances, custom Cursa Calcatta quartz countertops, fireclay farm sink, with elegant Vigo Edison Single handle kitchen faucet, designer pendant lighting, high-end cabinets with upgraded custom glass doors and wine cooler. Elevated light fixtures illuminate the homes natural light and beauty, creating cohesive simple elegance and luxurious feel . Other features include Custom Hunter Douglas Blinds and Curtains throughout, sitting balcony off master-berm suite, newly installed barn doors, in-unit washer/dryer & pantry. 1 car garage spot included (tandem)"
250001245,SOLD,"JC, Heights",414 NEW YORK AVE,Condominium,1373,6078,"$930,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,D,"JC, Heights",07307,1704,34,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,5,,"$930,000","$949,000",$677.35,$677.35,1/16/2025,3/13/2025,4/23/2025,56,54,,4/24/2025,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,North and Congress,"Only Two Units Left!! Let's start 2025 in a new home, on an excellent location .. There are tons of new contraction homes in Jersey City Heights, but there isn't another one like 414 New York! Discover unparalleled elegance and modern living at 414 New York Ave, a premier collection of 4 luxury condominiums, in a brand-new construction boutique building, on a tree-lined street, in the heart of vibrant Jersey City. Stunning Unit D, features 3-bedroom, 2-bathroom residence offering sleek contemporary design and high-end finishes throughout. Enjoy a spacious open-concept layout with expansive floor-to-ceiling windows that bathe the home in natural light throughout the day. The gourmet kitchen is a chef's dream, showcasing premium CAFE stainless steel appliances, custom cabinetry, brass fixtures and exquisite quartz countertops. Residents will appreciate the upscale amenities, including rooftop terrace with panoramic breathtaking city views, private storage and secure garage parking. Located in a thriving neighborhood with easy access to dining, shopping, parks and public transit, this condo offers the perfect blend of luxury and convenience. Experience the epitome of refined urban living at 414 New York Ave."
230008195,SOLD,"JC, Heights",427 LIBERTY AVE,Condominium,2250,6005,"$930,000",CONDO-COOP,,1&2,1,"JC, Heights",07307,2503,33,Heights,,,,,3,3,1,8,,"$930,000","$879,000",$413.33,$413.33,5/18/2023,5/31/2023,7/7/2023,13,13,,7/12/2023,,,,$0,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Lincoln & Thorne,"Stunning new construction on the JC Slope. Approx. 2250 square feet of luxury living. Luxury living is FOUND at this property located in the prime Western Slope section of Jersey City Heights! This gorgeous, new construction triplex unit is expansive and boasts luxury features throughout such as a  modern kitchen with pot filler, smart appliances and quartz countertops, Italian tile bathrooms, fireplace feature wall, and sleek European entry doors. The nice sized paver patio and grass backyard is private and ready for entertaining this summer! So many things to see at this property gem. Also comes with a 5-year tax abatement and a 10-year builder warranty. Close to everything and just a few short blocks away from public transportation. With so many extras, this home won’t last long!  "
240017374,SOLD,"JC, Heights",159 HOPKINS AVE,Condominium,1438,1186,"$931,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07306,6601,12,,,,,,3,0,2,6,,"$931,000","$939,000",$647.43,$647.43,9/4/2024,12/4/2024,12/26/2024,91,91,,12/27/2024,,,,,,,,Conventional,No,No,,,,Summit Ave and Central Ave.,"Welcome to your new home at 159 Hopkins, where  new construction condo await your purchase ,in one of the most sought out sections of Jersey City Heights. This unit boasts generous floorplans, 10-foot ceilings, Base and Crown Molding. Kitchens feature beautiful quarts counters and Island, black LG stainless steel appliances, microwave, and wine cooler. Other features include oak flooring throughout, central HVAC, Samsung Washer/Dryer and shared garage side by side parking. Unit 2 features 1438 Sq. Feet of spacious living w/ 3 bedrooms and 2 bathrooms and an additional 390 sq. foot roof deck overlooking spectacular NYC views.. Private balcony overlooking backyard. Experience the pinnacle of luxury living where you will enjoy nearby Riverview Park and a plethora of other recreational activities. A 10-year construction warranty and a 5-year tax abatement further only enhance the appeal of your new home. Owner is a licensed NJ Realtor. Pictures are virtually staged."
230020318,SOLD,"JC, Heights",73 BEACON AVE,Condominium,1850,1724,"$935,000",CONDO-COOP,,1 & 2,1,"JC, Heights",07306,05905,00005,Heights,,,,,3,0,3,6,,"$935,000","$999,000",$505.41,$505.41,12/7/2023,12/27/2023,3/11/2024,20,21,,3/12/2024,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Baldwin and Oakland Ave.,"Welcome to this stunning and spacious new construction in the heart of Jersey City Heights! Over 1850 sq this extra wide contemporary duplex is meticulously designed for cutting-edge home technology and entertainment. Featuring wide plank solid hardwood floors, soaring 10ft ceilings, 8ft doors, sleek crown molding, in-unit washer and dryer, energy-efficient LED lighting, side by side garage parking w/ electric charger, and a serene private backyard retreat! Immerse yourself in the elegance of pure white quartz countertops with a cascading waterfall design, coupled with custom cabinetry, top-of-the-line stainless steel appliances, and opulent finishes that create an atmosphere of sophistication in your home. Unit 1 offers 3 generously sized bedrooms and 3 full bathrooms, along with an additional living area, providing ample space for both relaxation and social gatherings. Enjoy the charm of a beautiful private backyard that's perfect for outdoor entertaining. Nestled in the highly sought-after JC Heights area, this property boasts excellent accessibility to major commuting routes, with direct bus lines to NYC Port Authority, Hoboken, and Downtown JC, ensuring a hassle-free daily commute. Nearby Hudson Light Rail Stations add to the convenience, while Pershing Field's indoor pool and ice skating rink, just a few blocks away, provide year-round recreation. Furthermore, residents can relish the natural beauty of Riverview Park, offering not only breathtaking vistas but also hosting a vibrant array of activities, from Farmers Markets to enjoyable movie nights and engaging neighborhood events. Welcome home to luxury living in the heart of Jersey City Heights!  Seller is offering buyers $10,000 towards closing costs/ rate buy down.  A 10 year new construction warranty is provided, and seller will file for a 5 year tax abatement."
220005241,SOLD,"JC, Heights",404 PALISADE AVE,Condominium,1726,5845,"$935,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,3,"JC, Heights",07307,03903,00018,,,,,,4,0,3,8,,"$935,000","$829,000",$541.71,$541.71,3/28/2022,4/2/2022,6/1/2022,5,5,,6/1/2022,,,,"$11,530",2021,$283,,Conventional,,,,,,Griffith and Hutton,"With a luxurious combination of custom finishes, soaring 11+ foot ceiling and multiple private outdoor spaces - this 1,700+ sqft 4 bed / 3 bath is truly one-of-a-kind, and turnkey ready for you to make it your home. The main floor has an airy open layout complete with a richly-appointed kitchen with a sizable breakfast bar and wine fridge.  Custom cabinets, built-in bookshelves, and designer lighting finish a living / dining area perfect for entertaining. Three bedrooms flank the first floor, giving plenty of privacy between rooms.  The tucked away primary bedroom is complete with a quiet patio, designer bedside reading lights, spacious walk-in closet, and en-suite bath with recently remodeled frameless shower. Upstairs you’ll find the extra-large 4th bedroom featuring a custom work-from-home area, and another full bath.  The current owners have professionally wired the upstairs with 5.1 surround sound should you wish to use this as a family room.  To top it all off, this gem of a home is complete with an exclusive and inviting rooftop patio large enough to host a gathering - while enjoying NYC skyline views.  No detail has been overlooked including in-home laundry, sub ceilings to minimize sounds, and rental parking nearby has been secured. Feel at home with comfort and convenience on Palisade Avenue which is bustling with excellent restaurants, cafes, boutique shopping, and public transportation into NYC.  This home is only steps to Riverview Park, and a short distance to the light rail. Don’t miss out on this great home and convenient location.  "
210010930,SOLD,"JC, Heights",121 NORTH ST,Condominium,2264,1186,"$935,000",CONDO-COOP,,1st,1,"JC, Heights",07307,01505,00013,Heights,,,,,3,1,2,7,,"$935,000","$949,000",$412.99,$412.99,5/6/2021,6/29/2021,8/10/2021,54,54,,8/12/2021,,,,,TBD,$528,,Conventional,,,,,,Summit & Central Ave,"Welcome to this new, environmentally sustainable 3 bedroom, 3 bath condo with private roof deck over the garage, located in Jersey City. The building is designed using LEED and Passive House standards, as well as Biophilic design principles to bring in natural light and provide views of outdoor vegetation. The building features two unique units, equipped with Energy Star rated ‘white’ roof and vegetated ‘green’ roof.  The home features beautiful white solid oak flooring and high efficiency LED lighting. On the first level, you’ll find a beautiful open layout to enjoy a large living room, dining and kitchen area with Quartz countertops, Kohler sink & plumbing fixtures, and stainless steel appliances with gas-fired Bertazzoni range & direct vent exhaust hood, as well as a generously sized bedroom and bathroom.  Head up to the second level to the two bedrooms and two bathrooms, including the grand master bedroom/bathroom suite, as well as laundry on this level.  You’ll enjoy lots of natural light coming from your high efficiency triple pane windows and peace of mind with High Efficiency insulation on the interior side of all exterior walls and roof. Each unit features a washer dryer, parking space with electric vehicle charging station and common storage and so much more. Jersey City Heights is the go-to spot for living, eating and playing offering an abundance of lush green parks, shops, restaurants, and a fantastic arts district all at your fingertips."
260005337,ACTIVE,"JC, Heights",545 PALISADE AVE,Condominium,1730,1724,"$939,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2A,"JC, Heights",07307,02305,00029,Heights,,,,,3,0,3,7,,,"$939,000",$542.77,,3/26/2026,,,14,,,3/26/2026,,,,,,$380,,,,,,,,South St. & Bowers,"Step directly from your private in-unit elevator into a sun-filled open-concept residence with 10-foot ceilings.  The expansive 2 bedroom and 2 bathroom layout features a bonus recreation space. Finished with 4-inch wide oak hardwood floors throughout and oversized windows that flood the home with natural light. The kitchen anchors the living space with custom cabinetry, Calacatta quartz countertops, and high-end stainless-steel appliances. This unit includes an additional family room over the garage. The space includes a full bathroom and sun drenched space perfect for those looking for additional space with separate utilities.  The primary suite is generously proportioned and features a sleek, modern en-suite bathroom with Porcelanosa tile, a custom floating double vanity, and an oversized LED mirror. The suite also provides ample space for a dedicated home office or additional storage. The second bedroom is thoughtfully set apart, making it ideal for guests or family, while the overall layout allows for the potential creation of a third bedroom, should a buyer desire.  Buyers may have the opportunity to customize layouts and select finish packages, offering flexibility to tailor the home to individual needs.  Ideally located on Palisade Avenue, the home is steps from neighborhood dining, shopping, and cafés, with nearby bus routes and light rail access providing convenient connectivity throughout Jersey City and into New York City."
230010201,SOLD,"JC, Heights",245 OGDEN AVE,Condominium,1715,6199,"$940,000",CONDO-COOP,,2 & 3,2,"JC, Heights",07307,03903,00052,,,,,,2,1,2,8,,"$940,000","$999,000",$548.10,$548.10,6/20/2023,7/21/2023,9/4/2023,31,31,,9/6/2023,,,,"$15,266",,$245,,Conventional,,,,,,Griffith St & Franklin St,"Stunning, one-of-a-kind, pristine duplex on Ogden Ave, the most sought after street in Jersey City Heights. Enjoy a perfect mix of urban sophistication and modern spaciousness with a spectacular NYC view! 245 Ogden Ave #2 is a bright and airy duplex condo with 1715 sq ft of luxurious living, soaring 19ft ceiling, 2 car parking and a grand and gorgeous roof deck with spectacular NYC views. Light floods in through the impressive and abundant windows onto the gorgeous Brazilian cherry wood floors throughout the home. An entertainer's dream... enjoy the tastefully designed and updated kitchen with quartz countertops, stylish pendant lighting and smart refrigerator with an open first floor layout including a very spacious dining area that can easily accommodate a large table. The beautiful staircase guides you to the welcoming second floor that includes a well-groomed living room equipped with built-ins, and 2 very sizable bedrooms. The cheerful, large primary bedroom suite offers a wonderful custom walk-in closet, full bath, and a charming terrace on which to sip your morning coffee. The roomy second bedroom also has 2 large closets and room to accommodate a queen-size bed, desk and more. Take the stairs up to the cherry on top! The jaw-dropping roofdeck is magnificent and beautifully made with a remarkable NYC skyline view! Garage parking is included plus a second spot in the driveway. Benefit from the great care and pride the owners took in designing and maintaining this beautiful home. Location! Location! Location! Live in this vibrant community— 1/2 block to Riverview Fisk Park, bus to NYC, 100 steps to Hoboken, Light Rail & all the cool coffee shops, bakeries & restaurants. Rare find & a true must see! Floorplan in pictures. This one won’t be around for long. Come experience it today!"
210010337,SOLD,"JC, Heights",253 HANCOCK AVE,Condominium,2035,1581,"$940,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1,"JC, Heights",07307,1602,20,,,,,,3,0,3,8,,"$940,000","$948,000",$461.92,$461.92,4/30/2021,5/11/2021,9/3/2021,11,11,,9/3/2021,,,,"$9,500",2020,$275,2020,Conventional,,,,,,Congress St & North St,"Welcome Home! Visualize yourself living in the heart of Jersey City Heights just blocks away from Washington Park & LightRail Station in this beautifully designed, Condominium with Impeccable features!! This completely gutted duplex has everything you could ever need & the location is incomparable! Take this opportunity to live on one of the most sought after streets of the Jersey Heights! Indulge and reside in this incredibly designed one-of-a-kind 2,000+ sqft duplex. This modern duplex occupies a total of 3 spacious bedrooms, 3 full baths with 1 car parking! It’s first floor features a large impeccably designed gourmet kitchen with beautiful quartz counters and same slab back splash, state of the art stainless steel appliances, a large island for seating as well as a eating area with double pantry, and a spacious open layout living room with an abundance amount of natural lighting, a full bathroom, and a storage/laundry room equipped with a washer & dryer! If you are looking to entertain, look no further! This unit also boasts large custom built-in wet bar with waterfall edge counters & floating shelves while also featuring gleaming hardwood floors & tiles. In addition, you will also have an in-home office work area that which leads to its large privately fenced backyard with some space for gardening! Its 2nd floor area occupies 3 bedrooms including a Master Bed En-Suite and 2 full bathrooms beautifully equipped with a marble-tiled shower wall feature all perfectly paired with black matte fixtures and built-out closets for ample storage. Ideally, residing here will have you just blocks away from parks, cafes, shops, and restaurants along with public transportation like NJ transit, the light rail, and the NY/NJ PATH, getting you into Manhattan in just minutes. This condominium is the epitome of urban luxury living! Schedule a private tour today to see your dream condominium!"
210011450,SOLD,"JC, Heights",430 OGDEN AVE,Condominium,1950,6199,"$940,000",CONDO-COOP,,home,2,"JC, Heights",07307,,,,Hobson Court,,,,3,2,2,12,,"$940,000","$870,000",$482.05,$482.05,5/12/2021,5/22/2021,7/12/2021,10,10,,7/13/2021,,,,"$12,735",2020,$325,,Conventional,,,,,,South St & Congress St,"It is finally here.. the home you have been searching for in the location you desire! Fall in love with this approx 1950 sq ft PRIVATE TOWNHOME with a ONE FAMILY FEEL. Gorgeous NYC views, beautiful courtyard and your very own private garage parking on sought after Ogden Ave! Everything you have been searching for and more with 3 bed/2 full bath/2 half bath on 4 floors of spectacular living. This home checks all the boxes and is ideal for entertaining or a growing family. Grand open floor plan with large living area which flows seamlessly into the spacious dining area. Well laid out and sun filled eat in kitchen with sliding glass doors leads to private deck which is the perfect spot to sip your morning coffee. Enjoy the panoramic NYC views from your very own rooftop solarium, a perfect space for relaxing or gathering with friends and family. Extra family room / office area and laundry room when you enter. Plenty of rooms for multiple people to work from a home office and have privacy. This coveted home easily parks 2 cars has a spacious private garage for parking and storage. Must see to believe with central air, HWF & recessed lighting throughout. Common gated courtyard with picnic area, play area and garden. Location! Location! Vibrant and artistic community with Riverview Fisk Park, farmers market, cool coffee shops & restaurants in easy walking distance. Commuters dream.. steps to the direct bus to Port Authority and Hoboken 9th Street Light Rail elevator. Don't miss out!"
230007111,SOLD,"JC, Heights",34 MANHATTAN AVE,Condominium,1950,1597,"$943,500",CONDO-COOP,,"1,2,3",1,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,4,2,3,6,,"$943,500","$899,000",$483.85,$483.85,5/3/2023,5/8/2023,10/4/2023,5,5,,10/4/2023,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Sherman ave & Central Ave,"Est Completion Mid Summer!  Move in to your very own masterpiece with this pristinely finished, gut renovated showpiece in Jersey City Heights. Step inside and be captivated by the carefully crafted, high-end finishes throughout. The expansive 1,950sq ft layout spans 3-stories, 4 bedrooms, 3 full baths, and 2 half baths, including 2 ensuites. Featuring not one, but two private outdoor spaces, owners enjoy a charming private courtyard, ideal for enjoying a cup of coffee or a glass of wine, plus a private roof deck with breathtaking views of the NYC skyline, ideal for entertaining guests or enjoying a quiet evening alone.  Settled on a quiet tree-lined street, the building boasts beautiful red brick exterior, adding a touch of classic charm to the modern interior. Inside opens to exceptional upgrades like red oak select grade floors, designer lighting by West Elm, plus smart home features like pre-wiring for entertainment, plus Nest thermostat for convenience and comfort. Custom kitchen from My House Kitchens showcases Caesarstone quartz waterfall countertops, Fabuwood Modern Shaker Cabinets with under lighting, and stainless Samsung appliances. Beautifully designed with added touches like matte black fixtures and pot filler, the eat-in bar is excellent for casual dining or entertaining.  Spacious bedrooms delight with thoughtful floorplans and ample storage. Magazine-worthy bathrooms feature details like imported Turkish bathroom vanities and imported Italian porcelain floor-to-ceiling tiles. With Manhattan views, ample outdoor spaces, and ultra-luxe finishes, this home is the perfect balance of modern luxury and urban living.  Just one block to Pershing Field Park and Reservoir and Central Avenue, this home is just around the corner from excellent shops, restaurants, cafes and parks. Jersey City Heights is known for its tight-knit community, great schools and easy access to NYC. Brought to you by talented local builder, M2M Development, these homes are known for their quality craftsmanship, superior design and carefully curated finishes. "
260000392,ACTIVE,"JC, Heights",221 COLUMBIA AVE,Condominium,1723,6078,"$944,000",CONDO-COOP,,2-4,2,"JC, Heights",07307,603,61,Heights,,,,,3,1,2,8,,,"$944,000",$547.88,,1/12/2026,,,87,,,1/12/2026,,,,,,,,,,,,,,Leonard & North,"Welcome and step into this elegant 1,723 sq ft duplex condo in the tranquil Western Slope section of Jersey City Heights. This thoughtfully designed 3-bedroom, 2.5-bath home offers multiple living spaces, top-tier finishes, and a massive private roof deck perfect for indoor-outdoor living. The first floor features a spacious living room, a designated dining area, and a modern kitchen with an oversized island, Samsung stainless steel appliances, sleek white cabinetry, and durable quartz countertops. A stylish half bath completes the main level. Upstairs, you’ll find a bright and spacious layout with three bedrooms and two full baths, including a large primary suite with a beautifully tiled en-suite bathroom. At the front of the home, a second expansive living area is framed by massive Andersen windows that flood the space with natural light, ideal for lounging, entertaining, or working from home. Enjoy the outdoors from your private 565 sq ft roof deck, built with Trex decking for long-lasting, low-maintenance enjoyment. With 5-inch-wide hardwood floors throughout, 10-foot ceilings, and high-quality finishes, Unit 2 offers the perfect blend of function and sophistication in one of Jersey City’s most peaceful and conveniently located neighborhoods."
220021318,SOLD,"JC, Heights",83 CONGRESS ST,Condominium,1450,5069,"$945,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07307,2204,20,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,7,,"$945,000","$929,000",$651.72,$651.72,12/12/2022,1/13/2023,3/15/2023,32,32,,3/15/2023,,,,$0,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Central and Palisades,"Welcome to 83 Congress, a Luxurious New Construction 3 bedroom 2 full bath duplex unit designed by one of Jersey City's top Home Builders, Blue Chip Properties, known for their unique interior design, high end finishes and quality craftsmanship. This home is a minutes walk to Congress St Light Rail, Washington Park, Riverview Park and Central/Palisade shops! Your main floor enters to an open concept Dining Room / Living Room featuring 12 ft high walls lined with Andersen windows and natural light. Your Chef's kitchen features Top-Line two tone cabinetry, smart stainless-steel appliances, pot filler, waterfall quartz center island and countertops backed with luxurious porcelain backsplash and accent lighting.   Main level features Primary bedroom designed with wooden accent wall, modern bedside lighting, barn door walk in-closet and private balcony. Your ensuite bath has been designed with modern yet warm natural tones to create a spa like ambience. Two additional bedrooms, full bath and laundry room hookups complete your main level.   Your private rooftop showcases unobstructed NYC views from downtown to midtown and features a custom interior wet bar as well as gas, water and electric exterior hookups. Full Smart Home technology allows for ease of living, complete with Ring doorbell, Google thermostat, Lighting Dimmer Switches, and more all accessible via smart phone. Garage features non-tandem parking and High Voltage EV Charging outlet for each unit. Property is Eligible for Low Rate Loan options and comes with 5 Year Tax Abatement and 10 year warranty."
