250002608,SOLD,"JC, Heights",122-124 NEW YORK AVE,Condominium,1500,1724,"$980,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,201,"JC, Heights",07307,04504,00001,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,6,,"$980,000","$999,000",$653.33,$653.33,2/8/2025,3/5/2025,5/7/2025,25,25,,5/7/2025,,,,,,$484,2022,Conventional,,,,,,Ferry St. & Franklin St.,"A tranquil oasis is awaiting you in the Jersey City Height with unobstructed Manhattan views! With large serene private wrap-around terrace and direct elevator access to a the huge communal deck; this elevator building optimizes every square foot of the floor plan and includes two communal rooftop decks, a large garage, and a bike rack on the 1st floor. Radiant and inviting, this airy condominium entails 3 bedrooms and 2 bathrooms. Equipped with chef's kitchen, Bosch stainless steel appliances, modernized cabinetry, in-unit washer/dryer, and in-ceiling speakers managed by Sonos amplifier. 5 wide french oak plank hardwood floors throughout, Porcelanosa tile and plumbing fixtures, LED lighting and heated bathroom floors create a true luxurious experience. The builder spared no cost in making this home sound proofed by using sound channels and sound clips, Quietrock, green/noise proofing compound, and even foam insulation, dampening the noise. This rare Heights location is easily commutable and accessible to nightlife, shopping, grocers, public transportation being only 1 block from Palisade Ave; with direct bus lines to NYC Port Authority, Hoboken, and Downtown JC. The Hudson Light Rail Stations are only minutes away as well as Pershing Field's indoor pool and ice skating rink being only 3 blocks away. Riverview Park with its amazing views offers Farmers Market, movie nights, and neighborhood events. Garage parking available."
210011640,SOLD,"JC, Heights",209 BOWERS ST,Condominium,0,1693,"$980,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1,"JC, Heights",07307,2703,6,,,,,,3,1,3,8,,"$980,000","$989,000",,,5/14/2021,7/9/2021,1/4/2022,56,56,,1/4/2022,,,,"$5,136",2019,,,Conventional,No,No,,,,Milton Ave & Summit Ave,"Welcome to a Brand New Luxury Triplex Condominium/Townhouse In Jersey City Heights! Be the first to live in this brand new triplex, three floors of living offering modern condo living with garage parking, a private yard and a private rooftop.  Enjoy the perks of a 5-year tax abatement. The developer is willing to let new owners choose their finishes. Both units 1 & 2 have a 3 bed/3.5 Bath layout that features hardwood floors throughout, large Anderson windows boasting natural light, 10-foot high ceilings, a huge living and dining area perfect for entertaining guests with a kitchen with quartz countertops. Enjoy the perks of an on-site laundry area, two separate roof decks, and private garage parking. This property is conveniently close to schools, shops, restaurants, and a few minutes commute to Route 09 for a quick commute to NYC. Floor plan available in documents. Don’t miss out on this great unit - book your showing today!"
260005339,ACTIVE,"JC, Heights",547 PALISADE AVE,Condominium,1345,1724,"$984,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,3,"JC, Heights",07307,2305,28,Heights,,,,,3,1,2,6,,,"$984,000",$731.60,,3/26/2026,,,14,,,3/26/2026,,,,,,,,,,,,,,South and Bowers,"Welcome to Unit 3 at 547 Palisade Avenue, an exceptional Heights residence that combines modern design, breathtaking views, and unbeatable location. This spacious 1,345 sq ft open-concept home features natural hardwood floors, a chef’s kitchen equipped with Bosch appliances, and a layout designed for both everyday living and entertaining.  Step up to your private rooftop deck and enjoy panoramic NYC views — an outdoor extension of your living space perfectly suited for alfresco dining or sunset gatherings. The living spaces flow seamlessly with abundant natural light, creating an inviting atmosphere throughout. The spacious primary bedroom offers flexibility with room for an office nook, reading lounge, or additional custom closet build-outs to suit your storage needs. Secondary bedrooms are well-sized with ample natural light and storage options. Located just 0.2 miles from the 9th Street Light Rail Station, commuters can access the Hudson-Bergen Light Rail with ease, connecting to Hoboken, Newport, and the waterfront for fast transit connections. Multiple bus stops are also steps from your door, making travel to Manhattan and throughout Hudson County a breeze. Convenience extends to walkable neighborhood amenities including local cafés, restaurants, and shops that define the vibrant Jersey City Heights lifestyle.   Sitting atop the New Jersey Palisades, offering elevated views, scenic parks, and community energy while remaining connected to city life. Leonard J. Gordon Park, Pershing Field, and Riverview-Fisk Park provide green spaces for recreation and relaxation. The Heights’ Central Avenue corridor features an eclectic mix of eateries, boutiques, and services, adding to the neighborhood’s charm."
230006271,SOLD,"JC, Heights",35 PROSPECT ST,Condominium,1800,298,"$984,000",CONDO-COOP,,2&1,1,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,3,1,2,10,,"$984,000","$979,000",$546.67,$546.67,4/19/2023,4/28/2023,6/23/2023,9,9,,6/23/2023,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,off Palisade Ave,"Welcome to 35 Prospect Street -- the stunning details throughout this new construction home are a MUST-SEE! Attractively located in the highly sought after JC Heights, this duplex boasts ceilings that soar up to 11 feet, extra tall doorways, floor-to-ceiling windows, and complementing modern trim throughout - the photos do not do these features justice. A custom chef's kitchen with top-of-the-line Samsung appliances and waterfall quartz countertops is completed with a unique built-in wine cellar and extends into an open-concept living space, flooded with natural light. A sleek staircase finished with an accent wall and statement lighting leads down to a second family room, featuring a designer half bath and full wet bar equipped for entertaining on your private outdoor patio!  Beautiful oversized glass doors lead out to your private patio and backyard. The lower level is also complete with additional closet space and direct access to the garage. The home includes 3 bedrooms, 2.5 bathrooms, and garage parking- with Electric Vehicle hook-ups. The master bedroom features a walk-in closet, ensuite bathroom with double sink vanity, and a private balcony. Very well connected to public transportation, a quick walk to trendy restaurants, cafes, and parks. Other design features include custom built-out closets, red oak hardwood flooring, distinctive lighting, imported porcelain tile, elegant and modern finishes throughout. More features include high efficiency HVAC, built in security and entertainment system, central vacuum, 5-year tax abatement, 2-10-year New Home Warranty, and manufacturer warranties. "
230008177,SOLD,"JC, Heights",31 BLEECKER ST,Condominium,2485,5678,"$985,000",CONDO-COOP,,1 & 2,1,"JC, Heights",07307,01508,00005,Heights,,,,,3,1,3,8,,"$985,000","$999,000",$396.38,$396.38,5/18/2023,6/2/2023,7/12/2023,15,15,,7/12/2023,,,,,,$300,,Conventional,,,,,,Central Ave & Summit Ave,"Experience upscale living with this exquisite 3-bedroom, 3.5-bathroom duplex condo located in highly sought-after Jersey City Heights. Boasting almost 2,500 square feet of living space, this home features an open concept floor plan showcasing a generous living room and a modern kitchen outfitted with top-of-the-line stainless steel appliances, quartz countertops, island, and ample cabinet space. On the first floor, you'll find an expansive bedroom with a luxurious en-suite bathroom complete with dual vanity, bathtub, and shower. This room also provides direct access to the private backyard featuring a paver patio perfect for outdoor dining and entertaining. The second floor houses two additional bedrooms, each with their own en-suite bathrooms, and a versatile flex space with a cozy fireplace - ideal for a home office, family room, or play area. Additional highlights include high ceilings, central A/C, in-unit washer/dryer, recessed lighting, two fireplaces, a smart home thermostat, and transferrable rental parking. Commuting to NYC is a breeze with direct buses to Port Authority and easy access to the Light Rail, which provides direct access to Hoboken PATH. Take advantage of nearby Washington and Riverview-Fisk Parks, which offer panoramic NYC views, a farmer's market, water fountain, dog-run, and basketball courts. This home also boasts a high walk score and is situated near Central Ave & Palisade Ave, offering an array of coffee shops, restaurants, shopping, and groceries options. Schedule a visit today and seize this opportunity to elevate your lifestyle! "
230014922,SOLD,"JC, Heights",865 SUMMIT AVE,Condominium,1836,1724,"$985,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07307,04303,00015,Heights,,,,,3,1,2,7,,"$985,000","$999,000",$536.49,$536.49,9/7/2023,9/13/2023,11/3/2023,6,6,,11/6/2023,,,,,,,TBD,Conventional,No,No,,,,Manhattan & Carlton Ave.,"Introducing a Stunning New Construction Condo in the Heart of Jersey City Heights. This newly constructed home, ideally located just a mere 5-minutes from the Journal Square PATH station, presents an exceptional living experience. From the moment you step inside, you'll be greeted by a spacious and airy open layout that effortlessly combines modern elegance with comfort. The first level of this exquisite condo boasts a generously sized living room bathed in natural light, thanks to its floor-to-ceiling windows. These windows also provide access to a charming Juliet balcony, where you can savor the providing breathtaking scenery and stunning views of Pershing Field Park. The living room seamlessly flows into a modern kitchen equipped with top-of-the-line stainless steel appliances and an abundance of sleek cabinetry, making it a culinary enthusiast's dream. Adjacent to the kitchen is a thoughtfully designed powder room, adding convenience and sophistication to the living space. Travel upstairs to the upper level, where you'll discover three spacious bedrooms that offer both comfort and versatility. The master suite, a true retreat, provides a dedicated office/den space, large windows that flood the room with light, and a master bath that is elegantly designed with porcelain tiles, double vanity and illuminating/defog mirror creating a spa-like oasis within your own home. The two additional bedrooms offer ample space, allowing for various layout possibilities, and are complemented by spacious closets to accommodate all your storage needs. One bedroom grants access to a private balcony, perfect for enjoying the fresh air and a peaceful moment outdoors. Venture up to the 428 sq ft rooftop, and you'll discover a spacious and private roof deck, enhanced with Bluetooth speakers, perfect for entertaining, relaxing, or taking in the stunning city views. Beyond the exceptional features of this condo, its location is a true gem. Situated just 5 minutes away from the Journal Square PATH station, commuting to New York City or other destinations is a breeze. Moreover, the property is strategically positioned directly in front of Pershing Field Park, providing breathtaking scenery and stunning views of the iconic New York City skyline. For those seeking a vibrant neighborhood experience, simply take a short one-block stroll to Central Avenue, where you'll discover an array of restaurants, cultural attractions, and the bustling energy that defines this dynamic community. This new construction condo embodies the perfect blend of modern luxury, convenience, and urban living. Don't miss your opportunity to call this exceptional residence your own and experience the best of Jersey City Heights living. This property has a 5 year Tax Abatement- call JC tax assessor's office for more details."
