and NYC views, gas / electric and water hook ups making it perfect for entertaining and creating memories.  Full Smart Home technology allows for ease of living, complete with Google Nest doorbell, Security Cameras, Google Smart Hub, Smart Thermo and Smart Touch Screen Switches, Lighting Dimmer Switches, and more all accessible via smart phone. Garage features OVERSIZED SIDE BY SIDE parking and separate Level 2 High Voltage EV Charging outlet for each unit. Home is complete with exterior facade and recessed driveway lighting and landscaping. Please note that sqft is approx. New Home Warranty and Tax Abatement."
230010237,SOLD,"JC, Heights",541 CENTRAL AVE,TOWNHOUSE,2100,5069,"$1,249,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,A,"JC, Heights",07307,803,26,Heights,,,,,3,0,3,7,,"$1,249,000","$1,249,000",$594.76,$594.76,6/20/2023,8/28/2023,8/28/2023,69,69,,8/28/2023,,,,$0,,,,Conventional,No,No,Yes,,,Central Avenue,"541 Central, an Oversized ultra-lux Duplex condo by a top luxury home builder. This home offers 3 oversized bedrooms and 3 ensuite baths across 2100 sqft. Your main living room level consists of a range of high end finishes: wide white oak floors, wood grain matched air vents, Legrand smart tone lighting, ecobee smart thermo, all encased within top line noise suppression materials and Marvin windows. Your kitchen also showcase a wide range of high end finishes / fixtures: custom cut Italian porcelain waterfall island with warm recessed lighting underneath, Subzero Refrigerator, Wolf Range with Miele Hood, Sharp microwave drawer, Miele dishwasher hidden seamlessly within your custom Italian cabinetry.   Your main bedroom suite enters from a private wood and smoked glass door to a warm space lit by pendant lighting, Marvin windows, oversized bathroom with Italian double vanity, bronze pendant lights, floor to ceiling porcelain slab as well as multi head matte black shower fixtures. Your main suite is completed with an Italian custom  built closet with dark wood tones, warm lighting and configurable shelving and drawers.   Completing your main level is an additional oversized bedroom with floor to ceiling built in closets and high end full bath which includes pendant lighting, Italian vanity, full slab porcelain shower with matte black shower finishes.   Your lower level consists of an oversized Entertainment Room / Bedroom with full ensuite bath and laundry room. This space is also accessible through a private entrance which makes for the ideal High End AirBnb and or In-Law Suite. Directly off this space is a private multi level 1000 sqft backyard with custom built patio, retaining wall, grass area, beautiful low maintenance landscaping and warm recessed lighting throughout. Tandem garage with State of Art Autel EV charger, tinted glass garage door, padded floors and security system completes this home.   This home’s location offers convenient access to Washington Park, award winning restaurants, shops and stores, Congress St Light Rail and easy NYC bus access. Home also includes 5 year tax abatement and 10 year warranty.   "
260002949,ACTIVE,"JC, Heights",33 GRAHAM ST,Condominium,1936,6705,"$1,250,000",CONDO-COOP,,2&3,2,"JC, Heights",07307,1504,14,Heights,,,,,3,1,2,6,,,"$1,250,000",$645.66,,2/19/2026,,,49,,,2/19/2026,,,,,,,,,,,,,,Summit & Central Ave,"Introducing 33 Graham St, Unit 2, an exceptional newly built 3-bedroom, 2.5-bath duplex condominium featuring sophisticated finishes and an exclusive private rooftop retreat. Designed for modern living, this bright and airy home boasts an open-concept floor plan that effortlessly connects the living and dining areas to a contemporary chef-inspired kitchen with generous counter space and clean, elegant lines. The spacious primary suite includes a beautifully finished en-suite bath, while two additional bedrooms provide flexibility for guests, a home office, or growing households. With 2.5 thoughtfully designed bathrooms, comfort and functionality are seamlessly integrated throughout. This property was built with premium sound control in mind—the developer installed spray foam insulation between floors, combined with resilient channel framing and double 5/8” Sheetrock, creating a significantly enhanced sound barrier between levels. The result is a quieter, more private living experience that exceeds typical construction standards. The showpiece of this residence is the private rooftop deck, the perfect setting for entertaining, relaxing, or enjoying sweeping neighborhood views. Located in a desirable neighborhood close to transportation to and from NYC, shops, dining, and green spaces, this home delivers luxury, lifestyle, and location in one remarkable package."
250025161,ACTIVE,"JC, Heights",81-83 HUTTON ST,Condominium,1481,1597,"$1,250,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,201,"JC, Heights",07307,,,,,,,,3,0,2,6,,,"$1,250,000",$844.02,,12/4/2025,,,126,,,12/17/2025,,,,,,,,,,,,,,Cambridge & Central,"Welcome to Everton House. A nine-residence elevator building in Jersey City Heights, distinguished by curtain-wall glass imported from Spain, creating light-filled interiors with sweeping views of New York City. Everton House offers two, three, and four-bedroom residences, with select homes featuring private outdoor spaces and all residents enjoying access to a shared rooftop. Interiors are defined by dramatic ceiling heights and thoughtfully considered layouts. Kitchens are outfitted with JennAir appliances, including signature Black Obsidian interiors and a built-in coffee system. Primary bathrooms feature radiant heated floors, delivering a refined, spa-like experience. Additional amenities include garage parking with EV charging, a Swiftlane smart entry system, and a dedicated mail and package room designed for modern convenience.  Renderings showcase select units and are for illustration only; actual unit details may vary."
230015197,SOLD,"JC, Heights",336 PATERSON PLANK RD,Condominium,1912,1687,"$1,250,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07307,1703,9,,,,,,3,0,3,10,,"$1,250,000","$1,350,000",$653.77,$653.77,9/11/2023,11/15/2023,1/8/2024,65,65,,1/9/2024,,,,"$14,830",2022,,,Conventional,,,,,,Paterson Plank Rd and Congress,"Nestled in the vibrant Jersey City Heights neighborhood, this exquisite 3-bedroom, 3-bathroom condominium is a true architectural gem. Spanning 1912 square feet across two levels, this duplex offers not only space but also a lifestyle. As you step inside, you'll be greeted by a large open-concept living room, dining room, and kitchen bathed in incredible natural light from floor-to-ceiling windows and 15ft high ceilings. The real showstopper, however, is the 200-square-foot terrace that boasts jaw-dropping views of the most desired, NYC-Manhattan skyline. It's the perfect space for entertaining or simply enjoying a cup of coffee while admiring the city that never sleeps.  The kitchen is a haven for any culinary enthusiast, featuring high-end stainless steel appliances, including a Z-Line Gas-Range stove, GE Dishwasher and microwave, and LG double-door refrigerator. Additionally, the ground level is occupies a gym fully-equipped gym excellent for your health and wellness needs.   Heading upstairs, you'll discover three spacious bedrooms and two beautifully appointed full bathrooms. The primary ensuite bathroom is a true retreat with a jetted tub and a handheld rain shower-head, offering a spa-like experience within the comfort of your own home.  This 2007-built condominium not only offers luxury living but also practicality. You'll have the convenience of attached garage parking with ample storage space, and commuter dream location. The location is second to none, with the Congress Street Light Rail just 50 feet away and bus stops a block away, providing easy access to New York City and neighboring towns like Hoboken has never been easier. Its superior location also provides you with the benefit of being near major highways while also being 11 miles away from Newark International Airport.   366 Paterson Plank Rd will have you within close proximity to parks, dining, and entertainment options, making this condo a haven for both relaxation and exploration. This is your opportunity to own a piece of urban paradise with the best views Jersey City Heights has to offer."
260003711,ACTIVE,"JC, Heights",139 NEW YORK AVE,Condominium,1482,1725,"$1,250,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07307,,,,,,,,3,0,2,5,,,"$1,250,000",$843.45,,3/4/2026,,,36,,,3/4/2026,,,,"$17,540",,$267,,,,,,,,Franklin and Ferry Streets,"Behold, 139 New York Avenue! Built in 2023 by respected local builder Blue Chip Properties, this beautifully maintained 3BR / 2BA condo offers contemporary design and high-end finishes in one of Jersey City’s most desirable neighborhoods. Conveniently located near Hoboken, the Light Rail, and Riverview-Fisk Park. Open-concept living/dining area with 12’ ceilings, oversized Andersen windows and fully glass stairway provide exceptional natural light. The chef’s kitchen is fully equipped with WOLF range, smart stainless-steel appliances, pot filler, waterfall quartz island, and porcelain backsplash. The primary suite includes custom millwork, walk-in closet, private balcony, and ensuite bathroom. The private rooftop terrace features spectacular NYC views, a large section of syn-lawn, modern planter boxes with irrigation system, and gas/water/electric hookups plus a wet bar and wine refrigerator in the bulkhead. Additional highlights include laundry closet, Smart Home system (Google Nest doorbell & thermostat), non-tandem garage parking with EV charging outlet."
260000696,SOLD,"JC, Heights",10 SOUTH ST,Condominium,1574,1597,"$1,250,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,302,"JC, Heights",07307,,,,,,,,3,0,2,4,,"$1,250,000","$1,200,000",$794.16,$794.16,1/15/2026,2/4/2026,3/30/2026,20,20,,4/1/2026,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Palisade Ave and Ogden Avenue,"Discover an exceptional new collection of homes where historic character meets modern design. Rising up to four stories, these thoughtfully crafted residences capture the energy and sophistication of city living while offering a serene retreat at home.  Enjoy the convenience of a full-service elevator building with a secure lobby, intercom access, garage and handicap-accessible parking, and EV charging stations. Just three blocks from the Hoboken Light Rail, residents enjoy effortless access to Manhattan and beyond.  Inside, every detail has been considered—from European floor-to-ceiling windows and wide-plank white oak flooring to Gyp-Crete soundproofing that ensures quiet and comfort. Select homes include private balconies, dens, or roof decks designed for seamless indoor-outdoor living.  The interiors reflect a mid-century modern aesthetic with timeless craftsmanship, highlighted by granite waterfall islands, European cabinetry, Kohler fixtures, GE Café and Fisher & Paykel panel-door appliances, smart mirrors, and imported glass lighting. Open-concept kitchens flow into airy living spaces, creating the perfect backdrop for sophisticated urban life.  Private roof decks with full kitchens provide a refined setting for entertaining, complete with surround sound and green roof features.  For those seeking style, convenience, and connection, these residences reimagine Jersey City Heights living with an inspired blend of design, comfort, and modern amenities.  This home represents a 3 bedroom .  Parking is a separate cost."
250018015,SOLD,"JC, Heights",371 NEW YORK AVE,Condominium,1500,5069,"$1,250,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,7,,"$1,250,000","$1,295,000",$833.33,$833.33,9/3/2025,9/26/2025,11/13/2025,23,23,,11/13/2025,,,,$0,,,,Conventional,No,No,Yes,,,Palisade Avenue and Webster,"MOMENTS FROM CONGRESS ST LIGHT RAIL STATION AND RIVERVIEW FISK PARK. Welcome to 371 New York Avenue, Jersey City — Blue Chip Properties’ most iconic and sought-after project to date. This stunning 3-bedroom, 2-bathroom duplex home is located in the highly desirable New York Avenue enclave, known for its close proximity to the 9th Street Light Rail, Riverview-Fisk Park, Hoboken, and the gourmet dining scene of Palisade Avenue. Designed with timeless interior finishes, high-end fixtures, and meticulous craftsmanship, this residence also offers cutting-edge modern technology for elevated daily living.  The main level opens to a grand open-concept dining and living area with soaring 12-foot ceilings, oversized Andersen energy-efficient windows, a floor-to-ceiling tempered glass accent wall, abundant natural light, and a statement-making realistic flame fireplace. The chef’s kitchen is outfitted with designer two-tone cabinetry, Thermador appliance package with paneled refrigerator and dishwasher, 5 burner range, and heating drawer.  The oversized double waterfall quartz island showcases luxurious West Elm accent lighting, along with porcelain backsplash with a convenient Pot Filler, and an externally vented hood.  The primary suite is a serene retreat featuring custom warm wood-tone millwork, bedside pendant lighting, a walk-in closet with built-ins, and a private balcony with tree-lined views. The spa-like ensuite bath showcases modern natural tones, an oversized double vanity, soaking tub, warm pendant lighting, and a luxurious shower with multiple Kohler body sprays and rainfall showerhead. The two additional bedrooms include custom-finished closets and share a beautifully appointed full bath with double vanity and floor-to-ceiling tiles. A separate laundry room with top-of-the-line washer and dryer completes the main level.  Upstairs, a recessed lit staircase with a glass accent wall leads to an upper-level entertainment zone featuring a wet bar with custom cabinetry, backlit designer backsplash, and wine fridge. Step outside to your expansive rooftop with some of the best NYC skyline views in The Heights, complete with premium astroturf and Trex decking, gas, electric, and water hookups — ideal for entertaining.  This fully equipped smart home includes a Google Nest doorbell, security cameras, Google Smart Hub, smart thermostat, touchscreen light switches, dimmers, and more — all seamlessly controlled via smartphone. The XL garage offers RARE side-by-side parking and a dedicated Level 2 EV car charging outlet for each unit, along with a security camera system. The home is completed with Blue Chip Properties’ signature exterior facade, recessed driveway, and professional landscaping. Property includes a 10-year builder’s warranty and a 5-year Tax Abatement. Square footage is approximate."
220020549,SOLD,"JC, Heights",266 WEBSTER AVE,Condominium,2282,1702,"$1,250,000",CONDO-COOP,,3&4,2,"JC, Heights",07307,,,,,,,,4,1,2,6,,"$1,250,000","$1,250,000",$547.77,$547.77,11/23/2022,11/23/2022,11/23/2022,0,0,,11/23/2022,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Bowers & South,"Welcome to 266 Webster, a professionally designed boutique condo building located in one of the most desirable sections of Jersey City Heights. This ground up new development features two very large luxury condos. Unit 2 features 4 bedrooms, 2 and a half bathrooms spread over 2 floors and 2282sf. Throughout the home, you'll notice its 9ft ceilings, 4in oak flooring, central A/C, oversized windows, and an open floorplan. The designer kitchen features quartz countertops w/ a waterfall island, matching quartz backsplash, built-in microwave, 5-burner stove and a compact hood that exhausts outside. Bathrooms include high-end tiling, fixtures and hardware. Lastly, completing the unit, you will receive half of the oversized garage (set up for electric car charging) and a PRIVATE roof deck! The location is very ideal - just a block away from Washington Park, two blocks from Riverview Park, 5 blocks from the 9th St Light Rail station and within a short distance of all of Jersey City Heights best restaurants, bars and shopping options."
250006811,SOLD,"JC, Heights",77 CHARLES ST,Condominium,1900,1603,"$1,275,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07307,2704,9,Heights,,,,,4,1,2,7,,"$1,275,000","$1,275,000",$671.05,$671.05,4/8/2025,5/23/2025,9/19/2025,45,45,,9/19/2025,,,,$0,,,,Conventional,No,No,No,,,Summit Ave & Milton Ave,"Welcome to the condos at 77 Charles Street, located on a quiet and sought-after block in Jersey City Heights perfectly situated Summit Ave and JFK Boulevard. Consisting of two luxuriously fully renovated units, each is bathed in light and features crisp modern design, serene outdoor spaces and dedicated on-site parking with EV-charging functionality. Unit 2 is a sun-drenched 4 bedroom, 2.5 bath duplex with a large private roof-deck that boasts of incredible NYC views. The unit features a fully open-concept layout with soaring high ceilings and light-filled interiors framed by custom Pella Lifestyle casement windows. As you step in, your eye is drawn to the south-facing windows and balcony that let in tons of sunlight and the wide-plank white oak floors that run throughout the home. The kitchen wows with European-style oak veneer cabinets, floating shelves and stunning quartz countertops and backsplash. Pro-style luxury stainless steel appliances include a gas range with sleek vented hood, microwave drawer, large French door refrigerator and dishwasher. A custom wine cellar and must-have wine fridge makes this an impressive entertainment space. An electric fireplace sets the mood for cozy winter evenings. Step upstairs to the bedroom wing of this home. The large light-filled primary bedroom features a lovely South-facing balcony, private en-suite bathroom and walk-in closet. Three spacious guest bedrooms, a guest bathroom, and dedicated laundry-room provide all the space for today’s home-buyer. Both bathrooms feature elegant design, porcelain tiles, Delta shower fixtures and floating vanities; the master bath also provides an additional luxury with its heated floors. The crown jewel of this home is the large private roof-deck with 180 degree NYC views and comes fully equipped for entertaining with direct gas, water and electric connections. Other features include all new high efficiency central HVAC with Nest thermostat, tank-less water heater, superior noise suppression design, smart lighting, Ring doorbell and brand new roof. Dedicated on-site parking with EV-charging capability makes this a must-see! Close to shopping, dining, parks and a range of transport options. Commute to NYC in under 30 minutes!"
220010817,SOLD,"JC, Heights",580 PALISADE AVE,Condominium,2300,1692,"$1,280,000",CONDO-COOP,,2+3,201,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,The Riveview,,,,3,0,3,6,,"$1,280,000","$1,200,000",$556.52,$556.52,11/1/2021,11/22/2021,4/22/2022,21,0,,6/13/2022,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Congress and South,"Step inside and immediately feel at ease in this unit. BRAND NEW GROUND UP CONSTRUCTION at The Riverview offers impeccable comfort and convenience, situated on Palisade Avenue, at the heart of the neighborhood’s exciting retail/dining corridor. Choose from two- and three-bedroom residences in this intimate 13-unit building, crafted to meet your every need. The well-proportioned units are carefully constructed with today’s most in-demand elements. Flow-through rooms and thoughtful appointments combine for luxurious comfort. Expansive energy-efficient insulated windows frame the interiors with abundant natural light. Elegant top-line finishes include wide plank flooring, granite countertops and premium Fischer-Paykel appliances. Thoughtfully curated amenities bring ease to today’s busy lifestyles. A package room, 12-car parking garage with electric chargers and ground-level bike storage are among the building’s many essential comforts designed to enhance your lifestyle. Make this inspired collection of pet-friendly condominiums home. 10-year New Home Warranty, Manufacturer’s Warranty on all appliances and systems, and tax abatement. Photos are of model unit."
260003651,ACTIVE,"JC, Heights",31 GRAHAM ST,Condominium,2350,5069,"$1,299,000",CONDO-COOP,,1&2,1,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,3,2,2,8,,,"$1,299,000",$552.77,,3/3/2026,,,37,,,3/3/2026,,,,$0,,,,,No,No,Yes,,,Summit & Central,"Welcome to 31 Graham St, Unit 1 a 3 bedroom, 2 full bath, 2 half bath duplex by Green Home Developers, offering approximately 2,350 square feet of living space and RARE MULTI CAR SIDE BY SIDE GARAGE PARKING in Jersey City Heights. Your main level features an open concept living and dining area with 10 foot ceilings and oversized windows. Your chef’s kitchen features premium stainless steel appliances, waterfall quartz countertops, vented hood, and custom wood cabinetry, designed for both everyday living and entertaining. Your primary suite offers a walk-in closet with custom built-ins, a RARE wrap around private balcony, and ensuite bath with floor to ceiling large format tile, a smart mirror, and top-of-the-line shower fixtures. Also on the main level are two additional spacious bedrooms with built-in closets, a full bathroom with double vanity, powder room, dedicated laundry area, linen and coat closets for added storage, a flexible office space, and dual entry points for convenience. The ground level expands your living space with an OVERSIZED rec room ideal for entertaining, complete with a dry bar, powder room, and direct access to both the backyard and garage. The XL garage offers RARE MULTI CAR SIDE BY SIDE GARAGE PARKING, plus additional private storage closets. Situated on a quiet stretch of Graham Street, known for its elevated position and sweeping NYC views, this home offers the perfect blend of tranquility and accessibility. Just moments from Central Avenue shops, the 9th Street Light Rail, Washington Park, and the restaurants along Palisade Avenue, you’ll enjoy both breathtaking surroundings and exceptional convenience. Square footage is approximate."
230005073,SOLD,"JC, Heights",122 OGDEN AVE,Condominium,2139,1702,"$1,300,000",CONDO-COOP,,1 & 2,1,"JC, Heights",07307-1310,05202,00015,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,6,,"$1,300,000","$1,275,000",$607.76,$607.76,3/30/2023,4/12/2023,6/19/2023,13,13,,6/20/2023,,,,"$16,402",2022,$300,,Conventional,,,,,,Cuneo PL & Ogden's End,"Step into a truly amazing Ogden Avenue duplex, with everything you’ve been looking for: Modern open layout, expertly designed kitchen and baths, large bedrooms, gorgeous NYC skyline views from both levels, wonderful yard, outdoor deck, and multiple-car parking! Main level features an expansive and bright living area leading to an incredible kitchen with beautiful cabinetry, quartz-stone countertops, island with breakfast bar, top-quality stainless steel appliances and vented hood. Access the full-width deck/balcony that overlooks your yard and bask in the panoramic breathtaking views of the NYC skyline, East, North, and South! Two ample bedrooms with large windows, custom closets and a new full bathroom complete the floor, before you proceed to… The Main-Suite level, boasting a huge bedroom with walk-in closet, your own luxe fireplace, and a new bathroom worthy of a 7-star hotel; dual sinks, designer fixtures, large soaking bathtub and adjacent shower area, tastefully finished in stone and tile. Hardwood floors and excellent recessed lighting throughout, central ac/heat, and other special touches you must see. Indoor parking garage for one car, with plenty of storage, plus parking space outdoors.Best location in the Heights, mins to NYC or Hoboken (Bus) , NJ Transit Light Rail, and walkable to great cafes, restaurants, and more."
210014900,SOLD,"JC, Heights",230 OGDEN AVE,Condominium,2607,1702,"$1,308,000",CONDO-COOP,,3&G,3,"JC, Heights",07307,03904,00014,,,,,,4,1,3,9,,"$1,308,000","$1,295,000",$501.73,$501.73,6/19/2021,7/23/2021,9/24/2021,34,34,,9/27/2021,,,,,,$334,2021,Conventional,No,No,No,,,Griffith St & Franklin St,"Incomparable. In-com-pa-ra-ble. Definition: without an equal in quality or extent; matchless. Discreetly tucked away on the most exquisite and private block of the most sought after street in Jersey City Heights, The Penthouse at 230 Ogden Avenue is a 2,607 SF 4 bedroom, 3.5 bathroom with private elevator and garage parking for two cars that has been purpose-built to showcase jaw-dropping, panoramic views of the Hudson River and New York City with a 411 SF private roof deck, wrap-around balcony and floor-to-ceiling windows. Perched on the edge of the Palisades, the open-concept living, dining and entertaining area is framed on one end by a skylit open chef's kitchen with richly stained shaker millwork, under-cabinet lighting, granite countertops and a full suite of stainless steel appliances, and on the other by mesmerizing views of New York City that magically stretch from the Upper West Side to the Verrazano Bridge. The city's most iconic buildings are seemingly an outstretched hand away and perhaps even more astonishing when experienced from the private roof deck above. This space is outfitted with gas, water and electrical lines making a full outdoor kitchen an easy addition. The palatial owner's suite offers southern exposure, exceptional storage -- including a walk-in closet -- and a skylit en-suite spa bathroom with floor-to-ceiling Porcelanosa tile, oversized glass-enclosed walk-in shower, deep jacuzzi tub and a marble-topped double vanity. It is complemented by two generously sized bedrooms, crisply appointed bathroom with tub and marble vanity, and a perfectly located powder room. Accessible from the private elevator, The Penthouse also includes a 636 SF bonus room (incorporated in total of 2,607 SF) on the lower level that is fitted with a full bathroom and additional washer/dryer hook-up. This incredibly unique and flexible space is perfect for use as a guest room, au pair suite, gym, playroom or office/workspace. Life at home is further enhanced by an astonishing gallery with three skylights, central air, gas fireplace, full-size side-by-side washer/dryer and incredible storage. Benefiting from an ideal Jersey City Heights location with incredible walking access to a vibrant, evolving network of local shopping that includes grocery stores, farmer's markets and destination-worthy restaurants, bars and coffee shops, The Penthouse at 230 Ogden Avenue is also as commutable as can be -- it is within two blocks of multiple bus lines that service both New York City (Port Authority) and Hoboken Terminal (PATH, NY Waterway Ferry, NJ Transit), and an easy stroll to the 2nd Street Light Rail station which services Hoboken Terminal and points throughout downtown Jersey City and beyond. Riverview-Fisk Park, renowned for its panoramic views of New York City and impressive farmer's market, and Pershing Field Park, known for its running track, numerous ball fields and swimming pool, are each a short walk away. Images of the roof deck and concepts for the bonus room are virtually staged. Taxes to be determined."
260003109,ACTIVE,"JC, Heights",617 PALISADE AVE,Condominium,1844,1597,"$1,325,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,3,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,6,,,"$1,325,000",$718.55,,2/23/2026,,,45,,,2/23/2026,,,,,,$230,,,,,,,,Congress St & North St,"Seller offering $20K concession towards closing costs!  Brand new and unexpected, this home redefines modern living with rich tones, bespoke design, and a depth of finishes rarely seen. Featuring a 3 bed, 2 bath layout, the crown jewel belongs to the 1,100 sq ft rooftop with outdoor kitchen set up *plus* sweeping NYC views.   Inside, oversized windows welcome with striking scale, illuminating the 7” wide oak hardwood floors and deep-hued color-cap tray ceiling. The atmospheric fireplace is framed in pale oak and makes a statement, and includes a built-in beveled niche designed to cradle a flatscreen. The dynamic kitchen is open and inviting, with custom light-oak upper cabinetry with under lighting, peppercorn lower with matching hood and island kick-plate, tying it all together with clean white quartz countertops and backsplash. Additional finishes include Thermador appliance suite as well as a brass pot filler and matching designer pendant lighting.   In the primary suite, design carries with the continued color-cap ceiling treatment, plus a fluted wood accent wall lit by mounted sconces. The bathroom brings beauty and function together with a marble-tiled wet room, where a glass-enclosed shower with niche and accent lighting compliment the freestanding soaking tub, and the spacious double vanity in the same serene space. Conscientious storage abound with fully built walk-in closets throughout for effortless everyday luxury.  Set in a prime location in Jersey City Heights, this modern tan brick façade gives excellent curb appeal. Just one block to the 9th Street Light Rail elevator and beloved local favorites like Washington Park, Lil' Dove Cafe, The Cliff and more, these homes offer the best of lifestyle and location."
250025147,SOLD,"JC, Heights",619 PALISADE AVE,Condominium,1845,5069,"$1,330,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,3,"JC, Heights",07306,,,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,7,,"$1,330,000","$1,399,000",$720.87,$720.87,12/17/2025,12/27/2025,2/2/2026,10,10,,2/2/2026,,,,$0,,,,Conventional,No,No,Yes,,,Palisade Ave and Congress,"Seller offering $20K concession towards closing costs!  Welcome to 619 Palisade Avenue unit 3, a premier high-end new construction condo from NKAY Developers in the heart of Jersey City Heights, conveniently located on Palisade Avenue, just steps from Light Rail and Riverview Fisk Park. This unit features 3 XL bedrooms, 2 full baths, and private rooftop. Custom designed kitchen offers  top of the line stainless steel Thermador appliances including wine fridge, XL quartz waterfall counters and backsplash, oversized stainless steel sink, two-tone custom cabinetry, pot filler, stylish gold hardware and fixtures, and high-end pendant lighting. Open-Concept living and dining room are complete with a fireplace framed with custom millwork and wall to wall oversized Andersen windows with NYC views. Main bedroom suite offers ample natural light and boasts a luxurious accent wall with dual pendant lighting, walk in custom closet with custom built-in shelving and drawers and frosted glass doors. Ensuite bathroom offers clean design with white tile and porcelain slabs as well as oversized double vanity, dramatic warm accent lighting, and a top of the line waterfall shower, complete with sprayer and jets and soaking tub. Each additional bedrooms feature high end custom built-in closets and common bathroom. Washer/dryer in unit add to the convenience of the home. The home is also equipped with a smart doorbell, keyless entry, Legrand smart dimmers, and energy-efficient smart thermostats. Your private XL rooftop spans offers custom outdoor kitchen, accent lighting, gas / electric / water hook ups and multiple direct NYC views. The exterior facade has been designed with modern yet timeless features, exterior lighting, professional landscaping, and a fenced-in front yard. This property comes with a 10-year warranty and may qualify for a 5 year tax abatement. Highly sought after location being steps from new restaurants, shopping, palisade ave bus stop, Congress st light rail, Riverview Fisk park and much more! Please note that square footage is approximate. Off-site parking available."
250011781,SOLD,"JC, Heights",45 GRAHAM ST,Condominium,2300,5069,"$1,349,000",CONDO-COOP,,2&3,2,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,4,1,3,8,,"$1,349,000","$1,349,000",$586.52,$586.52,6/10/2025,6/18/2025,7/10/2025,8,7,,7/10/2025,,,,$0,,,,Conventional,No,No,Yes,,,Central Ave and Summit,"Welcome to 45 Graham Street, Unit 2, a stunning 4-bedroom, 3.1-bathroom duplex condo offering over 2,300 sqft of luxurious living space. Located in Jersey City Heights, this residence is conveniently close to the 9th Street Light Rail, Riverview-Fisk Park, Hoboken, and the vibrant dining scene along Palisade Avenue. Designed with timeless finishes and high-end fixtures, this home offers cutting-edge technology for modern living. The main level features an expansive open-concept dining and living area with 10-foot ceilings and oversized Andersen windows, creating a bright, airy atmosphere. A realistic flame fireplace with a tempered glass accent wall makes a bold statement. The chef’s kitchen includes two-tone cabinetry, Thermador appliances, a paneled refrigerator and dishwasher, a 5-burner range, warming drawer, and a double waterfall quartz island with West Elm accent lighting, a porcelain backsplash, pot filler, and externally vented hood. The first floor also includes a beautifully appointed powder room with warm accent lighting. Upstairs, the XL primary suite offers a serene retreat with custom wood-tone millwork, bedside pendant lighting, a walk-in closet with built-ins, and a private balcony. The spa-like en-suite bath boasts modern natural tones, an oversized double vanity, pendant lighting, and a luxurious shower with multiple Kohler body sprays and a rainfall showerhead. Two additional XL bedrooms feature custom closets with built-ins and share an elegant full bathroom with double vanity, soaking tub, rainfall showerhead, body sprays, and floor-to-ceiling tilework. An extra primary suite with custom closets and a full bathroom completes the upper level. The upstairs also includes a separate laundry room with top-of-the-line washer and dryer. A recessed lit staircase leads to an entertainment zone featuring a wet bar with custom cabinetry, a backlit designer backsplash, and a wine fridge. Step outside to a rare full-length rooftop with sweeping views of the NYC skyline. This outdoor space includes premium astroturf and Trex decking, as well as hookups for gas, electric, and water—perfect for entertaining.This smart home is equipped with Google Nest doorbell, security cameras, smart thermostat, touchscreen light switches, and dimmers, all controlled via smartphone. The property includes side-by-side parking in a private driveway. The home is completed with Blue Chip Properties' signature exterior facade, recessed driveway, and professional landscaping. Also qualifies for 5-year tax abatement. Sqft are approx. Don’t miss the chance to own this exceptional residence in one of Jersey City’s most desirable neighborhoods."
260001783,ACTIVE,"JC, Heights",81-83 HUTTON ST,Condominium,1486,1597,"$1,350,000",CONDO-COOP,,3,301,"JC, Heights",07307,,,,,,,,3,0,2,6,,,"$1,350,000",$908.48,,1/21/2026,,,78,,,2/3/2026,,,,,,,,,,,,,,Cambridge & Central,"Welcome to Everton House. A nine-residence elevator building in Jersey City Heights, distinguished by curtain-wall glass imported from Spain, creating light-filled interiors with sweeping views of New York City. Everton House offers two, three, and four-bedroom residences, with select homes featuring private outdoor spaces and all residents enjoying access to a shared rooftop. Interiors are defined by dramatic ceiling heights and thoughtfully considered layouts. Kitchens are outfitted with JennAir appliances, including signature Black Obsidian interiors and a built-in coffee system. Primary bathrooms feature radiant heated floors, delivering a refined, spa-like experience. Additional amenities include garage parking with EV charging, a Swiftlane smart entry system, and a dedicated mail and package room designed for modern convenience. Residence 301 features your very own wrap around terrace with city views.   Renderings showcase select units and are for illustration only; actual unit details may vary."
230002940,SOLD,"JC, Heights",391 PALISADE AVE,Condominium,1631,6199,"$1,360,000",CONDO-COOP,,6,PH601,"JC, Heights",07307,3901,24.01,Heights,Gallery Lofts,,,,3,0,2,8,,"$1,360,000","$1,325,000",$833.84,$833.84,2/22/2023,3/22/2023,5/15/2023,28,28,,5/16/2023,,,,"$14,758",2022,$629,,Conventional,,,,,,Franklin & Hutton,"A penthouse atop the Palisades, one that seems to sit eye-level with famed skyscrapers. The home synergizes with New York City, and carries a vibe that’s hard to recreate. You’ll feel it every day. Family and friends will too. The kitchen, couch and both rooftops align with The Greatest City in the World. Vintage Jersey City stands strong to the west. Flow between the views freely. Three bedrooms surround this hub, yours is en suite. Sunlight simply streams in. There are multiple entrances and foyers, which is rare in a condo. And your garaged parking spot is a short elevator ride down.  Unit 601 is the pride of Gallery Lofts, a 3 year old, steel and concrete building in blossoming Jersey City Heights."
250018016,SOLD,"JC, Heights",45 GRAHAM ST,Condominium,2800,5069,"$1,395,000",CONDO-COOP,,1&2,1,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,4,0,5,8,,"$1,395,000","$1,395,000",$498.21,$498.21,9/3/2025,10/30/2025,12/4/2025,57,57,,12/15/2025,,,,$0,,,,Conventional,No,No,Yes,,,Central Avenue and Summit,"One of the Largest New Condos in The Heights. Welcome to 45 Graham Street, Unit 1, Jersey City — Blue Chip Properties’ most iconic and sought-after project to date. This exceptional 4-bedroom, 5-bathroom duplex spans over 2,800 sqft and offers unparalleled convenience, with easy access to the 9th Street Light Rail, Riverview-Fisk Park, Hoboken, and the vibrant dining scene along Palisade Avenue. Designed with timeless finishes, high-end fixtures, and meticulous craftsmanship, this home is equipped with cutting-edge technology for modern living. The main level features an expansive open-concept dining and living area with soaring 10-foot ceilings and oversized Andersen windows that fill the space with natural light. A striking realistic flame fireplace adds both warmth and style. The chef’s kitchen is outfitted with two-tone cabinetry, a Thermador appliance package (including a paneled refrigerator and dishwasher), a 5-burner range, and a warming drawer. The large double waterfall quartz island is illuminated by West Elm accent lighting and is complemented by a porcelain backsplash, pot filler, and an externally vented hood. The first floor also includes a spacious guest bedroom with custom-finished closets and a beautifully designed bathroom with double vanity and floor-to-ceiling tilework. Additionally, there is a generous secondary primary bedroom suite with a private en-suite bath and modern natural tones. Upstairs, the XL primary suite serves as a serene retreat, featuring warm wood-tone millwork, bedside pendant lighting, a true walk-in closet with built-ins, and a private balcony. The spa-like en-suite bath offers an oversized double vanity, warm pendant lighting, and a luxurious shower with multiple Kohler body sprays and a rainfall showerhead. An additional XL bedroom with a walk-in closet and en-suite bath completes the upper level. A dedicated laundry room with top-of-the-line appliances adds convenience to the upper floor. This expansive home also boasts a full basement with 9-foot ceilings, multiple storage closets, a full bath, an oversized wet bar with a custom accent-lit backsplash and wine fridge, and wide-plank tile flooring. The private backyard is an entertainer's dream, featuring professional landscaping, a paver patio, accent lighting, and hookups for gas, electric, and water — perfect for creating lasting memories. This smart home is fully equipped with Google Nest doorbell, security cameras, smart thermostat, touchscreen light switches, and more, all controlled through your smartphone. The rare side-by-side parking driveway and Blue Chip Properties' signature exterior facade with recessed driveway and professional landscaping add to the home’s appeal. Also qualifies for 5-year tax abatement. Square footage is approximate."
250001257,SOLD,"JC, Heights",420 OGDEN AVE,Condominium,1660,5069,"$1,399,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07307,2404,38.01,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,6,,"$1,399,000","$1,399,000",$842.77,$842.77,1/18/2025,1/18/2025,2/24/2025,0,0,,2/24/2025,,,,,,,,Cash,No,No,Yes,,,South st and Hobson St,"Introducing a rare opportunity to own an OVERSIZED New Construction Duplex Condo located on the coveted Ogden Ave overlooking NYC Skyline. This Condo has been built by one of Jersey City's top Developers Dream Home Development and offers 3 Bedroom 2 Full Bathroom. 1st floor opens to living room and kitchen with floor to ceiling windows and sliding glass door with unobstructed NYC views and private glass enclosed balcony. Your chef's kitchen features Top Line VIKING Smart appliances, waterfall quartz countertops, two-tone cabinetry and designer light fixtures. Your Main Bedroom Suite offers custom floor to ceiling accent wall built in closets, accent pendant lighting and an OVERSIZED luxurious Main Bathroom Suite with Double vanity, shower with soaking tub, multiple jets, waterfall shower head and transom window for plenty of natural light. Completing your 1st floor are 2 additional bedrooms, a full bathroom, and laundry room. Your FULL LENGTH rooftop offers the perfect space for entertainment which overlooks the NYC Skyline with unobstructed views. Garage offers true SIDE by SIDE parking and EV charging outlet. Property comes with 10 Year Builder Warranty and potentially available for 5 year tax abatement. Please note that all sqft are approximate. Please notes pictures are from Similar Unit."
250000318,SOLD,"JC, Heights",418 OGDEN AVE,Condominium,1660,5069,"$1,400,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07307,2404,38.01,Heights,,,,,3,0,2,7,,"$1,400,000","$1,399,000",$843.37,$843.37,1/6/2025,2/20/2025,4/21/2025,24,24,,4/21/2025,,,,$0,,,,Conventional,No,No,Yes,,,Palisades Ave and Congress Street,"Introducing a rare opportunity to own an OVERSIZED New Construction Duplex Condo located on the coveted Ogden Ave overlooking NYC Skyline. This Condo has been built by one of Jersey City's top Developers Dream Home Development and offers 3 Bedroom 2 Full Bathroom.  1st floor opens to living room and kitchen with floor to ceiling windows and sliding glass door with unobstructed NYC views and private glass enclosed balcony. Your chef's kitchen features Top Line VIKING Smart appliances, waterfall quartz countertops, two-tone cabinetry and designer light fixtures. Your Main Bedroom Suite offers custom floor to ceiling accent wall built in closets, accent pendant lighting and an OVERSIZED luxurious Main Bathroom Suite with Double vanity, shower with soaking tub, multiple jets, waterfall shower head and transom window for plenty of natural light.  Completing your 1st floor are 2 additional bedrooms, a full bathroom, and laundry room. Your FULL LENGTH rooftop offers the perfect space for entertainment which overlooks the NYC Skyline with unobstructed views. Garage offers true SIDE by SIDE parking and EV charging outlet. Property comes with 10 Year Builder Warranty and potentially available for 5 year tax abatement. *Please note that all sqft are approximate."
250008425,SOLD,"JC, Heights",371 NEW YORK AVE,Condominium,0,1713,"$1,425,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1,"JC, Heights",07307,2303,30,,,,,,3,0,2,7,,"$1,425,000","$1,425,000",,,1/26/2025,1/28/2025,3/31/2025,2,0,,4/30/2025,,,,,,,,Conventional,,,,,,South St and Congress St," Welcome to 371 New York, built by one of Jersey City's most sought out Developers' Blue Chip Properties’. This 3 bedroom 2 full bath duplex unit was designed with timeless interior design, top line finishes and fixtures, quality craftsmanship and modern technological features. Your main floor opens to an open concept Dining & Living featuring 12 ft high walls lined with oversized Andersen Energy Efficient windows, floor to ceiling tempered glass accent wall, natural light and realistic flame fireplace. Your Chefs kitchen features designer - two tone cabinetry, Thermador Stove, Thermador Heating Drawer, Panel Ready Thermador Fridge, pot filler, oversized double waterfall quartz center island and countertops backed with luxurious porcelain backsplash, West elm accent lighting, Oversize Double Window and externally vented Hood Vent. Main level features Primary bedroom designed with custom millwork, bedside pendant lighting, double walk-in-closet with custom built-ins and large private balcony with NYC views. Your ensuite bath which has been designed with modern yet warm natural tones to create a spa like ambience and offers oversized double vanity, soaking tub, warm pendant lighting, multiple Kohler Body Sprays and shower head. Two additional bedrooms with finished custom closets, an Oversized Full bath with oversized double vanity and floor to ceiling limewash tiles, laundry room with Top Line Washer / Dryer complete your main level. Your upper outdoor level enters from recessed lit staircase, glass accent wall and wet bar backed with accent lit custom backsplash and wine fridge and custom cabinetry."
250016245,SOLD,"JC, Heights",91 HANCOCK AVE,Condominium,1750,5069,"$1,449,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07307,,,Heights,,,,,3,0,3,7,,"$1,449,000","$1,449,000",$828.00,$828.00,8/8/2025,8/25/2025,11/26/2025,17,17,,11/26/2025,,,,$0,,,,Conventional,No,No,Yes,,,Central Ave and palisade Ave,"Welcome to 91 Hancock Avenue—Unit 2, a brand new 3-Bedroom, 3-Bathroom build by Jack & Lumber, Jersey City’s premier ultra-luxury home builder and the only one in The Heights crafting true boutique residences. Owning one is more than an achievement; it is a richly deserved reward for your years of vision, ambition, and hard work. Reimagine your life in a home so extraordinary it inspires daily pride and leaves your guests in awe. We believe profoundly that our clients deserve something truly extraordinary, and work with unwavering dedication to deliver it. Our next-generation homes are defined by dazzling bespoke Italian kitchens—visually striking by incorporating glass and integrated LED lights and crafted with meticulous attention to detail. A Sub-Zero Designer Series paneled refrigerator and black glass Wolf appliances underscore our commitment to refined contemporary minimalism. The island, clad in Neolith porcelain from Spain, features an integrated sink and Wolf precision-control induction cooktop with advanced safety features, including automatic pan detection. We’ve partnered with Buster & Punch of London for our interior lighting and kitchen hardware—perhaps the most style-forward brand to emerge in design this past decade. Their solid brass fixtures, diamond-knurled with watchmaker-like precision, add sculptural tactility to every interaction. A hallmark of our design is the signature Jack & Lumber floating staircase—a sculptural centerpiece framed in minimalist glass and illuminated with integrated LED lighting. Both engineering marvel and art installation, it’s a defining statement of the home.  The bespoke Italian walk-in closets are nothing short of spectacular—designed to rival the most exclusive retail boutiques. Framed by smoked glass doors and illuminated by integrated LED lighting, each closet exudes a sense of drama and refinement. Custom shelving and meticulously planned layouts showcase both form and function, while premium finishes and precise detailing create an atmosphere that is as indulgent as it is organized. These wardrobes aren’t just storage—they’re immersive, high-design spaces that elevate the everyday ritual of dressing.   Windows and oversized sliding doors are custom-fabricated by Drutex of Poland, featuring triple-pane construction with insulating gas layers. This not only enhances energy efficiency but also dramatically reduces exterior noise,  creating a peaceful interior environment all year round.  Our passion for exceptional materials continues into the bathrooms. Clad in large-format Neolith slabs and illuminated by Buster & Punch lighting, each bathroom features Ditra-Heat radiant floors—a German-engineered system known for reliability, seamless integration, and comfort. Individual thermostats allow for intuitive temperature control, and all bathrooms include smart toilets, offering elevated hygiene and comfort through cutting-edge technology.  Throughout the residence, millwork reflects our uncompromising craftsmanship—from custom European interior doors imported from Spain to thoughtfully integrated architectural details. The solid 8-foot doors are custom-fabricated and clad in American walnut veneer, paired with concealed hinges and magnetic locks for a clean, uninterrupted profile. Even the base molding has been meticulously fabricated to match the walnut finish, reinforcing the residence’s seamless design language.    To top it all off, upstairs, a sleek wet bar leads the way to your private rooftop oasis—an open-air escape with sweeping NYC views. Whether you're entertaining under the stars or enjoying a quiet morning coffee, this elevated space seamlessly extends the home's refined interior to the outdoors.  Property comes with 10-Year Builder Warranty and may qualify for 5-Year Tax Abatement. Off-site Parking options available.  Schedule a private appointment—and fall in love with a Jack & Lumber masterpiece.  "
250016071,SOLD,"JC, Heights",382 OGDEN AVE,Condominium,2200,1653,"$1,450,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,2,"JC, Heights",07307,2404,22,Heights,,,,,4,1,2,9,,"$1,450,000","$1,450,000",$659.09,$659.09,5/15/2025,5/16/2025,7/14/2025,1,0,,8/6/2025,,"$1,550,000",2024,"$34,828",2023,$585,2025,Conventional,,,,,,PALISADE AVE & PATERSON,"Rare opportunity to live on Ogden Ave, Jersey City Heights most coveted address, in a sprawling renovated duplex apartment with sweeping NYC views, two private terraces and shared yard. This 4 bedroom/2.5 bath is perfect for entertaining. The huge main floor open living / dining room easily accommodates a crowd, and striking gas fireplace as a focal point. The spacious chef's kitchen features stainless steel appliances including a Blue Star stove, granite countertops with room to seat 10, numerous cabinets including a full pantry wall, and best of all, a wall of windows with panoramic views of the skyline. Step out on your private terrace to take in the view of the shared yard and the skyline beyond. The upper level features the primary bedroom with dramatic stone gas fir"
240015192,SOLD,"JC, Heights",246 WEBSTER AVE,Condominium,2800,1692,"$1,450,000",CONDO-COOP,,2 +3,2,"JC, Heights",07307,,,,,,,,4,1,3,8,,"$1,450,000","$1,450,000",$517.86,$517.86,5/27/2024,6/1/2024,8/5/2024,5,0,,9/3/2024,,,,$0,,,,Conventional,,,,,,South and Bowers,"A truly one of kind home crafted by a trusted builder – this luxurious oversized, brand new boutique condo is located in the heart of the Heights. At 2800 interior square feet, 246 Webster, Unit 2 offers all the space of a single family with all the simplicity of condo living. The property’s first level is a well appointed “typical” three bedrooms, two bath layout. The large kitchen is lit by a north facing picture window and finished with granite waterfall countertop, custom cabinets, and a designer Fisher & Pakal appliance package. Depending on your choice, with the additional living space upstairs, this floor’s living room can be used as a dining room that is fit for a mansion. Down the hallway, there are two spacious bedrooms, a high-tech washer and dryer room, a full bath completed with Porcelanosa tiles, a tasteful vanity, and nice fixtures. At the end of the hall sits one of two master bedrooms with an ensuite bathroom, glass enclosed shower, double vanity, walk in closet, and small balcony. We aren’t done yet! One flight up awaits a floor through expansive sun-soaked penthouse den with a full wet bar set up that could easily be a second kitchen. Entertain, live, work – your choice. Off this rare space is a half bathroom and down the hall sits a SECOND MASTER SUITE, same as the first with an ensuite bathroom, glass enclosed shower, double vanity, walk in closet, and small balcony that rises above the surrounding rooflines. But wait, there is more!!! The third level of this breathtaking hope is the private roof top terrace overlooking Jersey City and the Manhattan skyline beyond. Here too there is a full kitchen set up capping off the endless possibility of your next home. Smart technology throughout. Photos are renderings. Estimated CO date is June – nearly complete. Book your tour today!"
250001485,SOLD,"JC, Heights",418 OGDEN AVE,Condominium,1950,5069,"$1,475,000",CONDO-COOP,,1,1,"JC, Heights",07307,2404,38.01,Heights,,,,,3,0,3,7,,"$1,475,000","$1,499,000",$756.41,$756.41,1/22/2025,2/7/2025,7/10/2025,16,16,,7/10/2025,,,,$0,,,,Conventional,No,No,Yes,,,Palisade Ave and Congress St,"Introducing a rare opportunity to own an OVERSIZED New Construction Duplex Condo located on the coveted Ogden Ave overlooking the NYC Skyline. This Condo has been built by one of Jersey City's top Developers, Dream Home Development and offers 3 Bedroom 3 Full Bathroom.  1st floor opens to living room and kitchen with floor to ceiling windows and sliding glass door with unobstructed NYC views and private glass enclosed balcony. Your chef's kitchen features Top Line VIKING Smart appliances, waterfall quartz countertops, two-tone cabinetry and designer light fixtures. Your Main Bedroom Suite offers custom built in closets, accent pendant lighting, an OVERSIZED luxurious Main Bathroom Suite with Double vanity, shower with soaking tub, multiple jets, waterfall shower head and transom window for plenty of natural light.  Completing your 1st floor are 2 additional bedrooms, a full bathroom, and laundry room. Your ground floor offers the perfect space for entertainment across your interior and exterior living space. Interior spaces includes full bathroom, wet bar, rec room, direct access to garage and private side entrance. Your backyard has unobstructed NYC Views and is professionally landscaped with custom paver-turf design, planters and custom wood fence. Garage offers true SIDE by SIDE parking and EV charging outlet. Property comes with 10 Year Builder Warranty and potentially available for 5 year tax abatement. *Please note sqft are approximate.  "
250020156,SOLD,"JC, Heights",77 CHARLES ST,Condominium,2400,1603,"$1,500,000",CONDO-COOP,1900,B1,1,"JC, Heights",07307,2704,9,Heights,,24.6X100,"2,460",,4,1,2,8,,"$1,500,000","$1,500,000",$625.00,$625.00,3/1/2025,3/24/2025,9/24/2025,23,0,,9/30/2025,,"$486,600",2024,"$19,000",2025,$300,2025,Conventional,,,,,,SUMMIT AVE & MILTON AVE,"Two Luxuriously Fully Renovated Homes. Welcome to the condos at 77 Charles St located on one of the most sought-after blocks in Jersey City Heights and perfectly situated between Summit Ave and JFK Blvd. Consisting of two luxuriously fully renovated units each is bathed in light and features crisp modern design, serene outdoor spaces and dedicated on-site parking. Unit 1 is an expansive 2 400 sq. ft. 4 bedroom, 2.5 bath triplex with a massive lower level and large private backyard on a generous lot. Both units feature a with soaring ceilings light-filled interiors framed by custom Pella Lifestyle casement windows wide-oak floors sophisticated and timeless design, and finishes. Close to shopping, dining, parks and a range of transport options. Commute to NYC in under 30 minutes!"
250004516,SOLD,"JC, Heights",580 PALISADE AVE,Condominium,2168,6199,"$1,530,000",CONDO-COOP,,2,201,"JC, Heights",07307,2402,10.01,Heights,The Riverview,,,,3,0,3,6,,"$1,530,000","$1,499,000",$705.72,$705.72,3/11/2025,4/8/2025,5/12/2025,28,28,,5/12/2025,,"$778,700",2023,"$17,497",2023,$799,2025,Conventional,,,,,,Congress & South,"This home qualifies for the Community Loan Program, offering a low 5.6% interest rate, no PMI, and down payments as low as 5%. Don’t miss this fantastic financing opportunity! Experience the perfect fusion of timeless elegance and contemporary comfort at 580 Palisade Avenue, located in the heart of Jersey City’s thriving Heights neighborhood. This stunning residence is thoughtfully crafted to offer both style and functionality, making it an ideal retreat for modern living. Discover a bright and airy layout, where natural light pours through expansive windows, accentuating the rich hardwood floors and open-concept design. The sleek, chef-inspired kitchen is a culinary dream, featuring top-of-the-line appliances, custom cabinetry with gold hardware, a pantry with built-in shelving for organization, and an upgraded backsplash designed to flow seamlessly with the countertop—perfect for entertaining or everyday meals. The spacious bedrooms provide peaceful sanctuaries, with the primary suite offering a serene escape designed for ultimate relaxation beaming with natural light. Both upstairs bedrooms boast walk-in closets custom-designed by California Closets, ensuring ample storage, while partial city views can be enjoyed from both bedrooms. The luxurious ensuite master bathroom, accessed through a stylish barn door, boasts a sleek stand-up shower, a stand-alone soaking tub, and a double vanity for added convenience. The additional ensuite bathroom is equally well-appointed, featuring both a tub and a stand-up shower, along with a double vanity. Elegant finishes and high-end fixtures throughout create a serene, spa-like ambiance. Adding to its appeal, this home features an extended private outdoor space, complete with stone pavers, perfect for enjoying fresh air, unwinding after a long day, or entertaining guests during warm weather. Custom window treatments from The Shade Store adorn the entire home, enhancing privacy and style.  Beyond its impeccable interiors, this home is perfectly positioned just minutes from the light rail, offering seamless access to Manhattan. Surrounded by an array of parks, trendy restaurants, and boutique shops, the location captures the energy of city life while maintaining a welcoming neighborhood charm. 580 Palisade Avenue isn’t just a home—it’s a lifestyle. Discover refined living in one of Jersey City’s most sought-after communities."
240009405,SOLD,"JC, Heights",420 OGDEN AVE,Condominium,2000,1713,"$1,650,000",CONDO-COOP,,1&2,1,"JC, Heights",07307,2404,38,,,,,,3,0,3,9,,"$1,650,000","$1,650,000",$825.00,$825.00,5/17/2024,5/28/2024,9/10/2024,11,11,,9/11/2024,,,,$0,,,,Conventional,,,,,,Congress & South St,"Own the skyline! Welcome to this bright, spacious 2000 sq ft 3 bedroom 3 bathroom duplex with private backyard and balcony, garage EV ready parking, and New York City view. Meticulously designed, the living area seamlessly merges living, dining, and kitchen. Perfect for entertaining and highlighted by a wall of windows with breathtaking NYC views. Featuring hardwood floors throughout, over 10 ft ceilings and oversized windows, the condo's clever use of space and thoughtfully crafted floor plan optimizes the expansive layout. The kitchen showcases top-of-the-line Viking appliances, sleek cabinetry, quartz countertops, and ample countertop space. Find three generously sized bedrooms bathed in natural light on the second floor. Contemporary fixtures and elegant tile work adorn three full bathrooms, with frameless shower doors adding a touch of modernity and creating a spa-like ambiance. Additional features in this new development condo include an in-unit full-size Samsung washer and dryer and a separate bar/kitchen area on the garden level. Nestled in the vibrant and diverse neighborhood of The Heights in Jersey City. Known for its unique charm and eclectic atmosphere, this area offers a mix of historic architecture and modern amenities. With access to Riverview Fisk Park, local shops, restaurants, farmers market, and cafes, just steps away from your doorstep. The community is well-connected with easy access to public transportation, including buses and light rail, facilitating a seamless commute to downtown Jersey City and New York City."
